name: The Void
description: You are floating in nothing.

name: Limbo
description:
You are floating in a formless void, detached from all sensation of physical
matter, surrounded by swirling glowing light, which fades into the relative
darkness around you without any trace of edges or shadow.
   There is a \No Tipping\" notice pinned to the darkness.

name: Death Row
description:
Welcome to Death Row. You await judgment, and possibly punishment, by the
Immortals. Keep quiet, and your punishment may be reduced.

name: The Zombie Pen
description:
This extremely strange-looking room seems to contain dozens of zombies and
other charmed creatures penned up like livestock. Zombies of dead dragons
stand mindlessly next to towering fire elementals. In one corner, you see a
couple pigs in a pen that seem rather out of place. What a horrible, horrible
place.

name: The Ward Room
description: Screw around here and die.

name: Before A Large Altar
description:
This poorly lit room is fairly plain, with a floor of smooth stone.  There is
but one thing of interest.

name: A Quiet Path Along the River
description:
Thick trunks and branches alive with brightly colored leaves make the
river barely visible from the seclusion of the trail.  Between branches
and leaves, a cloudy fall sky peers down, keeping a silent watch over
its earthly children.  Now and then the dark, fierce water of the river
can be spotted as it rushes on its chosen course.  The trail takes a
slight incline before stopping at a break in the treeline.

name: On a Large Rock in the River
description:
The smooth, granite rock has been beaten down by the eternal passage
of the river, yet rises far enough above the water level to provide a
place of meditation.  Though the dark waters course past with a fierce
and angry passion, the river brings solace to those who come in search
of answers.  A slight breeze brings the scent of autumn, chilled and
refreshing.

name: A Path Through the Grove
description:
Colorful leaves hiss in protest as the chilled fingers of the autumn
wind plucks them from their homes in the treetops.  The sound of swiftly
moving water dances on the breeze as well, as it winds around the trunks
of the tower oak trees.  Crisp grass peeks through a blanket of orange,
red and golden leaves, its own green color paled by the cooler weather.

name: A Forest of Eternal Autumn
description:
A perfectly detailed, painted statue of the Goddess Ilanya stands on
a pedestal in the center of the room.  The floor and ceiling take on a
silvery liquid appearance but are completely solid to the touch.  No
candles or torches shed light in this silver sanctuary yet the source
must reside somewhere as you see actual beams being reflected from one
surface to the next.  A slight, chilling breeze ruffles your clothing.

name: A Peaceful Clearing
description:
Compared to the glaring brightness of the rest of the shrine, this
place is a pit of blackness.  Try as you might, your eyes refuse to
adjust to the surroundings.  By feeling along the walls you can find
that the room is circular and empty with the exception a pit in the
center.  The rim of the pit feels warm to the touch.

name: Before a Great Oak Tree
description:
A large, ornate throne made of silver and ivory looms down from a
raised platform at the far end of this lengthy room.  A red velvet
carpet runs from one end and stops at the foot of the throne.  Some
soft pillows rest luxuriously in the throne itself.  A candelabra
set with white candles burns on either side of the throne.

name: A Lapse in Time
description: DESC

name: A Secluded Path
description: DESC

name: In the Sheltering Arms of a Great Oak Tree
description: DESC

name: A Roaring Cavern
description:
The sound of the ocean beating up against the rocky walls of this cavern
echoes almost unbearably loudly into the depths.  A fine mist of salty water
drifts through the cavern, covering the dark rock with a damp, granular
film.  To the east, little other than darkness is visible, while back to the
west, you can return to the sea.

name: A Subterranean Courtyard
description:
The roaring of the water is still incredibly loud here.  Flickering light
emanates from two massive stone torches at the bottom of a stairwell of dark
gray marble leading up to a large structure, filling this place with an
almost warm glow.  A series of huge pillars hold up the roof of the
building, of which's depth is impossible to discern, as it is set into the
northern wall.

name: The Grand Foyer of the Palace
description:
This foyer is absolutely huge.  Seven flickering chandeliers are hung
from strategic points on the ceiling, so that the entire room is lit.  The
floor is made up of the same dark marble that made up the outside of the
building, however, in the center of the room is a large symbol composed of
many different colors of marble.  Exits lead in all directions.

name: A Narrow Hallway
description:
The walls of this hallway are white, covered with decorative velvet
drapes of deep purple.  Small walnut tables line the walls between the
drapes, each with a silver candelabra stocked with white candles.  A
tapestry covers the western wall.  To the north, the hallway leads into a
dimly lit chamber, while to the south it opens back out into the foyer.

name: A Circular Chamber
description:
This room is a perfectly round circle.  It spirals down into darkness
toward the center, which serves as a sort of staircase, shaped of concentric
circles that slowly get lower.  A flickering light can be seen at the
bottom.  A thick ledge along the wall leads around the abyss, allowing one
to look at the various pictures, symbols and plaques that have been painted
on the walls in a muralistic fashion, one fading gradually into another. 
The circular wall has been segmented into four large murals, each with its
own plaque.

name: Before a Large Door
description:
The walls are completely devoid of any markings, and the only source of
light here is that of a two candelabras that have been attached to the
pitch-black wall on either side of a door carved of dark walnut.  High
above, you can barely see the dim lighting of the circular chamber that
preceeded this one.  The only thing of note in this room is an open tome on
a bookstand set into an alcove in the southern wall.

name: The Chamber of Enlightenment
description:
This chamber of dark marble is cold, drafty and the scent of rock lingers
in the air.  A bizarre statue of a goat-headed man on one knee leans toward
the southern door, its snout pointing downward with its mouth slightly open
and its arms out forward, each serving as a torch.  Dozens of candles
surround it, and their warm, flickering light off of the dark gray, polished
marble makes the room seem almost alive.  The circular symbol maks yet
another appearance here on the floor beneath the statue.

name: An Elegant Lounge
description:
A fireplace has been set into the northern wall, and couches and pillows
of plush materials have been arranged for use of guests of this shrine's
Lord.  A temperate red carpet covers the floor, with a black mandala in the
center of the room.  Ornate tables have been arranged with all sorts of
drinks and gourmet foods, as gifts to his favored.

name: The Hall of Wrath
description:
The white walls of this hall are covered with pictures and tapestries of
slaughter and suffering, along with ancient weapons that are only useful as
decorations now, but still retain their violent memories.  To the north lies
a sealed door.

name: A Dark Clearing
description:
Darkness fills the air.  Tendrils of violet mist and hazy light swirl
through the air, a low rumbling noise echoing softly through the cavernous
infinity that you've found yourself within.  A single tree stands alone,
just in front of you, and tiny specks of sky-blue light waft out from the
tree like so much dust as a warm breeze softly shakes its leaves.  There is
no apparent way out.  As you step from where you've found yourself, the
darkness becomes more and more palpable, almost crushing you should you try
to wander too far.

name: An Alcove
description:
This alcove looks to be carved out by hand.  There are many
pelts and hides lining the wall, and the heavy stench of blood
lingers.  You see what looks to be a huge skull attached to
the ground at the base of the wall.  There is a torch on both sides,
and what seems to be a pickaxe carved in the wall.

name: Above the Cascade
description:
Hanging in the air before the luminous cascade, water streams down
endlessly from the cliffs which tower into the heavens above.  A fine mist
drifts through the air, illuminated in a pale yellow from the mossy plants
growing into the cliff walls.  An arched opening leads into the sheer face
of the cliff to the east, and far below the waters flow into a wide river.

name: An Illuminated Cavern
description:
The cavern here has been carved out in a circular shape, the jagged rock
walls illuminated by torches mounted on stands all around.  The floor is not
dirt, but hard clay tile, polished and glazed to create an intensely
brilliant white.  A set of stone stairs rises up from the center of the
chamber, leading up where a gap in the ceiling admits outside light.  A
small archway to the east leads into a quiet nook, while a larger opening to
the west leads out into open air, where the waters of a cascade rage past.

name: An Illuminated Cavern, Before an Altar
description:
A small archway offers entrance to another circular chamber, illuminated
by flaming braziers.  The tiled floor here is glazed to a brilliantly
shining black, interrupted by only a single circle of white marble in the
center.  On the eastern wall hangs a finely embroidered tapestry, depicting
a bird of prey diving through a forest canopy, talons extended.  The flames
crackle alarmingly, but there is no smoke to be seen rising toward the domed
ceiling overhead.  An archway leads west, into a larger chamber.

name: An Opening Above the Cavern
description:
This small area is partially exposed to the sky, with only an arching
column of stone obscuring the overhead view.  The arch resolves at its base
into a rather narrow passageway which leads off to the south where a wider
platform opens up atop the cliff face.  A large, square opening in the
ground here reveals a set of stairs carved into the stone, winding down into
a cavern below.

name: A Balcony Overlooking the Forest
description:
This balcony is built out over the top of a sheer cliff face which drops
hundreds of feet to the south and west.  Off to the west, the roar of
rushing water is audible where a cascade pours down from sources even higher
up in the mountains.  The view to the southwest is astounding, the entire
valley of Ilopheth visible below, and the faintest hints of civilization
visible on the horizon to the south.  Beyond the forest to the west a
towering range of mountain peaks rises up.  Off to the east, endless plains
and rolling foothills make up the landscape.  A small passage to the north
leads toward an opening in the ground.

name: The Start of a Rough Trail
description:
At the top of this ridge begins a beaten path through the well-known
Mount Cim, a double-peaked mountain that serves as a foundation for
the largest city in all of Shalar. To the east, a crowd of people
hustles and bustles to enter the pass to the north, while below
are the outskirts of Cimar.

name: The Start of a Rough Trail
description:
At the top of this ridge begins a beaten path through the well-known
Mount Cim, a double-peaked mountain that serves as a foundation for
the largest city in all of Shalar. A crowd of people hustles and bustles
to enter the pass while to the north, while below are the outskirts of
Cimar. To the east, the ridge continues. A stone marker marks the
beginning of the trail.

name: The Start of a Rough Trail
description:
At the top of this ridge begins a beaten path through the well-known
Mount Cim, a double-peaked mountain that serves as a foundation for
the largest city in all of Shalar. To the west, a crowd of people
hustles and bustles to enter the pass to the north, while below
are the outskirts of Cimar.

name: The Start of a Rough Trail
description:
At the top of this ridge begins a beaten path through the well-known
Mount Cim, a double-peaked mountain that serves as a foundation for
the largest city in all of Shalar. To the west, a crowd of people
hustles and bustles to enter the pass to the north, while below
are the outskirts of Cimar.

name: A Narrow Pass
description:
Two enormous structures of rock stand on either side of the trail,
narrowing it to hardly eight feet in width... Just enough for most
merchant caravans to be able to squeeze through. It would seem that
the two separate formations were once one, but they were somehow
artificially separated to make this trail possible. Two small wooden
ledges have been built into the walls about twenty feet up, where
archers have been stationed. The ground is obviously well travelled,
and its lack of rocks and brush is not surprising. All that covers
the light rock is a thin layer of powdery gray dirt.

name: A T-Crossing in The Mountain Pass
description:
Here, most of the traffic turns to the east. A few of the more rugged
adventurers slink off to the west, where the trail becomes quite a bit
rougher. Another elevated guard post is set into the northern rock wall
to watch for pickpockets, goblins or any other possible manifestation
of trouble.

name: A Worn Trail Through the Mountains
description:
The trail widens here, and the dusty gray earth seems to be becoming
lighter in hue. The crowd speaks freely here, showing that the danger
in this place is lesser than it is in other parts of the mountain.
To the west, there is a T-crossing in the path, while to the east
the trail continues, and becomes even lighter in color.

name: A Turn in the Worn Trail
description:
The bustling crowd here is continually kicking up the chalky grey dust
that covers the ground. The walls of rock and the sparse trees keep the
caravans following trail controlled, preventing travel anywhere off of
the trail for very far. The trail turns sharply, most of the crowd
heading to the north, where in the distance, it twists again.

name: A Turn in the Worn Path
description:
The bustling crowd here is continually kicking up the chalky grey dust
that covers the ground. The walls of rock and the sparse trees keep the
caravans following trail controlled, preventing travel anywhere off of
the trail for very far. The trail turns sharply, most of the crowd heading
to the east, where in the distance, it twists again.

name: A Turn in the Worn Path
description:
The bustling crowd here is continually kicking up the chalky light-grey
dust that covers the ground. The walls of rock and the sparse trees keep
the caravans following  trail controlled, preventing travel anywhere off
of the trail for very far. The trail turns sharply, most of the crowd
heading to the north, where in the distance, the dust seems to have
finally reached a brilliant white hue.

name: A Worn, White Path Through the Mountains
description:
The bustling crowd here is continually kicking up the chalky white dust
that covers the ground. To the south, the dust gets a bit darker.
Evergreen trees sporadically cover the slopes along the sides of the
path, and a few pine cones can be found on the floor here and there.
Fauna, however, does not show its face here. The sea of people has
begun to move a bit more quickly here due to the eagerness to reach
the end of this mountainous region, which is not far off.

name: A Worn, White Path Through the Mountains
description:
The bustling crowd here is continually kicking up the chalky white dust
that covers the ground. Evergreen trees sporadically cover the slopes
along the sides of the path, and a few pine cones can be found on the
floor here and there. Fauna, however, does not show its face here. The
sea of people has begun to move a bit more quickly here due to the
eagerness to reach the end of this mountainous region, which is not
far off. The ground slopes downward quite steeply here toward the
east, causing this path to intersect with another.

name: A Trail of Whitened Earth
description:
The bustling crowd here is continually kicking up the chalky white dust
that covers the ground. Evergreen trees sporadically cover the slopes along
the sides of the path, and a few pine cones can be found on the floor here
and there. Fauna, however, does not show its face here. To the east the
ground flattens out, and in the distance, beyond a cloud of this white
dust, lies a small village.

name: A Worn, White Intersection In the Mountains
description:
The bustling crowd here is continually kicking up the chalky white dust
that covers the ground. Evergreen trees sporadically cover the slopes
along the sides of the path, and a few pine cones can be found on the
floor here and there. Fauna, however, does not show its face here. The
main trail runs north and south, with an offshoot sloping up and to the
west to what appears to be another trail. Most of the traffic seems to
be travelling southward.

name: A Turn in the Worn, White Path
description:
The bustling crowd here is continually kicking up the chalky white dust
that covers the ground.  The vast majority of them are southbound, while
very occasionally, a few rugged-looking individuals struggle against the
crowd, heading north. Evergreen trees sporadically cover the slopes along
the sides of the path, and a few pine cones can be found on the floor here
and there. Fauna, however, does not show its face here. To the south lies
a crossroads of sorts, while to the north, the trail becomes a bit more
rough.

name: A Worn, White Path Through the Mountains
description:
The bustling crowd here is continually kicking up the chalky white dust
that covers the ground.  The vast majority of them are southbound, while
very occasionally, a few rugged-looking individuals struggle against the
crowd, heading north. Evergreen trees sporadically cover the slopes along
the sides of the path, and a few pine cones can be found on the floor here
and there. Fauna, however, does not show its face here. To the south, the
trail continues, while to the north, the trail becomes a bit more rough,
and the dirt becomes darker.

name: A Turn in the Worn Path
description:
The bustling crowd here is continually kicking up the chalky grey dust
that covers the ground.  The vast majority of them are southbound,
while very occasionally, a few rugged-looking individuals struggle
against the crowd, heading north. Evergreen trees sporadically cover
the slopes along the sides of the path, and a few pine cones can be
found on the floor here and there. Fauna, however, does not show its
face here. To the south, the trail becomes much brighter in color,
while to the west, it becomes a bit more rough.

name: A Turn in the Worn Path
description:
The bustling crowd here is continually kicking up the chalky grey dust
that covers the ground.  The vast majority of them are southbound, while
very occasionally, a few rugged-looking individuals struggle against
the crowd, heading north. Evergreen trees sporadically cover the slopes
along the sides of the path, and a few pine cones can be found on the
floor here and there. Fauna, however, does not show its face here. The
trail continues bending and winding to the north and to the east.

name: A Turn in the Worn Path
description:
The bustling crowd here is continually kicking up the chalky grey dust
that covers the ground.  The vast majority of them are southbound, while
very occasionally, a few rugged-looking individuals struggle against the
crowd, heading north. Evergreen trees sporadically cover the slopes along
the sides of the path, and a few pine cones can be found on the floor here
and there. Fauna, however, does not show its face here. The trail continues
bending and winding to the south and to the east.

name: A Narrow Trail
description:
The crowd here is relatively quiet, perhaps out of fear of a raid, or
perhaps out of a sort of claustrophobia. The trail has become narrow due
to the suddenly increased steepness of the slopes surrounding it to the
north and south. The grey powdery dirt is much rougher now, as many
pebbles tumble from the surrounding slopes. To the east, the trail
continues to narrow, while to the west, it opens back up.

name: A Narrow Trail
description:
The crowd here is relatively quiet, perhaps out of fear of a raid, or
perhaps out of a sort of claustrophobia. The trail has become narrow
due to the suddenly increased steepness of the slopes surrounding it to
the north and south. The grey powdery dirt is much rougher now, as many
pebbles tumble from the surrounding slopes. To the east, the trail
continues to be narrow, while further to the west, it opens back up.

name: A Narrow Trail
description:
The crowd here is relatively quiet, perhaps out of fear of a raid, or
perhaps out of a sort of claustrophobia. The trail has become narrow
due to the suddenly increased steepness of the slopes surrounding it
to the north and south. The grey powdery dirt is much rougher now, as
many pebbles tumble from the surrounding slopes. This narrow trail
continues to the east and west.

name: A Narrow Trail
description:
The crowd here is relatively quiet, perhaps out of fear of a raid, or
perhaps out of a sort of claustrophobia. Due to the bend in the trail,
there is some degree of gridlock in the traffic of the crowd. The
trail has become narrow due to the suddenly increased steepness of the
slopes surrounding it to the north and south. The grey powdery dirt is
much rougher now, as many pebbles tumble from the surrounding slopes.
The trail bends to the north and west.

name: A Narrow Trail
description:
The crowd here is relatively quiet, perhaps out of fear of a raid, or
perhaps out of a sort of claustrophobia. The trail has become narrow
due to the suddenly increased steepness of the slopes surrounding it
to the north and south. The grey powdery dirt is much rougher now, as
many pebbles tumble from the surrounding slopes. This narrow trail
continues to the north and south. To the south, things seem to be
slowing down slightly.

name: A Narrow Trail
description:
The crowd here is relatively quiet, perhaps out of fear of a raid, or
perhaps out of a sort of claustrophobia. The trail has become narrow
due to the suddenly increased steepness of the slopes surrounding it
to the north and south. The grey powdery dirt is much rougher now, as
many pebbles tumble from the surrounding slopes. This narrow trail
continues to the north and south.

name: A Narrow Trail
description:
The crowd here is relatively quiet, perhaps out of fear of a raid, or
perhaps out of a sort of claustrophobia. Due to the bend in the trail,
there is some degree of gridlock in the traffic of the crowd. The trail
has become narrow due to the suddenly increased steepness of the slopes
surrounding it to the north and south. The grey powdery dirt is much
rougher now, as many pebbles tumble from the surrounding slopes. The
trail bends to the south and east.

name: A Narrow Trail
description:
The crowd here is relatively quiet, perhaps out of fear of a raid, or
perhaps out of a sort of claustrophobia. Due to the bend in the trail,
there is some degree of gridlock in the traffic of the crowd. The
trail has become narrow due to the suddenly increased steepness of the
slopes surrounding it to the north and south. The grey powdery dirt is
much rougher now, as many pebbles tumble from the surrounding slopes.
The trail bends to the south and east, where you can make out a small
village.

name: A Winding Trail, Guard Outpost
description:
This trail is very rough, and is obviously traveled very rarely. It winds
back and forth around giant boulders and crevices and can become quite
narrow at points. A small band of guards have set up an outpost here to
keep any of the undesirable creatures from the mountains away from the
common travelers of these mountain roads and the city of Cimar. The trail
continues to the west, and to the east there is an intersection.

name: A Winding Trail
description:
This trail is very rough, and is obviously traveled very rarely. It winds
back and forth around giant boulders and crevices and can become quite
narrow at points. To the north lie a few trees, though the wildlife
around this area is scarce. To the east, the winding trail continues
toward an outpost.

name: A Winding Trail
description:
This trail is very rough, and is obviously traveled very rarely. It winds
back and forth around giant boulders and crevices and can become quite
narrow at points. Although it is far from a forest, there are a few trees
scattered about this area. From time to time, a small wilderness creature
can be spotted around here. The trail winds to the west and to the south.

name: A Winding Trail
description:
This trail is very rough, and is obviously traveled very rarely. It winds
back and forth around giant boulders and crevices and can become quite
narrow at points. Although it is far from a forest, there are a few trees
scattered about this area. From time to time, a small wilderness creature
can be spotted around here. The trail winds to the east and to the west.

This trail is very rough, and is obviously traveled very rarely. It winds
back and forth around giant boulders and crevices and can become quite

This trail is very rough, and is obviously traveled very rarely. It winds

This trail is very rough, and is obviously traveled very rarely. It winds

name: A Winding Trail
description:
This trail is very rough, and is obviously traveled very rarely. It winds
back and forth around giant boulders and crevices and can become quite
narrow at points. Although it is far from a forest, there are a few trees
scattered about this area. From time to time, a small wilderness creature
can be spotted around here. The trail winds to the west and to the north.

name: A Trail's End
description:
The trail ends here, and the wilderness begins. Although it is far from a
forest, there are a few trees scattered about this area. From time to time,
a small wilderness creature can be spotted around here. Rocks and steep
slopes make this a tiresome trek, but it is possible for the well-traveled
or stubborn to handle. To the east, you can return to the trail, while to
the north or to the west, the mountain awaits.

name: On the Western Side of Mount Cim
description:
This part of the mountain is rather steep, and it is possible to ascend
the mountain if navigated correctly. There are a few trees scattered about
this area. From time to time, a small wilderness creature can be spotted
around here. Large rocks and other such obstacles make this a tiresome trek,
but it is possible for the well-traveled or stubborn to handle. To the south
lies the end, or beginning, of a trail, while to the west, the side of the
mountain continues.

name: On the Western Side of Mount Cim
description:
This part of the mountain is rather steep, and it is possible to ascend
the mountain if navigated correctly. There are a few trees scattered about
this area. From time to time, a small wilderness creature can be spotted
around here. Large rocks and other such obstacles make this a tiresome trek,
but it is possible for the well-traveled or stubborn to handle. The side of
the mountain continues in all directions.

name: On the Western Side of Mount Cim
description:
This part of the mountain is rather steep, and it is possible to ascend
the mountain if navigated correctly. There are a few trees scattered about
this area. From time to time, a small wilderness creature can be spotted
around here. Large rocks and other such obstacles make this a tiresome trek,
but it is possible for the well-traveled or stubborn to handle. The side of
the mountain continues to the north and south.

name: On the Western Side of Mount Cim
description:
This part of the mountain is rather steep, and it is possible to ascend
the mountain if navigated correctly. There are a few trees scattered about
this area. From time to time, a small wilderness creature can be spotted
around here. Large rocks and other such obstacles make this a tiresome trek,
but it is possible for the well-traveled or stubborn to handle. The side of
the mountain continues to the east and west.

name: On the Western Side of Mount Cim
description:
This part of the mountain is rather steep, and it is possible to ascend
the mountain if navigated correctly. There are a few trees scattered about
this area. From time to time, a small wilderness creature can be spotted
around here. Large rocks and other such obstacles make this a tiresome trek,
but it is possible for the well-traveled or stubborn to handle. The rock
walls have formed a sort of culdesac here, though the rock to the northeast
seems stable enough to climb. To the south, the bottom of the western side
of the mountain continues.

name: On the Western Side of Mount Cim
description:
This part of the mountain is rather steep, and it is possible to ascend
the mountain if navigated correctly. There are a few trees scattered about
this area. From time to time, a small wilderness creature can be spotted
around here. Large rocks and other such obstacles make this a tiresome trek,
but it is possible for the well-traveled or stubborn to handle. The side of
the mountain continues to the north and east.

name: A Dead End
description:
The rock walls have formed a sort of culdesac here. This part of the
mountain is rather steep, and it is possible to ascend the mountain
if navigated correctly. There are a few trees scattered about this area.
From time to time, a small wilderness creature can be spotted around here.
Large rocks and other such obstacles make this a tiresome trek, but it is
possible for the well-traveled or stubborn to handle. The side of the
mountain continues to the south.

name: A Ledge on the Western Side of Mount Cim
description:
Along the side of this steep incline sits a narrow ledge that winds around
the mountain, allowing a relatively easy climb. The air begins to thin
noticeably. The ledge continues to the north, or you could descend back
to the lower part of the mountain.

name: A Ledge on the Western Side of Mount Cim
description:
Along the side of this steep incline sits a narrow ledge that winds
around the mountain, allowing a relatively easy climb. The air begins
to thin noticeably. The ledge curves around to the south and the east,
so that a part of it juts out into empty air.

name: A Ledge on the Western Side of Mount Cim
description:
Along the side of this steep incline sits a narrow ledge that winds around
the mountain, allowing a relatively easy climb. The air begins to thin
noticeably. The ledge continues to the east and to the west.

name: A Ledge on the Western Side of Mount Cim
description:
Along the side of this steep incline sits a narrow ledge that winds around
the mountain, allowing a relatively easy climb. The air begins to thin
noticeably. The ledge continues to the north and to the west.

name: A Ledge on the Western Side of Mount Cim
description:
Along the side of this steep incline sits a narrow ledge that winds around
the mountain, allowing a relatively easy climb. The air begins to thin
noticeably. The ledge comes to a halt to the north and east, while to the
west is nothing but space. The eastern wall is slanted, so that it looks
rather easy to climb.

name: Nearing a Plateau
description:
This broad, declining strip of land slopes downward to the east and
drops abruptly to the west. Off in the distance to the east, you can
see a forested plateau and the two frosted peaks of Mount Cim climbing
high into the clouds. To the south you can see the city of Cimar, far
below.

name: Nearing a Plateau
description:
This broad, declining strip of land slopes downward to the east and
climbs upward to the west. Off in the distance to the east, you can
see a forested plateau and the two frosted peaks of Mount Cim climbing
high into the clouds. To the south the slope continues, toward the forested
plateau.

name: A Forested Plateau
description:
The ground is relatively even, with the exception of the odd up or down
slope or outstanding tree root. The trees here are exceptionally tall,
and the forest is rather dense, making passage difficult. The air is
rather thin and cold, and occasionally, a patch of snow can be found on
the ground. To the north, the forest thins out and the terrain becomes
more mountainous again.

name: A Forested Plateau
description:
The ground is relatively even, with the exception of the odd up or down
slope or outstanding tree root. The trees here are exceptionally tall,
and the forest is rather dense, making passage difficult. The air is
rather thin and cold, and occasionally, a patch of snow can be found on
the ground.

name: A Forested Plateau
description:
The ground is relatively even, with the exception of the odd up or down
slope or outstanding tree root. The trees here are exceptionally tall,
and the forest is rather dense, making passage difficult. The air is
rather thin and cold, and occasionally, a patch of snow can be found on
the ground.

name: At the Base of the Western Mountain
description:
This is where the western peak begins to rise from the plateau that
serves as a foundation for both peaks of the mountain. The air is
rather thin and cold, and occasionally, a patch of snow can be found on
the ground. To the east, the plateau leads away from the western peak, and
on the northern rock wall are some jagged rocks that could serve as
handholds.

name: Along the Base of the Western Mountain
description:
This is where the western peak begins to rise from the plateau that
serves as a foundation for both peaks of the mountain. The air is
rather thin and cold, and occasionally, a patch of snow can be found on
the ground. To the east and south, the plateau continues along the base
of the western peak.

name: Along the Base of the Western Mountain
description:
This is where the western peak begins to rise from the plateau that
serves as a foundation for both peaks of the mountain. The air is
rather thin and cold, and occasionally, a patch of snow can be found on
the ground. To the north and west, the plateau continues along the base
of the western peak.

name: Along the Base of the Western Mountain
description:
This is where the western peak begins to rise from the plateau that
serves as a foundation for both peaks of the mountain. The air is
rather thin and cold, and occasionally, a patch of snow can be found on
the ground. To the east, the plateau continues along the base of the
western peak, while to the south, a part of the plateau juts out over
Cimar.

name: Before a Jutting Cliff
description:
This cliff is composed of pure stone, and although narrow and somewhat
thin, it is very solid. Back to the north is a forested plateau, while to
the south, the cliff juts out into the air, giving a perfect bird's-eye
view of the city of Cimar.

name: A Forested Plateau
description:
The ground is relatively even, with the exception of the odd up or down
slope or outstanding tree root. The trees here are exceptionally tall,
and the forest is rather dense, making passage difficult. The scent of
pine fills the cold, thin air, and occasionally, a patch of snow can be
found on the ground. The wildlife is quite rich here, and the lushness
of this forest is remarkable, despite the climate. Something seems
strange about the floor here.

name: A Forested Plateau
description:
The ground is relatively even, with the exception of the odd up or down
slope or outstanding tree root. The trees here are exceptionally tall,
and the forest is rather dense, making passage difficult. The scent of
pine fills the cold, thin air, and occasionally, a patch of snow can be
found on the ground. The wildlife is quite rich here, and the lushness
of this forest is remarkable, despite the climate.

name: A Forested Plateau
description:
The ground is relatively even, with the exception of the odd up or down
slope or outstanding tree root. The trees here are exceptionally tall,
and the forest is rather dense, making passage difficult. The scent of
pine fills the cold, thin air, and occasionally, a patch of snow can be
found on the ground. The wildlife is quite rich here, and the lushness
of this forest is remarkable, despite the climate.

name: A Forested Plateau
description:
The ground is relatively even, with the exception of the odd up or down
slope or outstanding tree root. The trees here are exceptionally tall,
and the forest is rather dense, making passage difficult. The scent of
pine fills the cold, thin air, and occasionally, a patch of snow can be
found on the ground. The wildlife is quite rich here, and the lushness
of this forest is remarkable, despite the climate. The edge of the
plateau slopes down to a worn trail.

name: A Forested Plateau
description:
The ground is relatively even, with the exception of the odd up or down
slope or outstanding tree root. The trees here are exceptionally tall,
and the forest is rather dense, making passage difficult. The scent of
pine fills the cold, thin air, and occasionally, a patch of snow can be
found on the ground. The wildlife is quite rich here, and the lushness
of this forest is remarkable, despite the climate.

name: A Forested Plateau
description:
The ground is relatively even, with the exception of the odd up or down
slope or outstanding tree root. The trees here are exceptionally tall,
and the forest is rather dense, making passage difficult. The scent of
pine fills the cold, thin air, and occasionally, a patch of snow can be
found on the ground. The wildlife is quite rich here, and the lushness
of this forest is remarkable, despite the climate.

name: A Forested Plateau
description:
The ground is relatively even, with the exception of the odd up or down
slope or outstanding tree root. The trees here are exceptionally tall,
and the forest is rather dense, making passage difficult. The scent of
pine fills the cold, thin air, and occasionally, a patch of snow can be
found on the ground. The wildlife is quite rich here, and the lushness
of this forest is remarkable, despite the climate.

name: At the Base of the Eastern Mountain
description:
The forest thins here as it runs up against a sheer wall of granite. A few
stones stick out from the wall to the north, but they are perfectly shaped
and obviously artificial. It is apparent that the wilderness here is not as
pure and untouched as most would think. To the south, the forest continues,
while climbing the rock to the north would bring you closer to the peak.

name: High Up on the Western Mountain
description:
The chilling wind whips around you as the air becomes thinner by the
moment. Patches of frost have begun to appear at this impressive height,
and both the flora and the fauna have begun to disappear. You are able to
continue your trek to the east, or head downward, back to the flat, forested
area.

name: High Up on the Western Mountain
description:
The chilling wind whips around you as the air becomes thinner by the
moment. Patches of frost have begun to appear at this impressive height,
and both the flora and the fauna have begun to disappear. To the east
begins an incline, while to the west you can make your way back down
toward the safer forested area.

name: High Up on the Western Mountain
description:
The chilling wind whips around you as the air becomes thinner by the
moment. Patches of frost have begun to appear at this impressive height,
and both the flora and the fauna have begun to disappear. The incline
continues to the north, while the mountain declines toward the east. The
east and south are sheer rock and empty air, respectively.

name: High Up on the Western Mountain
description:
The chilling wind whips around you as the air becomes thinner by the
moment. Patches of frost have begun to appear at this impressive height,
and both the flora and the fauna have begun to disappear. To the north,
the climb continues, and to the south, the mountain declines gradually.

name: Below a Ledge, High on the Western Mountain
description:
The chilling wind whips around you as the air becomes thinner by the
moment. Patches of frost have begun to appear at this impressive height,
and both the flora and the fauna have begun to disappear. To the south,
the mountain declines gradually, and although you could continue further
to the west, it ends in a sheer wall of rock. The northern wall, though
is climbable.

name: High Up on the Western Mountain
description:
Patches of frost have begun to appear at this impressive height,
and both the flora and the fauna have begun to disappear. There is nothing
here, save a dead end and a way back to the east. The winds can't reach
you here, and it is quite peaceful compared to what lies back to the east.

name: A Ledge Below the Western Peak
description:
The chilling wind whips around you as the air becomes thinner by the
moment. Patches of frost abound at this impressive height, and the only
sort of plants that can survive these conditions are small, scraggly and
rough. To the south, this ledge continues, while below you lies the harsh
path back to the plateau.

name: A Ledge Below the Western Peak
description:
The chilling wind whips around you as the air becomes thinner by the
moment. Patches of frost abound at this impressive height, and the only
sort of plants that can survive these conditions are small, scraggly and
rough. To the north, this ledge continues, while the eastern wall is
climbable, and very possibly access to the western peak.

name: The Western Peak of Mount Cim
description:
Finally, you stand upon the icy apex of the western peak of Mount Cim.
Looking toward the northeast, the eastern peak is visible, and of
approximately the same height. All around you the air is very free,
but the ground is very steep, especially to the east. Below, Cimar
looks small, yet intricate and the bustling people in the pass near
the mountain's base aren't even visible. Much of the rest of the lands
further away seem very hazy due both to the facts that you are above
many of the clouds, and that you are simply very far away from them.

name: A Dark and Narrow Passage
description:
This cramped and narrow passage is composed entirely of a sort of
slick, jagged black rock, which is uncharacteristic of Mount Cim,
a mountain almost completely made of gray stone. To climb back up
to the peak from here is impossible, due to the sheerness and glass-
like smoothness of the rock. From here, you can only head to the south.

name: A Passage of Jagged Stone
description:
This cramped and narrow passage is composed entirely of a sort of
slick, jagged black rock, which is uncharacteristic of Mount Cim,
a mountain almost completely made of gray stone. The passage drops
down into darkness from here.

name: An Earthen Cave
description:
A thick pile of soft earth acts as a cushion to any who might have fallen
from above into here. Roots line the brown dirt walls, and a strange,
humid warmth permeates this cave. A cold breeze blows in from the south
from time to time.

name: A Mossy Crevice
description:
This crevice opens up into a secluded place somewhere between the two peaks
of the mountain. In the distance, you can hear and smell running water, and
a fine mist constantly drifts in from the south. The rocks around you are
covered with moss from the constant exposure to dampness.

name: A Hidden Waterfall
description:
A semicircle of rocks surround a small pool, into which a beautiful
waterfall flows. Although it is small, it makes a loud noise due to the
shape of the rocks behind it. There is something strange about the pool,
though... It has no obvious outlet, yet it never gets any more full than
it is.

name: A Damp Cavern
description:
Darkness envelopes this cavern almost as strongly as the scent of damp
earth does. The sound of the waterfall echoes loudly throughout the cave,
which continues to the south and east, while the waterfall lies back to
the west.

name: A Damp Cavern
description:
Darkness envelopes this cavern almost as strongly as the scent of damp
earth does. A strange symbol is carved into the northern wall. The sound
of the waterfall echoes loudly throughout the cave, which continues to the
south and west, while the waterfall lies back to the west.

name: A Damp Cavern
description:
Darkness envelopes this cavern almost as strongly as the scent of damp
earth does. The sound of the waterfall echoes loudly throughout the cave,
which continues to the north and east, while the waterfall lies back to
the west.

name: A Damp Cavern
description:
Darkness envelopes this cavern almost as strongly as the scent of damp
earth does. The sound of the waterfall echoes loudly throughout the cave,
which continues to the north, west and east, while the waterfall lies back
to the west. A breeze wafts in from the east.

name: A Beautifully Carved Alcove
description:
Thin beams of light enter this room from numerous holes in the ceiling,
revealing a shrine-like room. The walls are covered with multi-colored
shells from the southern seas, causing the reflecting light to take on
a prismatic effect. Numerous statues of odd-looking humanoids are carved
from the rock itself, so that the statues are literally part of the
mountain. It is quite obvious that this place has remained relatively
untouched for ages upon ages.

name: A High Ledge on the Eastern Mountain
description:
The chilling wind whips around you as the air becomes thinner by the
moment. Patches of frost have begun to appear at this impressive height,
and both the flora and the fauna have begun to disappear. To the west,
the ledge continues, and on the northern wall are some smooth stones that
make climbing down possible.

name: A High Ledge on the Eastern Mountain
description:
The chilling wind whips around you as the air becomes thinner by the
moment. Patches of frost have begun to appear at this impressive height,
and both the flora and the fauna have begun to disappear. To the south,
the ledge continues to rise, and to the east, the ledge declines gradually.

name: A High Ledge on the Eastern Mountain
description:
The chilling wind whips around you as the air becomes thinner by the
moment. Patches of frost have begun to appear at this impressive height,
and both the flora and the fauna have begun to disappear. To the south,
the ledge continues to rise, and to the north, the ledge declines
gradually.

name: A High Ledge on the Eastern Mountain
description:
The chilling wind whips around you as the air becomes thinner by the
moment. Patches of frost have begun to appear at this impressive height,
and both the flora and the fauna have begun to disappear. To the east,
the ledge continues to rise, and to the north, the ledge declines
gradually.

name: A High Ledge on the Eastern Mountain
description:
The chilling wind whips around you as the air becomes thinner by the
moment. Patches of frost have begun to appear at this impressive height,
and both the flora and the fauna have begun to disappear. To the east,
the ledge continues to rise, and to the west, the ledge declines
gradually.

name: Below the Eastern Peak
description:
The chilling wind whips around you as the air becomes thinner by the
moment. Much of the ground is covered by a layer of ice, and the plant-
life is completely nonexistant at thie height. To the west, a ledge
gradually slopes down and around toward the plateau below you. On the
southern wall, some indentations have been carved into the rock, allowing
an easy climb to the eastern peak.

name: The Eastern Peak of Mount Cim
description:
A broad ledge serves as footing here, for the peak itself is almost
unclimbable. The remainder of the peak rises about fifteen feet above
the ledge, but it is sheer and icy. Below you, you can see the entirety
of Mount Cim, along with the frosty clouds that swirl around both
peaks. Over to the west, you can see the other peak of the mountain,
standing at about the same height. A weathered trail branches off of
the ledge and leads around the peak to the south, while you can climb
down to a narrower ledge via some handholds below you.

name: An Ancient Trail Around the Eastern Peak
description:
This path is composed of intricately carved cobblestones that have been
weathered by the harsh climate up here. A thin layer of ice covers the
trail, making the carvings' features indistinguishable. A frigid wind
whips around you, bringing with it a puff of snow. To the north lies a
broad ledge, while to the east, the ancient trail continues.

name: An Ancient Trail Around the Eastern Peak
description:
This path is composed of intricately carved cobblestones that have been
weathered by the harsh climate up here. A thin layer of ice covers the
trail, making the carvings' features indistinguishable. A frigid wind
whips around you, bringing with it a puff of snow. The ancient trail
continues to the east and west.

name: An Ancient Trail Around the Eastern Peak
description:
This path is composed of intricately carved cobblestones that have been
weathered by the harsh climate up here. A thin layer of ice covers the
trail, making the carvings' features indistinguishable. A frigid wind
whips around you, bringing with it a puff of snow. The ancient trail
curves here to the north and to the west.

name: An Ancient Trail Around the Eastern Peak
description:
This path is composed of intricately carved cobblestones that have been
weathered by the harsh climate up here. A thin layer of ice covers the
trail, making the carvings' features indistinguishable. A frigid wind
whips around you, bringing with it a puff of snow. The ancient trail
curves here to the south and to the east.

name: The End of an Ancient Trail
description:
This is as far as it is physically possible to climb. The chilling
winds whip around the peak, and the trail stops abruptly, ending in
a sheer vertical cliff facing toward the east. Brilliantly white ice
covers the ground beneath you, and the footing is far from steady. To
the north, the mountain continues to climb for another twenty feet or
so. Just off the weathered trail, a small crevice is set into the ground.

name: A Small, Frigid Cave
description:
In this tiny, cramped cave, every wall is composed of frost-covered
jagged black stones.  In the eastern wall, there is a deep, mossy niche.
Cold wind drifts in from above, where the eastern peak stands proudly.  The
ground is solid, yet as you step, something crunches beneath your feet.  You
can climb back out of this cramped cavern using the rocks to the north.

name: Path in the plains
description:
You are walking on a path situated in the rough plains.
You feel the strong winds blow through your hair as you study
the beautiful landscaping here. The path continues east, north
and west leads to plains and you see the path which stretches
all the way to Melcene to your south.

name: Path in the plains
description:
You are walking on a path situated in the rough plains.
You feel the strong winds blow through your hair as you study
the beautiful landscaping here. The path continues east and west.

name: Path in the plains
description:
You are walking on a path situated in the rough plains.
You feel the strong winds blow through your hair as you study
the beautiful landscaping here. The path continues north and west.

name: Path in the plains
description:
You are walking on a path situated in the rough plains.
You feel the strong winds blow through your hair as you study
the beautiful landscaping here. The path leads north and south.
To the east and the west you have the grassy plains.

name: Path in the plains
description:
You are walking on a path situated in the rough plains.
You feel the strong winds blow through your hair as you study
the beautiful landscaping here. The Path leads north and south.

name: Path in the plains
description:
You are walking on a path situated in the rough plains.
You feel the strong winds blow through your hair as you watch the
beautiful landscaping here. To the east and west you see the grassy plains.
The path extends into small foothills to the north and also continues south.

name: Path in the foothills
description:
You are on the path leading through the small foothills.
The wind blow through your hair as you study the beautiful
landscaping here. From the north you sense a certain freshness.
The path continues east and south. You smell freshness from north.

name: Path in the foothills
description:
You are walking on a path situated in the small foothills.
The winds are more than average here but it feels nice. You can follow
the path east or west.

name: Path in the foothills
description:
You are walking on a narrow path in the foothills.
You feel the strong winds blow through your hair as you study
the beautiful landscaping here. The path goes north and west.

name: Path in the foothills
description:
You are walking on a path situated in foothills.
To the west you sense a certain freshness and the path continues
south and east.

name: Path in the foothills
description:
You are walking on a long path in the east-west direction.
The surroundings are green, vegetated foothills.
You are able to force your way through some dense plants to the north.

name: Path in the foothills
description:
You are walking on the long, narrow path through the foothills.
To your east you see a T-intersection and to the west the path
continues far.

name: The path intersection
description:
You are standing on an intersection between 3 paths.  To the west you can
follow a long, narrow path through the foothills.  To the north a wide path
opens up, leading eventually into a huge canyon.

name: The canyon road
description:
You are walking on a wide road with trail marks on it.  To the north
you see a huge canyon and to the south there is the T intersection.
You can enter the foothills west.  The foothills to your east are too
steep to climb.

name: On the cusp of Rivenrock Canyon
description:
You are standing just to the north of Rivenrock Canyon.
The village looks very small, but still a nice and safe place to stay.
You may enter the city to the north or journey towards the
T-intersection in the southern direction.

name: Gallow hill
description:
You walk in the grassy plains. On this little hill you can see
two gallows, with rotting human tissue hanging from the ropes.
There is a sign here.

name: Grassy plains
description:
You walk in the grassy plains among the herbs which grow here. The wind is
strong and rough. Far to the north you can see the foothills and further on
mountain peaks are visible.

name: Grassy plains
description:
You walk in the grassy plains among the herbs which grow here. The wind is
strong and rough. Far to the north you can see the foothills and further on
mountain peaks are visible. City of Melcene is to the south but so are some
VERY steep slopes.

name: Grassy plains
description:
You walk in the beautiful grassy plains. The wind is strong and rough.
Far to the north you can see the foothills and further on mountain peaks
are visible.

name: Grassy plains
description:
You walk in the grassy plains among the herbs which grow here. The wind is
strong and rough. To the north you can see the foothills and just behind
mountain peaks are visible.

name: Grassy plains
description:
You walk in some grassy plains. The wind is strong and rough. To the
north you can see the foothills and further on mountain peaks are visible.

name: Grassy plains
description: You walk in the grassy plains. The wind is fairly strong.

name: Grassy foothills
description:
You walk in the grassy foothills north of the plains. The wind is rough.
To the north you can see foothills and just behind them mountain peaks
are visible.

name: The steep foothills
description:
You walk in the steep foothills. It is rather hard to move here.
To the north you can see a grassy valley with wildflowers.

name: The steep foothills
description:
You are walking in the steep foothills. It is rather hard to move here.
To the north you can see the mountains towering over you.  Pine trees
grow here.

name: The steep foothills
description:
You are walking in the steep foothills. It is rather hard to move here.
Further to the north you can see the mountains towering over you.
Several pinetrees grow here.

name: The pool in the foothills
description:
You are standing by a pool in the small foothills. It is clear and cold.
A steep slope rises up into the foothills to the north. Behind them ...
the mountains.

name: The foothills
description:
You are walking in some foothills. It is rather hard to move here.
Further to the north you can see the mountains towering over you.
Several pinetrees grow here.

name: A Grassy Path
description:
Massive evergreens mark the beginning of the forest around you.  To the
north the forest becomes much more dense, and looms darkly in the distance. 
The vibrant sounds of the forest permiate the air all around you.  The
ground beneath your feet is a bit moist, and the smell of earth fills the
air.  The faint sound of water can be heard in the distance.  The plains
expand to the south of here.

name: In front of hut in foothills
description:
You are standing in the foothills. To the west, well hidden among the small
foothills and pines, you see a small hut. To the north you can see
the foothills, and some pineforrest. Further on mountain peaks are visible.

name: Hermit's hut
description:
You are inside the hermit's hut. It is rather old, but serves it purpose.
It keeps its habitant from the rough winds and dangerous beasts of the
plains and foothills. There is a small fireplace here.

name: The ancient path
description:
You are moving on an ancient path. The path is slightly covered with
leaves and twitches.
To the north you can see the T-crossing and the path continues south.

name: The ancient path
description:
You are standing on the ancient path which runs north and south.
The path is hardly visible here.

name: The ancient path
description:
You are standing on the ancient path which runs north and south.
The path is hardly visible here.

name: The ancient path
description:
The path runs north and east from here.  You notice some markers placed
along the side of the path.

name: The wooden bridge
description:
You have stepped upon a wooden bridge. It looks old but safe to cross.
It is made of a wood you haven't seen before.

name: The ancient path
description:
You find yourself located between the bridge and the rock formations.
As you approach the formations you begin to realize the true size of
them, about 15 feet tall and almost perfect rectangular shape.
You feel impressed with the awesome sight.

name: Grassy plains
description:
You walk in the grassy plains among the herbs which grow here. The wind is
strong and rough. Far to the north you can see the foothills and further on
mountain peaks are visible.

name: The Stones of G'harne
description:
You are in the center of 7, 15 ft tall monolith like black stones.
In the center of the ring formed by the monolith you can't help
noticing a big sacrifice altar. The ground is covered with dirt, but the
altar shows no sign of such. West of here is the ancient path.

name: Dark smelly tunnels
description:
You are standing in a gloomy tunnel leading south and west, right under
the altar of G'harne.  The walls are covered with a smelly slime and small
rotting pieces of a meat like substance, fills the air with an unbearable
stench.  You might be able to force your way up into fresh air from here.

name: Dead end of tunnel
description:
The tunnel comes to an abrupt end here. It simply looks like it
hasn't been excavated further.  North of here the tunnel makes a turn east.

name: Dark smelly tunnels
description:
You are standing in a gloomy tunnel leading east and west.
The walls are covered with a smelly slime and small rotting pieces of a
meat like substance, fills the air with an unbearable stench.

name: Dark smelly tunnels
description:
You are standing in a small smelly tunnel under the plains.
The smell is growing stronger to the west, so is the density of the
slime and other undeterminable substances ...

name: The Hall of G'harne
description:
You stand in the hall of G'harne. The walls are dressed with strange
carving, symbolizing human sacrifice and people worshipping giant worms.
Disgusting slime and gore are also very dominant in your view of this room.

name: Steep slope
description:
You try to climb down the slope.
>
You slip!
You fall and tumble.
You hit your head HARD.

name: On a Damp Path
description:
Small insects buzz obnoxiously about your face and body while the
trees continue to loom above you creating a nice canopy for shade.
You hear the occasional bird chirp as well as odd, seemingly amphibian
noise. Long vines hang from the trees and mosses and lichen grow an
just about anything. The trees to the north and west are too thick to
venture through, while a very damp path continues to the south and
east.

name: On a Damp Path
description:
Small insects buzz obnoxiously about your face and body while the trees
continue to loom above you creating a nice canopy for shade. You hear
the occasional bird chirp as well as odd, seemingly amphibian noise.
Long vines hang from the trees and mosses and lichen grow an just about
anything. The trees to the north are too thick to traverse, but the
damp path continues in most other directions.

name: A Turn in the Damp Path
description:
The path makes a slight bend here to avoid the solid wall of marshy
flora, which seems to surround you as well as coat everything in sight.
Long vines hang from the trees and mosses and lichen grow an just about
anything. Amidst the swampy grounds there are some oddly shape stone
objects. The path is halted to the north and east while it continues to
the south and west.

name: A Small Opening in the Canopy
description:
The sky above is now clearly visible through small gap in the natural
awning. This causes for a nice breeze to circle around you. Long vines
hang from the trees and mosses and lichen grow an just about anything.
The marsh stretches on in most directions. To the north is the edge of
the swamp.

name: Under an Awning of Cypress Trees
description:
The trunks of trees, sporadically coated with moss, spring up around
you. Their massive branches reaching towards the sky much like the
outstretched arms of religions fanatics. Random insects buzz around you
and the occasional amphibian noise is heard from some rotted out
hollow. The ground below your feet is damp and murky and the air is
thick with humidity. The marsh continues to the west and south. To the
north is the edge of the swamp.

name: On a Damp Path
description:
Small insects buzz obnoxiously about your face and body while the trees
continue to loom above you creating a nice canopy for shade. You hear
the occasional bird chirp as well as odd, seemingly amphibian noise.
Long vines hang from the trees and mosses and lichen grow an just about
anything. The trees to the north and west are too thick to venture
through, while a very damp path continues to the south and east.

name: On a Damp Path
description:
Small insects buzz obnoxiously about your face and body while the trees
continue to loom above you creating a nice canopy for shade. You hear
the occasional bird chirp as well as odd, seemingly amphibian noise.
Long vines hang from the trees and mosses and lichen grow an just about
anything. The murky path continues to the north, east and west. While
the was south is blocked by a massive stone pillar.

name: An Intersection in the Damp Path
description:
Although still draped with mosses and vines, the trees here seem less
frequent and spread apart. This is probably one of the places in the
marsh that receives plenty of travel from the local wildlife. The sky
is even a bit more visible here than in other parts of the dreary
marsh. Long vines hang from the trees and mosses and lichen grow an
just about anything.

name: On a Damp Path
description:
Small insects buzz obnoxiously about your face and body while the trees
continue to loom above you creating a nice canopy for shade. You hear
the occasional bird chirp as well as odd, seemingly amphibian noise.
Long vines have draped themselves across the branches of trees and
other local flora. The path continues to the north and east while the
south and west seem blocked off by the numerous vines.

name: Inside a Cave of Vines
description:
This small space is completely enclosed by vines, creating what must be
a natural shelter from the weather or other disasters. The ground is
not that damp here and it surely serves its purpose as a cover from
harm. In the corner you see what appears to be a makeshift bed. The
only way out is back through the vines.

name: On the Boggy Trail
description:
Although muddy and waterlogged as it is, a trail is clearly visible
running through the middle of the muggy ground. Various reeds spring up
on either side as it leads to what appears to be a shallow pool in the
marsh. A high-pitched buzz fills the air, emanating from a thin cloud
of tiny insects making the experience that much more distracting. The
trail continues to the east and the banks of a pool are to the south.

name: On the Boggy Trail
description:
Although muddy and waterlogged as it is, a trail is clearly visible
running through the middle of the muggy ground. Various reeds spring up
on either side while the air seems to get more dense with humidity and
insects. Long vines hang from the trees and mosses and lichen grow an
just about anything. The trail continues to the west and south from
here.

name: Under an Awning of Cypress Trees
description:
The trunks of trees, sporadically coated with moss, spring up around
you. Their massive branches reaching towards the sky much like the
outstretched arms of religions fanatics. Long vines hang from the trees
and mosses and lichen grow an just about anything. To the north you see
a bit of a clearing while the marsh continues to the east and south.

name: Underneath the Willow Tree
description:
The awning you were previously under is dwarfed in shocking comparison
to this weeping willow. Its long branches rain down, almost sweeping
the floor of the marsh creating a very peaceful and serene setting to
witness. The trunk is twice the width of a titan, and the dome-like
awning the tree creates is larger than many houses. Rows of smaller
cypress trees grow to the north, west and south, but you can get a
better view of the marsh by climbing up into the willow tree.

name: On a Damp Path
description:
Small insects buzz obnoxiously about your face and body while the trees
continue to loom above you creating a nice canopy for shade. You hear
the occasional bird chirp as well as odd, seemingly amphibian noise.
Long vines hang from the trees and mosses and lichen grow an just about
anything. The path winds to the east and west, weaving through the
slime and muck.

name: A Split in the Damp Path
description:
Small insects buzz obnoxiously about your face and body while the trees
continue to loom above you creating a nice canopy for shade. You hear
the occasional bird chirp as well as odd, seemingly amphibian noise.
The trees here grow in a straight row to the south, as if they were
planted instead of rising up on their own. Long vines drape down
through the trees to the east, making the path in that direction seem a
little less obvious than the thick, slimy mud you now travel on.

name: On a Thin Path
description:
The trees grow in straight lines on all sides of you. Their branches
extend out above the path as it turns, covering the walkway with a
natural arch and cutting off the light from above. Long vines stream
down from the trees, swaying slightly in a light breeze, appearing like
snakes hanging by their tails. The path opens up to the west, but gets
more dismal and dark to the south.

name: On a Damp Path
description:
Small insects buzz obnoxiously about your face and body while the trees
continue to loom above you creating a nice canopy for shade. You hear
the occasional bird chirp as well as odd, seemingly amphibian noise.
Long vines hang from the trees and mosses and lichen grow an just about
anything. The path winds to the north and south, weaving amidst the
slime and muck.

name: A Murky Pool
description:
At what must be a low point in the marsh, the water has collected to
form a shallow pool of standing water. With roots extended up out of
the water, the trees still grow abundantly here. The water is coated
with a thin film of scum, making it impossible to see far below the
surface. To the north and west the pool continues, but the vines and
trees are too dense to travel through.

name: A Murky Pool
description:
At what must be a low point in the marsh, the water has collected to
form a shallow pool of standing water. With roots extended up out of
the water, the trees still grow abundantly here. The water is coated
with a thin film of scum, making it impossible to see far below the
surface. To the north the pool continues, but the vines and trees are
too dense to travel through.

name: On the Banks of a Pool
description:
The boggy trail widens as the mud becomes softer, much like a dirt
soup. The ground slopes downward to the west towards a shallow pool in
the marsh. Small streaks of light make it through the overhanging
ferns, illuminating the moss covered area with a dull luster. A thick
patch of reeds and ferns lay eastward. The bank continues to the south
and the mud narrows to form a trail to the north.

name: On the Boggy Trail
description:
Although muddy and waterlogged as it is, a trail is clearly visible
running through the middle of the muggy ground. Various reeds spring up
on either side as it leads to what appears to be a shallow pool in the
marsh. A high-pitched buzz fills the air, emanating from a thin cloud
of tiny insects making the experience that much more distracting. The
trail continues to both the north and the east.

name: On the Boggy Trail
description:
Although muddy and waterlogged as it is, a trail is clearly visible
running through the middle of the muggy ground. Various reeds spring up
on either side as it leads to what appears to be a shallow pool in the
marsh. A high-pitched buzz fills the air, emanating from a thin cloud
of tiny insects making the experience that much more distracting. The
trail continues to both the west and the east.

name: On the Boggy Trail
description:
The canopy of ferns and trees closes in above you, making the area feel
much smaller. Moss covered rocks lie sporadically in the mud, but they
seem few and far between. Reeds have sprung up on either side of a thin
and very wet trail that wanders off to the east while a smaller, darker
trail winds to the south. The overhanging plants widen a bit to the
north.

name: High in the Willow Tree
description:
>From here you can see above most of the marsh while for once the air
isn't thick with humidity and insects. A strong breeze blows and it is
good to feel that fresh air against your skin. It is almost impossible
to see back down into the marsh in any place, and in a few spots the
tops of the trees interlock so well as to form what appears to be the
ground itself. There are a few taller trees which extend above the
canopy, but you still remain at the highest point in the marsh. Odd-
looking stone structures rise up from the marsh in all directions. The
most unique being a pair of matching towers to the south. Some words
are etched into one of the branches.

name: On a Damp Path
description:
Small insects buzz obnoxiously about your face and body while the trees
continue to loom above you creating a nice canopy for shade. You hear
the occasional bird chirp as well as odd, seemingly amphibian noise.
Rows of cypress trees and ferns line the sides of a muddy path which
leads off into the marsh to the  east. A very large tree can be seen to
the north.

name: An Overgrown Shrine
description:
The local flora sweeps around the area from the northern entrance
forming a large circle of plants. The branches of the trees extend
towards the middle of the circle almost unnaturally, making sure that
little light enters this ground. Rising up in the center is a
rectangular stone monument covered in moss and vines. The ground is no
longer the damp mud, but an ancient stone walkway coated in various
fungi and mosses. It leads up two wide steps to what looks like an
altar of sorts. The only way out is back to the north.

name: On a Damp Path
description:
Small insects buzz obnoxiously about your face and body while the trees
continue to loom above you creating a nice canopy for shade. You hear
the occasional bird chirp as well as odd, seemingly amphibian noise.
Long vines hang from the trees and mosses and lichen grow an just about
anything. The path winds to the north and to the east, weaving amidst
the slime and muck.

name: On a Damp Path
description:
Small insects buzz obnoxiously about your face and body while the trees
continue to loom above you creating a nice canopy for shade. You hear
the occasional bird chirp as well as odd, seemingly amphibian noise.
Long vines hang from the trees and mosses and lichen grow an just about
anything. The path winds to the west and south, weaving amidst the
slime and muck. A wall of pillars blocks the way to the east.

name: A Turn in the Line of Pillars
description:
You stand in the corner of what appears less like a marsh and more like
a bird sanctuary. A solid wall of pillars stands to north and to the
west. Small trees grow here, some blooming with fruit and flowers to
serve as food for the many exotic birds that now make this place their
home. A constant chirping and singing of the birds seems to emanate
mainly from the southeast. A small path leads through the trees and
lush animal paradise to the east and to the south.

name: The Northern Wall
description:
You stand in the corner of what appears less like a marsh and more like
a bird sanctuary. A solid wall of pillars stands to north. Small trees
grow here, some blooming with fruit and flowers to serve as food for
the many exotic birds that now make this place their home. A constant
 chirping and singing of the birds seems to emanate mainly from the
south. A small path leads through the trees and lush animal paradise to
the south, east and west.

description:

surface. To the west the pool continues, but the vines and trees are
too dense to travel through. A small creek pours into the pool from the
south.

patch of reeds and ferns lay eastward. The bank continues to the north

trail continues to both the south and the east.

description:

continue to loom above you creating a nice canopy for shade. You hear

description:
Small insects buzz obnoxiously about your face and body while the trees
continue to loom above you creating a nice canopy for shade. You hear
the occasional bird chirp as well as odd, seemingly amphibian noise.
Long vines hang from the trees and mosses and lichen grow an just about
anything. The path winds to the west, weaving amidst the slime and
muck. To the east it leads underneath an old stone archway.

name: An Ancient Entryway
description:
Two pillars on either side of you arch up to form an elegant archway
above your head. The pillars themselves are somewhat smooth due to
their lengthy stay in the marsh, but some of their carvings are still
visible along their sides and tops. Once through the entryway you enter
into a lush bird and animal paradise. Every fern and blade of grass
seems a bit more tropical than the flora in the rest of the swamp. A
constant chirping and singing emanates mainly from the east and a path
through the sanctuary leads to the north, south and east.

name: A Decrepit Stone Fountain
description:
The paths throughout this sanctuary come together here to an old stone
fountain now serving its purpose as a birdbath. The fountain is maybe
fifteen feet in diameter and in its center is a small statue of a nymph
frolicking. Exotic birds of all sorts don't even seem to notice you as
they splash around the garden, singing to their heart's content. A few
flowering plants grow around the fountain so the birds do not have to
travel too far from their apparent happiness. A small plaque is here to
commemorate the fountain.

name: The Eastern Wall
description:
You stand in the corner of what appears less like a marsh and more like
a bird sanctuary. A solid wall of pillars stands to east. Small trees
grow here, some blooming with fruit and flowers to serve as food for
the many exotic birds that now make this place their home. A constant
chirping and singing of the birds seems to emanate mainly from the
west. A small path leads through the trees and lush animal paradise to
the north, south and west.

name: On the Boggy Trail
description:
Although muddy and waterlogged as it is, a trail is clearly visible
running through the middle of the muggy ground. Various reeds spring up
on either side as it leads to what appears to be a shallow pool in the
marsh. A high-pitched buzz fills the air, emanating from a thin cloud
of tiny insects making the experience that much more distracting. The
trail continues to the north, but widens into a large clearing to the
east. The was south is blocked by a gigantic fallen tree.

name: A Large Clearing in the Marsh
description:
Only a few trees grow here, and what ones that do seem a bit shorter
than the average tree in the marsh. the ground is covered with some
light grasses and ferns, much more like a field than a swamp. It still
retains, however, a very damp and muddy composition. The sky is visible
above gaping holes in the otherwise thick tree line and it is a
refreshing sight in this dismal place. The clearing stretches on to the
south and east, while a small trail goes back into the thickened marsh
to the west.

description:

description:

name: Deep Inside a Hollow Log
description:
The inner workings of this log consist of various types of fungi and
mosses, relying on the deep saturation of the wood for their existence.
The wall of the trunk seems scratched and almost dug out, perhaps by
some animal in search for shelter. It all seems so fragile, though,
being rotten and waterlogged as it is. Moss that grows outside of the
hollow log creeps inside creating a nice carpeting for whatever animal
does abide here. They only way out is back to the east.

description:
