Long vines hang from the trees and mosses and lichen grow an just about
anything. The path winds to the north, weaving amidst the slime and
muck. To the west the path opens up into a large clearing.

name: An Old Stone Path
description:
A straight line of stones cuts the way north and south of here lined on
both sides by short overhanging trees. The path is about ten feet
across and the stones themselves are cracked and weathered allowing
grasses and weeds to creep through to the surface of the walkway. To
the south is a small rusted gate leading into a garden of some sort. To
the north the path opens into a large clearing.

name: An Overgrown and Decayed Garden
description:
A path of light colored grasses leads the way through this old garden.
Odd-looking, dead plants and flowers lay covered in weeds and ferns.
Instead of being an elegant natural treasure, all neat and orderly,
this garden has transformed into a mass of rotten flowers and plants
still in their rows, but spilling into the path in some places. The
path through the garden leads to the east and to the south. An old
rusted fence surrounds the garden to the north and to the west.

name: An Overgrown and Decayed Garden
description:
A path of light colored grasses leads the way into this old garden.
Odd-looking, dead plants and flowers lay covered in weeds and ferns.
Instead of being an elegant natural treasure, all neat and orderly,
this garden has transformed into a mass of rotten flowers and plants
still in their rows, but spilling into the path in some places. The
path through the garden leads to the south, east and west. An old
rusted gate is to the north, leading onto a stone path.

path through the garden leads to the west and to the south. An old

name: The Center of the Garden
description:
A path of light colored grasses circles around the center of this
ancient garden. Dead plants and flowers fall off the edges of a small
stone platform. In the very enter of it all is a large statue of woman
that has seen better times. Instead of being an elegant natural
treasure, all neat and orderly, this garden has transformed into a mass
of rotten flowers and plants still in their rows, but spilling into the
path in some places. The path through garden continues in most
directions.

name: An Overgrown and Decayed Garden
description:
A path of light colored grasses leads the way through this old garden.
Odd-looking, dead plants and flowers lay covered in weeds and ferns.
Instead of being an elegant natural treasure, all neat and orderly,
this garden has transformed into a mass of rotten flowers and plants
still in their rows, but spilling into the path in some places. The
path through the garden leads to the north, west and south. An old
rusted fence surrounds the garden to the east.

name: On the Muddy Creek
description:
A small stream of water cuts through the area. It is only a few feet
across and not that deep, but the wide muddy banks running on either
side of it suggest that the creek is not nearly as large as it used to
be. A thick wall of ferns and trees line either side of the muddy
banks, but they do not branch across and over the stream to form the
natural canopy they do in other places in the marsh. The creek widens
and flows into a small pool to the north and a small trail is cut
through the trees to the south leading to a small clearing.

name: On the Muddy Creek
description:

across and not that deep, but the wide muddy banks running on either
side of it suggest that the creek is not nearly as large as it used to

banks, but they do not branch across and over the stream to form the
natural canopy they do in other places in the marsh. The creek heads
upstream to the east and flows to the west.

this garden has transformed into a mass of rotten flowers and plants
still in their rows, but spilling into the path in some places. The
path through the garden leads to the north, east and west. An old
rusted gate is to the south, leading onto a stone path.

name: An Overgrown and Decayed Garden
description:
A path of light colored grasses leads the way through this old garden.
Odd-looking, dead plants and flowers lay covered in weeds and ferns.
Instead of being an elegant natural treasure, all neat and orderly,
this garden has transformed into a mass of rotten flowers and plants
still in their rows, but spilling into the path in some places. The
path through the garden leads to the west and to the north. An old
rusted fence surrounds the garden to the south and to the east.

name: On the Muddy Creek
description:
A small stream of water cuts through the area. It is only a few feet
across and not that deep, but the wide muddy banks running on either
side of it suggest that the creek is not nearly as large as it used to
be. A thick wall of ferns and trees line either side of the muddy
banks, but they do not branch across and over the stream to form the
natural canopy they do in other places in the marsh. The creek heads
upstream to the south and flows to the west.

name: On the Muddy Creek
description:
A small stream of water cuts through the area. It is only a few feet
across and not that deep, but the wide muddy banks running on either
side of it suggest that the creek is not nearly as large as it used to
be. A thick wall of ferns and trees line either side of the muddy
banks, but they do not branch across and over the stream to form the
natural canopy they do in other places in the marsh. The creek heads
upstream to the south and flows to the north.

name: An Old Stone Path
description:
A straight line of stones cuts the way north and south of here lined on
both sides by short overhanging trees. The path is about ten feet
across and the stones themselves are cracked and weathered allowing
grasses and weeds to creep through to the surface of the walkway. To
the north is a small rusted gate leading into a garden of some sort. To
the south the path leads to a small bridge over the muddy creek.

name: On the Muddy Creek
description:
A small stream of water cuts through the area. It is only a few feet
across and not that deep, but the wide muddy banks running on either
side of it suggest that the creek is not nearly as large as it used to
be. A thick wall of ferns and trees line either side of the muddy
banks, but they do not branch across and over the stream to form the
natural canopy they do in other places in the marsh. The creek heads
upstream to the south and flows to the north.

name: A Small Clearing
description:
The trees here seem a bit sparse and this small open space is quite
different from the rest of the marsh. Light colored grasses grow upon
ground that is a bit more firm than the muddy and moss-infested paths
which weave throughout the swamp. A calm breeze circles around this
clearing and even a couple of wildflowers are blooming along the base
of one of the trees. A small path leads through some trees to the creek
south of here.

description:

across and not that deep, but the wide muddy banks running on either
side of it suggest that the creek is not nearly as large as it used to
be. A thick wall of ferns and trees line either side of the muddy
banks, but they do not branch across and over the stream to form the
natural canopy they do in other places in the marsh. The creek flows to
the west and heads upstream to the east, traveling underneath a small
bridge.

name: A Bridge over a Muddy Creek
description:
The stone walkway from the north comes to a brief halt to make way for
a small wooden bridge that crosses a creek running through the marsh.
The wood of the bridge itself seems to be made up of nothing more than
a few trunks of some fallen trees lashed together with some old vines.
It is sturdy enough though and it looks as if it has been in place for
many years. The stone path continues past the bridge to the south.

description:

across and not that deep, but the wide muddy banks running on either
side of it suggest that the creek is not nearly as large as it used to
be. A thick wall of ferns and trees line either side of the muddy
banks, but they do not branch across and over the stream to form the
natural canopy they do in other places in the marsh. The creek heads
upstream to the east and flows to the west, traveling underneath a
small bridge.

name: A Bend in the Muddy Creek
description:
A small stream of water cuts through the area. It is only a few feet
across and not that deep, but the wide muddy banks running on either
side of it suggest that the creek is not nearly as large as it used to
be. A thick wall of ferns and trees line either side of the muddy
banks, but they do not branch across and over the stream to form the
natural canopy they do in other places in the marsh. The creek itself
starts a slow bend here from the north, to the west and on.

name: A Bend in the Muddy Creek
description:
A small stream of water cuts through the area. It is only a few feet
across and not that deep, but the wide muddy banks running on either
side of it suggest that the creek is not nearly as large as it used to
be. A thick wall of ferns and trees line either side of the muddy
banks, but they do not branch across and over the stream to form the
natural canopy they do in other places in the marsh. The creek
continues its slow curve here from the east and back to the north.

name: A Magnificent Archway
description:
This is what must have once been the gate to the large stone castle to
the south. A line of pillars leads the way up to the walls of the
archway, some fallen and some still in a decent condition. The edges of
the wall are still somewhat smooth and intact. At its top the outline
arcs up and comes to a sharp point. The gate itself must be at least
thirty feet tall and half that size in width. Small hinges can be seen
on the bottom corners of the arch from what must have been a drawbridge
that fell over the creek to the north. Small weathered statues can be
seen on the tops of the pillars. The main entryway lies to the south
while a small bridge over an even smaller creek is to the north.

name: On the Muddy Creek
description:
A small stream of water cuts through the area. It is only a few feet
across and not that deep, but the wide muddy banks running on either
side of it suggest that the creek is not nearly as large as it used to
be. A thick wall of ferns and trees line either side of the muddy
banks, but they do not branch across and over the stream to form the
natural canopy they do in other places in the marsh. The start of the
stream is to the east while it flows onward to the north.

name: Start of the Muddy Creek
description:
Bubbling up from the ground, a small natural spring creates the creek
that flows through the marsh. Tall trees line the sides of this small
stream, but they do not branch out across to one another forming a
canopy like most places in the swamp. The creek itself is only a few
feet wide and not deep at all. The muddy banks running along the sides
of the water are much wider than the creek itself, suggesting that the
creek used to be much wider than it is now. A creeks flows to the west
and a small trail leads off through the trees to the north to a small
clearing.

name: A Toppling Entryway
description:
Tall stone walls rise up on either side of this small corridor leading
into the rest of the castle. At their top they come together in an
archway, which for the most part, is still intact. The purpose of this
space was as an extra defensive mechanism. Small windows are spaced up
high in the walls where archers would shoot invaders who made it into
the corridor. Since there is no gate to the north or to the south it is
unlikely to be able to serve that purpose now. The main gate, or what's
left of it, is to the north and a long east to west hallway is to the
south.

name: The Top of a Stone Tower
description:
>From the top of this tower you can overview the entirety of the marsh.
So odd that the remnants of the castle that you peer from are a mere
bit of what once must have been extreme grandeur. How this place simply
gave in to the will of nature and drown in this marsh is a perplexing
thought. You can see a large will tree off to the north and the twin
tower to the east. Back down is the only was off this unsteady tower of
stone.

name: The Base of a Crumbling Tower
description:
Some broken steps lie in a dusty heap beneath a stairway that seems
anything but sturdy. For how old this castle must be, it is surprising
to see that this tower has retained most of its circular shapes. The
stone floor is considerably cracked and small plants seep through them.
A long hallway extends back to east, while it is possible to make it up
the battered staircase.

name: Amidst the Castle Ruins
description:
The long hallway is cracked to almost no end. A wall that surely must
be toppling runs along the north of the hall, while the ceiling and
everything to the south is completely unrecognizable as it looks just
like a mass of fallen and broken rocks. this large pile of debris
stretches far to the south and it is impossible to cross through it.

name: Amidst the Castle Ruins
description:
The long hallway is cracked to almost no end. A wall that surely must
be toppling runs along the north of the hall, while the ceiling and
everything to the south is completely unrecognizable as it looks just
like a mass of fallen and broken rocks. this large pile of debris
stretches far to the south and it is impossible to cross through it.

name: Amidst the Castle Ruins
description:
You stand at the center of a long ruined hallway. The stones in the
floor are severely cracked in many places allowing grasses and mosses
to seep through. From the looks of it, the entryway to the north is
lucky to still be standing and nothing to the south of you is. It all
lies in a massive heap of rubble and stone. The tragedy that befell
here certainly intended not to take any prisoners. The hallway heads to
the east and west.

name: Amidst the Castle Ruins
description:
The long hallway is cracked to almost no end. A wall that surely must
be toppling runs along the north of the hall, while the ceiling and
everything to the south is completely unrecognizable as it looks just
like a mass of fallen and broken rocks. this large pile of debris
stretches far to the south and it is impossible to cross through it.

name: Under an Awning of Cypress Trees
description:
The trunks of trees, sporadically coated with moss, spring up around
you. Their massive branches reaching towards the sky much like the
outstretched arms of religions fanatics. Random insects buzz around you
and the occasional amphibian noise is heard from some rotted out
hollow. The ground below your feet is damp and murky and the air is
thick with humidity. The marsh continues to the east and south. To the
north is the edge of the swamp.

name: Under an Awning of Cypress Trees
description:

you. Their massive branches reaching towards the sky much like the

name: Forests lining the Old Southern Road
description:
Closest to the road are short trees and large shrubs stretching towards
the expanse of light that shines over the road. The canopy of the trees
have left the forest floor bare, covered only with fallen vegetation.
The trees are closely packed granting only enough space for a horse to
pass between the trunks, occasionally there is a great oak or pine that
has survived above all others.

name: Fields of the Old Southern Road
description:
Grasses cover the undulating ground of the fields to the side of the old
southern road. Sprouting up from the thick weave of grasses is the
occasional shrub and small bush. Large rocks can be seen raising their
head above the tips of the long grasses, lizards absorbing the heat lay
on the surface. The winds passing over the grasses flows like a river
weaving in and out through the rocks and bushes.

name: At a paved roads end
description:
The paved road is swallowed up buy the layers of dust then finally by the
grasses. Goat trails lead in all directions from here, as if the road had
never continued onwards. Cutting corners to another road or just leading
of into the forest, the trails snake widely. These trails are more worn
than that of the road indicating that their use is still regular enough
to keep the grasses at bay.

description:

the expanse of light that shines over the road. The canopy of the trees
have left the forest floor bare, covered only with fallen vegetation.

pass between the trunks, occasionally there is a great oak or pine that
has survived above all others.

on the surface. The winds passing over the grasses flows like a river
weaving in and out through the rocks and bushes.

name: Along the Old Southern Road
description:
Portions of the paved road have sunken into the wet ground making the
road uneven. Pave corners that are exposed are heavily worn and give the
road a worn riverbed look, ripples of living stone. Raised mounds of dirt
grow a short cropped layer of grass that is finger than the other wide
bladed grass that you have encountered.

description:
Curls of dust wisp over the paved road forming into dry puddles. Two deep
tracks run down each side of the road from the heavy carts that use it,
grass and weeds striving for a footing sprout out in all directions
indicating that the road has not seen regular use in some time. On the
edge of the road the grass thrives and grows to almost two feet, long
blades hang out over the road.

name: Forests lining the Old Southern Road
description:
Closest to the road are short trees and large shrubs stretching towards

name: Deep within the thick forest
description:
The moisture level within here is slightly higher than on the edge, the
smell of the forest floor floods your nose. Decaying vegitation and the
smell of pollen aren't a aweful smell, but it still blocks out all other
sense of smell. Light flickers through the canopy as the winds above
ripple their way across the tops of the taller trees. There is a weird
noise now and again that seems unlike a bird or a animal, but it doesn't
sound dangerous.

name: Deep within the thick forest
description:
The moisture level within here is slightly higher than on the edge, the
smell of the forest floor floods your nose. Decaying vegitation and the
smell of pollen aren't a aweful smell, but it still blocks out all other
sense of smell. Light flickers through the canopy as the winds above
ripple their way across the tops of the taller trees. There is a weird
noise now and again that seems unlike a bird or a animal, but it doesn't
sound dangerous.

name: A mountain trail
description:
The mountain terrain around you is mostly covered in rocks and dotted
randomly with trees and shrubs. The vegitation has found foot holds in
pockets of dirt that has gathered from the sedimentary weathering of the
rock surface. The winds here are alot stronger as there is little cover.
The trail leads up the mountain side and back towards the thick forest
below.

name: Fields of the Old Southern Road
description:
Grasses cover the undulating ground of the fields to the side of the old
southern road. Sprouting up from the thick weave of grasses is the
occasional shrub and small bush. Large rocks can be seen raising their
head above the tips of the long grasses, lizards absorbing the heat lay
on the surface. The winds passing over the grasses flows like a river
weaving in and out through the rocks and bushes.

name: Along the Old Southern Road
description:
Curls of dust wisp over the paved road forming into dry puddles. Two deep
tracks run down each side of the road from the heavy carts that use it,
grass and weeds striving for a footing sprout out in all directions
indicating that the road has not seen regular use in some time. On the
edge of the road the grass thrives and grows to almost two feet, long

name: Fields of the Old Southern Road
description:
Grasses cover the undulating ground of the fields to the side of the old
southern road. Sprouting up from the thick weave of grasses is the
occasional shrub and small bush. Large rocks can be seen raising their
head above the tips of the long grasses, lizards absorbing the heat lay
on the surface. The winds passing over the grasses flows like a river
weaving in and out through the rocks and bushes.

name: Along the Old Southern Road
description:
Portions of the paved road have sunken into the wet ground making the
road uneven. Pave corners that are exposed are heavily worn and give the
road a worn riverbed look, ripples of living stone. Raised mounds of dirt
grow a short cropped layer of grass that is finger than the other wide
bladed grass that you have encountered.

name: A steep mountain cut stairs
description:
Cut directly into the exposed stone is a very steep set fo stairs. A
small chain has been attached to the stone as a support line for those
who are climbing the stairs. These stairs would be next to impossible to
climb down. The stairs do not look like they have been used in a very
long time. Spiders have had time to spin their webs across the passage.

name: Forests lining the Old Southern Road
description:
Closest to the road are short trees and large shrubs stretching towards
the expanse of light that shines over the road. The canopy of the trees
have left the forest floor bare, covered only with fallen vegetation.
The trees are closely packed granting only enough space for a horse to
pass between the trunks, occasionally there is a great oak or pine that
has survived above all others.

name: Fields of the Old Southern Road
description:
Grasses cover the undulating ground of the fields to the side of the old
southern road. Sprouting up from the thick weave of grasses is the
occasional shrub and small bush. Large rocks can be seen raising their
head above the tips of the long grasses, lizards absorbing the heat lay
on the surface. The winds passing over the grasses flows like a river
weaving in and out through the rocks and bushes.

name: Deep within the thick forest
description:
The moisture level within here is slightly higher than on the edge, the
smell of the forest floor floods your nose. Decaying vegitation and the
smell of pollen aren't a aweful smell, but it still blocks out all other
sense of smell. Light flickers through the canopy as the winds above
ripple their way across the tops of the taller trees. There is a weird
noise now and again that seems unlike a bird or a animal, but it doesn't
sound dangerous.

name: Hidden trail
description:
This trail is very well hidden, the forrest has growen extremly dense and has
begun to weave it's web of vines and hanging shrubs. Cutting your way through
you can just tell where the trail has continued onward. You notice that there
are no longer any noises coming from the forest.

name: Hidden trail
description:
This trail is very well hidden, the forrest has growen extremly dense and has
begun to weave it's web of vines and hanging shrubs. Cutting your way through
you can just tell where the trail has continued onward. You notice that there
are no longer any noises coming from the forest.

name: Below a Forested Plateau
description:
You are only a few dozen feet below the forested plateau above you, but
there is a significantly less amount of wildlife and foliage than on the
plateau above you.  The wind whips down this incline, biting at your face as
you look about.  From here, you can head to the edge of the cliffs below, or
attempt to climb back to the plateau above you.

name: Below a Forested Plateau
description:
You are only a few dozen feet below the forested plateau above you, but
there is a significantly less amount of wildlife and foliage than on the
plateau above you.  The wind whips down this incline, biting at your face as
you look about.  From here, you can head to the edge of the cliffs below, or
attempt to climb back to the plateau above you.

name: At the Edge of a Cliff
description:
You stand at the edge of a cliff, the ground dropping off sharply here
into the valley below.  From here, you can see across the forest within the
valley, a small lake to the west by the mountains, and plains beyond the
eastern cliffs of the valley.  Winds blow swiftly across the terrain here,
making the edge of the cliffs dangerous, and the cliff-face itself is too
smooth and steep here to descend, even for the most adventerous.

name: Below a Forested Plateau
description:
You are only a few dozen feet below the forested plateau above you, but
there is a significantly less amount of wildlife and foliage than on the
plateau above you.  The wind whips down this incline, biting at your face as
you look about.  From here, you can head to the edge of the cliffs below, or
attempt to climb back to the plateau above you.

name: At the Edge of a Cliff
description:
You stand at the edge of a cliff, the ground dropping off sharply here
into the valley below.  From here, you can see across the forest within the
valley, a small lake to the west by the mountains, and plains beyond the
eastern cliffs of the valley.  Winds blow swiftly across the terrain here,
making the edge of the cliffs dangerous, but it does appear possible for the
adventerous to descend the cliff-face here.

name: In a Forested Valley
description:
You are in a broad valley to the east of the mountains.  What little
light that manages to reach this valley between the cliffs is further dimmed
by the thick canopy of trees above you, though the underbrush is small and
sparse.  A disturbing quiet hangs over the forest, making the absense of
wildlife even more noticable.

name: Beneath a Small Cliff
description:
You find yourself beneath a small cliff along the lower slopes of Mount
Cim, marking the border between valley and mountains.  Within the valley,
great trees grow out of the moist, black soil.  There are very few younger
plants though, oddly, and a disturbing quiet hangs over the forest.  The
cliffs here are too steep and smooth to climb, leaving your only option to
walk back into the valley.

name: At the Edge of a Cliff
description:
You stand at the edge of a cliff, the ground dropping off sharply here
into the valley below.  From here, you can see across the forest within the
valley, a small lake to the west by the mountains, and plains beyond the
eastern cliffs of the valley.  Winds blow swiftly across the terrain here,
making the edge of the cliffs dangerous, but it does appear possible for the
adventerous to descend the cliff-face here.

name: Beneath a Small Cliff
description:
You find yourself beneath a small cliff along the lower slopes of Mount
Cim, marking the border between valley and mountains.  Within the valley,
great trees grow out of the moist, black soil.  There are very few younger
plants though, oddly, and a disturbing quiet hangs over the forest.  It
appears possible to climb up the cliff here, or you can head further into
the valley.

name: Near an Ancient Tower
description:
You are in a broad valley to the east of the mountains.  What little
light that manages to reach this valley between the cliffs is further dimmed
by the thick canopy of trees above you, though the underbrush is small and
sparse.  A disturbing quiet hangs over the forest, and you notice a small
tower to the north, rising up among the forest.

name: Along the Southern Lakeshore
description:
You stand along the edge of a small lake, with trees and bushes thick
until merely a few feet away from the water's edge to your north, where the
soil becomes too damp and wet for such plants as the ground level drops
below the water.  In other directions, the forest spreads out among the
valley floor, becoming exceedingly dense to the west, blocking passage.

name: Along the Southeastern Lakeshore
description:
You stand along the edge of a small lake, with trees and bushes thick
until merely a few feet away from the water's edge to your northwest, where
the soil becomes too damp and wet for such plants as the ground level drops
below the water.  In other directions, the forest spreads out among the
valley floor.

name: Beneath a Small Cliff
description:
You find yourself beneath a small cliff along the lower slopes of Mount
Cim, marking the border between valley and mountains.  Within the valley,
great trees grow out of the moist, black soil.  There are very few younger
plants though, oddly, and a disturbing quiet hangs over the forest.  It
appears possible to climb up the cliff here, or you can head further into
the valley.

name: Near an Ancient Tower
description:
You are in a broad valley to the east of the mountains.  What little
light that manages to reach this valley between the cliffs is further dimmed
by the thick canopy of trees above you, though the underbrush is small and
sparse.  A disturbing quiet hangs over the forest, and you notice a small
tower to the east, rising up among the forest.

name: Among the Ruins of an Ancient Tower
description:
You stand among some ancient ruins, a small tower rising up from the
surrounding landscape.  The immediate area is covered with large stones,
many of which likely came from above you, where the tower still stands,
amazingly.  To your north and west, the ground descends into the forested
valley, while Mount Cim dominates your view to the south, and plains appear
to spread out to your northeast.

name: Near an Ancient Tower
description:
You are at the eastern edge of the valley, though the ground rises too
sharply to be able to exit the valley over the cliffs.  To your west, you
can see a small tower, as the forest thins slightly in that direction.

name: Along the Eastern Lakeshore
description:

name: On the Southern Riverbank
description:
The ground here drops off abruptly as you come to the southern bank of a
shallow river.  The trees and other plants in the area grow right up to the
edge of the river, making it almost unnoticable until you are nearly right
above it.

name: In a Forested Valley
description:
You are in a broad valley to the east of the mountains.  What little
light that manages to reach this valley between the cliffs is further dimmed
by the thick canopy of trees above you, though the underbrush is small and
sparse.  A disturbing quiet hangs over the forest, making the absense of
wildlife even more noticable.

name: In a Forested Valley
description:
You are in a broad valley to the east of the mountains.  What little
light that manages to reach this valley between the cliffs is further dimmed
by the thick canopy of trees above you, though the underbrush is small and
sparse.  A disturbing quiet hangs over the forest, making the absense of
wildlife even more noticable.

name: On the Southern Riverbank
description:
The ground here drops off abruptly as you come to the southern bank of a
shallow river.  The trees and other plants in the area grow right up to the
edge of the river, making it almost unnoticable until you are nearly right
above it.  To your east, the cliffs which line the eastern edge of the
valley are not so steep, possibly passable.

name: A Pass Between the Cliffs
description:
The ground here is steeply sloped, but not as sharp and dramatic a change
as the cliffs which border you to the north and south.  To the west, the
ground descends into heavily forested valley, while leading off into the
plains, to the east.

name: On the Southern Riverbank
description:
The ground here drops off abruptly as you come to the southeastern bank
of a shallow river.  The trees and other plants in the area grow right up to
the edge of the river, making it almost unnoticable until you are nearly
right above it.

name: On the Southern Riverbank
description:
The ground here drops off abruptly as you come to the southwestern bank
of a shallow river.  The trees and other plants in the area grow right up to
the edge of the river, making it almost unnoticable until you are nearly
right above it.

name: High within a Ruined Tower
description:
You are high within the remains of what appears to once have been a
watchtower of some sort.  From it's height, this tower must be centuries old
to have existed before this forest, at a time it could have served some
purpose.  Your explorations up to the top of this tower draw your
sensibilities into question, though, as most of the northwestern walls have
crumbled down, and the others stand in little better shape.

name: Beneath a Waterfall
description:
You are at the southwest corner of the lake, fed by a small waterfall as
a stream cascades down from the mountains near Mount Cim to the southeast,
curving around west of the valley, then heading north towards the horizon. 
The water is rather dark here, as the water stirs the soil, and the lake
spreads out to your north and east.

name: On the Southern Edge of a Lake
description:
You are on the southern edge of the lake, the water here still a little
rough and murky, but settling beneath you as it flows away from the
waterfall that can be heard to the west.  The lakeshore south of here is
forested, but the vegetation on that bank is much thicker than elsewhere in
the area, and appears difficult to pass.  You can see the waters of the lake
spreading out to the north, and forests to your east, beyond the edge of the
lake.

name: On the Southeastern Edge of a Lake
description:
You are on the southeastern edge of the lake, the water beneath you
sedate and clear.  To your south and east, forest dominates the valley,
while the waters of the lake spread out around you in other directions as
they flow slowly northward.

name: On the Western Edge of a Lake
description:
You are at the western edge of the lake, where the mountains block any
further travel in that direction.  The water beneath you is somewhat rough,
not quite settled smoothly after it's descent over the waterfall, and it is
still rather dark and murky.  The waters of the lake surround you in all
directions but west, and you can see the valley's forests beyond the eastern
lakeshore.

name: On the Waters of a Lake
description:
You are at the middle of the lake, the water beneath you calm and clear,
slowly flowing towards the northeast, until it turns into a river flowing
further into the valley.  The waters of the lake surround you in all
directions here.

name: On the Eastern Edge of a Lake
description:
You are on the eastern edge of the lake, the water beneath you sedate and
clear.  To your east, the forest dominates the valley, while the waters of
the lake spread out around you in other directions as they flow slowly
northward.

name: On the Western Edge of a Lake
description:
You are at the western edge of the lake, where the mountains block any
further travel in that direction.  The water beneath you here is relatively
sedate, slowly flowing towards the northeast, until it turns into a river,
flowing further into the valley.  The waters of the lake surround you in all
directions but west, and you can see the valley's forests beyond the eastern
lakeshore.

name: On the Waters of a Lake
description:
You are at the middle of the lake, the water beneath you calm and clear,
slowly flowing towards the northeast, until it turns into a river flowing
further into the valley.  The waters of the lake surround you in all
directions here.

name: On the Eastern Edge of a Lake
description:
You are on the eastern edge of the lake, the water beneath you sedate and
clear.  To your east, the forest dominates the valley, while the waters of
the lake spread out around you in other directions as they flow slowly
northward.

name: On the Northwestern Edge of a Lake
description:
The waters of the lake flow slowly eastward here, sedate and clear
beneath you.  To your north, what appear to be the ancient ruins of a great
castle still stand, though they are dwarfed by the immensity of the great
mountains which make up the western border of this valley.  To your east,
the valley leads north and south, with the lake draining into a river that
flows through the forest that covers the valley floor.  Around you, the lake
leads off towards the south.

name: On the Northern Edge of a Lake
description:
The waters of the lake flow slowly eastward here, sedate and clear
beneath you.  To your north, a great stone ruin rises up, blocking any
attempt at travel or even sight, in that direction.  To your east, the
valley leads north and south, with the lake draining into a river that flows
through the forest that covers the valley floor.  Around you, the lake leads
off towards the south.

name: On the Northeastern Edge of a Lake
description:
You are on the northeastern edge of the lake, the water beneath you
sedate and clear.  To your north, a great stone ruin rises up, blocking any
attempt at travel in that direction, while the waters of the lake flow past
you to the east, turning into a shallow river flowing across the valley.

name: On a Shallow River
description:
You are on the waters of a shallow river, about six feet deep here as it
flows out from the lake.  The water is clear near the surface, though
somewhat clouded near the floor where the same black soil that covers the
rest of the valley is stirred up by your passage.

name: On a Shallow River
description:
You are on the waters of a shallow river, hardly more than four feet at
most as it flows slowly along the valley floor.  The water is clear near the
surface, though somewhat clouded near the bottom as your passage kicks up
the black soil of the valley that lines the bottom of the river.

name: In a Flooded Area of the Ruins
description:
Water covers an expanse of the ruins here, centuries of decay having
defeated a section of the ancient walls.  In places, the water is still
shallow enough that some of the stones of the walls reach up above the
water's surface, vainly attempting to hold back the water that has slowly
begun to claim the castle grounds.

name: On a Shallow River
description:
You are on the waters of a shallow river, hardly more than four feet at
most as it flows slowly along the valley floor.  The water is clear near the
surface, though somewhat clouded near the bottom as your passage kicks up
the black soil of the valley that lines the bottom of the river.

name: On a Shallow River
description:
You are on the waters of a shallow river, hardly more than four feet at
most as it flows slowly along the valley floor.  The water is clear near the
surface, though somewhat clouded near the bottom as your passage kicks up
the black soil of the valley that lines the bottom of the river.

name: On a Shallow River
description:
You are on the waters of a shallow river, hardly more than four feet at
most as it flows slowly along the valley floor.  The water is clear near the
surface, though somewhat clouded near the bottom as your passage kicks up
the black soil of the valley that lines the bottom of the river.

name: On a Shallow River
description:
You are on the waters of a shallow river, hardly more than four feet at
most as it turns southward here, flowing past the cliffs to the east.  The
water is clear near the surface, though somewhat clouded near the bottom as
your passage kicks up the black soil of the valley that lines the bottom of
the river.

name: On a Shallow River
description:
You are on the waters of a shallow river, hardly more than four feet at
most as it turns eastward, flowing out of the valley here, where the river
has worn a path in the cliffs.  The water is clear near the surface, though
somewhat clouded near the bottom as your passage kicks up the black soil of
the valley that lines the bottom of the river.

name: A Path through the Plains
description:
You are in the middle of some open plains which stretch great distances
to the north and south between the mountains to the west, and the village of
Dagdan to the east.  Tall grasses grow around you, bending in the wind, and
every now and then, you can see the flash of movement, as some animal moves
across the plains.

name: At the Bottom of a Lake
description:
You are in the deepest portion of the lake, the water exceedingly dark
and murky, making it difficult to see beyond a few feet.  The lake floor
beneath your feet consists of heavy, black dirt, though there are a great
deal of small boulders, but no great expanses of stone that one might expect
to form the floor of a mountainous lake.

name: At the Bottom of a Lake
description:
The lake floor descends to your west, rising to the north and east, while
to your south, the ground rises sharply at the lake's edge, becoming too
shallow to stay underwater.  The water itself is rather murky, making it
difficult to see, though there is not much to see, beyond the large rocks
protruding from the black soil of the lake bed.

name: At the Bottom of a Lake
description:
The lake floor descends towards the west, rising to the south and east,
becoming too shallow to stay submerged beneath the surface.  A few aquatic
plants and fish can be seen, but for the most part the lake is rather empty,
with the black soil of the lake bed, and a large number of small boulders
dominating your view.

name: At the Bottom of a Lake
description:
The lake floor slowly descends from the northeast towards the south, with
the western edge of the lake being abruptly determined by the great mass of
stone rising up, forming the base of mountains to the west.  The water
itself is relatively clear, though your passage begins to stir up some of
the black soil, making it murky and difficult to see through.

name: At the Bottom of a Lake
description:
The lake floor continues to slope downwards from the northeast, towards
the southwest, the water becoming much darker, and murkier towards the
southwest.  Aside from the soil being stirred up among the water, there is
little else in the water.  Merely the great boulders that seem to be
everywhere among the valley, and the lake floor.

name: At the Bottom of a Lake
description:
The lake floor descends to the southwest, continuing to rise to the east,
becoming too shallow to stay submerged beneath the surface.  A few aquatic
plants and fish can be seen, but for the most part the lake is rather empty,
with the black soil of the lake bed, and a large number of small boulders
dominating your view.

name: At the Bottom of a Lake
description:
The lake floor slowly descends from the northeast towards the south, with
the western edge of the lake being abruptly determined by the great mass of
stone rising up, forming the base of mountains to the west.  The water
itself is relatively clear, though your passage begins to stir up some of
the black soil, making it murky and difficult to see through.

name: At the Bottom of a Lake
description:
The lake floor continues to slope downwards from the northeast, towards
the southwest, the water becoming much darker, and murkier towards the
southwest.  Aside from the soil being stirred up among the water, there is
little else in the water.  Merely the great boulders that seem to be
everywhere among the valley, and the lake floor.

name: At the Bottom of a Lake
description:
The lake floor continues to rise to the north and east, becoming too
shallow to stay submerged beneath the surface.  A few aquatic plants and
fish can be seen, but for the most part the lake is rather empty, with the
black soil of the lake bed, and a large number of small boulders dominating
your view.

name: At the Bottom of a Lake
description:
You find yourself at the northwest edge of the lake floor, great bulks of
stone sharply defining the lake's borders here, instead of the rising ground
which defines the other borders of the lake.  The lake floor itself is still
composed of the heavy black soil of the forest, though it is relatively
settled, and the water here much clearer.

name: At the Bottom of a Lake
description:
The lake floor ends abruptly to the north, blocked by a large mass of
stone, many of which look as though they had once been worked with tools. 
The lake bed rises to the east, becoming too shallow to keep beneath the
water's surface, while to the southwest, the lake continues to become
deeper.

name: Near an Ancient Castle
description:
Ancient stones cover much of the ground here, moss and small plants
claiming what is left as their own.  To your west, a great, ancient castle
rises up, looking down over the valley, while to your south, you can see a
shallow river flowing slowly past, and the forest which fills the valley.

name: On the Northern Riverbank
description:
The ground here drops off abruptly as you come to the northern bank of a
shallow river.  The trees and other plants in the area grow right up to the
edge of the river, making it almost unnoticable until you are nearly right
above it.  Aside from the river flowing past to your south, the forest is
the only other thing to be seen, spreading out in all directions.

name: On the Northern Riverbank
description:
The ground here drops off abruptly as you come to the northern bank of a
shallow river.  The trees and other plants in the area grow right up to the
edge of the river, making it almost unnoticable until you are nearly right
above it.  Aside from the river flowing past to your south, the forest is
the only other thing to be seen, spreading out in all directions.

name: On the Northern Riverbank
description:
The ground here drops off abruptly as you come to the northern bank of a
shallow river.  The trees and other plants in the area grow right up to the
edge of the river, making it almost unnoticable until you are nearly right
above it.  As the river flows past to the south of you, the forest spreads
out along the valley beyond it, and to your north and west, though stopping
abruptly as the ground rises sharply to the east, preventing travel.

name: Near an Ancient Castle
description:
Ancient stones cover much of the ground here, moss and small plants
claiming what is left as their own.  To your west, a great, ancient castle
rises up, looking down over the valley.  Neglect and decay have reclaimed
much of the castle, though most of the outer walls, and the great portcullis
still stand against the outside world.

name: In a Forested Valley
description:
You are in a broad valley to the east of the mountains.  What little
light that manages to reach this valley between the cliffs is further dimmed
by the thick canopy of trees above you, though the underbrush is small and
sparse.  A disturbing quiet hangs over the forest, making the absense of
wildlife even more noticable.

name: In a Forested Valley
description:
You are in a broad valley to the east of the mountains.  What little
light that manages to reach this valley between the cliffs is further dimmed
by the thick canopy of trees above you, though the underbrush is small and
sparse.  A disturbing quiet hangs over the forest, making the absense of
wildlife even more noticable.

name: Eastern Edge of the Valley
description:
You are at the eastern edge of the valley, though the ground rises too
sharply to be able to exit the valley over the cliffs.  Tall trees fill the
valley, right until the cliff edge, though you still see little else in the
way of underbrush or animals.

name: Near an Ancient Castle
description:
Ancient stones cover much of the ground here, moss and small plants
claiming what is left as their own.  To your west, a great, ancient castle
rises up, looking down over the valley.  Neglect and decay have reclaimed
much of the castle, though most of the outer walls still stand against the
outside world, and it remains an impressive sight.

name: In a Forested Valley
description:
You are in a broad valley to the east of the mountains.  What little
light that manages to reach this valley between the cliffs is further dimmed
by the thick canopy of trees above you, though the underbrush is small and
sparse.  A disturbing quiet hangs over the forest, making the absense of
wildlife even more noticable.

name: In a Forested Valley
description:
You are in a broad valley to the east of the mountains.  What little
light that manages to reach this valley between the cliffs is further dimmed
by the thick canopy of trees above you, though the underbrush is small and
sparse.  A disturbing quiet hangs over the forest, making the absense of
wildlife even more noticable.

name: Eastern Edge of the Valley
description:
You are at the eastern edge of the valley, though the ground rises too
sharply to be able to exit the valley over the cliffs.  Tall trees fill the
valley, right until the cliff edge, though you still see little else in the
way of underbrush or animals.

name: Near an Ancient Castle
description:
You find yourself in a small section of forest between the ancient castle
walls, and even older mountains to the north.  Large stones from the ruins,
and nearby mountains are scattered about, some massive boulders the size of
small titans.  This section of forest is relatively thick, however, and you
even see a few birds flying among the canopy.

name: Northern Border of the Forest
description:
The forest is somewhat sparser here, than the southern areas of the
valley, though the terrain begins to rise towards the mountains to the
north.  The forest continues to spread out in other directions, though you
notice an large mass of stone to your southwest, barely visible through the
trees.

name: Northern Border of the Forest
description:
The forest becomes noticably denser here, even moreso to the north, where
the foliage becomes a thick wall, making passage difficult.  In other
directions, the forest spreads out along the valley, though you notice
something out of place to the southwest.

name: Northern Border of the Forest
description:
The forest becomes noticably denser here, even moreso to the north, where
the foliage becomes a thick wall, making passage difficult.  In other
directions, the forest spreads out along the valley, though you notice
something out of place to the southwest.

name: Northern Border of the Forest
description:
The forest is noticibly denser here than to the south, though the forest
does begin to thin some as it nears the cliffs, which form the borders of
the valley.  The ground here is a much drier, brown soil, unlike the rest of
the forest, and lacks the sense of unease that pervades the rest of the
forest.

name: A Small Elven Camp
description:
You find yourself in a small, though relatively busy camp hidden behind
the thick amounts of brush and trees to the south.  Elves pass you often,
too occupied with their business to question your presence here.  The camp
is built in and among the surroundings, creating as little disruption to its
surroundings as possible.

name: A Small Elven Camp
description:
You find yourself in a small, though relatively busy camp hidden behind
the thick amounts of brush and trees to the south.  Elves pass you often,
too occupied with their business to question your presence here.  The camp
is built in and among the surroundings, creating as little disruption to its
surroundings as possible, though there is a small firepit here, apparently
used quite frequently.

name: A Small Elven Camp
description:
You find yourself in a small, though relatively busy camp hidden behind
the thick amounts of brush and trees to the south.  Elves pass you often,
too occupied with their business to question your presence here.  The camp
is built in and among the surroundings, creating as little disruption to its
surroundings as possible.

name: A Secluded Corner of the Elven Camp
description:
Sheltered slightly in a small cave near the rest of the camp, this is the
most peaceful and secluded portion of camp.  From the amount of papers and
other items around the area, it is apparent that this is where all the
activity of the elvish party here is planned and ordered.

name: A Small Elven Camp
description:
You find yourself in a small, though relatively busy camp hidden behind
the thick amounts of brush and trees to the south.  Elves pass you often,
too occupied with their business to question your presence here.  The camp
is built in and among the surroundings, creating as little disruption to its
surroundings as possible.

name: A Small Elven Camp
description:
You find yourself in a small, though relatively busy camp hidden behind
the thick amounts of brush and trees to the south.  Elves pass you often,
too occupied with their business to question your presence here.  The camp
is built in and among the surroundings, creating as little disruption to its
surroundings as possible.

name: A Small Elven Camp
description:
You find yourself in a small, though relatively busy camp hidden behind
the thick amounts of brush and trees to the south.  Elves pass you often,
too occupied with their business to question your presence here.  The camp
is built in and among the surroundings, creating as little disruption to its
surroundings as possible.

name: Among the Eaves of the Forest
description:
You manage to find a somewhat secure perch here among the eaves of the
forest, concealed from sight by those below you by the lower branches of the
trees.  From here you can see out above the rest of the treetops, offering a
view of the plains east of the valley, the mountain ranges bordering the
other sides of the valley, and what appears to be a small tower to your
southeast.

name: Among the Eaves of the Forest
description:
You manage to find a somewhat secure perch here among the eaves of the
forest, concealed from sight by those below you by the lower branches of the
trees.  From here you can see out above the rest of the treetops, offering a
view of the plains east of the valley, the mountain ranges bordering the
other sides of the valley, and the small lake to your west.

name: Among the Eaves of the Forest
description:
You manage to find a somewhat secure perch here among the eaves of the
forest, concealed from sight by those below you by the lower branches of the
trees.  From here you can see out above the rest of the treetops, offering a
view of the plains east of the valley, the mountain ranges bordering the
other sides of the valley, and huge ruins to your west.

name: A Hidden Campsite
description:
You have managed to stumble onto an exceedingly well hidden campsite. 
Sheltered cleverly against the cliffs to the southwest, with the foliage in
the area carefully arranged to further conceal this area, the campsite is
practically invisible from the outside.  By the layout of the site, it
appears to be often used by someone, with things laid out in sensible,
well-placed patterns.

name: Ath'ashe Road
description:
The people meandering down the road are a mixed lot of people.  Tourists make
up the majority of those walking toward the Glass Tower, while messengers and
members of assorted guilds move in both directions.  The tower itself casts
long shadows across parts of the street, its presence dominating the entire
city of Melcene.  Few citizens roam along this portion of the city, as little
brings them out from their own cozy district.

name: A Practice Chamber
description:
This room is surprisingly large, compared to the size of this tower as a
whole.  No decorations line the rough stone walls, and the staircase that
leads back down into the main area of the tower is tucked away in the
corner, as to not distract those who wish to study in this chamber.

name: Approaching a Great Tower
description:
Large groups of tourists stand in awe at the large structure that towers over
them.  A magical aura pulses from its very presence, making some of the
resident mages even stop and stare with wonder.  The air is heavy with silence,
those who are visitors and those who are citizens well aware of how important
the studies inside the tower truly are.

name: Diraclya Road
description:
The people meandering down the road are a mixed lot of people.  Tourists make
up the majority of those walking toward the Glass Tower, while messengers and
members of assorted guilds move in both directions.  The tower itself casts
long shadows across parts of the street, its presence dominating the entire
city of Melcene.  Few citizens roam along this portion of the city, as little
brings them out from their own cozy district.

up the majority of those walking toward the Glass Tower, while messengers and
members of assorted guilds move in both directions.  The tower itself casts
long shadows across parts of the street, its presence dominating the entire
city of Melcene.  Few citizens roam along this portion of the city, as little
brings them out from their own cozy district.

The people meandering down the road are a mixed lot of people.  Tourists make
up the majority of those walking toward the Glass Tower, while messengers and
members of assorted guilds move in both directions.  The tower itself casts
long shadows across parts of the street, its presence dominating the entire
city of Melcene.  Few citizens roam along this portion of the city, as little

description:
The people meandering down the road are a mixed lot of people.  Tourists make
up the majority of those walking toward the Glass Tower, while messengers and
members of assorted guilds move in both directions.  The tower itself casts
long shadows across parts of the street, its presence dominating the entire
city of Melcene.  Few citizens roam along this portion of the city, as little
