smooth to the touch, made of fine white marble. Warmth seems to emit from the
very walls in invisible waves, wrapping around you, rendering you silent.  A
throb of energy fills the room, making the walls look alive.  The noise grows
louder and louder, echoing into your sensitized ears.  The throbbing suddenly
lessens in intensity, leaving you with a sense of awe.  You think you see a
tiny spiralling stairway tucked away to one side.

name: A short hallway
description:
The hallway looks similar to that of the downstairs halls, walls fuzzily waver
between solidity and a cotton texture.  The decor of this portion of the exotic
mansion is drab, nothing more than necessary, as it is mainly for the use of
students and other regular visitors.  A few modest paintings make the walls seem
a little less bare, and a rough and practical rug runs down the middle of the
floor.  Doors can be seen set in both the north and south ends of the hallway.

name: A large bedroom
description:
Brightly colored rugs made of woven canvas and cloth lay scattered upon the
sturdy looking floor of the large sleeping quarters.  Magical lights send some
colorful patterns against the relatively plain cloudy walls.  Numerous beds
line the walls, covered in soft blankets filled with down, and fluffy pillows.
Stacks of thickly bound books are piled near just about every bed, and a few
are lined upon the sparse bookshelves along one wall.  Three or four desks have
made their home in this room as well, beckoning you to sit down and study the
art that is Magic.  The bedroom sprawls out to the east and south, and a small
door is set in the northern wall.

name: A storage closet
description:
A small closet filled with various cleaning agents and accessories occupies
this space, tucked away between the two bedrooms.  The wooden door appears to
be made of pine, and in taking a deep breathe you can still smell the sticky
sap that made it's home there.  Brooms, soap, scrubbing brushes are all set
neatly onto their shelves and stands.  There doesn't seem to be any apparent
dust on any of the objects within, giving you the impression that the mages
who live here keep their quarters tidy.

description:

name: A crystalline tower
description:
The ground beneath your feet and the structure of the entire tower, looks to
be made from solid ice.  The walls look to be made from blocks of the frosty
stuff, yet they show no signs of melting despite the relative warmth of the
air in here.  As you walk through the tower, you notice that the floor is not
slippery as one might expect, but you are able to keep your steps firmly on
the ground without a problem.  A few windows look out upon the surrounding sky
and clouds, reminding you just how far up you really are.  You see more of the
tower to the south and east.

name: A crystalline tower
description:
The ground beneath your feet and the structure of the entire tower, looks to
be made from solid ice.  The walls look to be made from blocks of the frosty
stuff, yet they show no signs of melting despite the relative warmth of the
air in here.  As you walk through the tower, you notice that the floor is not
slippery as one might expect, but you are able to keep your steps firmly on
the ground without a problem.  A few windows look out upon the surrounding sky
and clouds, reminding you just how far up you really are.  You see more of the
tower to the south and west, and to the east, a spiral stairway.

name: A spiraling stairway of clouds
description:
The stairs here are once again made of the cloudlike substance that you found
beneath your feet earlier.  In a manner that makes you uneasy, it seems to only
solidify with every step you make upon this stairway.  The stairs themselves
are rather narrow, as if made for those with much smaller feet than the average
human.  Looking further up, you can see that the stairway itself is tight, not
allowing for much movement other than following the stairs up.  You see the rest
of the tower to the south and west, and the insubstantial stairway leads up and
down.

and clouds, reminding you just how far up you really are.  You see more of the
tower to the north, east and west, and to the south you see the entrance to a
grand library.

description:
The ground beneath your feet and the structure of the entire tower, looks to
be made from solid ice.  The walls look to be made from blocks of the frosty
stuff, yet they show no signs of melting despite the relative warmth of the
air in here.  As you walk through the tower, you notice that the floor is not
slippery as one might expect, but you are able to keep your steps firmly on

tower to the west, and a set of stairs to the north.

name: The library
description:
Glowing spheres of multicolored light dance high within the towering painted
ceilings of this vast library.  Books cover the walls from floor to ceiling,
some newly printed out, some fragile and tattered.  Rugs lie scattered about
the library, worn and threadbare from the constant patter of feet.  Tables,
desks and chairs are positioned about the room, covered in scrolls, pens and
other writing tools.  It would seem that this place is not only for research,
but for restoration as well, as you see copied sheets of paper lying next to
many of the older books on the tables.  The giant pillar stands quiet and
looming in the center of the library.  You see the massive library to the east
and west.

name: Entrance to a grand library
description:
A large archway made of marble leads into an expansive library.  Large oaken
doors are swung inward, their surface smooth with the exception of the vast
decorative carvings made into them.  Books fill your vision from as far as you
can see, and air smelling strongly of old papers and book bindings fills your
nostrils.  A strong urge to grab a book and consume as much knowledge as you
can overwhelms you, and it takes a moment to bring yourself back to reality.
A fine, plush rug lays before the door, soothing the soles of your feet. You
see the library branch off to the east and west, and a tower to the north.

name: A small workroom
description:
The walls of this room seem to be made of some stony looking material, gray
and brown in color.  The texture of these stones are smooth in some places,
yet rigid in others, and bringing your hand closer, you can feel the heat
emitting off of them, and bouncing around the room.  As like all the other
parts of the strange building, the room is lit with a multitude of glowing
spheres of light, varying in color.  The door leading back to the library is
set in the western wall.

name: A spiraling stairway of clouds
description:
The cloudlike substance beneath your feet seems to solidify with every step
you make upon this stairway.  The stairs themselves are rather narrow, as if
made for those with much smaller feet than the average human.  The stairway
itself is tight wound, not allowing for much movement other than following
the stairs up or down.

name: The ivory tower observatory
description:
The top of this spired tower gives a splendid view over all of Shalar.  Clouds
move slowly through the sky, and on a given night, the stars shine with clarity
and brilliance.  A small desk used for note taking is here, as well as a cot.
A few smaller spheres glow dimly near some torn papers tacked to the wall.

name: An old dirt track
description:
Scuttling beetles and sprigs of grass look to be the only creatures that
actively use the dusty old track beneath your feet.  Shadows play across
the ground thanks to the gentle breeze that tugs at your clothing.  You
notice several ruts in the dirt, likely from the traffic of wagons that
may have once passed through here.  Pines, spruce and oak trees speckle
the landscape all around you, branches swaying under an unseen force.
The track meanders north and south, where the trees begin to grow more
thickly together.  Before you make your decision, you spot an old and
rotted post pounded into the ground, bearing a small wooden sign.

name: An old dirt track
description:
Scuttling beetles and sprigs of grass look to be the only creatures that
actively use the dusty old track beneath your feet.  Shadows play across
the ground thanks to the gentle breeze that tugs at your clothing.  You
notice several ruts in the dirt, likely from the traffic of wagons that
may have once passed through here.  Pines, spruce and oak trees speckle
the landscape all around you, branches swaying under an unseen force.
The track meanders north and south, the trees beginning to grow more
thickly together.

name: An old dirt track
description:
Scuttling beetles and sprigs of grass look to be the only creatures that
actively use the dusty old track beneath your feet.  Shadows play across
the ground thanks to the gentle breeze that tugs at your clothing.  You
notice several ruts in the dirt, likely from the traffic of wagons that
may have once passed through here.  The trees that sprinkled your vision
from the north have grown closer together, hunched to the south like a
vulture over its scavenged meal.  The track continues its meandering to
the north and east.

name: An old dirt track
description:
The forest looms just south of where you stand, the dirt track leading
directly into the thick of it.  The busy beetles that scurried about
before have now taken shelter beneath the forest's hovering shadows.
The ruts in the track have completely disappeared now, and an array of
plants have sprung up from the swiftly disappearing trail.  A strange
silence weighs heavily at the entrance, trees knit closely together
like a warm woolen sweater.  The track meanders north and south, toward
the dead quiet of the forest.

name: Edge of a dark forest
description:
You find yourself standing at the edge of a thick, dark forest.  Any
light reaching down to the trail from the sky has been extinguished by
thickly leaved branches.  Oaks and pines reach sky high, creating treetop
homes and pathways of their own for the busy, scurrying life of the tiny
forest creatures.  The chirping of birds and chattering of creatures seems
muffled by the damp, heavy air beneath the canopy.  A variation of full,
leafy plants and flowers press close against the gigantic trunks of the
ancient trees.  A dirt track leads north away from the trees, and a small
trail passes through the foliage to the east, leading deeper into the woods.

name: A path through the forest
description:
Somehow you still manage to find a path through dense darkness of
the forest.  Oaks and pines reach sky high, creating treetop homes
and pathways of their own for the busy, scurrying life of the tiny
forest creatures.  Any light reaching down from the sky has been
extinguished by the thickly leaved branches.  The sounds of chirping
of birds and chattering of creatures has silenced, leaving you with
an eerie feeling.  A variation of full, leafy plants and flowers press
close against the gigantic trunks of the ancient trees.  Pine needles
snap beneath your feet, protesting as you continue through the woods.

name: A hidden path
description:
Through luck or fate, you stumble upon poorly hidden (but hidden none
the less) path in the heart of the forest.  Like the rest of the woods,
the sounds of every day life of squirrels and birds has hushed to dead
silence.  While picking your way through the tangled undergrowth, you
hear a rustle coming from within one of the nearby bushes.  Passing the
noise off as nothing more than movement of some nocturnal creatures, you
search along the ground on hands and knees, attempting to find where the
path leads.

description:
The crackle of dried pine needles confirms that you haven't traveled off
the course of the trail.  Like the rest of the woods, the sounds of every
day life of squirrels and birds has hushed to dead silence.  While picking

being watched.  The bubbling of a nearby stream plays softly to your ears,
filling the silence around you.  The air around you has brightened slightly,
allowing you to see the path more freely.

name: A hidden path
description:
The forest around you has brightened again, allowing you to see the path
more freely.  Like the rest of the woods, the sounds of every day life of
squirrels and birds has hushed to dead silence.  While picking your way
through the tangled undergrowth, you hear the sound of muffled voices
speaking an unfamiliar language.  As you press along the forest floor, your
noise hushes the whispers, and you get an intense feeling of being watched.
The bubbling of a nearby stream plays softly to your ears, filling the
silence around you.

name: A path through the forest
description:
Somehow you still manage to find a path through dense darkness of
the forest.  Oaks and pines reach sky high, creating treetop homes
and pathways of their own for the busy, scurrying life of the tiny
forest creatures.  Any light reaching down from the sky has been
extinguished by the thickly leaved branches.  The sounds of chirping
of birds and chattering of creatures has silenced, leaving you with
an eerie feeling.  A variation of full, leafy plants and flowers press
close against the gigantic trunks of the ancient trees.  Pine needles
snap beneath your feet, protesting as you continue through the woods.

name: A well hidden trail
description:
Somehow you have stumbled upon a trail placed with broken tree limbs
and loose foliage.  It's very likely that someone wanted this path kept
well hidden from passerbys, and now you have managed to unearth its only
visible entrance.  The trees surrounding the path seem to bend in your
way in a vain attempt to keep the remainder of the trail under guard.
Light reaches down between limbs and leaves, casting a few lonely shadows
across the mess before you.  The sounds of chirping of birds and chattering
of creatures has silenced, leaving you with an eerie feeling.  A variation
of full, leafy plants and flowers press close against the gigantic trunks
of the ancient trees.  The path might continue in some direction, but it's
going to take you some time to figure out which.

name: Edge of a dark forest
description:
You find yourself standing at the edge of a thick, dark forest.  Any
light reaching down to the trail from the sky has been extinguished by
thickly leaved branches.  Oaks and pines reach sky high, creating treetop
homes and pathways of their own for the busy, scurrying life of the tiny
forest creatures.  The chirping of birds and chattering of creatures seems
muffled by the damp, heavy air beneath the canopy.  A variation of full,
leafy plants and flowers press close against the gigantic trunks of the
ancient trees.  A dirt track leads south away from the trees, or you can
venture north into the darkness of the forest.

name: An old dirt track
description:
The forest looms just north of where you stand, the dirt track leading
directly into the thick of it.  The busy beetles that scurried about
before have now taken shelter beneath the forest's hovering shadows.
The ruts in the track have completely disappeared now, and an array of
plants have sprung up from the swiftly disappearing trail.  A strange
silence weighs heavily at the entrance, trees knit closely together like
a warm woolen sweater.  The track meanders south and north, toward the
dead quiet of the forest.

name: Beneath a large oak tree
description:
A gigantic tree stands proudly before you, branches and leaves shaking
as if it had a mind of its own.  The girth of the tree is outstanding,
likely taking ten or so of you with arms outstretched encircle it.  In
the highest reaches of the tree, rickety pathways and bridges run from
branch to swaying branch.  A ladder made from rope dangles down against
the bark, beckoning you for a climb.  The sounds of chirping of birds
and chattering of creatures carries on all around you, soothing any
fears you have of being lost in the woods.  A variation of full, leafy
plants and flowers press close against the gigantic trunks of the ancient
trees.

name: Beneath a large oak tree
description:

as if it had a mind of its own.  The girth of the tree is outstanding,
likely taking ten or so of you with arms outstretched encircle it.  In
the highest reaches of the tree, rickety pathways and bridges run from
branch to swaying branch.  A ladder made from rope dangles down against

and chattering of creatures carries on all around you, soothing any
fears you have of being lost in the woods.  A variation of full, leafy
plants and flowers press close against the gigantic trunks of the ancient
trees.

name: Within a light forest
description:
Light from the sky reaches through the tangled leaves and branches
above to shed thin rays upon the forest undergrowth.  The humming of
every day forest life blends into a soothing drone, not unlike the
gentle buzzing of honey bees.  A variation of full, leafy plants and
flowers press close against the gigantic trunks of the ancient trees.
The melodic chirping of songbirds stands out of the drone, confirming
the safety of the surrounding trees.  A particularly large tree stands
proudly to the west, otherwise the forest continues as far as you can
see.

name: A tiny treetop fort
description:
For all the bending and swaying of the oak tree's branches, this compact
yet useful hideout proves to be very sturdy.  A small wooden table has
been secured on the platform for general use.  A quiver full of arrows
leans peacefully against a tree branch, but peacefully for how long is
unknown.  You find it strange that the bandits who inhabit the area would
build a place like this until you see the breathtaking view to the north.
A clear shot of the track outside the forest can be seen from the cover
of the leaves, creating an excellent scouting advantage over any wouldbe
travelers.  A flimsy rope bridge connects to a tree directly east of you,
otherwise the ladder leading down to the forest floor remains.

name: Within a dark forest
description:
Huge trees huddle together in every direction.  Oaks and pines reach sky
high, creating treetop homes and pathways of their own for the busy,
scurrying life of the tiny forest creatures.  Any light reaching down from
the sky has been extinguished by the thickly leaved branches.  The sounds of
chirping of birds and chattering of creatures has silenced, leaving you with
an eerie feeling.  A variation of full, leafy plants and flowers press close
against the gigantic trunks of the ancient trees.  The darkness of the
forest prevents you from regaining your sense of direction.  A small trail
passes through the foliage to the west.

name: A dead end in a light forest
description:
Light from the sky reaches through the tangled leaves and branches above
to shed thin rays upon the forest undergrowth.  The humming of every day
forest life blends into a soothing drone, not unlike the gentle buzzing of
honey bees.  A variation of full, leafy plants and flowers press close
against the gigantic trunks of the ancient trees.  The melodic chirping of
songbirds stands out of the drone, confirming the safety of the surrounding
trees.  In all directions but east, the foliage grows too dense to travel.

name: At the edge of a small clearing
description:
Neatly trimmed undergrowth marks the edge of the small clearning that
you have stumbled upon.  The ground is well trodden here, packed dirt
blanketed thickly with pine needles.  Though a few tree limbs reach out
over the clearing, the sky beyond is easily visible, and allowing for
a greater light source.  In addition to the humming of forest life, the
sound of bandits hard at work with their chores blends in, just barely
distinguishable from the natural forest noise.  The melodic chirping of
songbirds stands out of the drone, carrying on despite the continual work
presence of the bandits.  Likely they have grown used to them.  You can
follow along the edge of the clearing to the south and east, while the
puzzling forest encroaches everywhere else.

name: Within a dark forest
description:
Huge trees huddle together in every direction.  Oaks and pines reach
sky high, creating treetop homes and pathways of their own for the busy,
scurrying life of the tiny forest creatures.  Any light reaching down
from the sky has been extinguished by the thickly leaved branches.  The
sounds of chirping of birds and chattering of creatures has silenced,
leaving you with an eerie feeling.  A variation of full, leafy plants
and flowers press close against the gigantic trunks of the ancient trees.
The darkness of the forest prevents you from regaining your sense of
direction.

name: A dead end within a dark forest
description:
Huge trees huddle together in every direction.  Oaks and pines reach sky
high, creating treetop homes and pathways of their own for the busy,
scurrying life of the tiny forest creatures.  Any light reaching down from
the sky has been extinguished by the thickly leaved branches.  The sounds of
chirping of birds and chattering of creatures has silenced, leaving you with
an eerie feeling.  A variation of full, leafy plants and flowers press close
against the gigantic trunks of the ancient trees.  The unnaturally dense
undergrowth halts any travel but east.

name: Within a dark forest
description:

your sense of direction.

name: Within a light forest
description:
Light from the sky reaches through the tangled leaves and branches
above to shed thin rays upon the forest undergrowth.  The humming of
every day forest life blends into a soothing drone, not unlike the
gentle buzzing of honey bees.  A variation of full, leafy plants and
flowers press close against the gigantic trunks of the ancient trees.
The melodic chirping of songbirds stands out of the drone, confirming
the safety of the surrounding trees.  In every direction you see the
living puzzle of the forest.

name: Within a light forest
description:

The melodic chirping of songbirds stands out of the drone, confirming

living puzzle of the forest.

name: At the edge of a small clearing
description:
Neatly trimmed undergrowth marks the edge of the small clearning that
you have stumbled upon.  The ground is well trodden here, packed dirt
blanketed thickly with pine needles.  Though a few tree limbs reach out
over the clearing, the sky beyond is easily visible, and allowing for
a greater light source.  In addition to the humming of forest life, the
sound of bandits hard at work with their chores blends in, just barely
distinguishable from the natural forest noise.  The melodic chirping of
songbirds stands out of the drone, carrying on despite the continual work
presence of the bandits.  Likely they have grown used to them.  You can
follow along the edge of the clearing to the south and north, while the
puzzling forest encroaches everywhere else.

name: The center of a bandit camp
description:
Seedlings and other undergrowth has been cleared away to make an inviting
area around the campfire.  A few tree logs rest sleepily in the wake of
the crackling flames, waiting for the bandits to rest wearily with them.
Stones guard the flames, keeping them contained from the easily excitable
pine needles and dried leaves of the past autumn.  An iron kettle nestles
within the outer coals of the fire, likely containing the next meal for the
bandits.  The noise of the camp itself is quite hushed in attempt to keep
their lair hidden from outsiders.  The camp spreads out around you, hidden
within the forests arms.

name: Beside a clear running stream
description:
You feel a cool, clear stream cross your path as you continue to wander
through the darkness of the forest.  The flow of the water feels like it
runs from northeast to southwest as it continues its travels through the
maze of undergrowth and tree trunks.  You can feel a few barren spots of
trodden dirt cling close to the water, impressed with the split hooved
tracks of deer.  The strange silence surrounds you still, only broken by
the soft gurgle of the stream.  The darkness of the forest prevents you
from regaining your sense of direction.

name: Within a dark forest

leaving you with the faint sound of running water.  A variation of full,

ancient trees.  The darkness of the forest prevents you from regaining
your sense of direction.

name: At the edge of a clearing
description:
The eerie silence that has continued on through this darker part of the
forest continues into the clearing sprawled before you.  The ground that
lies beneath your feet appears to be well trodden, impressions of bare
feet meshed together on the dirt.  Toward the center of the clearing you
can't miss the large altar carved of stone standing proudly.  The limbs
of the tress behind you hug the clearing tightly and you feel as though
they are trying to push you toward the altar.  You can either do as they
suggest, continue along the edge or return to the thick of the forest to
the north and west.

name: Before a stone altar
description:
Crafted completely from one piece of granite, the large altar stands
omniously in the center of the clearing.  Strange geometric shapes are
carved into the sides of the huge rock, and the top of the altar is so
smooth that you can see a vague reflection of yourself on it.  The whole
of the altar is immaculately clean, though wear from the weather and
from use is apparent.  Every form of life within the clearing has been
stilled, either out of respect for the monument or fear.  The clearing
leaves a wide berth in every direction from the altar.

scurrying life of the tiny forest creatures.  Any light reaching down
from the sky has been extinguished by the thickly leaved branches.  The
sounds of chirping of birds and chattering of creatures has silenced,
leaving you with an eerie feeling.  A variation of full, leafy plants
and flowers press close against the gigantic trunks of the ancient trees.
The darkness of the forest prevents you from regaining your sense of
direction.

description:

forest prevents you from regaining your sense of direction.  The tangled
underbrush prevents any further traveling.

name: At the edge of a clearing
description:
The eerie silence that has continued on through this darker part of the
forest continues into the clearing sprawled before you.  The ground that
lies beneath your feet appears to be well trodden, impressions of bare
feet meshed together on the dirt.  Toward the center of the clearing you
can't miss the large altar carved of stone standing proudly.  The limbs
of the tress behind you hug the clearing tightly and you feel as though
they are trying to push you toward the altar.  You can either do as they
suggest, continue along the edge or return to the thick of the forest to
the south and west.

name: A dead end within a dark forest
description:
Huge trees huddle together in every direction.  Oaks and pines reach sky
high, creating treetop homes and pathways of their own for the busy,
scurrying life of the tiny forest creatures.  Any light reaching down from
the sky has been extinguished by the thickly leaved branches.  The sounds of

an eerie feeling.  A variation of full, leafy plants and flowers press close
against the gigantic trunks of the ancient trees.  The unnaturally dense
undergrowth halts any travel but west.

name: Within a light forest
description:
Light from the sky reaches through the tangled leaves and branches
above to shed thin rays upon the forest undergrowth.  The humming of
every day forest life blends into a soothing drone, not unlike the
gentle buzzing of honey bees.  A variation of full, leafy plants and
flowers press close against the gigantic trunks of the ancient trees.
The melodic chirping of songbirds stands out of the drone, confirming
the safety of the surrounding trees.  In every direction you see the
living puzzle of the forest.

name: Within a light forest
description:

above to shed thin rays upon the forest undergrowth.  The humming of

running water somewhere within the mixture of the noises.  In every

name: Beside a clear running stream
description:
A cool, clear stream crosses your path as you continue to wander through
the forest.  The flow of the water runs from northeast to southwest as it
continues its travels through the maze of undergrowth and tree trunks.  A
few barren spots of trodden dirt cling close to the water, decorated with
the split hooved tracks of deer.  The humming of every day forest life
blends into a soothing drone, not unlike the gentle buzzing of honey bees.
A variation of full, leafy plants and flowers press close against the
gigantic trunks of the ancient trees.  The melodic chirping of songbirds
stands out of the drone, confirming the safety of the surrounding trees.
In every direction you see the living puzzle of the forest.

name: Beneath a large oak tree
description:
A gigantic tree stands proudly before you, branches and leaves shaking
as if it had a mind of its own.  The girth of the tree is outstanding,
likely taking ten or so of you with arms outstretched encircle it.  In
the highest reaches of the tree, rickety pathways and bridges run from
branch to swaying branch.  A ladder made from rope dangles down against
the bark, beckoning you for a climb.  The sounds of chirping of birds
and chattering of creatures carries on all around you, soothing any
fears you have of being lost in the woods.  A variation of full, leafy
plants and flowers press close against the gigantic trunks of the ancient
trees.

name: A tiny treetop fort
description:
For all the bending and swaying of the oak tree's branches, this compact
yet useful hideout proves to be very sturdy.  A small wooden table has
been secured on the platform for general use.  A quiver full of arrows
leans peacefully against a tree branch, but peacefully for how long is
unknown.  You find it strange that the bandits who inhabit the area would
build a place like this until you see the breathtaking view to the south.
A clear shot of the track outside the forest can be seen from the cover
of the leaves, creating an excellent scouting advantage over any wouldbe
travelers.  A flimsy rope bridge connects to a tree directly east of you,
otherwise the ladder leading down to the forest floor remains.

name: A tiny treetop fort
description:
For all the bending and swaying of the oak tree's branches, this compact
yet useful hideout proves to be very sturdy.  A small wooden table has
been secured on the platform for general use.  A quiver full of arrows

unknown.  You find it strange that the bandits who inhabit the area would
build a place like this until you see the breathtaking view to the south.
A clear shot of the track outside the forest can be seen from the cover
of the leaves, creating an excellent scouting advantage over any wouldbe
travelers.  A flimsy rope bridge connects to a tree directly west of you,
otherwise the ladder leading down to the forest floor remains.

name: An old dirt track
description:
Scuttling beetles and sprigs of grass look to be the only creatures that
actively use the dusty old track beneath your feet.  Shadows play across
the ground thanks to the gentle breeze that tugs at your clothing.  You
notice several ruts in the dirt, likely from the traffic of wagons that
may have once passed through here.  Pines, spruce and oak trees speckle
the landscape all around you, branches swaying under an unseen force.
The track meanders south and north, the trees beginning to grow more
thickly together.

name: An old dirt track
description:
Scuttling beetles and sprigs of grass look to be the only creatures that
actively use the dusty old track beneath your feet.  Shadows play across
the ground thanks to the gentle breeze that tugs at your clothing.  You
notice several ruts in the dirt, likely from the traffic of wagons that
may have once passed through here.  Pines, spruce and oak trees speckle
the landscape all around you, branches swaying under an unseen force.
The track meanders south and north, the trees beginning to grow more
thickly together.

name: Twisty cavern
description:
The way twist this way and that and its all you can do to keep your head
from spinning.  The air is very cold here and layers of ice on the wall.
The sounds of metal on ice echo through the cavern. A side passage leads
east and the main passage goes north and south.

name: Striped tunnel
description:
The walls of the tunnels have many brilliant colors in them from the
various veins of crystals running in them.  An odd twinkling comes from
the east.

name: Prism cave
description:
The roof of this cave peaks over a hundred feet high making it one of
the biggest in the catacombs.  Crystals of every color cast prismatic
sprays of light everywhere.  The light from your lamp causes almost a
blinding flare of brilliance as more light is added to the multi-colored
twinkling phenomenon that exists here.  This is also the lair of the
fabled and feared Prism Dragon.

name: Ruined monument
description:
A monument to a famous king once stood here. Not much is left to even
signify that is was here at all.  A building of some sort can be entered
through a basement to the east.  The southern gate of the grounds is to
the south.

name: Basement
description:
Its dark and it smells like. ...BATS down here!  All you see is a swirl
of the darkness and lots of scratching bats madly flailing around. A set
of stairs go up into the building and a broken window leads west.

name: Fresh graves
description:
The graves here seem very recent.  You notice many signs of digging and
defilement.  There are piles of fresh bodies here awaiting burial.  A
strange sense of evil magic from the south makes the hairs on the back
of your neck to stand on end!

name: Southern gate
description:
A rusty gate here no longer keeps anyone out or in.  You see a lonely
E/W passage to the south.  A little used trail winds east through a
crack in the wall.

name: Scene of ghastly horror
description:
An army of undead creatures of all types are lined up patiently. Their
leader is an evil demonoid necromancer.  His plans to use his army of
undead to take over the world seem about ready to get underway.

name: Twisty passage
description:
The passage bends north and east here.  To the east your not certain
what lies ahead due to all the twists and turns you've made.  To the
north is seems cold.

name: Cross of caverns
description:
A little-used cavern enters from the south. A passage twists away to
the west.  An odd twinkling comes from the cave to the north.

name: Lonely tunnel
description:
Something indescribable makes you feel lonesome and sad here. Its just
a feeling you get from this tunnel.  The tunnel east and west.

name: Lonely tunnel
description:
Something indescribable makes you feel lonesome and sad here. You see a
gate to a burial ground to the north.  This lonesome tunnel sighs along
west and east.

name: Bend in the lonely tunnel
description:
Something indescribable makes you feel lonesome and sad here. The
tunnel bends west and south.

name: Lonely tunnel
description:
Something indescribable makes you feel lonesome and sad here. The very
walls of the tunnel seems to groan.  to the north the tunnel bends and
east is an intersection.

name: Intersection
description:
To the north you enter the burial grounds.  a trail of blood leads that
direction.  Also you feel an ominous sense of evil magic from there.
The tunnel to the west creaks and sighs as if alive.  To the south you
smell a hint of fresh air.

name: Tunnel
description:
The tunnel heads north and south.  North you see an intersection and
far to the south you sense light and smell a fresh breeze.

name: Tunnel
description:
The tunnel slopes noticeably down to the north and you sense the surface
could be reached to the south.

name: Southern entrance to the catacombs
description:
Through a trapdoor above you streams light.  Through a doorway to
the south streams darkness.  A message has been scrawled upon the wall
here.  The message reads:
     Adventure for the strong yet calculating
     Death for the weak and shallow
     Treasure for the smart and lucky
     Death for the stupid and accursed
An ancient Glyph above the entrance keeps monsters from wandering up
from the catacombs.

name: Unknown passage
description:
Oh dear you seem to have lost your way.  You look back from whence you
came but there's no exit there anymore.  There are exits in other
directions but you have a feeling that you are hopelessly lost.

name: Unknown passage
description:
Oh dear you seem to have lost your way.  You look back from whence you
came but there's no exit there anymore.  There are exits in other
directions but you have a feeling that you are hopelessly lost.

name: Unknown passage
description:
Oh dear you seem to have lost your way.  You look back from whence you
came but there's no exit there anymore.  There are exits in other
directions but you have a feeling that you are hopelessly lost.

name: Unknown passage
description:
Oh dear you seem to have lost your way.  You look back from whence you
came but there's no exit there anymore.  There are exits in other
directions but you have a feeling that you are hopelessly lost.

name: North entrance to the catacombs
description:
You are almost surprised to see a tunnel leading off to the south
into utter darkness.  The floorboards above you haven't been moved
in a long time, yet there is life down here.  A beam of light from
the opening above you falls upon a message scrawled on the wall here.

The message reads:
     Adventure for the strong yet calculating
     Death for the weak and shallow
     Treasure for the smart and lucky
     Death for the stupid and accursed

An ancient Glyph above the entrance keeps monsters from wandering up
from the catacombs.

name: North/south tunnel
description:
This part of the catacombs looked roughly hewn and man-made. There is
a large cross painted on the floor of the tunnel.To the south it seems
maybe a bit lighter for some odd reason.  To the north a ray of light
comes in from a hole in the ceiling.

name: Weapon training area
description:
This is a place to keep up on there weapon skills.  Much of the
equipment looks old and worn but upon further inspection seems quite
sturdy in fact.

name: Prayer training area
description:
The templar's curious mix of religion and fighting is evident here.
A central painting depicts a cross composed of swords.  The elders
teach the ancient art of prayer to the young pages.

name: Junction of hallways
description:
Training facilities are evident to the west. To the south lies a hallway
which has doors every couple of feet, looks like living quarters of some
sort.  To the east the tunnel leads back into the natural catacombs.

name: Hallway
description:
The hallway takes on a more indoor look to the west.  To the east it
looks awfully dark.

name: Intersection
description:
The tunnel continues to the north and the south, becoming less hewn and
more natural to the south.  A passageway lined with paneling leads west.

name: Pages' sleeping quarters
description:
Several bunk beds are lined up across the room.  It looks rather spartan
and there is little evidence of toys or games.  Most of the desks are
filled with books and papers of little interest.

name: Templar Knights sleeping quarters
description:
This is a huge room which is filled wall to wall with beds. Apparently
all the low level knights all sleep in this one room.  A door on the
south wall is labelled \Elders only!\".

name: N/S hallway
description:
The hallway leads north an south.  A door leads to a templar's room to
the east.  The decoration looks rather sparse here.

name: A Middle-aged templar's room
description:
This is a room furnished in a room becoming a low level templar scribe.
No real amenities but better than a communal sleeping quarters. As far
as you can tell he would be a rank equivalent to a Sargeant.

name: Humid, damp tunnel
description:
As the tunnel leads south it gets more humid and damp.  Moss covers the
walls and ferns even grow in the cracks here and there.  To the north it
seems much more sterile.

name: Administration room
description:
The elders gather here to discuss training strategies and count their
loot.  You notice papers which look like important secret documents
lying around. An escape passage leads west.

name: N/S hallway
description:
The hallway continues to become more important-looking as you wander
south.  A room to the east looks rather more pleasant that some of the
others.

name: Mid-level leader's room
description:
A rather nice looking room considering the drab conditions down here.
Through all the signs of decoration you can still see evidence of water
leaks.

name: Mess hall
description:
The a huge table with an immaculate white table cloth stretches way off
to the south.  The room is kept immaculately clean by the nights
themselves.  They truly belive that cleanliness is next to godliness.

name: N/S hallway
description:
The hallway continues north and south.  A peculiar kind of glow seems
to come from somewhere further along the hallway to the south. The room
to the east looks like the lap of luxury.

name: High officer's room
description:
First thing you notice in this room is the pleasant aroma of cedar.  All
the paneling in the room is made of fine cedar.  A painting of an
elegant knight hangs on the wall.

name: Mossy intersection
description:
There is a turn off to the passage here.  The main passage leads north
and south. To the south it seems to get impossibly darker.  To the east
you hear... birds?  A small rivulet of water seeps in from the passage
east.  The air is very humid and damp here.

name: The holy grove
description:
A small grove of birches grow seem to grow from solid rock.  You hear
birds singing but try as you might you cant see any.  A strange glow
emanates from a place somewhere to the southeast in the grove.

name: The holy grove
description:
The trees seem real enough even though they take root in solid rock.
You hear other small animals scampering through the light undergrowth
yet you see nothing. The grove continues south, east and west. An out of
place passage way for some reason heads north.

name: The holy grove
description:
The grove continues west and south.  The glow is roughly to the south
somewhere.

name: Mess hall
description: \mess\" isn't exactly the best word to describe this room.  On the

area_id: contrary
room_id: it is immaculately clean.  A very long table stretches way off

area_id: to the north. A hallway is to the east.

name: End of a hallway
description:
You hear voices coming from a room to the west.  the hallway goes north.
To the east lies a room which seems to glow with power and piety.

name: Grand Templar's room
description:
All the items in this room look ancient yet strangely very powerful and
rich.  There is an aura of great holiness about the room.

name: Very dark passage
description:
This room is so dark that even powerful magic lights seems to barely
illuminate the ground in front of you.  If its possible it seems even
darker to the south.  The passage also leads back north.

name: The holy grove
description:
The grove continues north and east.  To the east a strange humming can
barely be heard.

name: The holy grove
description:
All of a sudden all the mysterious sounds of the grove stop. Or perhaps
its just the strange humming and glowing from a clearing to the south
drowning out everything else. There is a sort of magical forcefield door
to the south.

name: Very dark caveway
description:
This room is so very dark that no one is quite sure whats in it, so
there's nothing really to describe except maybe the powerful sense of
evil coming from the east and the almost overcoming urge to run to the
west.

name: Deep within the catacombs
description:
It stinks like a lair in here.  A rotten smell of humanoid flesh
lingers.  You stumble over what you think are corpses in the utter
darkness. You sense a evil growl from somewhere in the room. maybe
everywhere in the room. . ..

name: Very dark cavern
description:
The cavern is hard to describe due to the extreme magical darkness.
Probing with a light source seems to reveal nothing but more darkness.

name: The holy place
description:
A glowing stone lies in the center of the clearing.  You recognize it as
the stone of the Excalibur.  The strange humming glowing makes it
difficult to see if the Excalibur is there or not. Might want to take a
closer look if possible.

name: Misty passageway
description:
Warm mist swirl about you making you feel threatened as well as
protected at the same time.  The swirling mist makes it tough to tell
directions quite clearly, but you seem to be able to go north or south.
The mist gets denser to the south.

name: Intersection of caverns
description:
Caverns head north, south and east from this peculiar spot. Medium
sized caverns from the east and the north join to form a huge cavern
heading south.  The walls of the cavern are made of a bizarre mixture
of many shiny crystals.

name: Entrance to the burial grounds
description:
You have entered what appears to be a burial ground of sorts. The
templars buried their dead here.  Chills go down your spine as you feel
something watching you.  You hear the random groan of a ghost, the howl
of a wraith, and the dry clanking of bones.

name: The burial grounds
description:
Random tombs to unknown warriors were lain in rows as far as the eye
can see.  To your horror many of the graves are empty and desecrated.
A gap in the rows of tombs leads south and there are more graves to the
east and west.

name: The burial grounds
description:
It seems as if many of the warriors could not stop fighting even in
death.  They fight amongst each other and flail at any living being
that would wander near.

name: The burial grounds
description:
Legions of skeletal warriors wander by and battle the enemy even in
death.  Old battlelines have been forgotten and new ones made. Its a
gruesome scene.

name: New graves
description:
The tombs in this section seem somewhat more recent.  Rotting zombie
warriors groan and wail with blank stares.  You hear sounds of digging
off a bit to the south.

name: Misty cavern
description:
A chilling icy mist swirl about you.  The dampness and warmth has become
bitter cold.  The walls of the cavern are several feet thick with ice
here.  An icy wind blows from the south.

name: Misty cavern
description:
The temperature is a pleasant and mild here.  This is due to a warm wind
blowing in from the east and a chilly breeze blowing in from the west.
The updrafts create bizarre icy-steamy mists which dance along the
walls.

name: Mist cavern
description:
A warm wind blows in from the east.  The air is still stifling hot in
here despite the breeze.  The mist seems thick enough to be alive. . .

name: Waterfall of mist
description:
River of hot mist pour down in a cascade from a hole in the cavern.  It
falls like water down from the heights like a waterfall and creates
beautiful swirls.  It causes a hot wind to flow west.

name: Huge multicolored tunnel
description:
The tunnel leads north and south.  To the south there is an odd
twinkling phenomenon.

name: Desolate ruins
description:
Several mausoleums used to grace the way here but these have been
defiled. And most have been torn down and burned by looters. Some still
seem to be intact to the south.  To the northwest is a seeming field of
tombs of soldiers, now a battleground for the undead.

name: Curators place
description:
The undertaker, the historian and the curator used to be here. Now they
too have joined the legions of the undead.  From the looks of the place
they seem to have starved to death.  Rickety stairs head down into a
sort of basement.

name: Fresh graves
description:
Graves of recent casualties lie here.  Even the most recent don't seem to
have been left undisturbed.  You hear sounds of digging in progress
further to the south.

name: Below a filthy shack
description:
You are on the upper level of the sewers, the drains and pipes are just big
enough for you to crouch down and walk or crawl with ease on all fours. The
air is quiet clean, the occasional breeze bringing an unsavory smell. The
sludge and liquid that lines the ground you don't want to think of what it
could be. The pipe that you are in is broken and grants you access to the
floor of a filthy shack above. It appears that many have taken the path you
have for the cracked pipe is well worn.

name: Upper eastern sewers
description:
Breathing through your mouth to avoid the possible inhalation of scents
that might bring your last meal to visit, you look about at the small drain
you are within. The drain is compiled from multiple shards of mortared
slate with the occasional iron ring to give the structure more strength.
The sludge and liquids slowly trickle off down the drain.

name: Upper eastern sewers
description:
A newer section of pipe has been laid here, made from what looks to be a
fire heated mudbrick that has been lined with a thick yellow clay. You
don't feel to safe in here, whoever thought this would hold together must
have spent a night too many at the local inn..

name: Upper eastern sewers
description:
This piping looks older than some of the piping you have been through.
You were right to think that it wouldn't hold together, the yellow clay
lining has washed away in some sections exposing the raw stone and earth.
Other sections of the mudbricks have fallen into the pipe making the going
hard.

name: Within the sewers
description:
This is a very old drain, it must have been here for years or heavily used.
The large sections of stone are worn smooth from the water flow, the mortar
between the pieces has held and currently sprouts an assortment of green
sludge and outgrowths. You notice that the iron rings here are in fact steel
and haven't corroded away like some of the iron ones.

name: Within the sewers

fours. The air is quiet clean, the occasional breeze brings a unsavory

don't want to think of what it could be.

description:
Breathing through your mouth to avoid the possible inhalation of scents
that might bring your last meal to visit, you look about at the small
drain you are within. The drain is compiled from multiple shards of
mortared slate with the occasional iron ring to give the structure more
strength. The sludge and liquids slowly trickle off down the drain. You

name: An alcove within the sewers
description:
This alcove is completely clean, and looks to have been inhabited recently.
The ground is lined with hemp sacks and there is a small wooden box with
a melted candle and a couple scraps of food and drink. Perhaps this was a
place where a thief might have hidden whilst things cooled down in the
city and his bounty long forgotten.

name: Upper eastern sewers
description:
This piping looks older than some of the piping you have been through.
You were right to think that it wouldn't hold together, the yellow clay
lining has washed away in some sections exposing the raw stone and
earth. Other sections of the mudbricks have fallen into the pipe making
the going hard.

name: A hidden room within the sewers
description:
This is more like what you expected, on the west side of this room is a
large black leather tarp that has been hung to block any light from this
room shining out into the sewer west. It would also aid in reducing the
noise. The room is similar to alcove to the west and south from here,
but is alot more lived in.

tiny spindle wheel that seems to be locked shut preventing all access to
the lower levels of the sewer.

name: Under a grate within the sewers
description:
This sewer pipe is quiet large in comparison to the rest of the sewer.The
air here is still clean and there is a ocasional breeze from above where
there is a grate covered in a large pile of rubish. Light softly filters
through, lighting up the dark recesses of this sewer.

description:

strength. The sludge and liquids slowly trickle off down the drain. The
west side of the drain has crumbled and filled what was a westward leading
pipe.

name: Well worn sewer pipes
description:
A newer section of pipe has been laid here, made from what looks to be a
fire heated mudbrick that has been lined with a thick yellow clay. You
don't feel to safe in here, whoever thought this would hold together must
have spent a night too many at the local inn..

name: Well worn sewer pipes
description:
This piping looks older than some of the piping you have been through.
You were right to think that it wouldn't hold together, the yellow clay
lining has washed away in some sections exposing the raw stone and
earth. Other sections of the mudbricks have fallen into the pipe making
the going hard.

name: Well worn sewer pipes
description:
This is a very old drain, it must have been here for years or heavily
used. The large sections of stone are worn smooth from the water flow, the
mortar between the pieces has held and currently sprouts an assortment
of green sludge and outgrowths. You notice that the iron rings here are
in fact steel and haven't corroded away like some of the iron ones.

name: Well worn sewer pipes
description:
You are on the upper level of the sewers, the drains and pipes are just
big enough for you to crouch down and walk or crawl with ease on all
fours. The air is quiet clean, the occasional breeze brings a unsavory
smell though. The sludge and liquid that lines the ground you are sure
you don't want to think of what it could be.

name: Well worn sewer pipes
description:

that might bring your last meal to visit, you look about at the small
drain you are within. The drain is compiled from multiple shards of
mortared slate with the occasional iron ring to give the structure more
strength. The sludge and liquids slowly trickle off down the drain.

Salty air wafts up from below through a large grate that has a spindle
wheel locking it shut.

description:
This whole room has been carved deep into the rock, extremely large
compared to the pipes and drains that you have been crawling through.
There are many crates boxes and chests in this room. Some thief or even
perhaps a guild has been stashing things here for a extremely long time.

name: The main drain of the sewers
description:
This is a massive room which has a large amount of sewage flowing in from
the south, east and west. It all pours down the massive hole in the center
of the room like a waterfall. The noise nulls out everything else, the
constant clanking of a massive chain that is attached to the ceiling
flicks back and forth as the sewage thunders over it. The sewage sprays
the tunnel below as it passes through a large grate, which has a spindle
wheel attached to it.

description:

name: Western sewers
description:
This sewer tunnel is almost three times the size of the smaller upper
tunnels that weave their way through the rest of the sewers. The added
size allows you to walk upright upon the raised stone walking pavers.
To the west you can hear the clanking of metal and the roar of the fast
flowing sewage, to the north the stepping stones continue.

name: Western sewers
description:
This sewer tunnel is almost three times the size of the smaller upper
tunnels that weave their way through the rest of the sewers. The added
size allows you to walk upright upon the raised stone walking pavers.
To the south and east the sewer continues with the some of stepping stones
linked with rotting planks of wood.

name: Western sewers
description:
This sewer tunnel is almost three times the size of the smaller upper
tunnels that weave their way through the rest of the sewers. The added
size allows you to walk upright upon the raised stone walking pavers.
The stepping stones are well worn on this section of the sewer you
will have to take large steps, or step in something unpleasant.

name: Within a western sewer junction
description:
This sewer tunnel is almost three times the size of the smaller upper
tunnels that weave their way through the rest of the sewers. The added
size allows you to walk upright upon the raised stone walking pavers.
The sewer continues to the north, east and south, but only the pavers
continue on to the east and the south.

name: Western sewers
description:
A newer section of pipe has been laid here, made from what looks to be a
fire heated mudbrick that has been lined with a thick yellow clay. You
don't feel to safe in here, whoever thought this would hold together must
have spent a night too many at the local inn.

name: Western sewers
description:
This sewer tunnel is almost three times the size of the smaller upper
tunnels that weave their way through the rest of the sewers. The added
size allows you to walk upright upon the raised stone walking pavers.
The stepping stones lead east and west and there appears to be a dull
haze of light coming from the east.

name: Below a massive grate
description:
Directly above you is a massive grate, you can see people walking up on the
surface. A nice cool clean breeze blows down into the room that you stand
in and you squint a little as your eye's adjust to the light alteration.
There seem to be well worn tracks leading north and west, perhaps many
travel this way.

name: Within the sewers
description:
This sewer tunnel is almost three times the size of the smaller upper
tunnels that weave their way through the rest of the sewers. The added
size allows you to walk upright upon the raised stone walking pavers.
Leaving the light to your south shadow grow from next to nothing and
engulf what was once a open sewer tunnel.

name: Within the sewers
description:
This sewer tunnel is almost three times the size of the smaller upper
tunnels that weave their way through the rest of the sewers. The added
size allows you to walk upright upon the raised stone walking pavers.
Treated timber planks link the stepping stones enabling quick and quiet
passage down this section of the sewer.

name: Within the sewers
description:
This sewer tunnel is almost three times the size of the smaller upper
tunnels that weave their way through the rest of the sewers. The added
size allows you to walk upright upon the raised stone walking pavers.
Treated timber planks link the stepping stones enabling quick and quiet
passage down this section of the sewer.

name: Within the sewers
description:
This sewer tunnel is almost three times the size of the smaller upper
tunnels that weave their way through the rest of the sewers. The added
size allows you to walk upright upon the raised stone walking pavers.
Treated timber planks link the stepping stones enabling quick and quiet
passage down this section of the sewer.

name: Within the sewers
description:
This section of the sewers is rather dry compared with the rest. There is
a large crate with picture playing cards atop and a halberd wedged into the
corner wall which holds a burning lantern. Strangely enough there seems to
be no people playing the cards. Then you think you see the shadows move.

name: Below the thief guild
description:
This room has a bright shining ball of magic with four thick columns
erected around it that cast long dark shadows over the rest of the room.
The pure brightness of the ball makes the shadows even more dark.

name: Within the sewers
description:
This sewer tunnel is almost three times the size of the smaller upper
tunnels that weave their way through the rest of the sewers. The added
size allows you to walk upright upon the raised stone walking pavers.
Treated timber planks link the stepping stones enabling quick and quiet
passage down this section of the sewer.

name: Within the sewers
description:
This sewer tunnel is almost three times the size of the smaller upper
tunnels that weave their way through the rest of the sewers. The added
size allows you to walk upright upon the raised stone walking pavers.
Treated timber planks link the stepping stones enabling quick and quiet
passage down this section of the sewer. Fresh air blows in from the west
and you instinctively inhale.

name: a junction at the entrance of the sewers
description:
This sewer tunnel is almost three times the size of the smaller upper
tunnels that weave their way through the rest of the sewers. The added
size allows you to walk upright upon the raised stone walking pavers.
Treated timber planks link the stepping stones enabling quick and quiet
passage down this section of the sewer. The planks have been thatched
across this section providing a small area for many people to stand.
The stepping stones and linking planks continue to the east, west and
north. To the north you think you can make out what looks to be light
flooding into the tunnel.

name: At an exit from the sewers
description:
This drain has been made a lot wider you can stand up with ease, the floor
seems to be heavily worn. All those that wish to enter the city without
being stupid and searched by the gate guards probably come through this or
another similar drain. Who ever controls these sewers must make a nice
profit.

name: Within the sewers
description:
This sewer tunnel is almost three times the size of the smaller upper
tunnels that weave their way through the rest of the sewers. The added
size allows you to walk upright upon the raised stone walking pavers.
Treated timber planks link the stepping stones enabling quick and quiet
passage down this section of the sewer. To the east the sewer appears
to open up into a large junction.

name: Within the sewers
description:
This sewer tunnel is almost three times the size of the smaller upper
tunnels that weave their way through the rest of the sewers. The added
size allows you to walk upright upon the raised stone walking pavers.
Treated timber planks link the stepping stones enabling quick and quiet
passage down this section of the sewer both east and westward.

name: A junction within the sewers
description:
This sewer tunnel is almost three times the size of the smaller upper
tunnels that weave their way through the rest of the sewers. The added
size allows you to walk upright upon the raised stone walking pavers.
Treated timber planks link the stepping stones enabling quick and quiet
passage down this section of the sewer. The pavers and planks take a
sharp turn southward even though there is a tunnel to the west.

name: Within the sewers
description:
stepping from the planks of wood and into the smaller sewer pipe you start
to realize that the darkness is getting darker than normal. The air is full
of a stench that you cannot place. To the east the sewer continues to the
west the darkness disappears into a void.

name: Within the sewers
description:
The sewer pipes have melded in the darkness into the stone, you nolonger
seem to be traversing the wide tunnels, but now you seem to be walking
within a set tunnel. The sewer putrid smell is repalced with a dry stale
smell that doesn't seem to sit well with your stomach.

name: Entrance to the crypt of the lost
description:
As you step into this room both pillars either side of you flare with
brilliant blue white plasma that arcs from pillar to pillar leaving you
unharmed. The runes and sigils slowly die down and emit a soft hue color
that is enough to see by. Before you is a small arch with a inscription
carved into the arc above the doorway that least northward.

name: Within the sewers
description:
This sewer tunnel is almost three times the size of the smaller upper
tunnels that weave their way through the rest of the sewers. The added
size allows you to walk upright upon the raised stone walking pavers.
Treated timber planks link the stepping stones enabling quick and quiet
passage down this section of the sewer.

name: Within the sewers
description:
The drain here is also well worn and relatively dry on the upper corners
of the piping. A small trickle flows down the center, making soft echoing
dripping noises. On the east wall is a Torch holder fixed to a flat iron
bracket. The planks and stepping stones come to a halt in this sewer
tunnel.

name: Hidden within the sewers
description:
Your still in a sewer drain but it is clean and dry, to the west is the
hidden door you just walked through and to the south is what looked to
be a hidden room under the assassin guild.

name: Under the assassin guild
description:
This room is split level, the upper section has very low head room but also
has the slide trapdoor that allows entrance up into the assassin guild. The
lower level has a table with posters of the latest bounty and rewards for
assassinations.

name: Within the sewers
description:
This is a very old drain, it must have been here for years or heavily used.
The large sections of stone are worn smooth from the water flow, the mortar
between the pieces has held and currently sprouts an assortment of green
sludge and outgrowths. You notice that the iron rings here are in fact
steel and haven't corroded away like some of the iron ones.

don't feel to safe in here, whoever thought this would hold together must
have spent a night too many at the local inn..

name: Within a sewer pipe
description:
This piping looks older than some of the piping you have been through.
You were right to think that it wouldn't hold together, the yellow clay
lining has washed away in some sections exposing the raw stone and earth.
Other sections of the mudbricks have fallen into the pipe making the going
hard.

name: Western sewers
description:
This is a very old drain, it must have been here for years or heavily
used. The large sections of stone are worn smooth from the water flow,
the mortar between the pieces has held and currently sprouts an
assortment of green sludge and outgrowths. You notice that the iron
rings here are in fact steel and haven't corroded away like some of
the iron ones.

name: Western sewers
description:
You are on the upper level of the sewers, the drains and pipes are just
big enough for you to crouch down and walk or crawl with ease on all
fours. The air is quiet clean, the occasional breeze brings a unsavory
smell though. The sludge and liquid that lines the ground you are sure
you don't want to think of what it could be.

name: Western sewers
description:
Breathing through your mouth to avoid the possible inhalation of scents
that might bring your last meal to visit, you look about at the small
drain you are within. The drain is compiled from multiple shards of
mortared slate with the occasional iron ring to give the structure more
strength. The sludge and liquids slowly trickle off down the drain.

name: Tablet of Remberance
description:
You step into this crypt with great caution after passing between the
pillars that are to your south. The floor is lined with a extremely old
looking rock which has over time been worn smooth in the center, small
piles of dirt gathering in the corners. Before you is a massive tablet
which looks to have been scraped and gouged rendering the writings that
once were chiseled upon it unreadable.

name: Within the crypt
description:
Graves line the walls from floor to ceiling five deep. Each grave has
a rotten decayed corpse half bound in material which had decayed or
been eaten away over time. There is a small ion stone imbedded in the
silver braced wooden support beam that long ago might have radiated
light as you near it granting light to this wretched place. The fact
that it doesn't indicates that this crypt has been here for a extremely
long time.

from the silver bracket what it is for you do not know.

name: Within the burial
description:
This room of the crypt has no graves lining the walls at all. Centered
at the center of the room is a massive stone casket which is almost
ten feet long and five foot wide. What ever is buried in there must
be massive.

name: Within the burial of Triesteal
description:
This is the burial chamber of a royal for sure, and seems to have been
left undiscovered by thieves and looters. There is a small golden throne
in the center of the room that has a rather fresh looking corpse sitting
in it. Resting on the armrest of the throne is a small sceptre. This
corpse doesn't quiet look dead yet.

name: Within the crypt
description:
Graves line the walls from floor to ceiling five deep. Each grave has
a rotten decayed corpse half bound in material which had decayed or been
eaten away over time. There is a small ion stone imbedded in the silver

indicates that this crypt has been here for a extremely long time.

name: The burial of the lost
description:
Indeed you have found the main burial chamber but it is not at a price,
sitting at the massive adamantite throne is a skeleton that is wearing
a crown and a amulet that pulses with raw power. Either side of the
large throne are two gargoyles of mithril, they don't move now but by
the look of the face on skeleton a single word shall bring them into
action.

description:

name: The shrine of the lost
description:
Upon entering this room you instantly notice the far end of the chamber
is raised with a altar set upon it humming with raw magic. Wisps of
green mist swirl around the altar and seems to swirl with vigor upon
each pulsate of magical energy.

name: The inner crypt
description:
The walls floor and roof are all paneled in white marble and there is
not a single grave in this room. There is a strange humming noise that
seems to pulse every minute or so.

name: The inner crypt
description:
The walls floor and roof are all paneled in white marble and there is
not a single grave in this room. There is a strange humming noise that
seems to pulse every minute or so.

name: The inner crypt
description:
The walls floor and roof are all paneled in white marble and there is
not a single grave in this room. There is a strange humming noise that
seems to pulse every minute or so.

name: The inner crypt
description:
The walls floor and roof are all paneled in white marble and there is
not a single grave in this room. There is a strange humming noise that
seems to pulse every minute or so.

name: The inner crypt anode
description:
Sitting in the center of this massive white marble room is a large sky
blue crystal that rotates slowly. Green mist from the surrounding walls
seeps into the bottom of the crystal and then the humming noise builds
up to a ear splitting discharge of plasma that spurts into the room to
the east.

name: The inner crypt
description:
The walls floor and roof are all paneled in white marble and there is
not a single grave in this room. There is a strange humming noise that
seems to pulse every minute or so.

name: The inner crypt anode
description:
Sitting in the center of this massive white marble room is a large sky
blue crystal that rotates slowly. Green mist from the surrounding walls
seeps into the bottom of the crystal and then the humming noise builds
up to a ear splitting discharge of plasma that spurts into the room to
the west.

name: The inner crypt altar
description:
In the center of this room is a massive Mithril altar, Still in pristine
condition this altar glows and hum with a massive amount of power.
Green mist swirls up from cracks in the floor and is absorbed into the
fine sigils and runes that line the bottom of the Altar. There is a thick
dew smell in the air as plasma burst from the west and east wall at the
same time striking the altar. Shortly following that the altar turns a
bright purple color as all the runes activate, releasing a bizarre beam
that is focused upon the heartstone earthing rod in the roof. There is a
neat bookshelf that appears to hold a single book bound with crystal clips.

name: Before the ruins of old
description:
To the south lies something darker and more horrid than you had thought
possible The putrid stench of true death floods your nose, as the stench
reaches near to the base of altar it flares and turns into a visible
green mist. The walls are dug from the rock and earth leaving only slate
steps as a base to walk upon. To the south you notice movement in the
darkness. Half burred in the earthen walls are two more pillars with
sigils on them, exactly the same as those that were out the front of
the crypt entrance.

name: The War Chamber
description:
This chamber is what you would expect for a warrior's guild... padded
training dummies are mounted on the walls and massive racks of sharp
implements of war and burnished steel armor decorate every square foot of
the room.  In one corner is a barrel of water, and hanging from the rafters
are sacks of drying fruit.  As barbarians and swordmasters walk through,
you note that they all have at least one thing in common:  they appear to
be very, very well trained.

name: A Sun-Baked Yard
description:
This is a square patch of dirt, about twenty or thirty paces on a side,
and a quick glance around the area reveals nothing of note aside from the
man standing at the northern edge.  The loose, dry dirt of the ground
beneath you has been baked by the sun for years, all nutrients burned from
it by the heat.  It is dead soil, and it seems to have been raked neatly,
and fairly recently.  Here and there you see a few flecks of blood where
the rake did not quite clear the ground thoroughly enough, and tiny shards
of steel and wood litter the edges of the yard.

name: A Pile of Rocky Debris
description:
Having hurled yourself from atop Cimar's great northern wall, you can now
see how so many armies have dashed themselves against it over the last few
centuries without any discernible effect.  It stands very high and quite
indomitable, towering over you as you lie prone considering your recent
actions.  With luck, some passerby will notice your broken form and come to
your aid, but for now you lie helpless, thanks to your rash decision to
leap from the parapets.

name: Atop the North Wall of Cimar
description:
You scramble up the pile of trash, and find that it's a relatively short
hop from its apex to the top of Cimar's huge outer wall.  And now that
you're here, you can see almost everything in Cimar - this wall is very,
very high.  From this vantage point, you can make out every building in
High Cimar, nestled among the foothills of Mount Cim.  You can see the tiny
people dodging each other in Cimar's business district, the trees at
Cimar's center where the ranger guild makes its home, the frothy point
where the Talis River plummets from the top of a cliff into the ocean to
the south, and even some of the larger boats in the harbor.  From here, the
city's corruption and general state of decay are things unseen and
unminded, and Cimar is once again a grand and beautiful thing.  To your
south, you can climb back down the pile of trash and to your north, a very
sudden drop leads to some extremely sharp rocks at the base of the wall,
more than forty feet down...

name: New Cimar
description:
You stand in the strip of homes and plots of land between Cimar's outer
and inner walls.  It's known as New Cimar in polite circles, and sometimes
as Leechtown or Fungusville in impolite ones.  It houses some of the lesser
families of Cimar, in their smaller homes and less extravagant businesses,
but also holds in its confines the powerful and world-renown mage guilds of
Cimar and the highly trained Cimarrite Army.  For now, though, these things
are at the back of your mind as you kick your way through the litter and
debris.  To the north, a large pile of garbage stands up against the
northern outer wall.  East, the sound of crashing bodies and slashing
weapons is growing louder.  To your south is Toller Road.

name: The Eastern Arch
description:
The massive stone walls of Cimar open here, forming an archway through
which its inhabitants and visitors pass when entering or leaving.  Gates
which look as though they would take a small dragon to tow open and shut
stretch forty feet over your head.  The traffic here has worn the
cobblestones under your feet to a smooth surface, almost flat and nearly
shining, reminiscent of dulled and unpolished marble.  Several of the
city's complacent Watchmen lounge at the edges of this massive contour,
glaring at passing members of the Cimarrite Army.  The street stretches off
to the west, and becomes a major trade route leading into the east.  Noisy
barracks lie to the south and the sound of clashing weapons floats in from
the north, while Mount Cim dominates the entire setting from the sky to the
northwest.

name: East Toller Road
description:
This is the main road in Cimar, running east and west its entire length.
Off to the west, you can see that it stretches through the Inner Gate and
over the river toward a vast marketplace.  Though you can't see the road
beyond that, the inner wall on the other side of Cimar is barely visible.
Just a bit to the east, the massive Eastern Arch towers over you.  To the
north, you can hear the sounds of weapons crashing together as warriors
train, and to the south you see the Cimarrite Army's barracks in a long
row.  Bustling traffic buffets you from all sides here as business moves in
and out of the city, and from sector to sector.  Keep moving, or pay the
price and be buried alive beneath a mountain of sweaty, hurrying flesh.

name: East Toller Road
description:
This is the main road in Cimar, running east and west its entire length.
Off to the west, you can see that it stretches over the river toward a vast
marketplace.  Though you can't see the road beyond that, the inner wall on
the other side of Cimar is barely visible.  Just a bit to the east, the
inner wall is penetrated by the Inner Gate, and past that stands the
massive Eastern Arch.  The road widens to the north here, to facilitate
major traffic.  To your south, a dark alleyway looks to be a good place to
avoid.

name: East Toller Road
description:
This is the main road in Cimar, running east and west its entire length.
Off to the west, you can see that it stretches over the river toward a vast
marketplace.  Though you can't see the road beyond that, the inner wall on
the other side of Cimar is barely visible.  Just a bit to the east, the
inner wall is penetrated by the Inner Gate, and beyond that you hear the
sounds of clashing weapons as warriors train.  The road is wide here to
facilitate major traffic, and you can move to the south to avoid the
carriages which normally inhabit this half of the road.  Bustling traffic
buffets you from all sides here as business moves in and out of the city,
and from sector to sector.  Keep moving, or pay the price and be buried
alive beneath a mountain of sweaty, hurrying flesh.

name: The North Bridge
description:
Huge old steelwood beams, as thick as an abyss titan's leg and as smooth
as an elf's posterior, make up the North Bridge and allow Toller Road to
pass over the Talis River.  The river swells here, running high toward the
waterfall to the south, and the bridge is barely a foot above water level.
You feel no hazard, though, as passing horses, carriages and titans do not
even cause the beams beneath you to shudder slightly.  The edge of the
bridge is to your north, guarded by sturdy handrails, and you can see the
other edge of this very wide bridge ten yards off to the south.  East of
you lies Toller Road, and the bridge continues to the west.

name: The North Bridge
description:
Huge old steelwood beams, as thick as an abyss titan's leg and as smooth
