name: A Modest Home
description:
Given some of the other magnificent and beautiful houses in Old Cimar, this
one seems a bit out of place.  It stands directly next to a small core of
untouched land at the center of the city;  a tightly-packed cluster of
ancient trees, a small pond, a few worn old pathways, and this dwelling.
Made of simple stone and wood, it looks to have withstood the tests of time
rather well, perhaps because of the shelter of the grove of trees nearby.  A
rocking chair stands in one corner away from the door, next to a large brick
fireplace.  A table is at the other end of the room, with a wooden bowl and
spoon set out for a meal;  scents of cooking waft in from the eastern door.
A thick canvas apron and a large wood axe hang on pegs near the door to the
north, which leads back out to Rantid Road.

name: A Small Kitchen
description:
An oven made of stones, a table of gnarled wood, and utensils carved out of
sticks and bones, everything in this kitchen has come from nature.  None of
Cimar's modern developments have gone into making this home, and no cast iron
or other technology have created its components.  The oven burns hot, as its
slate hatch holds the smoke in, and something which was likely caught earlier
in the day is prepared with a hickory scent cooked into it.  A small door to
the north holds breezes outside and the heat of the kitchen in, and windows
to the east and south look out on the streets and trees of Old Cimar.  An
open doorway to the west leads back into the main room of this quaint and
modest home.

name: A Large Home
description:
It's not obvious whose home this is, but so near to the center of Old
Cimar, it must be that of a rather important person.  It's a beautiful home,
and wooden beams and log construction all around compose every wall of the
residence.  The location would lead one to believe that this was one of the
first homes in the original settlement of Cimar, and yet it would have to be
nearly 1500 years old for that to be true.  If it's the case, then the wooden
framework construction must have been renewed several times.  It certainly
doesn't look like wood that's been there for one and a half millennia.  To
the south, a large door leads out to West Rantid Road, while to the east and
west lie a bedroom and kitchen, respectively.

name: A Bedroom
description:
An incredibly comfortable-looking bed graces the center of this room.
Quilted sheets of varicolored cloth stuffed full with something quite soft,
it sings quietly to a weary body of the joys of rest.  A night table to the
side of the bed holds a reading lamp which burns oil, giving off a slight
scent of pine needles.  Also on the table lies an open book, bound with soft
leather and printed upon yellowed parchment with a handsome script.  There is
a large bear skin covering the floor at the foot of the bed, and the solid
oak archway to the west leads to the main room of the home.  Through a window
to the south, you see West Rantid Road.

name: A Kitchen
description:
Pots and pans dangle from a rack on the ceiling of this cooking area.  You
see a beautiful cast iron stove in one corner, a large wooden table with a
silver washing basin in another.  The smell of fresh bread reigns in this
room perpetually, mingled with spices and the scent of a wood fire.  The
brick floor is spotless, and the mop and broom in the corner show no signs of
dust or cobwebs;  the owner of this kitchen must be a fastidious cleaner.  To
the east, a door leads into the main room of this home, and to the south, a
large plate glass window looks out on West Rantid Road.  Across the street, a
small grove lends itself to a very pretty view.

name: The Captain's Residence
description:
This lavish home is where the captain of the Cimar Cityguard Corps resides
when not on duty.  Which, were you to ask most people, is not very often.  It
is a lush compartment indeed, furnished with the finest woods, cut out of the
forests to the north and lacquered in the cities to the east.  An elaborately
patterned rug covers the floor with a brilliant depiction of some ancient
ceremony.  It seems, in fact, to be a rather old and likely very valuable
rug;  the captain walks on it daily, however, with no regard for history or
art.  It's easy to grow to despise the man, looking around his home.  All
manner of artifacts adorn glass shelves around the room, from clay pots to
unidentifiable objects of some archaic origin or another.  The door by which
you may leave is to the east.

name: A Grand Hall
description:
One of the most extravagant homes in Cimar is this, the cityguard captain's
abode.  Sometimes referred to as the old man's \base of operations

name: West Toller Road
description:
The main street in Cimar, Toller Road runs its entire width from east to
west.  The road is narrower here than in the eastern half of the city, as
most traffic moves through the north and east gates.  But you still find
yourself surrounded by a large number of citygoers, from businessmen and
merchants to fairly obvious thieves and purse snatchers.  While there isn't
much traffic moving directly through the city here, there is quite a lot
between the business district in Cimar's southwest quadrant and other parts
of the city.  This part of Toller Road is in Old Cimar, running parallel with
the inner wall to the north.  The Highgate stands tall and proud north of
here, and the Regal Theatre is to the south.

name: West Toller Road
description:
The main street in Cimar, Toller Road runs its entire width from east to
west.  The road is narrower here than in the eastern half of the city, as
most traffic moves through the north and east gates.  But you still find
yourself surrounded by a large number of citygoers, from businessmen and
merchants to fairly obvious thieves and purse snatchers.  While there isn't
much traffic moving directly through the city here, there is quite a lot
between the business district in Cimar's southwest quadrant and other parts
of the city.  This part of Toller Road is in Old Cimar, running parallel with
the inner wall to the north.  Lined on both sides by private homes and
branched from by several north-to-south avenues, it bustles with activity
through most of the day.  A very large home lies to the north.

name: West Toller Road
description:

west.  The road is narrower here than in the eastern half of the city, as
most traffic moves through the north and east gates.  But you still find

branched from by several north-to-south avenues, it bustles with activity
through most of the day.  A kiosk lies off the road to the south.

description:
The main street in Cimar, Toller Road runs its entire width from east to
west.  The road is narrower here than in the eastern half of the city, as
most traffic moves through the north and east gates.  But you still find
yourself surrounded by a large number of citygoers, from businessmen and
merchants to fairly obvious thieves and purse snatchers.  While there isn't

between the business district in Cimar's southwest quadrant and other parts
of the city.  This part of Toller Road is in Old Cimar, running parallel with
the inner wall to the north.  Lined on both sides by private homes and
branched from by several north-to-south avenues, it bustles with activity
through most of the day.  North from here, a small path moves through a hole
in the inner wall toward High Cimar.

name: The Western Arch
description:
The massive stone walls of Cimar open here, forming an archway through
which its inhabitants and visitors pass when entering or leaving.  Gates
which look as though they would take a small dragon to tow open and shut
stretch forty feet over your head.  The traffic here has worn the
cobblestones under your feet to a smooth surface, almost flat and nearly
shining, reminiscent of dulled and unpolished marble.  Several of the city's
complacent Watchmen lounge at the edges of this massive contour, glaring at
passing members of the Cimarrite Army.  The street stretches off to the east,
and becomes a mountain route leading into the west.  Broker Avenue stretches
off to the south through the bustling business district of Cimar, while
Mount Cim dominates the entire setting from the sky to the northwest.

name: A Small Kiosk
description:
The atmosphere of a bazaar permeates this small structure, open both to
the north and the south.  A tall wooden lance stands upright at the center
of the pavillion, holding a tent away from the ground.  The corners of that
thick canvas sheet are tamped to the soft dirt of this area, and more wooden
struts about half the length of the center strut support each edge of the
fabric square to the east and west.  A metal arch holds the north and south
edges up into doorway-like openings.  The air moves freely through this
shop; it is the only temporary building in the neighborhood, and stands out
in a strange way.  The smells of a dozen different varieties of food fill
the breeze, and travel up and down Toller Road to the north, luring in
customers like a fisherman's line.

name: Behind the Wall
description:
This strange space is created by a hole in the inner wall of Cimar.  Were
it not for this hole, there would not be enough room between the residence to
the east and the wall itself for anything larger than an imp;  as it stands,
this is a viable option for passage between Rantid Road to the south, Toller
Road to the north, and the business district to the west.  Whether the
residents of the home to your east appreciate the trespassing this convenient
route causes isn't able to be determined at the moment.  From the amount of
wear on the ground, however, it's apparent that not many people care.

name: The Smithy's Cache
description:
The sound of ringing metal fills the air in this armory;  the finest armors
in Cimar come from the forge here, in the Smithy's Cache.  The room is well-
lit, owing mostly to large holes in the ceiling covered by what seems to be an
incredible variety of almost-transparent metal.  Another strange type of metal
is set into a lamp-like structure against one wall;  as it slowly burns -- as
if that weren't remarkable enough -- it sheds the light of the sun,
necessitating a shield so as not to blind customers.  Truly, marvels such as
this one might never have expected to see from a mere metal worker.  Perhaps
the man who works here sidelights as an alchemist.

name: The Warrior's Storehouse
description:
Every inch of this shop looks as though it could kill a man.  The walls
bristle with armaments, claymores and crossbows dangle from hooks on the
ceiling, and all varieties of traded-in weapons are piled on the floor in
places.  Rough customers come through, but from the looks of the men behind
the counter to the south, fighting inside is fairly easily discouraged.  To
the north, a doorway leads back out into the business district of Cimar.  The
pungent smell of a burning forge wafts through the air, and the sharp hiss of
hot metal being cooled in a bucket of river water slices its way to your ears
occasionally.  Some weapons gleam as if made of polished silver while others
are dull as a day with a family of halflings, but all are as lethal as a
devil's tooth.

name: Broker Avenue
description:
Nestled beneath the gargantuan outer wall of Cimar, where it is almost
lost in shadow, this road fires its way from the grand Western Arch
straight into the harbor.  Forming the western border of Cimar's business
district, Broker Avenue is named for the activity which takes place in the
many widely varying shops and stores along its considerable length:
negotiating, bargaining, and haggling.  In the shade for most of the day,
between the high-roofed places of business to the east and the towering
wall to the west, the street's cobblestones are not blanched pasty grayish-
white as they are elsewhere in the city.  At the center of the path, they
are worn down by traffic, but at the edges, they retain a sort of healthy
shade and shine as though new.

name: The Business District
description:
The busiest sector of Cimar -- and perhaps in this region of Shalar -- the
business district's buzz of activity is audible from anywhere in the city.
Prices screamed by full-lunged shopkeepers and offers made at a shout ring
through the streets and bounce from Cimar's massive outer wall to the west.
It is said that anything in the world can be obtained here;  it is also
widely assumed that that claim is exaggerated, but standing within the
district, you find it to be possibly not so far-fetched.  Shops are visible
in every direction, and without specific instructions and a goal in mind it
would be quite easy to be very lost.  To the north and south, you see shops,
to the west is Broker Avenue, and east of here you may plunge further into
the district.

name: The Business District
description:
The busiest sector of Cimar -- and perhaps in this region of Shalar -- the
business district's buzz of activity is audible from anywhere in the city.
Prices screamed by full-lunged shopkeepers and offers made at a shout ring
through the streets and bounce from Cimar's massive outer wall to the west.
It is said that anything in the world can be obtained here;  it is also
widely assumed that that claim is exaggerated, but standing within the
district, you find it to be possibly not so far-fetched.  Shops are visible
in every direction, and without specific instructions and a goal in mind it
would be quite easy to be very lost.  South of here, you see District Alley;
though dark and uninviting, it is still an oft-used avenue between parts of
the district.

name: District Alley
description:
Between the shops of the business district and the inner wall of Cimar, a
narrow space runs along most of the border between the old city and the
District.  As you walk here, you see and hear and smell evidence of each
shop's wares;  this alleyway runs behind most of the stores in the area, and
quite a lot of trash has been thrown here and left to rot.  A loaf of bread
here, a lump of ruined mithril there, the items nobody sees in their shopping
make their way here.  A perfectly viable route from the north side of the
District to the south side, you can see why the alley gets as little traffic
as it does, despite its convenience.  You pick your way carefully through the
sludge on the ground by the light provided from the narrow slit between the
edges of the roofs and the wall up above.

name: The Business District
description:
The busiest sector of Cimar -- and perhaps in this region of Shalar -- the
business district's buzz of activity is audible from anywhere in the city.
Prices screamed by full-lunged shopkeepers and offers made at a shout ring
through the streets and bounce from Cimar's massive outer wall to the west.
It is said that anything in the world can be obtained here;  it is also
widely assumed that that claim is exaggerated, but standing within the
district, you find it to be possibly not so far-fetched.  Shops are visible
in every direction, and without specific instructions and a goal in mind it
would be quite easy to be very lost.  To the north and south, you see shops,
to the west is Broker Avenue, and east of here you may plunge further into
the district.

name: The Business District
description:
The busiest sector of Cimar -- and perhaps in this region of Shalar -- the
business district's buzz of activity is audible from anywhere in the city.
Prices screamed by full-lunged shopkeepers and offers made at a shout ring
through the streets and bounce from Cimar's massive outer wall to the west.
It is said that anything in the world can be obtained here;  it is also
widely assumed that that claim is exaggerated, but standing within the
district, you find it to be possibly not so far-fetched.  Shops are visible
in every direction, and without specific instructions and a goal in mind it
would be quite easy to be very lost.  North of here, you see District Alley;
though dark and uninviting, it is still an oft-used avenue between parts of
the district.

name: District Alley
description:
Between the shops of the business district and the inner wall of Cimar, a
narrow space runs along most of the border between the old city and the
District.  As you walk here, you see and hear and smell evidence of each
shop's wares;  this alleyway runs behind most of the stores in the area, and
quite a lot of trash has been thrown here and left to rot.  A loaf of bread
here, a lump of ruined mithril there, the items nobody sees in their shopping
make their way here.  A perfectly viable route from the north side of the
District to the south side, you can see why the alley gets as little traffic
as it does, despite its convenience.  You pick your way carefully through the
sludge on the ground by the light provided from the narrow slit between the
edges of the roofs and the wall up above.  A small shop lies to the west.

name: The Redwater Tap
description:
This is the most desirable location in all of Cimar at which to own a
building.  It lies at the southernmost tip of the business district, where
the greatest traffic comes through the city, and in full view of the
beautiful harbor and sea to the south... and the lucky owners of the Redwater
Tap have obtained it for their bar.  All manner of people are seated around
this establishment at high tables surrounded with plush stools.  The walls
are decorated with paintings, clocks, and bits and pieces of maritime
artifacts such as anchors, block, and lines.  There's even a huge headpiece
over the bar itself, depicting a topless mermaid.  And at the south end of
the bar, opposite the doorway, a huge window -- which likely cost a fortune
-- looks out for a gorgeous view of the crimson ocean.

name: General Store
description:
This is perhaps the least phenomenal of the shops in Cimar's business
district.  With walls made of simple wooden boards and a floor of dusty
stone, the shop functions perfectly well without much fanfare or frilliness.
This is where the denizens of this great city come -- be they mere peasants
or members of the highest order of aristocrats -- when they need the simplest
of supplies.  Many think of such a store as a great equalizer, though the
uppity folk who are forced to come from their mansions to shop consider its
relatively boring appearance to be more of a slap in the face than anything
else.  To the north, you may exit back to the business district, while the
counter where earnest men do their work lies to the south.

name: The Kraken Army
description:
This room is made up to look like an army bunker, very similar to those at
the eastern end of Cimar.  Rows of cots and shelves line each wall, and
members of the Kraken Army mill about unprofessionally.  Mercenaries for hire,
this \army\" shows its true colors by appearing simply as a group of uneducated

area_id: ruffians.  A few books lie strewn about
room_id: along with diagrams of various

area_id: races' anatomies
room_id: and practice dummies line the back wall

area_id: crumpling desk near the doorway has a tiny cracked brass bell sitting on its
edge
room_id: upon which a customer looking to hire a street tough might presumably

area_id: ring to receive service.  This back-alley organization has all the spit and
polish of a band of orcs
room_id: yet enough brawn that hiring a member is a viable

area_id: option.  To the east
room_id: a darkened alleyway lurks.

name: The Wizard's Wynd
description:
The walls of this shop have been painted in such a manner so as to make it
seem as though it stretches on out of sight to some point in infinity
directly behind the counter.  The actual result is a rather ridiculous effect
which suggests that a child might have been able to design something better;
at the very least, it's done in a relatively attractive shade of blue.  Racks
and shelves all around the shop are covered with stacks of wands and
grimoires, scrolls and seals, canes and staves.  To the west, a door leads out
to Broker Avenue.  At the east end of the room, behind the shop's table of
business, bits of lifeless wood and scraps of paper pile up waiting to be
enchanted by skilled and artful hands.

name: The Apothecary
description:
Upon entering this shop, the sense of smell is the first to be assaulted;
hundreds of different herbs and chemicals spout their pungent odors into the
air, and nothing keeps them from their apparent business of multiplying and
becoming all the more offensive.  At a counter to the east, miniature shelves
hold tiny bottles filled with liquids of dozens of unique shades.  Large
boards mounted horizontally against the walls serve as shelves for the
ingredients of many of these potions:  roots, herbs, crumbling rocks of
unidentifiable minerals, and bits of dried animal.  To the west, a small door
is covered with a large blanket;  it holds in the scents to keep the shop
fresh, no doubt.

name: Harbor Lights Road
description:
Circling around a rocky outcropping of the cliffs at the south end of
Cimar, Harbor Lights Road is one of the most picturesque points in the city.
The reddish waters of the sea to the south stretch on to the horizon, and
over a metal railing embedded in the rock, the cliff is a thirty foot drop
straight to the harbor below.  This loop of road extends the business
district, and from here, the torches on the ships in the harbor are visible
at night -- hence its name.  The gorgeous view to the south is somewhat
blunted by the harried sounds which roll from the north, but at night this
place is silent.

name: Harbor Lights Road
description:
Circling around a rocky outcropping of the cliffs at the south end of
Cimar, Harbor Lights Road is one of the most picturesque points in the city.
The reddish waters of the sea to the south stretch on to the horizon, and

name: Harbor Lights Road
description:
Circling around a rocky outcropping of the cliffs at the south end of
Cimar, Harbor Lights Road is one of the most picturesque points in the city.
The reddish waters of the sea to the south stretch on to the horizon, and
over a metal railing embedded in the rock, the cliff is a thirty foot drop
straight to the harbor below.  This loop of road extends the business
district, and from here, the torches on the ships in the harbor are visible
at night -- hence its name.  The gorgeous view to the south is somewhat
blunted by the harried sounds which roll from the north, but at night this
place is silent.  A winding pathway here leads down the cliffside to Cimar's
docks.

name: Harbor Lights Road
description:
Circling around a rocky outcropping of the cliffs at the south end of
Cimar, Harbor Lights Road is one of the most picturesque points in the city.
The reddish waters of the sea to the south stretch on to the horizon, and
over a metal railing embedded in the rock, the cliff is a thirty foot drop
straight to the harbor below.  This loop of road extends the business
district, and from here, the torches on the ships in the harbor are visible
at night -- hence its name.  The gorgeous view to the south is somewhat
blunted by the harried sounds which roll from the north, but at night this
place is silent.

name: Harbor Walk
description:
Moving down the side of the cliff at the southern end of town, a large
staircase beautifully constructed of red wood descends to water level.
Bolted together with steel ties and lashed to the crimson-stained rock of the
cliff, it holds steady through all weather.  Below, the wooden docks are
likewise mounted to the sea's floor and the cliff's side, stretching out
into the reddish water of the harbor.  At the moorings along the docks, many
varieties of ships are tied up;  fishing schooners, royal ships, military
vessels, all are visible from here.  Above you, the outer wall of Cimar opens
for several yards in both directions to allow traffic down to the harbor, and
also to provide a stunning view of the sea from inside the city.

name: The Dock of Cimar
description:
An ever-so-slight swaying is detectable below your feet on this dock.  As
well-founded as it is, a bit of movement in the tides and the possible eight
foot swells of the sea to the south is inevitable.  The sun-baked boards upon
which you walk are massive;  as thick as a human torso, and as wide.  Their
surface is bleached grey by the hot days of summer, and worn smooth by year-
round traffic.  The pilons to the east and west, repeated every ten feet, are
thick enough to appear as though the god of the sea had thrust his fingers up
in support of the walkway.  They are banded several inches from the top by
iron to prevent decay, but the exposed wood is very splintered.  Dry rot has
set in, and bits of the pilons fleck off into the red water below.  The docks
continue to the south, and ships are moored at the eastern edge.

name: The Dock of Cimar
description:
An ever-so-slight swaying is detectable below your feet on this dock.  As
well-founded as it is, a bit of movement in the tides and the possible eight

iron to prevent decay, but the exposed wood is very splintered.  Dry rot has
set in, and bits of the pilons fleck off into the red water below.  The docks
continue to the north and south, and ships are moored at the eastern edge.

name: The End of the Dock
description:
An ever-so-slight swaying is detectable below your feet on this dock.  As
well-founded as it is, a bit of movement in the tides and the possible eight
foot swells of the sea to the south is inevitable.  The sun-baked boards upon
which you walk are massive;  as thick as a human torso, and as wide.  Their
surface is bleached grey by the hot days of summer, and worn smooth by year-
round traffic.  The pilons to the east and west, repeated every ten feet, are
thick enough to appear as though the god of the sea had thrust his fingers up
in support of the walkway.  They are banded several inches from the top by
iron to prevent decay, yet the exposed wood is very splintered.  Dry rot has
set in, and bits of the pilons fleck off into the red water below.  Here, the
dock comes to an end.  To the north, it runs toward Cimar, and to the south,
nothing but expansive sea.

name: An Unused Mooring
description:
At this slot on the end of the pier, no ships are docked.  Huge pilons with
massive mooring ties await a floating fortress or a rowboat;  any seaworthy
vessel will sate the dock's needs.  To the north, you see that the rest of the
dock has been filled with many ships of varying size and apparent purpose.
The reddish water below you seems almost grainy in texture, as if millions of
tiny flecks of rust are what gives it its hue.  The waves in the harbor lap
against both the dock to the west and the ship to the north, and the sounds of
splashing waves and breaking surf surround you.  The massive cliff of Cimar
shows its crimson face to the north, and the city's gargantuan walls are
perched atop it.

name: An Exotic Yacht
description:
Certainly a beautiful ship, this vessel seems to have come a long way,
judging by the fact that ships like it simply do not come from anywhere near
Cimar.  Huge gilded winglike structures protrude from each side of the craft,
their tips dipping gently into the water's surface.  On the bow of the ship,
the wooden bust of a maiden perches.  Not just any maiden, the lady depicted
upon this ornament has stylized elvish ears, far longer and more pointed than
a real elf's, and delicately feathered wings which stretch back along the
sides of the ship.  You cannot tell what these decorative structures have been
made of... wood would be a safe assumption, but nothing on the ship shows any
signs of wear.  Even the deck of this yacht is spotless and new.  Suddenly,
with a start, you realize that the ship has no mast, and no sails.

name: A Fishing Ship
description:
Huge nets strung up above you drip foul-smelling water down onto the deck
where you stand.  The entire vessel reeks of fish, though the brackish water
of the bilges and the dozens of barrels of chum gladly contribute their odors
to the stench as well.  A mop and bucket stand to the side, near the rail, but
only as a token gesture;  the ground is covered with fish guts, heads,
eyeballs, tails, fins, gills, and several bits which seem not to have come
from fish at all.  The whole ship creaks and whines in protest as the waves
tip it back and forth, but miraculously, it remains whole.  A mooring rope as
thick as a human's arm has been draped around a piling on the bow of the ship,
and its newness clashes with everything else on board.

name: A Large Vessel
description:
Easily the largest ship on the docks at the moment, this vessel's main mast
reaches above the thirty foot high cliff to the north and pokes a good way
into visibility from the streets of the city up above.  Sixty feet from stem
to stern, its purpose isn't clear, but its excellent construction and massive
size lead you to believe it is of military or some other official origins.
The ship is obviously quite old, as the floorboards have a significant amount
of grime packed between them, and the corners of the deck are far from
spotless.  However, it is in a very good state of repair.  The rigging is
brand new, no frayed rope or splintered wood has been allowed to go
unreplaced.  It sways almost imperceptibly in the waves of the harbor, its
sheer size stabilizing it nicely.

name: The Red Harbor
description:
The crimson cliffside to the north, thrust up by the earth and scorched
with its hue by the hand of the gods, has surely taken a hand in coloring
this water.  All around you, swirling currents and breaking waves all take on
a perverse bloodlike hue.  To the west, boats toss up and down in the swells
of the sea while moored to the docks of Cimar, and to the south, the small
inlet at which the Talis River meets the sea opens up into a huge ocean.  You
see a few boats paddling and sailing about here, near the shore, but their
numbers thin considerably as you peer out to sea.  Looking down, you find
that you cannot see far enough into the ruddy red water even to tell how far
you're seeing.

name: The Main Chamber
description:
A strange room indeed.  Some unseen light source allows you to see that
the walls, ceiling and floor are of the purest white marble, perfectly flat
and featureless.  A single comfortable-looking chair adorns the room,
placed directly in the center.  It beckons to you silently, and you can
almost hear its unspoken command to sit.  Tearing your eyes away from its
ashen contours, its sleek black arms and base, you turn around to find that
the exit behind you has disappeared completely.  In its place is a tiny
brass plate, bolted in place and inscribed upon in very tiny print.

name: The Royal Bedchamber
description:
Amazingly, this bed chamber is more elaborately and intricately decorated
than the main body of the palace.  Interior to the building, and indeed,
interior to the foothills the building is embedded in, it has no windows and
no natural light.  It would be quite possible to sleep for days without
realizing the sun has come and gone in such a room as this.  A chandelier
hangs overhead with softly flickering candles, dripping tiny puddles of wax
into gold-plated dishes beneath each light.  The gilding covering nearly
everything in this room reflects the orange light and creates the impression
of being inside a gold nugget.

name: The Outskirts of Cimar
description:
Standing here, beside Cimar's glorious outer wall, you are awestruck by
its sheer size and perfection.  Not a single foot of it has degraded or
begun to crumble, and its gleaming white length stretches off to the north
as far as you can see.  South of here, it turns west out of sight along the
cliff at the edge of the ocean.  Towering above you, the top of the wall is
a dizzying sight.  Through the gate to the west, you see the inside of the
city, and to the east, you see the Old Southern Road.

name: The Hive's Maw
description:
The rough walls of this cavernous tunnel look as though they were scooped
directly from the soft earth and brittle stone of this area.  Jagged shards
of sandy rock spike their way in from the perimeter toward you, long shadows
making the shallow penetrations appear much larger than they truly are. 
Water dribbles down the walls, and the floor is muddy and slick; strange,
gashing marks slice through the floor, as though an army of swords has
marched through.

name: Within the Hive's Main Chamber
description:
An eerie hollow light illuminates this deep chamber, casting an odd
pallor over all proceedings within.  Piles of dirt and stone, piles of
vegetation, and piles of rusty armor and body parts litter the ground.  A
terrible clattering sound fills the air, pervading your senses and driving
thought from your mind.  Acrid pools of liquid here and there cast a searing
stench into the atmosphere, and your eyes water uncontrollably.

name: The Core
description:
You have breached the sanctum sanctorum of this insect lair, and here
lies the Hive Queen's bedding of flesh.  Torn bodies and blood-soaked cloth
are arranged in a large circle at the center of the chamber, some of which
you could conceivably recognize as pieces of those who fell in the defense
of Cimar far above.  Each wall of this cavernous dwelling is filled with
pockets and holes, each of which is in turn filled with dozens of fist-sized
eggs.

name: The Western Edge of the Cavern
The Northwestern Edge of the Cavern
The Northern Edge of the Cavern
The Southern Edge of the Cavern
The Center of A Meeting Hall
Connecting room
description: This room is going to be used to connect the cavern entrance to side of Mt Cim

name: Entrance to the Depths
description:
Digging deeply into the side of the massive mountain, a large hole tunnels
its way inward towards the heart of the ancient stone monolith. Cool air
wafts from the interior of the caverns, leaving a musty smell in its wake.
North lies the cavern entrance, while south leads back towards the plains.
East and west are blocked by the walls of the mountain cleft.

name: Inside the Cave Mouth
description:
Breaching the side of the mountain, a cool crisp breeze rushes at you. In
its wake, it leaves a mixture of smells that remind you of unwashed bodies
and mold. The air in the immediate area seems to be reaching a stable,
cool temperature as well. Even this short distance into the mountain, you
already have the sense of thousands of tons of stone, rock and dirt
overhead. Southward, a faint light glimmers and you can almost hear the
birds chirp, while eastward the tunnel continues it's ancient trek inward.

name: A Bend in the Tunnel
description:
Following the path intently, you come across a sharp turn. South, the air
seems to be a bit fresher, if only a little. East, the darkness consumes
the area completly.

name: Inside the Caverns
description:
The atmosphere has reached a cool, consistant temperature here. The dark
has completly engulfed everything as well. The tunnel is big enough for
two to three titans standing abreast, leaving enough space for plenty of
elbow room. To the north, the tunnel slowly continues its journey inward,
while the west a faint light glimmers.

name: Before a massive cave, on the mountainside
description:
Barely managing to clumb the enormous mountainside, you seem to stumble
on to an enormous creation, set in cold stone.  Before you is a magnificent
sight, a massive hole has been torn into the rockface of this mountain,
forming a dark cave.  The foliage which surrounds the mountain seems to be
parted and destroyed around the cave, giving it an eerie, bare appereance.

name: Within a slightly-lit cave
description:
Small rays of sunlight beam in from the south, shedding light to a small
portion of the cave.  The rocks here range from a smooth gray to a slightly
dusted black color.  Though not a single drop of moisture can be seen along
the walls.  The ground below your feet is rather rough, it is quite obvious
that few, if any men, have passed through here recently.  The tunnel
continues to the north, and exits to the south.

name: Within a dark cave
description:
It's pitch-black in here, and the only faint bit of light you can see,
shines from the south.  The rocks are almost undetectable, but carry the
same texture and color, a smooth pale gray, to a dusted almost coal color. 
Not a drop of moisture can be seen as these tunnels look very bare.  The
tunnel continues to the north and south.

name: Before a small intersection, within a dark cave
description:
Not a strand of light is here, though you begin to feel as though you
are being watched in the cold, dark cave.  At times, you seem to hear a
whisper or chuckle, though it all sounds so faint, that it seems like your
mind is playing tricks on you.  The rocks around here are a bit darker in
shade then the one's seen before the entrance of the cave.  As you feel the
cold, rock surface, you seem to spot a small marking on the wall of the rock
face, it's small in design, below it point two arrows, one to the east, and
the other to the west.

name: Along a thin tunnel, within a dark cave
description:
This tunnel is extremely thin, though much like the rest of the cave,
it's very high, the size of at least three adult human males.  The ground
below you is a little smoother, leading you to believe that someone has been
through here recently.  Twisted, jagged rocks protrude from the walls, it's
as through something is warning you, to pass no further.

name: Along a thin tunnel, within a dark cave
description:
This tunnel is extremely thin, though much like the rest of the cave,
it's very high, the size of at least three adult human males.  The ground
below you is a little smoother, leading you to believe that someone has been
through here recently.  The thin tunnel twists into a sudden curve, you may
go north deeper into the tunnel, or back west.

name: Along an odd tunnel, within a dark cave
description:
You stand along an odd tunnel, it's a complete semi-circle to every
extent.  You can only imagine that some form of sorcery was used to shape
it.  Dark rocks, all around you, seem to be taking on a reddish-hue.  The
air around you seems quite humid.  The tunnel continues to the north.  To
the south, the tunnel begins to grow thinner.

name: Along an odd tunnel, within a cave
description:
You stand along an odd tunnel, it's a complete semi-circle to every
extent.  You can only imagine that some form of sorcery was used to shape
it.  Dark rocks, all around you, seem to be taking on a reddish-hue.  The
air around you seems quite humid.  The tunnel continues to the north and
south.

name: Before a sharp turn, in the dark cave
description:
You stand before a sharp turn in the tunnel.  A large, jagged wall is
before you, it's entire surface marked with etchings of odd designs and
runes.  The rocks here seem to take on a reddish-hue, emitting the warm air
around you.  Something eerie is about, you feel as though you are being
watched again.  The tunnel twists to the east and heads back south.

name: Along a very small tunnel, in the dark cave
description:
Fit for only the smallest of creatures, anything taller then a imp or
sidhe will be forced to duck or crawl.  Unlike the majority of rocks seen at
the entrance of the cave, here they emit a faint orange glow.  The tunnel
streches to the east and west.

name: Along a very small tunnel, in the dark cave
description:
Fit for only the smallest of creatures, anything taller then a imp or
sidhe will be forced to duck or crawl.  Unlike the majority of rocks seen at
the entrance of the cave, here they emit a faint orange glow.  To the
northern wall of the tunnel, some rocks seem to be broken, chipped and
missing, leading you to believe that their may be something beyond the
obvious.  The faint sound of water dripping, echoes from the east.  The
tunnel continues to the east and west.

name: A dark pool of water, before an enormous cavern
description:
A small stream of fresh, mountain water, trickles into a pool that has
been freshly dug into the eastern side of the wall.  As the cold, fresh
water touches the pool it turns ebony.  The walls of the cave are a deep,
warm, ebony... they are set in a intricate pattern along the southern
portion of the tunnel, circling around a massive hole, which leads into some
hideous cavern.  Towards the south the faint sound of chuckling and laughter
can be heard.

name: Within a cavern
description:
Small, almost devilish creatures swarm about you, everywhere, they seem
to be quite unkempt... rags and trash, litter the ground.  They seem to live
here with delight, painting strange, yet horrific images on the walls, some
of which depicting cities, being ravaged, which you recognize.  These small
creatures seem to thrive in this cavern.  The cavern continues to the east,
west, and south, though exits through the north.

name: Within a cavern
description:
This cavern is filthy, and littered with rags and trash.  Something odd
catches your eye, towards the north-western edge of the wall hangs a
deceased sidhe, tormented and skinned, set up for some sort of game
involving darts.  These devilish creature's are all about you, but they only
seem to eye you curiously, as though they hold back, in fear, to strike at
you for entering their home.

name: Within a cavern
description:
Creeping further into the hideous cavern, you notice that the imps seem
to have no care in all of Shadar about their appearance.  Filthy, smug grins
seem to be permanently plastered to their small, petite faces.  Though, they
obviously lack the morale, and spirit to do anything about you invading
their privacy.  The cavern continues to the north and east.

name: Within a cavern
description:
These small, hideous creatures pester you as a rodent would, following
your every movement.  Gathering in packs, watching you move about, studying
each footstep carefully.  Garbage piled to your ankles is all about, but
imps just don't seem to care, indulging in this disgusting sight, they
thrive in this waste.  The cavern continues to the east, west and north.

name: Within a cavern
description:
These small, hideous creatures pester you as a rodent would, following
your every movement.  Gathering in packs, watching you move about, studying
each footstep carefully.  Garbage piled to your ankles is all about, but
imps just don't seem to care, indulging in this disgusting sight, they
thrive in this waste.  The cavern continues to the north and west.

name: Within a cavern
description:
A small part of the imps culture can be seen here, strange paintings
adorn the east wall, paintings of a small city, being invaded underground,
through what seem to be the sewers.  Though still, the same disgusting
scene, of trash tossed about can be seen here, like every other portion of
the cavern.  To the south and west, the cavern continues.

name: A hidden passage, in the dark cave
description:
Stumbling through the rocks in the wall, you manage to find yourself
before a dark passage, in the caves.  Obviousley man-made, the ground is
paved well, stretching north, for atleast a few leagues.  The rocks around
here, are squared and well-kempt, carrying a smooth texture, and a lovely,
granite color.  The faint sound of footsteps can be heard all around you. 
The passage continues to the north.

name: A hidden passage, in the dark cave
description:
The passage streches as far as the eye can see, snaking it's way to the
north, obviousley fashioned by some, well-experienced race.  It seems to
slope downward just a bit, with each footstep, it's as though this passage
takes you, below the surface of Shadar.  The faint sound of footsteps grows
louder to the north, it's as though something very large is here.  The
passage continues to the north and south.

name: A small clearing, along the hidden passage, in the dark cave
description:
You seem to have stumbeled unto a small clearing, along the hidden
passage.  Dark ebony stones have been set along the walls, though as you
peer ahead, the passage seems to grow darker and darker.  The air is humid,
and the faint sound of footsteps can be heard all around you, you feel quite
certain, that something very large lurk's in this part of the cave.  The
passage continues to the north and south.

name: Deep within a hidden passage, in the dark cave
description:
Rather thin compared to the majority of tunnels found in this cave, this
part of the passage seems to twist on and on.  Though just as you begin to
walk through, taking little notice of your surroundings, you manage to spot
something strange on the rockface.  It seems that a few stones on the
western side of the passage are broken and cracked.  Humidity is very fierce
around this part of the passage.  The passage continues to the north, and
leads to a small clearing, towards the south.

name: Along a secret passage, in the dark cave
description:
You seem to have found a secret passage in the dark cave.  Bits of broken
stone litter the ground, though unlike the dark stones seen earlier, these
one emit a gentle, orange light.  Taking in a deep breath of air, your lungs
begin to burn, the air around you is disgustingly humid.  Towards the west,
you hear the echo of metal being smashed against metal, as though someone or
something is hard at work.

name: Before a fiery cavern, in the dark cave
description:
You stand before an enormous cavern, filled with fire.  The towering
pillars of flame, seen inside, seem to light this part of the passage.  The
stones around you are unlike any other's you have seen before, they range
from a dark emerald, to a majestic crimson in color.  The sound of metal
being smashed against metal resonates all around you.  The passage continues
to the east, and enter's a colossal cavern towards the west.

name: Inside a fiery cavern, in the dark cave
description:
The cavern is simply amazing... crimson stalactites hang from the ceiling
of the cavern, while set at all corners are enormous, pillars of flame.  The
cavern is well lit, and seems to be the home of some enormous titan. 
Massive hammers, thrice the size of an ordinary one you've seen hang along
the walls, towards the north, you can hear the sound of metal, crashing
against metal, grow louder and louder.

name: The forge of Ur'Tazi
description:
An anvil, crafted from a smooth, ebony metal is before you.  Standing
just behind it, is a massive titan, twice the size of any titan you have
ever seen in Shadar.  Along the walls of this cavern, hang assorted tools,
used by a blacksmith.  Each tool, being at least thrice the size of any
ordinary tool a blacksmith would use.  Assorted weapon's and armor hang
along the walls of the forge, though they each are so large, that only a
titan could hope to use them.

name: Along a secret passage, in the dark cave
description:
The atmosphere around you, suddenly grows darker... a cold wind begins to
sweep through the tunnel.  The rocks here are jagged, twisted, and
deformed... ebony stalactites hang from the ceiling of the passage.  Sloping
further and further down, you can only hope that this passage takes you to
some place of safety.  The passage continues to the north and south.

name: Along a secret passage, in the dark cave
description:
The air around you is cold... yet not a drop of moisture can be seen
along the rough, jagged walls of the passage.  Ebony stalactites hang from
the ceiling, their sharp points, hanging by little more then a thread.  The
passage seems to be curving towards the north, leading deeper and deeper
into the cave.  Down and down the passage etches, taking you deeper and
deeper, below the surface of Shalar.  The passage continues to the north and
south.

name: The Foyer of a Great Mausoleum
The Foyer of a Great Mausoleum
The Entrance to a Great Mausoleum
The Foyer of a Great Mausoleum
The Foyer of a Great Mausoleum

description:
The sound of dripping water ripples through the stale darkness of this
stone corridor, accompanied by the sickly sweet scent of death.  Brown
streaks of mildew cover the gray granite walls along with a great number of
rusted and empty torch-holders, which obviously haven't been put to use for
quite some time.  Chunks of rock litter the ground, long since having rotted
off of the walls and the ceilings.  The corridor continues to the north and
to the east, each direction equally dark.

name: A Damp Section of a Crumbling Corridor
description:
Shallow puddles are scattered about the corridor here, giving rise to the
sour odor of mildew.  Water drips at an uneven pace from the ceiling to feed
these foul puddles.  Rusty chains hang ominously from the walls, some still
closed and locked, hauntingly enough.  Chunks of wet rock and mud litter the
ground, long since having rotted off of the walls and ceiling.  The corridor
continues to the east and west, and a heavy iron door is set into the
northern wall.

name: A Crumbling Corridor
description:
A bright circle of light is set into the ground here, illuminating the
pitch-black dungeon around it.  The sound of dripping water ripples through
the stale darkness of this stone corridor, accompanied by the sickly sweet
scent of death.  Brown streaks of mildew cover the gray granite walls along
with a great number of rusted and empty torch-holders, which obviously
haven't been put to use for quite some time.  Chunks of rock litter the

stone corridor, accompanied by the sickly sweet scent of death.  Brown
streaks of mildew cover the gray granite walls along with a great number of
rusted and empty torch-holders, which obviously haven't been put to use for
quite some time.  Chunks of rock litter the ground, long since having rotted

coming from the south.

description:
The sound of dripping water ripples through the stale darkness of this
stone corridor, accompanied by the sickly sweet scent of death.  Brown
streaks of mildew cover the gray granite walls along with a great number of
rusted and empty torch-holders, which obviously haven't been put to use for
quite some time.  Chunks of rock litter the ground, long since having rotted
off of the walls and the ceilings.  The corridor continues to the north and
south.  A heavy iron door is set into the eastern wall.

name: A Narrow Crypt
description:
The horrid stenches of dust and stale death assault your senses.  The air
here is unfit for mortal breath.  Clay urns line the walls, each set into
its own small alcove.  A sarcophagus sits in the middle of the room...
empty.

name: A Narrow Crypt
description:

here is unfit for mortal breath.  Clay urns line the walls, each set into
its own small alcove.  A sarcophagus sits in the middle of the room...
empty.

here is unfit for mortal breath.  Clay urns line the walls, each set into
its own small alcove.  A sarcophagus sits in the middle of the room...
empty.

name: The Entrance to the Corrupted Fane
description:
Cold, hard silence sits heavily on this barren room.  A dim light shines
from several candles on the walls.  The room is exquisitely clean, with not
a bit of dirt, dust, or anything else on the walls or the floor.  A strange
feeling accompanies the emptiness in this room.  No living creatures stir
and nothing breaks the extreme silence.  Despite the nausea in your stomach,
you feel drawn to continue forward.

name: The Corrupted Fane
description:
Harsh red light floods your vision, pouring in from the south.  Even the
pale gray of the walls seems to reflect the hellish light.  The floor is
covered with an intricate mosaic, displaying a large hellhound.  Intense
cold seems to accompany the red light as it rushes in, illuminating a
shadowy alcove in the northern wall.  Though devoid of all life, the room
reeks with the stench of rotting flesh.  The eastern wall is home to a
painting depicting a cave of small minotaurs.  As the cold continues to fill
your body, you feel pulled to the south.

name: The Grand Altar
description:
Glowing a fierce red that illuminates the entire room, an intricate altar
rises directly from the floor.  The walls here bear no candles, but glow
with the same blood-red light.  Behind the altar, corpses seemingly human
rot on thick wooden pikes.  The aroma of death is palpable in the air,
enticing you into its sickly sweet embrace.  Covering the floor completely
is a pool of blood, gleaming in the light from the altar.  A dripping sound
draws your attention towards a ledge above the eastern wall.  Rows of teeth
meet your gaze as you look into the mouths of voracious hellhounds leaning
over the ledge, blood slowly dripping from their teeth.  Embossed into the
southern wall is a horned visage, grinning sardonically.  Its eyes glow with
a fire brighter than the altar.  The face belongs to a minotaur or a demon,
but you cannot tell which.  Only the blood-red light escapes this room,
rushing to the north.

name: The Corrupted Fane
description:
The two walls of this room contrast starkly, the western covered with
weapons and the southern covered by a bookshelf.  Weapons of every
classification, each dripping with blood, hang from the western wall.  Its
racks contain freshly-bloodied swords, axes, flails, whips, and several
implements you can only imagine are used for torture alone.  Seeming far
more mundane than the western wall, the southern wall is mostly covered by a
large bookshelf.  What you can see of it is inscribed with strange magical
runes and icons.  Covering the shelf are hundreds of books and tomes, their
paper yellowed with age.  The books seem free of dust, though a smeared
reddish substance is evident on many of them.  The combined smells of aged
paper and fresh corpses assault your nose.  As you look over the room, the
distinct taste of blood fills your mouth.  A strange cold fills you, coaxing
you eastward.

Haaar

name: Before the Gates of Cimar
description:
The massive Eastern Arch of Cimar towers before you, a monument to mortal
ingenuity and testament to the wealth of glorious Cimar.  Reaching well over
forty feet towards the skies, the arch supports massive blocks of granite
that reach even higher.  Beyond the equally massive wooden gates to the
west, stretches a broad thoroughfare that runs through the heart of Cimar. 
The clamor of restless activity emanates from the west, rolling out across
the worn cobblestone roads of the city.  To the east, the road runs between
two narrow walls before widening and disappearing into the horizon.

name: A Narrow-Walled Avenue
description:
The path is narrow here, cramped between the walls of massive guard
towers that loom to the north and south.  Armored silhouettes patrol the
ramparts above, and an occasional glint of steel is visible through one of
the myriad arrowslits that line the side of each tower.  The walls of Cimar
and the great Eastern Arch loom to the west, while the road narrows
considerable and stretches eastward toward the horizon, flanked by rows of
trees on either side.

name: Within the Dense Foliage
description:
The forest around you is remarkably dense here, with rows of trees
reaching up to blot out all but tiny slivers of sky.  The presence of
wildlife surrounds you, from the faint chirping of crickets, to the mossy
earth beneath your feet, to the blurs of motion at the edge of your field of
vision.  Though the woods become impenetrably dense to the north and west,
the forest stretches eastward, and through breaks in the trees to the south,
you can clearly make out the beginning of the Cimarrite Causeway.  Amazing,
how nature can be so lush and vibrant mere feet away from the stamp of
civilization.

name: Approaching the Walls of Cimar
description:
The road here is broad, leading westward toward the towering walls of
Cimar, where the path narrows and runs between two guard towers.  Eastward,
the road stretches on well into the distance, widening further as it carves
a clean swath from the surrounding forests.  Evenly-spaced rows of trees
line the road on the northern and southern sides here, the gaps revealing a
surprisingly lush verdant sprawl.  Weeds and assorted other small brush peek
through the odd space between the cobblestones here, serving as a reminder
of the limits of mortal encroachment upon nature.

name: Within the Dense Foliage
description:
The forest around you is remarkably dense here, with rows of trees
reaching up to blot out all but tiny slivers of sky.  The presence of
wildlife surrounds you, from the faint chirping of crickets, to the mossy
earth beneath your feet, to the blurs of motion at the edge of your field of
vision.  Though the woods become impenetrably dense to the west, the forest
stretches to the east and south, and through breaks in the trees to the
north, you can clearly make out the beginning of the Cimarrite Causeway. 
South of here, another road is somewhat visible.

name: Within the Dense Foliage
description:
The forest around you is remarkably dense here, with rows of trees
reaching up to blot out all but tiny slivers of sky.  The presence of
wildlife surrounds you, from the faint chirping of crickets, to the mossy
earth beneath your feet, to the blurs of motion at the edge of your field of
vision.  The forest stretches to the south, east, and west, and through
breaks in the trees to the north, you can clearly make out the beginning of
the Cimarrite Causeway.  Amazing, how nature can be so lush and vibrant mere
feet away from the stamp of civilization.

name: Along the Cimarrite Causeway
description:
This broad cobblestone road, known far and wide as the Great Shalaran
Road, has been paved and re-paved many times through the centuries.  To the
north and south, the sizeable forests of the region grow wild, deciduous and
evergreen trees both intermingling and creating a field of patchwork green. 
The road upon which you stand runs straight east and west here, between the
trade centers of Cimar and Melcene.

name: Within the Dense Foliage
description:
The forest around you is remarkably dense here, with rows of trees
reaching up to blot out all but tiny slivers of sky.  The presence of
wildlife surrounds you, from the faint chirping of crickets, to the mossy
earth beneath your feet, to the blurs of motion at the edge of your field of
vision.  The forest stretches to the north, east, and west, and through
breaks in the trees to the south, you can clearly make out the beginning of
the Cimarrite Causeway.  Amazing, how nature can be so lush and vibrant mere
feet away from the stamp of civilization.

name: Within a Dark Forest
description:
The forest around you is remarkably dense here, with rows of trees
reaching up to blot out all but tiny slivers of sky.  The presence of
wildlife surrounds you, from the faint chirping of crickets, to the mossy
earth beneath your feet, to the blurs of motion at the edge of your field of
vision.  The forest stretches southward, and through the trees to the east,
you can make out a trail cut through the foliage.

name: A Path Through the Forest
description:
The forest around you is remarkably dense here, with rows of trees
reaching up to blot out all but tiny slivers of sky.  The presence of
wildlife surrounds you, from the faint chirping of crickets, to the mossy
earth beneath your feet, to the blurs of motion at the edge of your field of
vision.  A small trail here widens out somewhat to the north, where the
general mood and hue of the forest is much darker.

name: A Path Through the Foliage
description:
The forest around you is remarkably dense here, with rows of trees
reaching up to blot out all but tiny slivers of sky.  The presence of
wildlife surrounds you, from the faint chirping of crickets, to the mossy
earth beneath your feet, to the blurs of motion at the edge of your field of
vision.  A small trail here continues off to the north, where the general
mood and hue of the forest is much darker.

name: Along the Cimarrite Causeway
description:
This broad cobblestone road, known far and wide as the Great Shalaran
Road, has been paved and re-paved many times through the centuries.  To the
north and south, the sizeable forests of the region grow wild, deciduous and
evergreen trees both intermingling and creating a field of patchwork green. 
The road upon which you stand runs straight east and west here, between the
trade centers of Cimar and Melcene.

name: A Trail Through the Trees
description:
Framed to the east and west by very dense foliage, this worn trail leads
between the Cimarrite Causeway to the north and the Old Southern Road in the
opposite direction.  The dirt trail itself, tamped into hard earth by many
passing feet, lets up very little dust as you pass.  The shade offered by
the huge, leafy branches above you is most welcome during the heat of the
day, and yet casts an almost eerie pallor over the area during the moonlit
night.  Cobble beckons to the north and south, deep forest to the east and
west.

name: Within the Dense Foliage
description:
The forest around you is remarkably dense here, with rows of trees
reaching up to blot out all but tiny slivers of sky.  The presence of
wildlife surrounds you, from the faint chirping of crickets, to the mossy
earth beneath your feet, to the blurs of motion at the edge of your field of
vision.  The forest stretches to the south, east, and west, and through
breaks in the trees to the north, you can clearly make out the beginning of
the Cimarrite Causeway.  Amazing, how nature can be so lush and vibrant mere
feet away from the stamp of civilization.

name: Along the Cimarrite Causeway
description:
This broad cobblestone road, known far and wide as the Great Shalaran
Road, has been paved and re-paved many times through the centuries.  To the
north and south, the sizeable forests of the region grow wild, deciduous and
evergreen trees both intermingling and creating a field of patchwork green. 
The road upon which you stand runs straight east and west here, between the
trade centers of Cimar and Melcene.

name: At the Edge of a Swamp
description:
The ground here has become rather wet and soggy, drowning most of the
shorter varieties of grass that grow nearby.  A few dark, moss-covered trees
spring up here and there, all emanating a mildewy stench.  Many more spring
up to the south, where a humid haze settles about the area.  To the north
lies the relative safety and comfort of the Great Shalaran Road.

name: At a Traveler's Camp
description:
A small lean-to constructed of a large burlap sheet draped over the low
branch of a pine tree occupies the northern edge of this tiny clearing.  A
crackling fire at the center of the area pops and fizzles, sending glowing
sparks upward in a dancing spiral.  The leafy branches wave and sway in the
rising heat and smoke from the campfire, resulting in an almost dreamlike
ocean-wave effect... you fight off the urge to lie back and stare at the
sky.  To all sides but the south, trees grow very closely together, and you
cannot see what lies beyond.  South of here, some dense foliage grows at the
edge of the Great Shalaran Road.

name: Within the Dense Foliage
description:
The forest around you is remarkably dense here, with rows of trees
reaching up to blot out all but tiny slivers of sky.  The presence of
wildlife surrounds you, from the faint chirping of crickets, to the mossy
earth beneath your feet, to the blurs of motion at the edge of your field of
vision.  The forest stretches to the east and west, but the trees to the
north grow too closely for you to pass between them.  Through breaks in the
trees to the south, you can clearly make out the Great Shalaran Road.  From
the north, a few wisps of campfire smoke drift in on the breeze.

name: On Marshy Ground
description:
Thick mud sloshes beneath you, little creatures languishing in its sloppy
filth.  Trees jut out of the ground here and there, thin vines hanging down,
nearly touching the stubborn and scummy grayish-brown mud.  To the north,
you can see a road, while to the west the marshy ground begins to turn into
a full-fledged swamp.

name: On Marshy Ground
description:
Thick mud sloshes beneath you, little creatures languishing in its sloppy
filth.  Trees jut out of the ground here and there, thin vines hanging down,
nearly touching the stubborn and scummy grayish-brown mud.  To the north and
to the east, the marshy ground continues.

name: On Marshy Ground
description:
Thick mud sloshes beneath you, little creatures languishing in its sloppy
filth.  Trees jut out of the ground here and there, thin vines hanging down,
nearly touching the stubborn and scummy grayish-brown mud.  The trees here
begin to become thicker, and the ground a bit less marshy... It's still a
marsh though.  To the north, you can make out the Great Shalaran Road, while
to the east the short, gnarled trees become even thicker.

name: Along the Great Shalaran Road
description:

south and west, the sizeable forests of the region grow wild, deciduous and
evergreen trees both intermingling and creating a field of patchwork green.

stretching between the trade centers of Cimar and Melcene.

vision.  The forest stretches to the west, but the trees to the north and
east grow too closely for you to pass between them.  Through breaks in the
trees to the south, you can clearly make out the Great Shalaran Road.

name: Amidst a Copse
description:
Thick shrubs and small trees grow up to about fifteen feet here, there is
the occasional breeze that rustles the branches and leaves, the rich smell
of foliage fills your nose and carries a slight scent of pollen.  At the
base of all the shrubs and small trees are small animal paths, about three
to four feet high and well used.  The ground is covered with dead material
fallen from the surrounding plant life, in some areas where the trails are
often used the ground is worn bare to the compacted dirt underneath.

name: Along the Great Shalaran Road
description:
This broad cobblestone road, known far and wide as the Great Shalaran
Road, has been paved and re-paved many times through the centuries.  To the
north and south, the sizeable forests of the region grow wild, deciduous and
evergreen trees both intermingling and creating a field of patchwork green. 
The road upon which you stand runs east and west here, stretching between
the trade centers of Cimar and Melcene.

name: At the Edge of a Stunted Forest
description:
The ground here is damp and soft, providing poor footing for the tiny
pine trees that grow out from the ground here.  A number of these trees are
leaning in one direction or another, due to this.  This area is surprisingly
quiet for one of such an untamed nature.

name: At the Edge of a Stunted Forest
description:
Stunted and twisted trees are scattered about the wild ground here.  A
strange silence fills the air, unbroken by the traffic that traverses the
Great Shalaran Road that abruptly interrupts this forest to the north.  The
forest continues to the east and west.

name: At the Edge of a Darken Wood
description:
This area of the forest is dry compared to the marshy, swamp-like ground
to the west.  South of the road, it must somehow get less light than other
places in this region... for this entire area is covered in pitch darkness. 
The trees are black, the ground is scorched dark brown, and even the leaves
above you are such a deep shade of green that they seem to swallow light. 
Very little animal activity rises up in this area, and the surroundings are
very still and quiet.  To the north, you see the light of the Great Shalaran
Road between the trees, and to the east and west, the forest continues.

name: A Trampled Path
description:
This path is fairly narrow, held in place by two walls of solid
vegetation to the east and west.  The floor of the forest here is full of
vegetation, but has been trampled and stomped completely flat.  Broken plant
stalks and random petals strewn about season the ground with a mix of
detritus.  To the north, the path winds back toward the darkened woods near
the Great Shalaran Road.  South of here, the path curves around into deep
places within the forest which you cannot see.

description:

detritus.  To the west, the path winds back toward the darkened woods near

hastily-abandoned campsite.

name: An Abandoned Camp
description:
The firepit here has been kicked over and drowned beneath a tiny lake of
water.  A swath of glowing embers to one side indicates that this campsite
has not been in its current state for very long.  Through the smoke and soot
in the air, the light from above stabs downward, patterning itself after the
canopy of vegetation overhead.  A twig snaps, a leaf rustles, and suddenly
every sound around you is reminiscent of an approaching bandit.  Back to the
north, the worn and flattened path of dead vegetation leads toward the open
road, and safety.

name: Before a Shaded Spring
description:
The thick, gnarled tangles have parted, revealing a small clearing; some
larger trees have found root here and managed to survive.  The air is more
moist here, and the quiet yet soothing noises from the spring come to your
ears, along with the occasional bird call.  Around the edge of the spring is
a line of large rocks which holds back the water making the spring deeper. 
Over time, the gaps in between the rocks have been filled with soil and
plants have taken hold.  A weird assortment of long grasses sprout outward
over the edges of the spring.

name: Deep Within a Thicket
description:
Thick, gnarled tangles twist and climb out of the ground, which is not
even visible now, due to the amount of wild plant growth.  Thick yet wispy
spider webs connect in many places in the tangle, the new permanent home to
many bugs native to the microcosm that is this thicket.  You stand now so
deep within the knotted thicket that the sky and road are no longer visible.

name: Within a Thicket
description:
Thick, gnarled tangles twist and climb out of the ground, which is not
even visible now, due to the amount of wild plant growth.  Thick yet wispy
spider webs connect in many places in the tangle, the new permanent home to
many bugs native to the microcosm that is this thicket.

name: Along the Great Shalaran Road
description:
This broad cobblestone road, known far and wide as the Great Shalaran
Road, has been paved and re-paved many times through the centuries.  To the
north and west, the sizeable forests of the region grow wild, deciduous and
evergreen trees both intermingling and creating a field of patchwork green. 
The road upon which you stand runs east and bends south here, stretching
between the trade centers of Cimar and Melcene.

name: Along the Great Shalaran Road
description:
This broad cobblestone road, known far and wide as the Great Shalaran
Road, has been paved and re-paved many times through the centuries.  To the
east and west, the sizeable forests of the region grow wild, deciduous and
evergreen trees both intermingling and creating a field of patchwork green. 
The road upon which you stand runs north and south here, stretching between
the trade centers of Cimar and Melcene.

name: Along the Great Shalaran Road
description:
This broad cobblestone road, known far and wide as the Great Shalaran
Road, has been paved and re-paved many times through the centuries.  To the
south and east, the sizeable forests of the region grow wild, deciduous and
evergreen trees both intermingling and creating a field of patchwork green. 
The road upon which you stand runs west and curves to the north here,
stretching between the trade centers of Cimar and Melcene.  To the east, an
overgrown road continues on toward a tiny inn.

name: At the Edge of a Darken Wood
description:
This area of the forest is dry compared to the marshy, swamp-like ground
to the west.  South of the road, it must somehow get less light than other
places in this region... for this entire area is covered in pitch darkness. 
The trees are black, the ground is scorched dark brown, and even the leaves
above you are such a deep shade of green that they seem to swallow light. 
Very little animal activity rises up in this area, and the surroundings are
very still and quiet.  To the north, you see the light of the Great Shalaran
Road between the trees, and to the east and west, the forest continues.

name: At the Edge of a Darken Wood
description:
This area of the forest is dry compared to the marshy, swamp-like ground
to the west.  South of the road, it must somehow get less light than other
places in this region... for this entire area is covered in pitch darkness. 
The trees are black, the ground is scorched dark brown, and even the leaves
above you are such a deep shade of green that they seem to swallow light. 
Very little animal activity rises up in this area, and the surroundings are
very still and quiet.  To the north, you see an overgrown road between the
trees, and to the east and west, the forest continues.

name: At the Edge of a Darken Wood
description:
This area of the forest is dry compared to the marshy, swamp-like ground
to the west.  South of the road, it must somehow get less light than other
places in this region... for this entire area is covered in pitch darkness. 
The trees are black, the ground is scorched dark brown, and even the leaves
above you are such a deep shade of green that they seem to swallow light. 
Very little animal activity rises up in this area, and the surroundings are
very still and quiet.  To the north, you see an overgrown road between the
trees, and to the west, the forest continues.

name: On an Overgrown Trail
description:
The path beneath you is barely visible through the vines and wild grass
which have grown to cover it.  To the north, a wild thicket grows, through
which you can just barely make out the gleaming Melcene Way.  West of here,
the Great Shalaran Road stretches off toward Cimar.  To your south, the
woods grow dark and foreboding, and barely any light escapes to tell your
eyes the tale.  This road, mostly overgrown as it is, continues to the east
toward a tiny inn.  All around you, the sounds of wild birds fluttering
through the air and singing to one another crackle through the still air
like a bolt of lightning.

name: Before an Abandoned Inn
description:
As you might have suspected, approaching it via the horribly overgrown
path to the west, this inn is utterly abandoned.  Cracked windows and
shattered furniture are well-lit due to the mostly missing roof.  The bar
remains in an almost religious pristine condition, however, and a few of the
bottles behind it have somehow not been broken.  All around you, clear as
day is the evidence of vandalizing thieves stashing loot beneath the floor,
trampling wayward beasts confused at the lack of a path or even trees, and
many thousand wild birds unceremoniously leaving offerings before departing.

name: On an Overgrown Trail
description:
The path beneath you is barely visible through the vines and wild grass
which have grown to cover it.  To the north, a wild thicket grows, through
which you can just barely make out the gleaming Melcene Way.  West of here,
the Great Shalaran Road stretches off toward Cimar.  To your south, the
woods grow dark and foreboding, and barely any light escapes to tell your
eyes the tale.  This road, mostly overgrown as it is, continues to the east
toward a tiny inn.  All around you, the sounds of wild birds fluttering
through the air and singing to one another crackle through the still air
like a bolt of lightning.

name: Within a Thicket
description:
Thick, gnarled tangles twist and climb out of the ground, which is not
even visible now, due to the amount of wild plant growth.  Thick yet wispy
spider webs connect in many places in the tangle, the new permanent home to
many bugs native to the microcosm that is this thicket.

name: Along the Melcene Way
description:
Far off in the distance, the top of the Glass Tower is just a bit more
than an uneven speck to the northeast.  All around this bend in the road are
even rows of short trees, though very few animals can be seen in their
brances or on the ground beneath them.  The cobblestones underfoot that make
up this road continue to the east and west.

name: Within a Tamed Wood
description:
Short, neat rows of trees have obviously been planted here.  Though they
aren't meticulously upkept, they are far from the chaotic tangles that most
natural forests are... Too far.  Leaves and needles litter the ground, and
to the north, the Great Shalaran Road can be made out.

description:

up this road continue to the east and west.

even rows of short trees, though very few animals can be seen in their
brances or on the ground beneath them.  The cobblestones underfoot that make
up this road continue to the north and west.  Off to the north, you can see
that the road bends again to the east.

name: Along the Melcene Way
description:
This road is very heavily traveled.  Small tufts of trampled grass grope
for nourishment and sunlight on the side of the road, but do not find the
success that their taller relatives do further north and south.  In the
distance, Melcene can be made out.  Its large stone walls and the great
tower that it was built around stand proudly against the horizon.

name: Within a Tamed Wood
description:
Short, neat rows of trees have obviously been planted here.  Though they
aren't meticulously upkept, they are far from the chaotic tangles that most
natural forests are... Too far.  Leaves and needles litter the ground, and
to the south, the Great Shalaran Road can be made out.
