name: In a Narrow Field
description:
This small strip of field between the Great Shalaran Road and the
Southern Forests seems almost out of place.  To the northeast, the Glass
Tower can be made out, a black shape sitting upon the horizon.  Trees line
the southern and western edge of this field, though the ones to the west
seem to be less thick.

name: Along the Melcene Way
description:
This road is very heavily traveled.  Small tufts of trampled grass grope
for nourishment and sunlight on the side of the road, but do not find the
success that their taller relatives do further north and south.  In the
distance, Melcene can be made out.  Its large stone walls and the great
tower that it was built around stand proudly against the horizon.

name: In a Narrow Field
description:
This narrow strip of field sits between the Great Shalaran Road and a
dense wall of trees and thick foliage.  The great city of Melcene and the
Glass Tower are visible in the distance.  To the west, a thin forest of
somewhat stunted trees interrupts the fields.

name: In a Narrow Field
description:
This narrow strip of field sits between the Great Shalaran Road and a
dense wall of trees and thick foliage.  The great city of Melcene and the
Glass Tower are visible in the distance.  To the east, a road is visible,
past the tall grass but before Melcene.

name: Approaching Melcene
description:
The cobblestone road underfoot continues to the east and west.  To the
east, the strangely-marked gates of Melcene lie open for merchants and
travelers, the darkly colored and almost ominous Glass Tower looming high
over the city.  A smaller trail leads around the city to the north and the
south, while to the west, the Great Shalaran Road leads back toward Cimar,
another pillar of civilization.

name: In a Narrow Field
description:
This small strip of field between the Great Shalaran Road and the
Southern Forests seems almost out of place.  To the northeast, the Glass
Tower can be made out, a black shape sitting upon the horizon.  Trees line
the southern edge of this field, and to the east and west, it continues.

name: In a Narrow Field
description:
This small strip of field between the Great Shalaran Road and the
Southern Forests seems almost out of place.  To the northeast, the Glass
Tower can be made out, a black shape sitting upon the horizon.  Trees line
the southern edge of this field, and to the west, it continues.

name: Approaching Melcene
description:
The cobblestone road underfoot continues to the east and west.  To the
east, the strangely-marked gates of Melcene lie open for merchants and
travelers, the darkly colored and almost ominous Glass Tower looming high
over the city.  A smaller trail leads around the city to the north and the
south, while to the west, the Great Shalaran Road leads back toward Cimar,
another pillar of civilization.

name: In a Narrow Field
description:
This narrow strip of field sits between the Great Shalaran Road and a
dense wall of trees and thick foliage.  The great city of Melcene and the
Glass Tower are visible in the distance.  To the east, a road is visible,
past the tall grass but before Melcene.

name: Before the Gates of Melcene
description:
The cobblestone road underfoot continues to the east and west.  To the
east, the strangely-marked gates of Melcene lie open for merchants and
travelers, the darkly colored and almost ominous Glass Tower looming high
over the city.  A smaller trail leads around the city to the north and the
south, while to the west, the Great Shalaran Road leads back toward Cimar,
another pillar of civilization.

name: The Beginnings of an Old Road
description:
The ground here is torn up and hardened by great amounts of travel, lack
of care and weather.  Curls of dust wisp over the paved road forming into
dry puddles.  Two deep trakc run down each side of the road from the heavy
carts that use it, grass and weeds striving for a footing sprout out in all
directions, indicating that the road has not seen regular use in some time. 
On the edge of the road, the grass thrives and grows almost two feet, long
blades hang over the road.

name: Inside the Southern Gate
description:
A wide gateway stands just to the south, black walls framing the dark
portcullis that digs deeply into the dark mountain rock that litters the
ground.  Snow drifts up against the city walls, melting into a slush before
the traveled gateway.  To the south, a road leads off toward Melcene, while
to the north, the main snakes through the city.

name: A Worn Street Through the City
description:
The ground here is composed of densely packed dirt, wet and frozen over
many times by nature to produce a frosty substance hardly softer than rock. 
It accomodates hooves just fine.  The buildings surrounding this street are
made of bricks of dark stone that have been masterfully placed by craftsmen.
The street continues to the north and south, where you can see the southern
gate of the city.

name: A Worn Street Through the City
description:
The ground here is composed of densely packed dirt, wet and frozen over
many times by nature to produce a frosty substance hardly softer than rock. 
It accomodates hooves just fine.  The buildings surrounding this street are
made of bricks of dark stone that have been masterfully placed by craftsmen.
The street continues to the north and south, while to the west, a wide
alleyway opens up.  A few doors and signs cover the sides of the buildings
that form the northern and southern borders of the alleyway, and a fair
amount of the little traffic that traverses the city enters and exits.

name: A Worn Street Through the City
description:
The ground here is composed of densely packed dirt, wet and frozen over
many times by nature to produce a frosty substance hardly softer than rock. 
It accomodates hooves just fine.  The buildings surrounding this street are
made of bricks of dark stone that have been masterfully placed by craftsmen.
The acrid smell of molten metal fills the air here.  The smoke stacks set
upon the top of the building to the east that billow dark smoke into the sky
probably have something to do with that.  A heavy wooden door leads into the
building to the east and a small sign hangs over it.  The street continues
to the north and south, where the southern gate lies.

name: A Worn Street Through the City
description:
The ground here is composed of densely packed dirt, wet and frozen over
many times by nature to produce a frosty substance hardly softer than rock. 
It accomodates hooves just fine.  The buildings surrounding this street are
made of bricks of dark stone that have been masterfully placed by craftsmen.
The street continues to the east and south, heading deeper into the city and
to the southern gate, respectively.

name: A Worn Street Through the City
description:
The ground here is composed of densely packed dirt, wet and frozen over
many times by nature to produce a frosty substance hardly softer than rock. 
It accomodates hooves just fine.  The buildings surrounding this street are
made of bricks of dark stone that have been masterfully placed by craftsmen.
The street continues to the east and west, where in the distance it bends to
the south.

name: A Worn Street Through the City
description:
The ground here is composed of densely packed dirt, wet and frozen over
many times by nature to produce a frosty substance hardly softer than rock. 
It accomodates hooves just fine.  The buildings surrounding this street are
made of bricks of dark stone that have been masterfully placed by craftsmen.
A door leads into a building to the south.  Through frosty windows, you can
make out the warm glow of a fireplace and hear some laughter.  To the west,
the street continues.

name: A Worn Street Through the City
description:
The ground here is composed of densely packed dirt, wet and frozen over
many times by nature to produce a frosty substance hardly softer than rock. 
It accomodates hooves just fine.  The buildings surrounding this street are
made of bricks of dark stone that have been masterfully placed by craftsmen.
The street continues to the north and west.

name: A Worn Street Through the City
description:
The ground here is composed of densely packed dirt, wet and frozen over
many times by nature to produce a frosty substance hardly softer than rock. 
It accomodates hooves just fine.  The buildings surrounding this street are
made of bricks of dark stone that have been masterfully placed by craftsmen.
A sort of intersection is here.  To the north and south, the street
continues, while to the east, a bridge-like walkway leads off to the eastern
gate and a series of other places.

name: A Worn Street Through the City
description:
The ground here is composed of densely packed dirt, wet and frozen over
many times by nature to produce a frosty substance hardly softer than rock. 
It accomodates hooves just fine.  The buildings surrounding this street are
made of bricks of dark stone that have been masterfully placed by craftsmen.
The street continues to the north and bends to the west, and to the south.

name: A Worn Street Through the City
description:
The ground here is composed of densely packed dirt, wet and frozen over
many times by nature to produce a frosty substance hardly softer than rock. 
It accomodates hooves just fine.  The buildings surrounding this street are
made of bricks of dark stone that have been masterfully placed by craftsmen.
The street continues to the west, where it eventually splits off into many
directions, and to the south.

name: A Worn Street Through the City
description:
The ground here is composed of densely packed dirt, wet and frozen over
many times by nature to produce a frosty substance hardly softer than rock. 
It accomodates hooves just fine.  The buildings surrounding this street are
made of bricks of dark stone that have been masterfully placed by craftsmen.
To the west, whatever traffic happens to fill the streets splits into
several different directions, and a bit of steam can be seen rising up into
the air.

name: Tarvhaalik's Square
description:
A fair amount of traffic ends up passing through this one particular
area.  This is no anomaly, considering that the temple lies atop the stairs
to the south, the most frequently used well has been dug here for ages, and
from here, most of the city is easily accessible.  The ground is made of
densely packed and frozen dirt.  A rim of frost even surrounds the well,
which steam constantly billows out of.  To the north and west are some of
Iseldheim's bridges and walkways, serving to connect the mountain city,
which spans many ledges.

name: Upon a Wide Wooden Walkway
description:
The planks from which this walkway is made are of ironwood, the strongest
and most durable kind of wood in all of Shalar.  The hollow clomping of
hooves upon the wood can be heard as the natives of these mountains make use
of it.  To the east, you can make out Tarvhaalik's Square, to the southeast
a massive stairway rises up to meet a neighboring mountain, and to the west,
the walkway continues.

name: Upon a Wide Wooden Walkway
description:
The planks from which this walkway is made are of ironwood, the strongest
and most durable kind of wood in all of Shalar.  The hollow clomping of
hooves upon the wood can be heard as the natives of these mountains make use
of it.  To the east, you can make out Tarvhaalik's Square, to the southeast
a massive stairway rises up to meet a neighboring mountain, and to the
south, the walkway continues.

name: Upon a Wide Wooden Walkway, Before a Lift
description:
The planks from which this walkway is made are of ironwood, the strongest
and most durable kind of wood in all of Shalar.  The hollow clomping of
hooves upon the wood can be heard as the natives of these mountains make use
of it.  To the north, the walkway continues.  To the northeast, you can see
Tarvhaalik's Square and a massive stairway.  A huge mechanism that involves
gears, ropes and a wooden platform towers above the platform and descends to
the street far below begins where the walkway abruptly ends.  
A small sign has been placed next to the contraption.

name: A Well-Paved Street, Before a Lift
description:
Paved smoothly by the city's artisians, this street winds from the
western to the northern side of the city.  A bit of frost and snow lines the
sides of the street, yet the middle portion is clean and dry for the most
part.  Frost still does creep across the path at times, but the road is
maintained so that it is not overrun.  Buildings sit upon either side of the
street, and above, wooden walkways connect rocky black ledges.  The road
continues to the north, and to the east, a strange mechanism towers high
above you, connecting to the walkway above.  The western gate lies to the
west.  
A small sign has been placed next to the contraption.

name: Inside the Western Gate
description:
A wide gateway stands just to the west, crafted from the thick black rock
as the surrounding mountains.  Snow drifts up against the city walls,
melting into a slush before the traveled gateway.  Beyond the gates, to the
west, a worn and barren trail leads off into the wilderness.  To the east
you can see the streets of Iseldheim.

name: Upon a Wooden Walkway, Before a Lift
description:
The planks from which this walkway is made are of ironwood, known for its
strength and beauty throughout Shalar.  The hollow clomping of hooves upon
the wood can be heard as the natives of these mountains make use of it.  A
large mechanism of gears, ropes and a broad wooden platform rises high above
to another walkway.  To the west, a worn street runs to the north and south.
A small sign has been placed next to the contraption.

name: Upon a Wooden Walkway, Before a Lift
description:
He planks from which this walkway is made are of ironwood, the strongest
and most durable kind of wood in all of Shalar.  The hollow clomping of
hooves upon the wood can be heard as the natives of these mountains make use
of it.  To the east, the walkway turns into a ramp that leads up to the
eastern gate, while to the south, the walkway continues to a landing.  To
the west, a contraption set with gears, ropes and a broad platform descends
to the city below.  
A small sign has been placed next to the contraption.

name: At the Bottom of a Wide Ramp
description:
Here, a wooden ramp leads down from the eastern gate to meet a walkway,
which leads to the rest of the city.  Both the ramp and the walkway are
crafted from ironwood.  The hollow clomping of hooves upon the wood can be
heard as the natives of these mountains make use of it.  To the west, the
walkway continues, while above and to the east lies the eastern gate.

name: Overlooking the City of Iseldheim
description:
From here, you can see almost all of Iseldheim.  Most of it lies below
you, save the Great Temple, which towers above you still atop a mountain's
peak.  The entire city is spread out over many levels, strange contraptions,
steam and smoke from forges and fireplaces, and and plenty of work and
wandering going on in the streets below.  Soft, white snow blankets much of
the city, and contrasts greatly with the jagged black rocks that make up
most of the surrounding mountains.  The silver mines can be seen to the
northwest, forming the northern border of the city.

name: Inside the Eastern Gate
description:
A wide gateway stands just to the east, black walls framing a dark
portcullis that digs deeply into the dark mountain rock that litters the
ground.  Snow drifts up against the city walls, melting into a slush before
the traveled gateway.  Off to the west, smoke rises into the air
accompanying the odor of molten metal.  A path to the east runs off into the
wilderness, blanketed with snow.  To the west the road comes sharply to an
overlook, beyond which the city of Iseldheim is visible in its totality.

name: Upon a Narrow Walkway
description:
The planks from which this walkway is made are of ironwood, the strongest
and most durable kind of wood in all of Shalar.  The hollow clomping of
hooves upon the wood can be heard as the natives of these mountains make use
of it.  To the south, you can make out Tarvhaalik's Square and the stairway
to the temple.  To the north, the walkway continues.

name: Upon a Narrow Walkway, Before a Lift
description:
Here, the walkway ends abruptly.  A large mechanism set with metal gears
and huge, thick ropes towers up above the walkway and connects to a broad
wooden platform.  Far below, you can make out a well-paved street that leads
to the north and southwest.  To the south, the walkway continues until it
reaches Tarvhaalik's Square.  The city itself continues far to the north
until it reaches the jagged horizon of the silver mines in the distance.  
A small sign has been placed next to the contraption.

name: A Well-Paved Street, Before a Lift
description:
Paved smoothly by the city's artisians, this street winds from the
western to the northern side of the city.  A bit of frost and snow lines the
sides of the street, yet the middle portion is clean and dry for the most
part.  Frost still does creep across the path at times, but the road is
maintained so that it is not overrun.  Buildings sit upon either side of the
street, and above, wooden walkways connect rocky black ledges.  The street
continues to the north and south, and to the east, a strange mechanism
towers high above you, connecting to the walkway above.  
A small sign has been placed next to the contraption.

name: A Well-Paved Street
description:
Paved smoothly by the city's artisians, this street winds from the
western to the northern side of the city.  A bit of frost and snow lines the
sides of the street, yet the middle portion is clean and dry for the most
part.  Frost still does creep across the path at times, but the road is
maintained so that it is not overrun.  Buildings sit upon either side of the
street, and above, wooden walkways connect rocky black ledges.  The road
continues to the north and south, and to the east squats a rather large
complex.

name: A Well-Paved Street
description:
Paved smoothly by the city's artisians, this street winds from the
western to the northern side of the city.  A bit of frost and snow lines the
sides of the street, yet the middle portion is clean and dry for the most
part.  Frost still does creep across the path at times, but the road is
maintained so that it is not overrun.  Buildings sit upon either side of the
street, and above, wooden walkways connect rocky black ledges.  The street
continues to the north and west.

maintained so that it is not overrun.  Buildings sit upon either side of the

continues to the east and west.

name: A Well-Paved Street
description:
Paved smoothly by the city's artisians, this street winds from the
western to the northern side of the city.  A bit of frost and snow lines the
sides of the street, yet the middle portion is clean and dry for the most
part.  Frost still does creep across the path at times, but the road is
maintained so that it is not overrun.  To the west, a narrow and rough trail
snakes down the side of the mountain, dropping beneath sight.  To the north
and south, the street continues.

name: A Well-Paved Street
description:
Paved smoothly by the city's artisians, this street winds from the
western to the northern side of the city.  A bit of frost and snow lines the
sides of the street, yet the middle portion is clean and dry for the most
part.  Frost still does creep across the path at times, but the road is
maintained so that it is not overrun.  Here, the street intersects with an
side street, which does not seem to be as well kept as most of the city's
streets.  The main road continues to the north and south, while the side
street crosses to the east and west.  The jagged black rocks of the silver
mine slouch over the city further to the north.

name: A Well-Paved Street
description:
Paved smoothly by the city's artisians, this street winds from the
western to the northern side of the city.  A bit of frost and snow lines the
sides of the street, yet the middle portion is clean and dry for the most
part.  Frost still does creep across the path at times, but the road is
maintained so that it is not overrun.  The road seems to become more rough
gradually, however, and buildings no longer sit upon either side of the
street.  The jagged black rocks of the silver mine slouch over the city
further to the north.

name: A Well-Paved Street
description:
Paved smoothly by the city's artisians, this street winds from the
western to the northern side of the city.  A bit of frost and snow lines the
sides of the street, yet the middle portion is clean and dry for the most
part.  Frost still does creep across the path at times, but the road is
maintained so that it is not overrun.  The road seems to become more rough
gradually, however, and buildings no longer sit upon either side of the
street.  The jagged black rocks of the silver mine slouch over the city
further to the north.

name: A Well-Paved Street
description:
Paved smoothly by the city's artisians, this street winds from the
western to the northern side of the city.  A bit of frost and snow lines the
sides of the street, yet the middle portion is clean and dry for the most
part.  Frost still does creep across the path at times, but the road is
maintained so that it is not overrun.  To the west, a narrow and rough trail
snakes down the side of the mountain, dropping beneath sight.  To the north
and south, the street continues.

name: A Rough Road
description:
This road seems to have been formed more by constant traffic than by
actual paving.  The dirt is marked by wheels and hooves, while snow and ice
make it firm and hard.  The jagged black rocks of the silver mines can be
seen to the north, yet there seems to be an obstacle of some sort in the
way, blocking the pathway to the entrance.  To the south lie the streets of
Iseldheim.

name: A Snow-Covered Side Street
description:
This street is not as well-kept as most of the city's streets, as it is
covered in snow and ice.  The bricks that make these buildings up are jagged
and uneven, as if they were pulled straight out of the surrounding mountains
for construction.  Pungent odors waft through this area, highly detectable
despite the cold weather.  The sign above the door set into the seemingly
unstable building to the north may provide an explaination.

name: A Snow-Covered Side Street
description:
This street is not as well-kept as most of the city's streets, as it is
covered in snow and ice.  The bricks that make these buildings up are jagged
and uneven, as if they were pulled straight out of the surrounding mountains
for construction.  Some rugged-looking men wander in and out of the building
to the south, which bears a rather large and ornate sign above its doorway.

name: A Snow-Covered Side Street
description:
This street is not as well-kept as most of the city's streets, as it is
covered in snow and ice.  The bricks that make these buildings up are jagged
and uneven, as if they were pulled straight out of the surrounding mountains
for construction.  The street continues to the east, where you can see the
its end and to the west.

name: A Snow-Covered Side Street
description:
This street is not as well-kept as most of the city's streets, as it is
covered in snow and ice.  The bricks that make these buildings up are jagged
and uneven, as if they were pulled straight out of the surrounding mountains
for construction.  To the east, a large wrought iron fence has been
constructed to keep the city's denizens from wandering beyond, into
treacherous, cliff-ridden rocky grounds.

name: A Snow-Covered Side Street
description:
This street is not as well-kept as most of the city's streets, as it is
covered in snow and ice.  The bricks that make these buildings up are jagged
and uneven, as if they were pulled straight out of the surrounding mountains
for construction.  To the south, a wooden door bearing a plaque has been set
into the wall of a short, squatty building.

name: A Snow-Covered Side Street
description:
This street is not as well-kept as most of the city's streets, as it is
covered in snow and ice.  The bricks that make these buildings up are jagged
and uneven, as if they were pulled straight out of the surrounding mountains
for construction.  To the north is an odd little door with a small sign
hanging over it, while to the east and west, the side street continues.

name: A Snow-Covered Side Street
description:
This street is not as well-kept as most of the city's streets, as it is
covered in snow and ice.  The bricks that make these buildings up are jagged
and uneven, as if they were pulled straight out of the surrounding mountains
for construction.  To the west is a wall of solid rock, while to the east
the alley continues toward the main street.

name: A Roadblock
description:
A large, wooden structure has been used to seal off the entrance of the
silver mines from ordinary citizens.  The jagged black rocks of the mines
hide as many secrets as they do silver, and it will be some time before the
denizens of this city allow common folk to enter the mines unattended.

name: A Wide Wooden Landing
description:
This landing is almost perfectly square and very broad.  The tall wooden
railing on all sides of it helps to keep any unfortunate mishaps from
occuring, while still allowing one to see the view.  Below this landing is
the jagged peak of a small crag, into which has been placed a thick pillar
to support this landing.

name: Upon a Flat Plateau
description:
Snow covers the hard, flat ground atop this mesa, along with a few
seemingly strangled brown weeds that grope desperately for air.  Just to the
north lies a doorway to a lone house that sits on here, puffing out smoke. 
Off of every side of this natural platform, there is a sheer drop, though a
short distance away and almost on the same level on each side, you can see
the rest of the city.

name: The Weapon Forge
description:
The entire inside of this cold, small building is made up of granite
blocks.  A number of steel and iron weapons are on display, and a single
mithril weapon rests in a display case on the eastern wall.  The forge is in
plain view, next to the northern wall.  A short granite counter squats right
in front of the forge, often times becoming quite hot.  A door leads out of
the building to the south.

name: A Wooden Bridge Leading to a Ledge
description:
Thick wooden planks make up the floor of this bridge as well as the rails
on its sides.  Far below, on either side of the bridge, lie other, smaller
crags and rock formations.  To the west, a somewhat small, mesa-like crag
stands alone from the rest of the city.  A house sits near its center.  To
the east, the bridge stops at a small landing and turns to the north.

name: A Frigid Cobblestone Alley
description:
Only a slight amount of cold light has found its way into this alleyway. 
Dark buildings loom over the alley on the north and south sides.  The scent
of hickory smoke and cooking food lingers in the air, quite appetizing, and
the cold, dark shades that this alley consists mainly of are broken
occasionally by fireplaces that shine through windows of these buildings. 
The cobblestones that this alley consists of are incredibly fine and tiny,
achieving an interesting artistic effect as well as making it easier on the
hooves of the natives.  To the south, a door leads into the building.  A
small sign hangs over it.

name: A Frigid Cobblestone Alley
description:
Only a slight amount of cold light has found its way into this alleyway. 
Dark buildings loom over the alley on the north and south sides.  The scent
of hickory smoke and cooking food lingers in the air, quite appetizing, and
the cold, dark shades that this alley consists mainly of are broken
occasionally by fireplaces that shine through windows of these buildings. 
The cobblestones that this alley consists of are incredibly fine and tiny,
achieving an interesting artistic effect as well as making it easier on the
hooves of the natives.  To the north, a door leads into the building.  A
small sign hangs over it.

name: The End of a Frigid Cobblestone Alley
description:
The vast sky opens up to the west, snow-covered mountains in the
distance.  The wind whips through the open air and into the alley, running
its course and coming out the far end.  A sturdy iron rail connects to the
westernmost sides of the two buildings, preventing anyone unwary or drunk
from falling down the nearly sheer drop to the valley below.  Dark buildings
loom over the alley on the north and south sides.  The scent of hickory
smoke and cooking food lingers in the air, quite appetizing, and the cold,
dark shades that this alley consists mainly of are broken occasionally by
fireplaces that shine through windows of these buildings.  The cobblestones
that this alley consists of are incredibly fine and tiny, achieving an
interesting artistic effect as well as making it easier on the hooves of the
natives.

name: The Anteroom of the Armory
description:
Displays of plate armor and impressive-looking helms are set up all
around this room, most likely to show off the finest goods that the armorer
has to offer to those first entering the store.  The walls are made of large
stone bricks, as is the fireplace which provides heat to the room.

name: The Counter of the Armory
description:
A huge, black steel forge is visible a few feet behind the counter, and a
number of blocks and scraps of raw materials are strewn about the back room.
The counter itself is made up of the same sort of brick that the rest of the
building is made out of.  If it were made of wood, there would definitely be
danger of fire.  The anteroom lies back to the east.

name: The Entrance to the Ice Drake Inn
description:
The air in this room is dry, rich and warm, due to the numerous
fireplaces that burn within the confines of this building.  Carpets cover
parts of the floor, which is composed of polished wooden planks.  This small
entrance room is quite comfortable when compared to the harsh weather just
outside the door.  To the east, a doorway leads into a small room from which
a good deal of flickering warmth emanates, while to the west, a corridor
goes on for a way and bends to the north.

name: A Sitting Room Within the Inn
description:
A wooden ledge has been set into the walls, serving as a sort of bench
that wraps all the way around the room in an almost full square.  In the
center of the room lies a caged fire pit, which provides warmth to those who
lounge in this small side room.

name: A Short Hallway
description:
Patterned carpeting covers the floor in this short hallway, muffling the
sound of the patrons' footsteps.  The air in this room is dry, rich and
warm, due to the numerous fireplaces that burn within the confines of this
building.  To the north lies the front desk of the Ice Drake Inn, while to
the east lies the entrance.

name: The Front Desk
description:
A short counter juts out of the western wall, spanning halfway across the
room.  Behind this counter, against the northern wall, a wooden staircase
leads up into the upper level of the building.  Inn patrons constantly walk
up and down the stairs, creating quite a racket.  To the west, the scent of
smokey food and ale wafts in, while to the south a hallway leads back toward
the entrance.

name: A Hallway Within the Inn
description:
Ill-lit, this carpeted hallway leads to the Inn's rooms.  It feels
slightly stuffy up here, and it is only a little bit warmer than it is
outside.  Wooden rafters hang relatively low from the ceiling, and the
wooden walls are decorated with various old and strange things, such as a
set of antlers and an old, worthless belt.  To the south, the hallway
continues and opens up to the east and west.

name: The Ice Drake Tavern
description:
The air is thick with sweet-smelling hickory smoke, and a rather large
number of people sit about tables around the room eating meals of a roasted
meat of some sort.  Reaching across the northern side of the room, the bar
houses a great number of alcoholic drinks.  Sounds of clinking and clanking
glasses and the scraping of forks and knives fill the air along with quite a
bit of conversation, both hushed and loud.  To the east lies the front desk
of the inn.

name: A Hallway Within the Inn
description:
Ill-lit, this carpeted hallway leads to the Inn's rooms.  It feels
slightly stuffy up here, and it is only a little bit warmer than it is
outside.  Wooden rafters hang relatively low from the ceiling, and the
wooden walls are decorated with various old and strange things, such as a
rusty tin cup and a cracked axe hilt.  The hallway continues to the north,
east and west, while a door rests in the southern wall.

name: A Hallway Within the Inn
description:
Ill-lit, this carpeted hallway leads to the Inn's rooms.  It feels
slightly stuffy up here, and it is only a little bit warmer than it is
outside.  Wooden rafters hang relatively low from the ceiling, and the
wooden walls are decorated with various old and strange things, such as a
useless ragdoll and a large iron nail.  To the north and south lie doors. 
To the west, the hallway continues.

name: A Hallway Within the Inn
description:
Ill-lit, this carpeted hallway leads to the Inn's rooms.  It feels
slightly stuffy up here, and it is only a little bit warmer than it is
outside.  Wooden rafters hang relatively low from the ceiling, and the
wooden walls are decorated with various old and strange things, such as a
burlap sack and an old humanoid bone.  Doors lie to the north and south, and
the hallway continues to the east.

name: Upon a Lift
description:
This lift is basically a wooden platform with a tall rail that runs
around the edge of all its sides.  In the middle of the eastern and western
sides, hinges are set into the rail, allowing it to open and close like a
door in those directions.

name: A Room in the Inn
description:
A thin layer of dust covers just about everything in this small room...
Not from disuse, simply from the wooden structure of the building.  Cobwebs
and spiderwebs make their homes in the corners, perhaps the insects'
testament to the strange sort of warm coziness of the room.  A bed lies in
the corner, its sheets disturbed slightly, and a door leads out to the
south.

name: A Room in the Inn
description:
A thin layer of dust covers just about everything in this small room...
Not from disuse, simply from the wooden structure of the building.  Cobwebs
and spiderwebs make their homes in the corners, perhaps the insects'
testament to the strange sort of warm coziness of the room.  A bed lies in
the corner, its sheets disturbed slightly, and a door leads out to the
north.

name: A Room in the Inn
description:
A thin layer of dust covers just about everything in this small room...
Not from disuse, simply from the wooden structure of the building.  Cobwebs
and spiderwebs make their homes in the corners, perhaps the insects'
testament to the strange sort of warm coziness of the room.  A bed lies in
the corner, its sheets disturbed slightly, and a door leads out to the
south.

name: A Room in the Inn
description:
A thin layer of dust covers just about everything in this small room...
Not from disuse, simply from the wooden structure of the building.  Cobwebs
and spiderwebs make their homes in the corners, perhaps the insects'
testament to the strange sort of warm coziness of the room.  A bed lies in
the corner, its sheets disturbed slightly, and a door leads out to the
north.  A small table sits in the center of the room, covered with papers
and books, and a splash of dark liquid has stained the wooden floor.

name: The Silversmith's Shop
description:
About six tables have been set up all around the room, each one holding
pillows and pieces of soft, thick cloth upon which many pieces of silver
jewelry have been placed.  This little shop is quite successful -- silver is
what Iseldheim is famed for.  A wooden counter with a large scale upon it
blocks the doorway to the back room, where various instruments for melting
and molding the silver can be seen.

name: Upon a Lift
description:
This lift is basically a wooden platform with a tall rail that runs
around the edge of all its sides.  In the middle of the eastern and southern
sides, hinges are set into the rail, allowing it to open and close like a
door in those directions.

name: The Bottom of a Tall Granite Staircase
description:
The weathered staircase that juts out of the mountain ledge that you
stand upon ascends rather steeply to a closely neighboring peak.  Its grey
stone is chipped in some places and weathered, but still incredibly stable. 
The faint scent of molten silver drifts by when the wind blows just right. 
Tarvhaalik's Square is back to the north.

name: A Broad Landing
description:
Strong and biting winds batter this solid stairway and those who walk
upon it.  It is wide enough for four large people to walk side by side and
still be safe, but it is not fitted with any sort of railing for a
safeguard.  The staircase continues upward for a way yet, its base lying
just below you.

name: Before the Temple of Iseldheim
description:
A simple and ancient temple rests upon the top of the stairs, upon a
flattened peak.  Chilling winds dart into the temple, giving it voice to
wail its mournful song to the earthen sentinels in the distance, grimly
hulking over their windswept valleys.  The stone stairway slowly descends to
the main square of the village to the north, its lack of railing almost
compensated for by its width.  Far below, the city of Iseldheim sprawls out
with its many bridges, walkways, smoke stacks and chimneys, letting off a
warm orange glow to contrast with the natural white and blue hues lent to
the area by the snow-covered mountains.

name: The Main Chamber of the Temple of Iseldheim
description:
A rectangular portal to the north opens up to the outside, revealing the
sky and the jagged horizon of what seems to be endless mountains.  Sharp
gusts of cold wind dart into this dark stone chamber, giving a hollow voice
to the temple's solemn walls.  Twin hallways branch off to the east and
west, bending in opposite directions into quiet darkness.

name: At the High Altar of Iseldheim
description:
The sound of the frigid winds howling through the ancient temple's maw
echoes through this dark stone chamber.  Despite this slightly unsettling
chorus, the temple still remains a place of peace, comfort and rest.  A
granite altar stands in the center of the room, its sides adorned with
somewhat weathered carvings.  Baskets filled with offerings from bread and
ale to gilded blades and trophies squat neatly about the chamber, around the
altar.

name: Before a Silver-Banded Archway
description:
This short, bent corridor is completely unlit.  A very small amount of
light flows in from the main chamber to the west, as well as from the room
to the north.  Some chanting and movement can be heard from that direction
as well.

name: Within a Spartan Room
description:
Completely empty, save a few wooden chairs, this room is quite cold most
of the time.  A single, small window lies up at the top of the eastern wall,
toward the ceiling, allowing a slight glimpse of the sky.

name: Before an Iron-Banded Archway
description:
This short, bent corridor is completely unlit.  A very small amount of
light flows in from the main chamber to the east, as well as from the room
to the south.  Some chanting and movement can be heard from that direction
as well.

name: The Chamber of Murals
description:
Detailed murals of terrible, bloody wars cover the walls of this small
room, along with banners imprinted with the symbols of various gods. 
Stained glass windows add strangely colored patterns to the already large
mixture of colors.  Arguments take place often within this chamber, but they
rarely escalate to violence.  The High Shaman would not hear of such a thing
within his temple.  To the north, a dark hallway goes on a short way then
bends to the east.

name: The Furrier
description:
The majority of this room is crafted of wood.  The dark wooden planks
that make up the floor is stained in many places with blood.  The scent of
tanning fluid is strong here.  Two large vats in the back of the room are
probably to blame for this.  Furry hides of all different sorts are hung
upon the wall, and most of them seem to be of high quality.

name: An Herb-Filled Shanty
description:
The inside of this weird little building is constructed from the same
black stone as the outside and wooden planks here and there.  A crude wooden
stand serves as both a counter and a dangerously flammable incense holder. 
Drying herbs hang from the ceiling by gnarled ropes, the scents of all of
the herbs combining with the scent of incense and raw wood to create an
overpowering aroma.

name: The Shop of Essentials
description:
Well-lit by both natural light and candles, this shop is one of the most
popular in the entire city.  All sorts of the more basic traveling supplies
are carried here, and a few people of varied races stand about looking over
the goods.  The streets of Iseldheim lie back to the north.

name: The First Bank of Iseldheim
description:
Obviously brand new and not used too often by most of the population,
this bank has yet to be crowded.  There is only enough space behind the
counter for a single teller, or two at best.  The building itself is brand
new, and constructed of both dark and light gray bricks.  On the lighter
bricks are set small decorative silver plaques, as if to celebrate this new
prosperity being enjoyed by the city.  A single archway leads out to the
south.

name: A Strange Little Room
description:
A number of crude charms such as talismans, dream-catchers, feathered
pendants and masks are hung up on display.  Symbols have been painted onto
the walls in earthen colored paints, probably with fingers.  The scent of
death lingers in the air, drawing attention to a large bucket filled with
goat heads on sticks.  The ants seem to have taken note of this as well. 
Some bead curtains cover a doorway to the west, and the exit is to the
south.

name: Behrum's Ward Shop
description:
The inside of this shop feels more like a tribal witchdoctor's hut than
anything else.  Beads, amulets, masks and a variety of other protective
magical things are currently on display.  Symbols have been painted onto the
walls in earthen colored paints, probably with fingers.  The scent of death
lingers in the air, drawing attention to a large bucket filled with goat
heads on sticks.  The ants seem to have taken note of this as well.  The
shop continues to the east.

name: A Broad Landing
description:
Strong and biting winds batter this solid stairway and those who walk
upon it.  It is wide enough for four large people to walk side by side and
still be safe, but it is not fitted with any sort of railing for a
safeguard.  Above you, you can make out some sort of structure against the
sky.

name: At the Entrance to a Large Hall
description:
This large house-like structure has two large doors, both left wide open
despite the wather.  The hall itself is made almost completely of wood, with
some iron reinforcements.  Shouts can be heard coming from inside and the
faint scents of ale and sweat can be detected from out here.  To the west
lies the main path, while to the north and south, the front halves of two
neighboring buildings block your way.

name: A Large Ale Hall
description:
This huge room is crafted completely of wood.  Large lamps hang down from
massive rafters that work to hold this structure together.  The air has a
thick, woody scent to it due to the fact that the entire hall is mainly
crafted of wood, and a good deal of it is wettened by the weather, blood or
ale.  Large tables are set up around the room where warriors of many races
shout, laugh, eat and brawl.  Most of it seems to be in good fun, or what
one who would choose this sort of lifestyle would deem to be good fun.

name: Upon a Lift
description:
This lift is basically a wooden platform with a tall rail that runs
around the edge of all its sides.  In the middle of the western and southern
sides, hinges are set into the rail, allowing it to open and close like a
door in those directions.

name: The Guildmaster's Quarters
description:
Appearing to be more like a library than a training room, these quarters
are where the guildmaster of the Warrior's Guild of Iseldheim spends most of
his time.  Shelves filled with books rest up against the northern and
eastern walls, along with posters and charts detailing the vital points of
many of Shalar's races.  Pads cover the center of the floor, allowing a
number of techniques to be safely demonstrated by the guildmaster.  The loud
shouts and strong scents of ale and burning meat waft in from the west.

name: A Rough Pathway
description:
This narrow, snowy trail lies behind some of the stone buildings of
Iseldhim, leading around a wall of rock, turning to the north in the
distance toward the western silver mines.  To the east, the more civilized
streets of the minotaur city await you.

name: A Rough Pathway
description:
The rough pathway bends here to the north around a rock formation, toward
the silver mines.  Up ahead, a strange black structure can be seen set into
the jagged rocks of the mines.  Off to a distance to the east, you can make
out the streets of Iseldheim.

name: A Rocky Ledge
description:
The frost-covered sharp black rocks that make up this mountainous
formation jut out in all directions.  The wind blows through the area
fiercely, the biting frigid breeze attacking every opening in your gear. 
The rocks seem to form natural steps that lead higher up into the mountain,
though they are cracked and crumbling.

name: Before An Abandoned Temple
description:
The frost-covered sharp black rocks that make up this mountainous
formation jut out in all directions.  The wind blows through the area
fiercely, the biting frigid breeze attacking every opening in your gear.  In
front of the top of the staircase rests a strange structure: a smoothed out
archway opening into the rock wall and leading into darkness.

name: A Crumbling Foyer
description:
The darkness within this chamber is so thick that it is almost palpable,
and so abundant that it is almost suffocating.  Dust covers the floor here,
which slopes downward slightly and to the north.

name: A Dusty Room
description:
A strange, warm and flickering light comes from below, shedding meager
light upon this dark room.  Strange stains and scrawlings are scratched into
the walls, their age unknown.  A deep, circular pit is set into the floor
with a ladder at the side to climb down.  From up here, you can see some
strange figures moving about and a circle of torches.

name: A Bone-Filled Pit
description:
The walls in this strange circular pit are smooth and black, darker where
it is stained.  The ground here is made of a rough beige tile, but debris is
scattered about the area.  There is an odd air about this place, and exactly
how many people or things are here is almost impossible to tell.  Shadows
dance upon the walls, adding to the confusion and mingling with the fading,
moving bodies that crouch about the room.

name: The Front Room of the Silver Horn Tavern
description:
The warm glow provided by the fireplace fills this small, cozy tavern.  A
few chairs and tables of dark wood are scattered about the room and most of
them are inhabited.  Some loud conversation and laughing can be heard, among
other things, and the scent of ale-soaked wood fills the air.  To the north,
a door leads out to the frigid streets of the city, while to the east, you
can see the bar.

name: At the Bar
description:
The bar is covered with half-empty glasses, crumbs of numerous meals and
dirty dishes, but this does not seem to bother the locals much.  A great
number of crude barrels lie stacked behind the bar, almost reaching the
ceiling in some places.  A window is set into the southern wall, where a
barbeque pit is plainly visible.  Some loud conversation and laughing can be
heard, among other things, and the scent of ale-soaked wood fills the air. 
Back to the west is the front room of the tavern.

name: Entrance to the tomb of Malkeran
At the bottom of a small shaft
Above the Forest Floor
description:
Broad, flat limbs extend themselves from this massive tree in a rather
neat spiral, virtually creating a winding staircase which runs into the
forest canopy above, and to the floor far below.  The mottled trunk is
impossibly wide, even at this height, and a host of forest creatures appear
to reside in its dark nooks and furrows.  A short distance above, the trunk
splits into two mighty halves.  Built into the tree near the split a large
platform can be seen.  A rope ladder hangs from above to offer access.

name: A Platform High in the Trees
description:
This sturdy platform consists of long, thick boards of beautiful hardwood
laid upon crossbeams built into the side of the mammoth tree.  The immense
trunk splits here, the two mighty halves reaching impossible heights into
the canopy, which grows even thicker above.  In spite of its intricate
construction, the platform is quite plain.  It's only ornamentation is a
large railing around the perimeter, which is certainly a detail of function
and not form.  The platform continues to the north and west, while a rope
ladder leads down into the tree below.

name: A Platform High in the Trees
description:
This sturdy platform consists of long, thick boards of beautiful hardwood
laid upon crossbeams built into the sids of the mammoth tree.  In spite of
its intricate construction, the platform is quite plain.  It's only
ornamentation is a large railing around the perimeter, which is certainly a
detail of function and not form.  The platform continues here to the east
and north.

name: A Platform High in the Trees
description:
This sturdy platform consists of long, thick boards of beautiful
hardwood laid upon crossbeams built into the sids of the mammoth tree.  In
spite of its intricate construction, the platform is quite plain.  It's only
ornamentation is a large railing around the perimeter, which is certainly a
detail of function and not form.  The platform continues here to the east
and south.

name: A Platform High in the Trees
description:
This sturdy platform consists of long, thick boards of beautiful
hardwood laid upon crossbeams built into the sids of the mammoth tree.  In
spite of its intricate construction, the platform is quite plain.  It's only
ornamentation is a large railing around the perimeter, which is certainly a
detail of function and not form.  The platform continues here to the west
and south.  To the north, a rope bridge sags out over the forest floor,
connecting this platform with another.

name: A Rope Bridge, High in the Trees
description:
Long, knotted cords form the frame of this bridge, with crosswise boards
providing a passable surface.  Other ropes provide a makeshift railing, but
it seems they would do little to guard against an actual fall.  The forest
floor can be seen below, man-sized bushes reduced to motes far beneath this
arbor paradise.  The bridge continues to the north, where it can be seen to
reach a platform a short distance ahead.  Another such platform lies more
immediately to the south, nestled into the mighty trunk of an enormous tree.

name: A Rope Bridge, High in the Trees
description:
Long, knotted cords form the frame of this bridge, with crosswise boards
providing a passable surface.  Other ropes provide a makeshift railing, but
it seems they would do little to guard against an actual fall.  The forest
floor can be seen below, man-sized bushes reduced to motes far beneath this
arbor paradise.  The bridge connects to a small platform to the north, built
into the side of a tree trunk.  A short distance to the south, a larger
platform is built into the forking trunk of a colossal tree.

name: A Platform, Before a Hollow Tree
description:
This narrow platform is anchored on several thin tree trunks, the
crossbeams overlaid with boards of sturdy hardwood.  A wooden railing to the
north and west makes a cursory effort at preventing falls into the
incredible emptiness below.  The platform runs to the east toward the
hollowed-out trunk of a mammoth tree, where a large archway offers entrance.
A rope bridge sags out over the forest to the south, where another platform
can be seen in the distance.

name: A Rocky Trail on the Mountainside
A Small Junction on the Mountainside
A Rocky Path, Above a Cliff
A Narrow Trail on a Cliff
A Narrow Trail on a Cliff
The End of a Cliffside Trail
A Dwelling in a Hollow Tree
A Passage in a Hollow Tree
A Strange Laboratory, Within a Tree
A Dwelling in a Hollow Tree
A Dwelling in a Hollow Tree
A Dwelling in a Hollow Tree
A Dwelling in a Hollow Tree
A Platform, Before a Gnarled Oak
A Foyer, Within the Gnarled Oak
A Library, Within the Gnarled Oak
A Bedroom, Within the Gnarled Oak
A Landing, Within the Gnarled Oak
A Balcony on the Gnarled Oak
A Balcony on the Gnarled Oak
A Balcony on the Gnarled Oak
A Balcony on the Gnarled Oak
A Balcony on the Gnarled Oak
A Balcony on the Gnarled Oak
A Balcony on the Gnarled Oak
A Balcony on the Gnarled Oak
Within a large cave
description:
Just a single fire burns here, and one or two moulded bedtrundles lie
scattered about.  A few raggish pelts are still nailed to the walls, yet
this part of the cave seems to have fallen in disuse.  Several collapsed
firepits line the floor, as well as various pieces of broken furniture.  The
end of the cave seems to have collapsed, a number of large boulders blocking
any passage deeper into the mountain.  Some rude sketches can still be
discerned on one of the larger boulders.

name: Within a large cave
description:
Some large, painted pelts are spanned across the walls with beneath them
a few woolly trundles, serving as beds.  Leather loops woven into the pelts
serve as hooks for the storage of various instruments.  Thin strips of meat
dry over a large wooden rack placed over three firepits, filling the cavern
with their odour.  To the east the cave entrance is visible, with outside
the northern part of the plateau.  Deeper into the mountain the cavern seems
to come to an abrupt end.

name: A large cave
description:
The cave's entrance is sheltered from the outside by the tanned hides
that are draped across it.  Some large, painted pelts are spanned across the
walls with beneath them a few woolly trundles, serving as beds.  Leather
loops woven into the pelts serve as hooks for the storage of various
instruments.  Several firepits are burning and primitive tanning tools are
scattered across the floor.  Deeper into the cavern a large foodrack is used
to dry some meat above a few fires.

name: Northern edge of the plateau
description:
The hidden plateau spreads out majestically to the south, displaying a
small village, isolated from the world outside.  People are milling about
the caves hewn into the mountain itself, and a few have gathered around the
triangular lake that lies in the centre of the valley.  To the north and
further away to the east, a massive ridge encloses the plateau.  A large
cave entrance lies to the west.

name: Northern edge of the plateau
description:
The hidden plateau spreads out majestically to the south, displaying a
small village, isolated from the world outside.  People are milling about
the caves hewn into the mountain itself, and a few have gathered around the
triangular lake that lies in the centre of the valley.  One of the smaller
caves is hewn into the northern ridge, while the plateau floor rises
somewhat to adjoin the boundary to the east.

name: A small cove
description:
The cove is barely three yards deep, and seems to serve as a storeroom. 
Weaponracks are placed along the sides, containing a variety of spears and
tridents, and a small fireplace is set in the entrance.  From here, the
whole plateau can be overseen, from the eastern boundary to the mountain
face in the south and west.  The lake's surface seems peculiarly placid from
up here, with not a single disturbing wavelet.

name: Northern edge of the plateau
description:
The hidden plateau spreads out majestically to the south and west,
displaying a small village isolated from the world outside.  People are
milling about the caves hewn into the mountain itself, and a few have
gathered around the triangular lake that lies in the centre of the valley. 
A layer of fog clouds a narrow passage to the north, hiding anything within
the ridge-breach from sight.

name: Eastern edge of the plateau
description:
The hidden plateau spreads out majestically to the west, displaying a
small village isolated from the world outside.  People are milling about the
caves hewn into the mountain itself, and a few have gathered around the
triangular lake that lies in the centre of the valley.  To the east, the
boundary forbids all passage, although it is becoming more gradual to the
south.  Further north a breach in the northern ridge can be discerned.

name: The center of the plateau
description:
The hidden plateau spreads out majestically to the north, south and east,
while in the west the mountains rise steeply.  People are milling about the
caves hewn into the mountain itself, and a few have gathered around the
triangular lake that lies in the centre of the valley.  To the southwest, a
steep path can be spotted, swirling its way up into the mountain.  A large
obsidian pillar stands here, its surface chiselled with various symbols.

name: The center of the plateau
description:
The hidden plateau spreads out majestically to the north, south and east,
while in the west the mountains rise steeply.  People are milling about
caves that are hewn into the mountain itself, and a few have gathered around
the triangular lake that lies in the centre of the valley.  To the
southwest, a thin fissure leads its way up the mountain.  The large obsidian
pillar east of here seems to be an object of reverence for the villager.

name: The center of the plateau
description:
The hidden plateau spreads out majestically to the north and east, while
an elongated slope from the western mountainside obstructs direct passage to
the southern part of the plateau.  People are milling about caves that are
hewn into the mountain itself, and a few have gathered around the triangular
lake that lies in the centre of the valley.  To the west, a thin fissure
leads its way up the mountain.  The large obsidian pillar northeast of here
seems to be an object of reverence for the villager.

name: Eastern edge of the plateau
description:
The hidden plateau spreads out majestically to the west, displaying a
small village isolated from the world outside.  People are milling about
caves that are hewn into the mountain itself, and a few have gathered around
the triangular lake that lies in the centre of the valley.  The boundary to
the northeast gradually declines and becomes passable, providing a way into
the foothills.

name: Southeastern corner of the plateau
description:
The hidden plateau spreads out majestically to the north and west,
displaying a small village isolated from the world outside.  People are
milling about caves that are hewn into the mountain itself, and a few have
gathered around the triangular lake that lies in the centre of the valley. 
A small path leads east, passing between an immense boulder and the mountain
itself.

name: Within an inhabited cave
description:
Some large, painted pelts are spanned across the walls with beneath them
a few skins, serving as beds.  All sorts of metal instruments are strung
along the walls, and a large stone serves as a primitive anvil.  Wood is
stacked in the back of the cave, serving as fuel for the fire burning in the
eastern wall.  A barrel in the corner provides the neccesary water to cool
down the white-hot iron.

name: Southern edge of the plateau
description:
The hidden plateau spreads out majestically to the north, displaying a
small village isolated from the world outside.  People are milling about
caves that are hewn into the mountain itself, and a few have gathered around
the triangular lake that lies in the centre of the valley.  A small path
leads south, passing between an immense boulder and the mountain itself.

name: Southern edge of the plateau
description:
The hidden plateau spreads out majestically to the north, displaying a
small village isolated from the world outside.  People are milling about
caves that are hewn into the mountain itself, and a few have gathered around
the triangular lake that lies in the centre of the valley.  One of the caves
is hewn into the southern mountainslope.  West, an elongated slope separates
a small part of the plateau from the main village.

name: Southern edge of the plateau
description:
This part of the plateau is squeezed between the southern mountainside
and an elongated slope from the western side.  With so little sun ever
reaching this part of the plateau, the walls are covered with moist and
algae.  To the south a small cave entrance is heavily draped with a curtain
of red-flowered vines.  While the normal villagelife bustled to the east,
people seem to avoid this part of the plateau.

name: A shamanic cove
description:
The cove is cramped, as in every nook and cranny all sorts of jawbones,
jugals, teeth and skulls are stashed.  Most are decorated with henna
drawings, while others are tied to various herbs with pieces of strings.  In
the midst of this all is a bare patch on the ground where a large pentagram
is drawn into the floor.  A curtain of red-flowered vines separates the cave
entrance from the world outside.

name: An ascending path
description:
The steps of this stairway are hewed in this once-natural fissure.  The
walls have been chiseled and polished with care.  The erratic twists and
turn limit your view to only half a dozen yards.  To the south, the fissure
provides passage to the plateau, while north it ascends higher up the
mountainslope.

name: A junction of paths
description:
The fissure here splits in two, one descending north, one descending onto
the southern part of the plateau.  The steps of this stairway are
meticulously hewed and the walls have been chiseled and polished with care. 
The erratic twists and turn limit your view to only half a dozen yards.  As
the fissure narrows to the west, it becomes even steeper, and the individual
steps are barely large enough for an abyss' foot.

name: A hidden terrace
description:
The fissure gives way for a small terrace , nearly a hundred foot above
the plateau itself.  Not only does it show a magnificient view of the
plateau itself, but it also shows the hill landscape that lies beyond the
ridge enfolding the village.  To the west, an altar of some sort can be
discerned.  The steps of the path leading down are meticulously hewed and
the walls have been chiseled and polished with care.

name: A hidden terrace
description:
The mountain makes way for a small terrace , nearly a hundred foot above
the plateau itself.  Not only does it show a magnificient view of the
plateau itself, but it also shows the hill landscape that lies beyond the
ridge.  A gruesome altar has been crafted out of a large block of obsidian
granite, depicting a young child entangled by four monstrous tentacles.  The
steps of the path leading down are meticulously hewed and the walls have
been chiseled and polished with care.

name: Northern pass
description:
The slopes of the ridge confine the pass to a narrow trail.  The slippery
remains of a rockslide do not ease travelling and the fog that limits the
view to the north obscures any details that might be discerned of the
plateau to the south.

name: Southeastern corner of the plateau
description:
The hidden plateau spreads out majestically to the north and west,
displaying a small village isolated from the world outside.  People are
milling about caves that are hewn into the mountain itself, and a few have
gathered around the triangular lake that lies in the centre of the valley. 
A massive boulder towers above you, easily as large as a palace.  The
surface of the boulder suggests that it once was part of the mountain
itself, but that it broke away hundreds of years ago.  Now a small pass has
formed between the mountain and the boulder, winding its way down.

name: Southern pass
description:
The slopes of the ridge confine the pass to a narrow trail.  The
shattered remains of a rockslide are sprayed throughout the pass.  A thick
layer of fog limits the view to only a few feet.  The pass continues to the
north and east.

name: At the shores of a lake
description:
The lake lies in the centre of the plateau.  Overshadowed by the mountain
peeks, it is dark and still, not a ripple caresses its surface.  All around
you, the plateau stretches to the unforgiving rock walls that enclose it. 
In several directions villagers are milling about, fulfilling their tasks. 
Lining the lake are some clay cauldrons, used by the savages to store their
catches.

name: At the shores of a lake
description:
The lake lies in the centre of the plateau.  Overshadowed by the mountain
peeks, it is dark and still, not a ripple caresses its surface.  All around
you, the plateau stretches to the unforgiving rock walls that enclose it. 
In several directions villagers are milling about, fulfilling their tasks. 
Lining the lake are some clay cauldrons, used by the savages to store their
catches.

name: At the shores of a lake
description:
The lake lies in the centre of the plateau.  Overshadowed by the mountain
peeks, it is dark and still, not a ripple caresses its surface.  All around
you, the plateau stretches to the unforgiving rock walls that enclose it. 
In several directions villagers are milling about, fulfilling their tasks. 
Lining the lake are some clay cauldrons, used by the savages to store their
catches.

name: Within a lake
description:
A few yards below the surface the world exists only in shades of black. 
The rough walls of the lake are covered with algae, and small schools of
fish rush through their world, fading in and out of sight.  Further down,
the lake narrows, giving it the shape of a giant funnel.  Strange currents
whirl and threathen to carry you away into the deep.  Underwater, the
gibberish of the savages has dimmed beyond hearing and an eerie silence is
all that is left behind.

name: Within a lake
description:
A few yards below the surface the world exists only in shades of black. 
The rough walls of the lake are covered with algae, and small schools of
fish rush through their world, fading in and out of sight.  Further down,
the lake narrows, giving it the shape of a giant funnel.  Strange currents
whirl and threathen to carry you away into the deep.  Underwater, the
gibberish of the savages has dimmed beyond hearing and an eerie silence is
all that is left behind.

name: Within a lake
description:
A few yards below the surface the world exists only in shades of black. 
The rough walls of the lake are covered with algae, and small schools of
fish rush through their world, fading in and out of sight.  Further down,
the lake narrows, giving it the shape of a giant funnel.  Strange currents
whirl and threathen to carry you away into the deep.  Underwater, the
gibberish of the savages has dimmed beyond hearing and an eerie silence is
all that is left behind.

name: Deep within a lake
description:
No surface light comes this deep, and the giant funnel's walls are smooth
and slimy with algae.  Strong currents whirl the water around.  Life becomes
rare here, and only far above school of fish can be still be seen flashing
by.  A few brightly coloured snails cling to the rock walls, grazing the
luminiscent algae.  Some whelks are actively preying on the grazing snails,
their feelers blindly searching for flesh to devour.

name: Before an underwater lair
description:
The currents seem to originate from an jagged cavemouth to the west. 
With the very little light that penetrates these depths, the weak
luminescence originating from deeper within the cave acts like a beacon. 
The hard rockbed on the bottom of the floor of the lake is covered with a
thick layer of mucus.  Several small stones are slowly sliding deeper into
the lair, dragged in by the strong currents.

name: An underwater aisle
description:
The walls of the aisle are covered with a thick layer of mucus, aglow
with the luminiscence of small algae.  Large anemones wave their tentacles,
filtering the water for any edible remains.  East, the darkness of the
lake's water looms, while to the west a faint glow reveals that the aisle
widens into a large cavern.  The currents pull you towards it, in an
insistent, nearly conscious way.

name: An enormous underwater cavern
description:
Monumental in size, this underwater chamber stretches out to the north,
south and west.  All along the cavern walls glimmering algae and plants
illuminate the scene.  Darting through them little squids, nearly
translucent in colour, their arms grabbing at invisible prey.  Overhead, the
light breaks and plays through the small ripples of an unknown water
surface.  To the east, a small aisle offers a way out of the cavern.

name: An enormous underwater cavern
description:
Monumental in size, this underwater chamber stretches out to the south
and west.  All along the cavern walls glimmering algae and plants illuminate
the scene.  Darting through them little squids, nearly translucent in
colour, their arms grabbing at invisible prey.  Overhead, the light breaks
and plays through the small ripples of an unknown water surface.  To the
east, a small aisle offers a way out of the cavern.

name: An enormous underwater cavern
description:
Monumental in size, this underground chamber stretches out to the north
and west.  All along the cavern walls glimmering algae and plants illuminate
the scene.  Darting through them little squids, nearly translucent in
colour, their arms grabbing at invisible prey.  Overhead, the light breaks
and plays through the small ripples of an unknown water surface.  To the
east, a small aisle offers a way out of the cavern.

name: An enormous underwater cavern
description:
Monumental in size, this underground chamber stretches out to the north,
south and east.  All along the cavern walls glimmering algae and plants
illuminate the scene.  Darting through them little squids, nearly
translucent in colour, their arms grabbing at invisible prey.  Overhead, the
light breaks and plays through the small ripples of an unknown water
surface.  To the east, a small aisle offers a way out of the cavern.

name: A small air bubble
description:
A stale and moist air bubble is captured in the ceiling of the cavern. 
The rocks are still wet enough to host some luminescent algae, and a few
polyps cling to the stone just above the water surface.  The algae's light
is shattered upon the rippling waves, making it impossible to see what lies
beneath the watersurface.

name: A grotto chamber
description:
A small, oval shaped chamber has formed in the rockwand.  The walls lack
the algae seen in other parts of the cavern and is covered with a black acid
secration.  A large pile of cadavers and bones and all sorts of armament lie
scattered across its surface.  To the east, the grotto opens into a cavern.

name: Inside a monstrous abdomen
description:
Everything around you bulges and convexes, mangled by gigantous muscles
in the stomach of the tentacled beast.  Various acid juices pour out of
glands, their sharp and dizzying fumes mixing with the putrid odour of the
half-digested carrion residing here.  You realize that unless you find a way
out of here quickly, either by blade or magic, your future might be black
indeed.

name: Entrapped by a monstrous tentacle
description:
Held by a gigantous tentacle, you are hauled through the water at high
velocity.  While time slowly deludes into nothingness, you find time to
study your captor.  The large slimy tentacle is covered with small jagged
fishscales, their tips ending in barbed hooks.  Your thoughts divert and you
ponder briefly on where the tentacle is taking you.

name: A forest pathway
description:
The dense forest has been cut away by man allowing passage deeper
into the forest. It seems that the trees were not only chopped down
but also magically singed to prevent them from growing back.
The pathway allows you to travel north or south.

name: A forest pathway
description:
The dense forest has been cut away by man allowing passage deeper
into the forest. It seems that the trees were not only chopped down
but also magically singed to prevent them from growing back.
The pathway allows you to travel north or south.

name: A forest pathway
description:
The dense forest has been cut away by man allowing passage deeper
into the forest. It seems that the trees were not only chopped down
but also magically singed to prevent them from growing back.
The pathway allows you to travel north or south.

name: A forest pathway
description:
The dense forest has been cut away by man allowing passage deeper
into the forest. It seems that the trees were not only chopped down
but also magically singed to prevent them from growing back.
The pathway allows you to travel north or south.

name: A small grove
description:
You are standing within a man made grove. The normal foilage has been trampled
to the ground but after time flowers and other grasses have come about to make
a new carpet for the forest.

name: A small grove
description:
Walking through the grove you see the normal foilage has been trampled 
to the ground but newly grown flowers and grasses have taken its place.
As you stand in the grove you start to notice a large building to the north.

name: A small grove
description:
Walking through the grove you see the normal foilage has been trampled
to the ground but newly grown flowers and grasses have taken its place.
As you stand in the grove you start to notice a large building to the north.

name: Before a vast ravine
description:
Before you lies a deep ravine spanned by a wooden bridge ahead.  The
massive canopy of trees above you destroys any posibility of sunlight
breaking through. The forest life about you sings with vibrance, and 
the smell of moist ground fills the air. The only way through the
dense woods is to the north or south.

name: Upon a wooden bridge
description:
You have stumbled upon a old looking wooden bridge. It is built
from old oak trunks, and is at least 10 feet wide. Looking down 
the ravine opens up before you revealing a rushing river that
continues to deepen the ravine.

name: Before the gates of the Elven Stronghold
description:
A large green hill covered in trees rises up before you.
Small windows of can barely be seen at the top of the hill,
and several smoke stacks poke through the hillside. A massive 
gate is set directly into the hill, and a golden plaque catches
your attention to the left of the gate.

name: The Entrance Hall
description:
You are beneath a spectacular dome painted with dozens of intricate
constellations.  Tall pillars guilded with gold and silver twist and turn
like the roots of a tree to the base of the dome.  Strange runes carved from
wood sit atop the massive pillars.  Intricate archways lead in every
direction from this room.

name: A Guard Room
description:
A rather small room surrounds you.  There is no furniture, only several
weapons hang from the wall.  Marble covers the entire floor seamlessly,
giving it a simple but elegant feel.

name: A Guard Room
description:
A rather small room surrounds you.  There is no furniture, only several
weapons hang from the wall.  Marble covers the entire floor seamlessly,
giving it a simple but elegant feel.

name: A Large Apex
description:
This room is even more spectacular than the room to the south.  A double
leveled dome rises high above you.  On the first level of the dome a
painting of a massive library can be seen, and the upper dome is adorned
with portraits of unknown elves that seem to look down upon you.  Pillars
sculpted to resemble tree branches reach high above you supporting the
domes.  Circular doorways are positioned in the four cardinal directions of
the room.

name: A Hallway Outside of the Grand Hall
description:
This wide hallway is lined with brass lanterns that causes the shadows to
dance about merrily.  Wreaths and bouquets of wildflowers decorate the wall
inbetween the lanterns.  The smells of food and incense wafts down the hall.
The smells and light look a bit brighter down the hallway to the east.

name: The Grand Hall
description:
You are in the massive hall known best for its merrymaking.  Huge wooden
tables line the main floor of this room.  Near the very center you can see
an area cleared out for dancing, and a small place where musicians play. 
Waiters and servants can be seen bringing trays of food and glasses of fine
wine back and forth to the guests.

name: The Grand Hall
description:
You are in the massive hall known best for its merrymaking.  Huge wooden
tables line the main floor of this room.  Near the very center you can see
an area cleared out for dancing, and a small place where musicians play. 
Waiters and servants can be seen bringing trays of food and glasses of fine
wine back and forth to the guests.

name: The Upper Gallery
description:
This entire gallery is set several feet above the rest of the hall,
giving it a spectacular view.  All of the dancing and feasting can be seen
in clear view from here.  A continous oak table lines the entire upper
gallery.  These seats are reserved for the distinguished guests of the Elven
Lord.

name: An Ornate Hallway
description:
This hallway is extremely extravegant.  The walls and floors have been
polished and buffed to a bright shine, and intricate designs have been
carved across them.  The floor is covered in a beautiful rug, and chairs and
tall golden lampstands line the halls.

name: An Ornate Hallway
description:
This hallway is extremely extravegant.  The walls and floors have been
polished and buffed to a bright shine, and intricate designs have been
carved across them.  The floor is covered in a beautiful rug, and chairs and
tall golden lampstands line the halls.

name: A Guest Room
description:
A large bed dominates this room.  Large silk sheets hang down above the
bed and a mass of pillows lies at the head.  One large lamp stands in the
corner next to a ornate wooden dresser and mirror.  A fine rug covers the
floor and the ceiling is stensiled with wildflowers.

name: An Arched Hallway
description:
This floor of this hallway is a beautiful black and white marble.  The
torches that line either side of the hall send the light dancing across the
marble.  The ceiling in ths room is arched and is supported by old looking
beams of wood that form an elaborate design because of thier formation.

description:
