name: A blood-stained room
description:
The details of the room are at first lost on you, overwhelmed by the smell
and sight of carnage that drips from the walls and gathers in pools on the
floor.  Handprints in bright red claw the warped floorboards and trail off
helplessly to the corner of the room.  The sparse furniture seems
incongruously mundane in such a spectacularly bloody room.  A simple redwood
table with matching chairs would be perfectly at place in a sun-lit kitchen
or homely family room if not for the light sprinkling of blood dotting the
tabletop.  A threadbare rug on the floor was once white but now stained
maroon.  Strangely not all the stains are fresh.  Though the floor is wet
with newly shed blood, there are also old brown marks in amorphous
configurations.  Scuffs from past fights are carved into the walls,
accompanied by stains scrubbed but not erased.  A guttural moan rises to fill
the room and you shudder, uncertain if the sound comes from your throat or
another or simply arises from the faint wind slipping through the rotten
walls.

name: A decaying footbridge
description:
A narrow little rope bridge joins two adjacent shacks, its rotten boards
unevenly placed.  The faint breeze, lazy as it is, shakes you as you stand,
exciting a chorus of creaks from the old ropes.  The village has designed its
own peculiar architecture in order to survive the malarial waters below and
the incoming tide to the south.  Each ramshackle house is up on long, wobbly
stilts and passage between them gained by short bridges such as this one.
Though this design is clever enough and might have once encouraged a close-
knit society within the village, now each bridge is precariously rotten,
dripping with parasitic moss, the damp boards wormeaten.  To the north and
south lie the relative shelter of other sprawling shacks.

name: A torch-lit room
description:
No daylight reaches this large room.  The windows are covered by thick
tapestries and the holes in the wall and floorboards are plugged with mud and
moss.  In the flickering light of scattered torches the place seems exotic
and faintly threatening.  Shapes and shadows appear and disappear, dancing on
the edges of your perception.  Heavy animal pelts hang on every wall, though
from what animal they were taken you could not say.  The musk of wild
animals, however, clings to the room.  A shelf on the western wall contains
row upon row of jars and earthenware filled with mysterious concoctions.  A
large seat stands against the southern wall, made of earth and bone, looking
rather like a throne.  A throaty hum of prayer or curse fills the room,
coming from no particular direction.

name: A filthy shack
description:
The stench of dirt, rot, and human waste rises from every corner of this
tiny room to assault your nostrils.  The air is thick with filth and heavy
with a sense of sadness and lethargy.  Neither floor nor walls nor the tiny
window to the south have been washed in many years.  A layer of dust and
rubbish covers the floor, interrupted only by a line of tiny, childlike
footprints that tiptoe from the door into the next room to the bed against
the southern wall.  No other furniture remains besides the bed, though
markings on the floor and wall seem to indicate that this was once a
relatively well-furnished room.  The wood is wet and rotten and will soon
give way, depositing the unfortunate inhabitants of this home into the
malarial swamp below.

name: A small bedroom
description:
The room is remarkably small, too tiny to serve as anything except perhaps
a child's bedroom.  Yet what a morbid place to keep a child.  No bed but a
small pile of moss in one corner.  No light to chase a way the terrors of a
child's fancy.  Only the makeshift bed and a large iron ring in the western
wall, the sort used to chain animals in a menagerie or prisoners in a
dungeon.  Dark brown and maroon blotches stain both floor and walls, the
indelible legacy of some poor victim's blood shed.

name: A dark altar
description:
The shadow-dancing darkness encroaches upon you, pressing the meagre glow
of your light into an ever-smaller circle of illumination.  The only source
of light in the room is a circle of flickering candles surrounding a pile of
bone and animal pelts standing in the center of the room.  The room is humid
with a strange, heavy scent, an exotic mix of animal blood and the sweaty
smell of human desperation.  A hairy touch upon the nape of your neck draws
your eyes toward the ceiling.  Rope-suspended figurines dangle from a roof
lost in smoky shadows, most carved in human shapes.

name: A filthy shack
description:
The stench of dirt, rot, and human waste rises from every corner of this
tiny room to assault your nostrils.  The air is thick with filth and heavy
with a sense of sadness and lethargy.  Neither floor nor walls nor the tiny
window to the south have been washed in many years.  A layer of dust and
rubbish covers the floor, interrupted only by a line of tiny, childlike
footprints.  Two tiny piles of grass and dirt lying in the eastern corner
might serve as beds, yet the thought of people actually inhabiting this hole
is disturbing to even the hardiest of souls.

name: A one-room shack
description:
Unlike the sparse, dilapidated furnishings of most of the shacks in the
village, the furniture in this home is ornate and colorful, if cheaply made.
Thick, velvety fabrics hang from all four walls.  Slightly faded but still
bright red carpets cover the floor.  Taking up the majority of the room, an
ornately carved blackwood canopy bed stands against the northern wall, hung
with filmy violet drapery.  Though the tracks worn into the thick carpet from
door to bed would suggest frequent traffic into and out of this room, you see
no sign of kitchen or bar that might invite customers.  Though someone has
burned musky incense in an effort to cover the smell, the one-room shack
still reeks of sweat and wickedness.

name: A decaying footbridge
description:
A narrow little rope bridge joins two adjacent shacks, its rotten boards
unevenly placed.  The faint breeze, lazy as it is, shakes you as you stand,
exciting a chorus of creaks from the old ropes.  The village has designed its
own peculiar architecture in order to survive the malarial waters below and
the incoming tide to the south.  Each ramshackle house is up on long, wobbly
stilts and passage between them gained by short bridges such as this one.
Though this design is clever enough and might have once encouraged a close-
knit society within the village, now each bridge is precariously rotten,
dripping with parasitic moss, the damp boards wormeaten.  The relative
shelter of sprawling shacks lies to the north and south.

name: The mission center
description:
Cloaked in white silk or satin drapery from ceiling to floor, the purity of
this large room is almost blinding after the dingy sights of the village.
The thick carpets must be frequently replaced, since despite the bustling
presence of men and women in white garments you can spy no thin or frayed
patches.  Though spare of trinkets or clutter, the walls are adorned with a
few excellent portraits of hawk-faced men and women.  A large, organically
carved desk stands against the eastern wall, bearing neat piles of parchments
and leather-bound books.  Strangely, despite the obvious wickedness and
decadence of the villagers and the shocking state of poverty prevalent in the
town, the air in this, the heart of the mission to convert Gannyte Shoals, is
brisk with optimism and a sense of purpose.

name: A decaying footbridge
description:
A narrow little rope bridge joins two adjacent shacks, its rotten boards
unevenly placed.  The faint breeze, lazy as it is, shakes you as you stand,
exciting a chorus of creaks from the old ropes.  The village has designed its
own peculiar architecture in order to survive the malarial waters below and
the incoming tide to the south.  Each ramshackle house is up on long, wobbly
stilts and passage between them gained by short bridges such as this one.
Though this design is clever enough and might have once encouraged a close-
knit society within the village, now each bridge is precariously rotten,
dripping with parasitic moss, the damp boards wormeaten.  The relative
shelter of sprawling shacks lies to the east and west.

name: A large white room
description:
The large bedroom in this satin-cloaked shack is a shocking contrast to
every other home in the village.  Though no serious effort has been put into
permanently repairing the house, wall-length white satin banners cover the
disfigured wooden boards and flowered silk carpets cover the gaps and bumps
in the old floor.  Pleasant oil paintings hang from the white-silk walls.
Rich furnishings stand about the room: a bedstand, a writing desk with
matching chair, and a large, comfortable bed.  A large window in the southern
wall looks out onto the beach and the ocean beyond.  A shallow balcony in the
northwest corner of the room juts out from the building, giving a nearly
complete view of the messy, sprawling village, such a marked contrast to this
tidy, clean abode.

name: A dirty one-room shack
description:
The home set precariously atop four sprawling poles is pathetically small,
only the size of one room and that smaller than a rich man's closet.  Few
furnishings or ornaments adorn the room, only a narrow, filthy bed in the
corner.  Wine stains spread in maroon rings on the floor.  The air is rife
with the scent of stale beer and spilled mead.  Glass bottles lie haphazardly
around the room, some chipped, some shattered and lying dangerously jagged on
the ground.  Vomit long since dried and hardened sits undisturbed on the
floorboards.  Nor pictures, shelves, or even windows break the monotony of
the rotting walls.

name: A marshy trail
description:
A waterlogged path of trodden grasses and thick, squelching swamp mud winds
its way toward the southeast, growing wetter with each step southward.  The
air is thick with the buzzing of insects and lazy rustlings of animals
underfoot.  The spot where you stand seems to be some sort of informal line
of demarcation.  The grasses and trees to the south are substantially more
overgrown and redolent with the smell of stagnation and rot, while northward
the way grows clearer.  As though to confirm this intuitive sense of
boundary, a broken piece of wood that might have once been a sign lies on the
ground.  Sudden laughter cuts through the humid air, high-pitched, perhaps
drunken, distant but clearly audible.  A sharp ear may catch the sandpaper
brush of the waves against the beach far to the south, but not the faintest
breath of fresh ocean air reaches this spot.

name: A marshy trail
description:
The sodden, marshy weeds give way to every-deepening water, part freshwater
swamp and part the salty overflow from high tide.  The trail opens up here to
reveal a rambling, rotten village to the southeast.  Curious looking little
hovels stand several lengths above the water, elevated on thick but none-too-
sturdy poles.  The poles are long and once probably quite strong but years of
neglect have left them teetering and uneven, sprawling like the uncertain
legs of a newborn colt.  Wicked indulgence wafts from the village itself; the
brassy smell of lechery, the screeching sound of laughter and violence.  Like
a symphony the scent and sound permeate the village, running up the hill to
sing to you here with a kind of disfigured beauty.  Dark green, malarial
waters cover every inch of land in this small town without road or earth,
only greasy waterways and makeshift rafts to navigate them.

name: A marshy trail
description:

name: A putrid waterway
description:
In place of ordinary streets or roads, this marshy village has only small,
poorly-tended channels that run between the rows of slant-legged houses.
Damaged boats and makeshift rafts clog the waterway in spots, abandoned by
their passengers upon a whim.  The air is thick with the busy hum of insects
and the waters beneath you writhe with vermin.  A bed of smooth-polished
rocks once marked the boundaries of the channel, but all that remains is the
occasional mold-slick marker.  Men and women, many of them from distant lands
and most crazed with drink, float through the village on teetering rafts.
What might once have been a prim, sleepy little village became a major port
with the explosion of the city to the north.  Now Gannyte Shoals is the haunt
of the decadent and rotten, a painted whore of a village, used for pleasure
but never taken as a permanent home.  Broken-down houses stand well above the
water to the south and east, while the waterway continues all around you.

name: Beneath a leaning shack
description:
The slowly rotting shack above you leaves a small square of shade in which
to huddle on a sweltering day.  Hiding from the sun and open air, all manner
of parasitic growth hangs from the shack floor and coats the long, sprawling
legs upon which the home stands.  Filmy ribbons of algae sway back and forth
as the water bobs slightly up and down.  Looking overhead you notice cracks
in the shack floor.  The sounds of smacking and slobbering, chomping and
grunting come to you, the unmistakable music of a meal being ravenously
devoured.  The delicious aroma of roasting meats mingles with the rancid
stench of the stagnant water to make a powerfully repulsive scent linger in
this spot.

name: Sandy docks
description:

north.  The beating of the waves has washed up sand and debris to form a kind
of embankment, upon which the villagers have built a long wooden dock that

village.  Houses held above the water on long, sprawling stilts stand gape-
windowed in various stages of decay.  The wretched cries of children mingle
with the screeching of whores and revelers to make a sad, decadent music.

name: A corner of the village
description:
The land rises slightly, emerging to form a dense forest to the north and
east.  From this vantage point, you can see most of the village.  From afar
the picture of debauchery loses all its wicked glamour, merging into a hazy
picture of sadness. Desperate lives scatter back and forth across the
teetering walkways.  Pathetic tragedy plunges into the mold-green waters.
Little fishing boats would once have bustled to and fro in this village,
going out to sea for a day's work and returning with a hearty catch.  Now
worm-eaten fragments of these boats float the waterways.  A sense of the
profound loss washes over you.

name: A corner of the village
description:
The land rises slightly, emerging to form a dense forest to the south,
north, and west.  From this vantage point, you can see most of the village.
From afar the picture of debauchery loses all its wicked glamour, merging
into a hazy picture of sadness. Desperate lives scatter back and forth across
the teetering walkways.  Pathetic tragedy plunges into the mold-green waters.

name: Beneath a leaning shack
description:
The slowly rotting shack above you leaves a small square of shade in which
to huddle on a sweltering day.  Hiding from the sun and open air, all manner
of parasitic growth hangs from the shack floor and coats the long, sprawling
legs upon which the home stands.  Filmy ribbons of algae sway back and forth
as the water bobs slightly up and down.  Looking overhead you notice cracks
in the shack floor.   Only the stench of old liquor and the stentorian roar
of a man's snoring come to you through those cracks.  The land rises around
you to the north, east, and south.  To the west lies the stagnant waters of
the village.

name: In murky water
description:
Beneath the greasy surface of the water, beneath floating debris and filmy
sheets of algae, the swamp waters of the village surround you.  Refuse of all
kinds rest on the murky bottom, covered with sludge, few things identifiable.
The filthy pollution of broken bottles, decaying wood, and human waste dumped
from the shacks above makes for dark waters. Looking around to the distance,
you notice the monotony of darkness and waterlogged trash broken by the
occasional wooden pole, driven deep into the ground to support the shacks
above.  The water recedes to the north and west, yielding to soggy land.

kinds rest on the murky bottom, covered with sludge, few things identifiable.
The filthy pollution of broken bottles, decaying wood, and human waste dumped
from the shacks above makes for dark waters. Looking around to the distance,
you notice the monotony of darkness and waterlogged trash broken by the
occasional wooden pole, driven deep into the ground to support the shacks
above.  The water continues in every direction.

name: The Gate Before the Tower
description:
The clouds are heavy and dark around this huge, crudely designed rock tower.
Shrill cries can be heard far above coming from an unknown source. Before you
is a huge silver gate, behind which lies the Dragon Tower. To the west is a
dark grove.

name: The Foyer of the Tower
description:
Dark candles rest in holders on the walls. The foyer of the tower is a decent
sized hall as your footsteps echo loudly throughout it. Grand tapestries hang
from the walls adorned with fine fabrics from around the world. There are
three doors to the north, east and west. To the south is the gate to the
tower.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the south is a doorway and to the north the hall continues.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the north and south the hallway continues.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the south the hallway continues and to the north the hallway ends
at two doors.

name: Hall's end
description:
The air in this room is well insolated. Warm and dry. The walls themselves
seem to have been created magically. The doors to your east and west are
both made of the strong wood of Arkham while to the south a hall continues.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the west is a door and to the east the hall turns.

name: A turn in the hallway
description:
Torches adorn the walls in ornate holders that sparkle with rare gems and
stones. The hallways from the west and south meet here in a junction that
lets you go in either direction.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the north you notice the hall forms a turn and to the south there
is a split in the hallway.

name: At a junction
description:
The hallway here connects with another hallway making a three-way junction.
The walls are cold to the touch and made of some strange, glass-like material
that sends a chill down your spine. To the east a hallway breaks away from
the north-south hallway.

stones. The hallways from the west and north meet here in a junction that
let's you go in both directions.

description:

touch. To the east is a junction and to the west the hall ends.

name: the dead end
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. Abruptly, the hallway comes to an end here, though there is faint
scuffing on the floor.

name: a small tunnel
description:
Dust covers the floor and fills the air in this small and cramped tunnel.
Looking up you see that a light shines through from above.

name: a small tunnel
description:
Dust covers the floor and fills the air in this small and cramped tunnel.
The dropping of water can be heard off in the distance which begins to
slowly tear away at your mind. The silence... The water...

name: a small tunnel's end
description:
The dust in this end of the tunnel is a little less frequent than it is
off to the east. The dropping of water is much louder here and your mind
races with ways to escape this madness. To the east the hallway continues.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. The hallway continues to the north and west while to the east is a
door.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the west is a junction in the hallway while to the east the hallway
continues.

description:

The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the west and east the hallway continues.

description:

The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the west and east the hallway continues.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the west the hallway continues and to the east there is a junction
in the hallway.

name: At a junction
description:
Two hallways connect here, making a three-way junction. The walls are made of
a strange, glass-like material that is cold to the touch and sends a chill
down your spine. To the west a hallway breaks away to the north while to the
south there is a tunnel.

name: an ice-covered tunnel
description:
The walls in this tunnel are strangely covered in ice. Fog covers the floor
making it difficult to see where your feet are. Loud cries and shreaks can
be heard from a general southern direction. To the north there is a junction
in the tunnel.

name: an ice-covered tunnel
description:
The walls in this tunnel are strangely covered in ice. Fog covers the floor
making it difficult to see where your feet are. Loud cries and shreaks can
be heard from a general southern direction.

name: an ice-covered tunnel
description:
The walls in this tunnel are strangely covered in ice. Fog covers the floor
making it difficult to see where your feet are. Loud cries and shreaks can
be heard from a general southern direction. The tunnel makes a turn here to
the east where it meets with a stairway.

name: an ice-covered Stairway
description:
The tunnel here comes to an end as it connects to a stairway leading into the
depths of the Tower. An ice-covered railing leading down helps with the
stairs so you do not slip, although since it is covered with ice as well, you
wonder how much aid it would give.

name: an ice-covered Stairway
description:
Ice covers everything around you and the chilly air bites at your skin. It
seems the further down you go, the colder it gets. An ice-covered railing
follows the steps up and down with you, but you wonder how much aid it would
provide since it is frozen, as well.

name: an ice-covered Stairway
description:
The tunnel here comes to an end as it connects to a stairway leading up into
the Tower. An ice-covered railing leading up helps with the stairs so you do
not slip, although since it is covered with ice as well, you wonder how much
aid it would give.

name: an ice-covered tunnel
description:
The walls in this tunnel are strangely covered in ice. Fog covers the floor
making it difficult to see where your feet are. Loud cries and shreaks can
be heard to the east of here, while to the west you see a stairway.

name: an ice-covered tunnel
description:
The walls in this tunnel are strangely covered in ice. Fog covers the floor
making it difficult to see where your feet are. Loud cries and shreaks can
be heard to the east of here.

name: an ice-covered tunnel
description:
The walls in this tunnel are strangely covered in ice. Fog covers the floor
making it difficult to see where your feet are. Loud cries and shreaks can
be heard directly east of here. It looks as though the tunnel opens up into
a cave, the lair of some beast.

name: The Ice-Covered Cave
description:
Ice covers everything in this room. The high ceiling reaches almost into the
heavens as you stare in awe at the intricate murals and sculptures chiseled
into the ice. The cold air in this room makes it perfect home to the large
and ancient white dragon.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the south there is a junction in the hallway, while to the north
the hallway makes a turn.

name: A turn in the hallway
description:
Torches adorn the walls in ornate holders that sparkle with rare gems and
stones. The hallways from the east and south meet here in a junction that
let's you go in both directions.

description:

description:

description:

description:

description:

name: A turn in the hallway
description:

name: A stairway
description:
A cold drip can be heard off in a corner somewhere as you notice how
dark and lonely this small corner of the Tower is. Some type of diamond
material has been carved and placed in a way that you can climb up them
like stairs. To the east is a hallway.

name: Top of a stairway
description:
Strange shimmering scales cover the walls at the top of this stairway. A
railing resembling the tail of some huge dragon beast follows the stairs
down below. To the west the hallway follows to a turn.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the east there is a stairway and to the west is a turn in the
hallway.

description:

description:

name: the bottom of a stairway
description:
This stairway is very hot and humid in a way that is very uncomfortable.
The steps themselves look as though they were melted from the rock instead
of having been carved. A hallway is to the east and you can go up the steps.

name: A hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very warm to the
touch. A stairway has been cut from the floor and leads down into darkness,
while to the east the warm temperature seems to rise.

name: A hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very hot to the
touch. Fierce and shrill cries can be heard coming from a dark cave to the
north, as does a thick stream of smoke, while to the west the hallway comes
to an end.

name: The Flaming Cave
description:
This large room before you is much, much hotter than the previous few rooms
you've had to endure. Flames spill forth from holes in the ground and you
notice in the corner of the cave a large pile of scorched bones.

touch. To the north and south the hallway continues.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the south you notice the hallway has stopped, but continues to the
north. The floor here has some strange scratches on it.

name: a Long, Dark Ladder
description:
This ladder looks as black as midnight, and twice as mysterious. It almost
seems to shift into and out of reality, melting into the shadows at times
making it increasingly difficult to climb. You notice it continues down into
the darkness and up towards an exit.

name: a Long, Dark Ladder
description:
This ladder looks as black as midnight, and twice as mysterious. It almost
seems to shift into and out of reality, melting into the shadows at times
making it increasingly difficult to climb. You notice it continues down into
the darkness and up towards an exit.

name: a dark tunnel
description:
The lack of torches or lanterns in this small tunnel merely impairs your
vision, as your eyes soon adjust to the darkness. On the far wall there is a
ladder made of a strange material that leads up towards the rest of the
tower. To the south you hear strange noises coming from a dark cave.

name: The Dark Cave
description:
As with the tunnel leading into this cave, the darkness here is quite
overwhelming. Seemingly the home of every shadow and shape available, the
darkness toys with your mind. You seem to float in and out of consciousness
and lose sense of what is real and what isn't. It is very obvious that this
cave is one of magical construct, and the creator must have been quite a
mage.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the north, west, and south are iron-bound doors, all with strange,
draconian symbols on them.

name: the Royal Quarters
description:
Ancient draconian paintings, framed in sculpted dwarven iron adorn the walls
of this grand bedroom. A very large bed glowing of wealth and power sits in
the middle of the room, it's canopy long and glamorous. Jewels and rare gems
rest atop a bedstand that is in the far corner of this room. A large, dark-
elven rug, woven of the finest silk covers most of the floor. To the south
is an iron-bound door.

name: The Guest Room
description:
This is the standard draconian guest room. One bed, one dresser, a decent
sized mirror covers the east wall. Various semi-valuable paintings hang
here and there on the walls. The only strange thing is that this certain
guest seems to be quite a mage, having spent hours of deep meditation and
concentration, he has opened a portal in the west wall. You wonder if it is
a temporary portal for while the mage stays here, or if he has taken up
residence in the Tower and will be here indefinately.  A crackling portal
shimmers on the wall here.

name: The Guest Room
description:
This is the standard draconian guest room. One bed, one dresser, a decent
sized mirror covers the east wall. Various semi-valuable paintings hang
here and there on the walls. The only strange thing is that this certain
guest seems to be a dark and deadly assassin. Knives and daggers rest in
pools of dried blood and poison. You wonder if it was a good idea to come
here when you glance around the various instruments he uses in killing.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the east and west the hallway continues.

name: At a junction
description:
Two hallways connect here, making a three-way junction. The walls are made of
a strange, glass-like material that is cold to the touch and sends a chill
down your spine. To the north a hallway breaks away to the east and west
hallways.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the east and west the hallway continues while to the south is an
iron-bound door.

name: The Guest Room
description:
This is the standard draconian guest room. One bed, one dresser, a decent
sized mirror covers the east wall. Various semi-valuable paintings hang
here and there on the walls. The only strange thing is that this certain
guest isn't what you'd expect to find in a place like this; a Ranger of the
forests. Books of peace and the forests clutter the floor, as do many various
plants from all around Shalar. You wonder why such a man would be visiting
this tower.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the east it looks like the hallway ends and to the west it
continues.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. A heavy, black iron trapdoor sits tightly against the stone floor.

name: the dark corridor
description:
Around the corner to the east comes a loud growl, almost shaking pieces of
the acid pitted walls to the floor. The smell of a nauseating sulfuric gas
hangs heavy in the air. The floor, like the cold, dark walls around you is
pitted in many places as well. Above, you see a heavy, black iron trapdoor
leading up into the rest of the Tower.

name: the dark corridor
description:
In a southern direction comes a loud growl, almost shaking pieces of the acid
pitted walls to the floor. The smell of a nauseating sulfuric gas hangs heavy
in the air. The floor, like the cold, dark walls around you is pitted in many
places as well.

name: the dark corridor
description:
In a southern direction comes a loud growl, almost shaking pieces of the acid
pitted walls to the floor. The smell of a nauseating sulfuric gas hangs heavy
in the air. The floor, like the cold, dark walls around you is pitted in many
places as well.

name: the dark corridor
description:
In a western direction comes a loud growl, almost shaking pieces of the acid
pitted walls to the floor. The smell of a nauseating sulfuric gas hangs heavy
in the air. The floor, like the cold, dark walls around you is pitted in many
places as well. The corridor opens up to the west of here, leading into a
large cave of some sort.

name: The Acid Pools
description:
The power of the fumes from the pools is so thick and nauseating that you
almost turn back. Acid pours from holes in the walls and fills the pools,
which in turn flow into a small stream of acid that follows around the floor.
The walls of this large cave seem to have been protected somehow, because
they seem almost pristine in their dark nature.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the north you notice a large and glamorous stairway.

name: the Large Stairway
description:
Marvelous jewels, gems and dragonscales adorn the bannister of an ivory carved
railing that follows the steps up to the next floor. The smell of a fine
smelling dinner wafts in from above, making your mouth tingle with a need to
taste.

name: the Large Stairway
description:
Marvelous jewels, gems and dragonscales adorn the bannister of an ivory carved
railing that follows the steps down to the next floor. The smell of a fine
smelling dinner wafts in from around you, making your mouth tingle with a
need to taste. You also notice a long table, extended full length through
this large hall leading north a bit and extended west.

name: Around the Dining Table
description:
As you progress around this very large table, you notice many fine wines and
foods, some of which you sample, that originate from around the world. The
Draconian King probably hopes this display of wealth will impress any of the
visiting guests. You notice all the chairs at this table have been removed,
giving you the impression that it is more like a buffet table, rather than a
fancy dining room. To the northwest you notice the King's throne.

name: Around the Dining Table
description:
As you progress around this very large table, you notice many fine wines and
foods, some of which you sample, that originate from around the world. The
Draconian King probably hopes this display of wealth will impress any of the
visiting guests. You notice all the chairs at this table have been removed,
giving you the impressing that it is more like a buffet table, rather than a
fancy dining room. To the north you notice the King's throne.

description:

foods, some of which you sample, that originate from around the world. The
Draconian King probably hopes this display of wealth will impress any of the
visiting guests. You notice all the chairs at this table have been removed,
giving you the impressing that it is more like a buffet table, rather than a
fancy dining room. To the northeast you see the King's throne.

foods, some of which you sample, that originate from around the world. The
Draconian King probably hopes this display of wealth will impress any of the
visiting guests. You notice all the chairs at this table have been removed,
giving you the impressing that it is more like a buffet table, rather than a
fancy dining room. To the northeast you notice the King's throne.
