Draconian King probably hopes this display of wealth will impress any of the
visiting guests. You notice all the chairs at this table have been removed,
giving you the impressing that it is more like a buffet table, rather than a
fancy dining room. To the east you notice the King's throne.

name: Around the Dining Table
description:
As you progress around this very large table, you notice many fine wines and
foods, some of which you sample, that originate from around the world. The
Draconian King probably hopes this display of wealth will impress any of the
visiting guests. You notice all the chairs at this table have been removed,
giving you the impressing that it is more like a buffet table, rather than a
fancy dining room. To the east you notice the King's throne.

name: The Throne
description:
Great scales of ancient dragons adorned with jewels of the finest quality
form the enormous throne before you. Cushioned with pillows so that the king
is more comfortable, it radiates high quality. From this particular part of
the room, you can see why the king's negotiating skills are to be reckoned
with. The throne is raised a bit higher than the rest of the chairs, giving
the king a strategic look of great importance.

name: Around the Dining Table
description:
As you progress around this very large table, you notice many fine wines and
foods, some of which you sample, that originate from around the world. The
Draconian King probably hopes this display of wealth will impress any of the
visiting guests. You notice all the chairs at this table have been removed,
giving you the impressing that it is more like a buffet table, rather than a
fancy dining room. To the west you notice the King's throne.

name: Around the Dining Table
description:
As you progress around this very large table, you notice many fine wines and
foods, some of which you sample, that originate from around the world. The
Draconian King probably hopes this display of wealth will impress any of the
visiting guests. You notice all the chairs at this table have been removed,
giving you the impression that it is more like a buffet table, rather than a
fancy dining room. To the west you notice the King's throne.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the south you see what looks to be the back of a throne. To the
north you notice a large stairway.

name: the Large Stairway
description:
Just as the strange glass-like material are of the walls, so is it of the
stairs that lead up, towards the very heights of the tower. A loud screech
pierces the air and sends a shiver down your spine. Following the long climb
up, you notice a dragonscale railing disappearing above you with the stairs.

name: the Stairs
description:
Just as the strange glass-like material are of the walls, so is it of the
stairs that lead up, towards the very heights of the tower. A loud screech
pierces the air and sends a shiver down your spine. Following the long climb
up, you notice a dragonscale railing disappearing above you with the stairs.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. A dragonscale railing comes up out of a hole in the floor formed by
the stairs that have been cut there.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the east and west the hallway continues.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the east the hallway continues while to the west the hallway seems
to cloud with a strange gas.

name: The cloudy hallway
description:
The hallway becomes increasingly difficult to breathe in as a thick, noxious
gas floats in from the cave to the west. Your eyes burn as you stand here,
contemplating what to do next. The walls here glow with a strange, dark,
ethereal brilliance. To the east the clouds of gas clear up and to the west
is a large cave.

name: the Smoke-filled Cave
description:
Clouds of poisonous gas fill this enormous cave. Breathing in this cave is
very difficult, as your mind is plagued with pain and headaches. The cave
itself was carved out of the same stone as the tower and the gas here seems
to keep any scratches or disruptions in the wall from being permanent. To the
east the clouds of smoke are a little less dense.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the east and west the hallway continues.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the east and west the hallway continues while in the far corner you
notice a ladder which leads up.

name: the base of the High Tower
description:
Immediately you sense you are in a hall of great importance. Glowing rocks
frame grand paintings of large dragons hang on the north and south walls,
while to the west you see the base of this enormous tower extends. The room
shakes a bit as you hear loud stomping and crashing coming from far above.
You notice there is a ladder leading down.

name: the base of the High Tower
description:
Immediately you sense you are in a hall of great importance. Glowing rocks
frame grand paintings of large dragons hang on the north and south walls,
while to the east you see the base of this enormous tower extends. The room
shakes a bit as you hear loud stomping and crashing coming from far above.
You notice there is a ladder leading up.

name: the bone-filled hallway
description:
Bones, picked clean of the flesh, blood, and any other things that used to
cover them. Stacked high and haphazardly, many fall and land near your feet.
The smell of the flesh and dried blood, unfortunately, was not removed. The
smell is repulsing and gives you a deep sense of doom to come. Whatever beast
could have made these... things it's dinner, is quite dangerous indeed. You
also notice a ladder leading down.

name: the bone-filled hallway
description:
Bones, picked clean of the flesh, blood, and any other things that used to
cover them. Stacked high and haphazardly, many fall and land near your feet.
The smell of the flesh and dried blood, unfortunately, was not removed. The
smell is repulsing and gives you a deep sense of doom to come. Whatever beast
could have made these... things it's dinner, is quite dangerous indeed.

name: the bone-filled Chamber
description:
This chamber, like the hallway to the south has many bones, picked clean of
the flesh, blood, and any other things that used to cover them. Stacked high
and haphazardly, many fall and land near your feet. The smell of the flesh and
dried blood, unfortunately, was not removed. The smell is repulsing and gives
you a deep sense of doom to come. Whatever beast could have made these...
things it's dinner, is quite dangerous indeed. To the north there is a large,
strange looking gate.

name: the Lair of Tiamat
description:
Dark storm clouds can be seen about here since the roof of this grand lair
has been removed. The lair of Tiamat is truely extraordinary. From this
height you can see all of the Shadow Grove below you, making you dizzy from
it's strange randomness. Lightning crackles and strikes the side of the tower
shaking it and knocking a few bones loose of a pile in the corner. The lair
itself seems to have been flown up here, rather than built or carved from
stone, since it's make up is truely magical in nature. The walls themselves
vibrate with strange energy around you, filling your soul with a strange
feeling.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the east and west the hallway continues.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the east the hallway turns while to the west it continues.

name: A turn in the hallway
description:
Torches adorn the walls in ornate holders that sparkle with rare gems and
stones. The hallways from the west and north meet here in a junction that
let's you go in both directions.

name: A turn in the hallway
description:
Torches adorn the walls in ornate holders that sparkle with rare gems and
stones. The hallways from the east and south meet here in a junction that
let's you go in both directions.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the west the hallway turns a bit and you see a ladder that leads
down. Looking down, you notice that it looks a bit longer than you'd prefer.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the east the hallway continues and you see a ladder that leads
up. Looking up, you notice that it looks a bit longer than you'd prefer.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the east the hallway turns and to the west down the hallway you
notice a ladder leading up.

name: A turn in the hallway
description:
Torches adorn the walls in ornate holders that sparkle with rare gems and
stones. The hallways from the west and south meet here in a junction that
let's you go in both directions.

name: A turn in the hallway
description:
Torches adorn the walls in ornate holders that sparkle with rare gems and
stones. The hallways from the east and north meet here in a junction that
let's you go in both directions.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the west the hallway turns and to the east down the hallway you
notice a ladder leading up.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the west the hallway continues and you see a ladder that leads
up. Looking up, you notice that it looks a bit longer than you'd prefer.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the north the hallway continues and you see a ladder that leads
down. Looking down, you notice that it looks a bit longer than you'd prefer.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the north the hallway continues, while to the south you notice a
ladder leading down.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the north you see the roof has been torn from the hallway and a
dark storm outside surrounds the tower.

name: the hallway
description:
A low rumbling can be heard through this hallway from an unknown direction.
The walls are made of a strange glass-like material, yet very cold to the
touch. To the north you see the roof has been torn from the hallway, as well
as a chamber a bit further north.

name: the torn hallway
description:
The wind picks up as you enter this loud and chaotic hallway. Dust and rain
fly wildly through the air, burning your skin. It is difficult to see, but
you get the feeling that somehow a storm was brought here and made to stay,
raging and tearing at this tower and you, it's only enemy.

name: the Lightning Chamber
description:
Without a roof, this chamber becomes a perfect home for a dragon. The fact
that a permanent storm has been transfered here, throwing lightning, rain and
other articles crashing around the chamber another story. A flash of a bright
lightning bathes the room in a blue light, almost making you forget the storm
itself. The wind shakes the roofless tower violently, making you hope that
the magic that built it holds out.

name: Udgaard's Mud School Lobby
description:
You stand in a posh lobby.  A ladder is leading down here.  Through a
door to the north, you see the famous courtyard of Udgaard.

name: The South East Corner of the Courtyard
description:
You stand in the south east corner of the courtyard.  A young traveler
walking south towards the mud school lobby kicks up a cloud of dirt.  A more
seasoned traveller heads east into Torden's Arms.

name: The Eastern End of the Courtyard
description:
You stand in the east courtyard entrance.  To the east lies East Street.
To the north, south and west is more of the courtyard.  From the west you
hear the sounds of slave trade.

name: Torden's Arms
description:
Surrounding you are Torden's Creations.  The room is filled with both
weapons and armor of extraordinary quality.  The only thing that impresses
you more than the goods are their price tags.  A sign hangs on the wall.

name: The North East Corner of the Courtyard
description:
You stand in the north east corner of the courtyard.  The Dark Temple of
Udgaard lies to the north.  The great temple staircase leads into the Dark
Clerics' Guild.  To the east is an entrance into Udgaard Loke's Palace.  To
the west and south is more of the courtyard.

name: The Southern End of the Courtyard
description:
As you enter the southern end of the courtyard, you are awestruck by the
size of the Dark Temple to the north.  Even more overwhelming is the Palace
of Udgaard Loke which towers above it.  To the north you hear the sounds of
slave trade.

name: East Street
description:
You walk along east street.  To the west is the courtyard.  To the east
is the intersection of East street and Jade street.  Above you, to the
north, looms Udgaard Loke's palace.

name: The Center of the Courtyard
description:
An enormous black stone block rests in the center of the courtyard.  On
the block stands the slave auctioneer, selling his wares.  Next to him,
chained to the stone, kneel the slaves.  You look to one, but see only a
humbled and broken individual.  All around you is the courtyard.  There is
writing etched on the stone.

name: Slave Room
description:
This is the room that all the slaves are kept in, it is vital that it
is immediately after the slave shop.

name: The Northern End of the Courtyard
description:
You stand in the Northern courtyard.  The great temple staircase leads
north into the Dark Temple.  To the east and west continues the great
staircase.  To the south you here the sounds of the slave trade.

name: South Street
description:
You are at the northern end of South Street.  To the north lies the famous
courtyard of Udgaard Loke's Farm.  To the south lies the intersection of
Bloodstone Lane and South Street.

name: The South West Corner of the Courtyard
description:
You stand in the south west corner of the courtyard.  The Justice members
of the town gather here to discuss the law.  A pit has been dug in the
courtyard for the sole purpose of settling disputes which the law cannot
resolve.  To the south lies the town courthouse.  West of here is the town
mess hall.  To the north and east is more of the courtyard.

name: The Intersection of East Street and Jade Lane
description:
You stand at the three way intersection of East Street and Jade Lane. 
Jade Lane leads south, while East Street continues east and west.  To the
north Udgaard Loke's Palace looms above you.

name: The Western End of the Courtyard
description:
You stand in the west courtyard entrance.  To the west lies West Street. 
To the north, south and east is more of the courtyard.  From the east you
hear the sounds of slave trade.

name: The Dark Temple
description:
You are in the Dark Temple of Udgaard.  Black marble columns line huge
hallways leading west to the Anti-Paladins' Guild and east to the Dark
Clerics' Guild.  The darkness of the room seems to creep upon you and the
floor seems colder than it naturally should be.  The temple is attended by
the Afskyelige, a cult of child priests.  You assume their altar is to the
north, in the temple's inner sanctum.  You decide not to enter.... Some
things are better left unseen.

name: The North West Corner of the Courtyard
description:
You stand in the north west corner of the courtyard.  The Dark Udgaard
Temple lies to the north.  The great temple staircase leads into the
Anti-Paladins' Guild.  To the west is an entrance into Udgaard Loke's
Palace.  To the east and south is more of the courtyard.

name: The Intersection of Bloodstone Lane and South Street
description:
To the east and west runs Bloodstone Lane.  To the north and south runs
South Street.

name: The Town Courthouse
description:
This is the judicial center of the law within this town.  Each judge sits
behind his thick wooden bench hearing cases.  You notice that the trials are
remarkably short and the sentences are remarkably long.

name: The Challenge Pit
description:
Fingernails left in the walls tell the tale of the ultimate justice
served here.  The remains of corpses still lie armed here.  A sign hangs
from the side of the pit....

name: The Mess Hall
description:
This area feeds the members of Udgaard Loke's army.  Long, heavy tables
are filled with soldiers of every race and class.  Their only unifying
feature is their alliance to evil.  To the east is the courtyard, while the
messhall continues to the west.  To the south a Jaette guard watches a large
wooden doorway.  Above the door a sign reads, \JAETTES ONLY!!\"

name: West Street
description:
You walk along West Street.  To the west lies the intersection of West
Street and Obsidian Lane and to the east lies the Eastern Courtyard.  North
of you looms Udgaard Loke's Palace, while to the south lies the mess hall of
his troops.

name: The Anti-Paladin's Guild
description:
You step into your guild house.  Several Knights of Legion are relaxing
here.  They bear the ensignia of high rank within Udgaard Loke's army.  You
ponder whether abiding by Loke's laws is worth the favor he gives
Anti-Paladins in his army of evil.

name: Bloodstone Lane
description:
You walk along Bloodstone Lane.  To the north is the rich exterior of the
Bank of Udgaard.  To the south, Jorgen's Gems awaits your business. 
Bloodstone Lane continues east, while the intersection of Bloodstone Lane
and South Street lies to the west.

name: The Intersection of South Street and Onyx Lane
description:
You stand at the intersection of South Street and Onyx Lane.  South
Street continues north, and to the south is the south gate.  Onyx Lane leads
east and west.  A few lines of writing are buried under the dust here.

name: Bloodstone Lane
description:
To the north you see a busy shop called Thorne's Sharps.  From the south
a delicious aroma from Kron's Spits invites your fancy.  Bloodstone lane
continues east, and meets an intersection with South Street to the west.

name: The Private Jaette Mess Hall
description:
You look around to see only Jaettes here.  Perhaps you have gone the
wrong direction.  The Jaettes seem upset at your intrusion.  Better get out
fast!  To the north is the large wooden doorway.

name: The Mess Hall
description:
This area feeds the members of Udgaard Loke's army.  Long, heavy tables
are filled with soldiers of every race and class.  Their only unifying
feature is their alliance to evil.  To the north is West Street.  To the
west is Obsidian Lane, while the mess hall continues to the east.

name: Intersection of West Street and Obsidian Lane
description:
You stand at the three way intersection of West Street and Obsidian Lane.
Obsidian Lane leads south, while West Street continues east and west.  To
the north Udgaard Loke's Palace looms above you.

name: The Bank of Udgaard
description:
Rich tapestries hang from the walls of this wealthy establishment. 
Mahogany desks are scattered about the room.  The pompous decadence suggests
to you that things come to those who want.  A silver plaque hangs on the
wall.

name: Bloodstone Lane
description:
You continue along Bloodstone Lane.  Too the north is the Circle Cafe. 
To the south is a large guard post.

name: Jorgen's Gems
description:
Unlike most jewelers you have been to, the jewels here are not in glass
cases.  Rather, they sit out upon the tables in the store.  Truly, this town
respects the law.

name: The Intersection of East Street and Marble Lane
description:
East Street leads to the west.  To the north and south runs Marble Lane. 
To the east is the east gate.

name: Jade Lane
description:
Mages walk all about this part of town.  To the west you see the Boiling
Cauldron, a magic user's bar.  To the east is the Magic Arcade.  Jade lane
continues to the north and south.

name: Onyx Lane
description:
You walk along Onyx Lane.  You are flanked on the south by the thick
spear wall surrounding Udgaard Loke's Farm, and on the north by the western
warriors' guild.

name: The South Gate of Udgaard Loke's Farm
description:
Flanked by twin towers, an enormous stone gateway rises to protect the
city.  A darkened steel portcullis here serves to close the gates when
necessary.  Jutting out of the thick grating, huge spikes fend off would-be
assailants.  Archer's slits look down into the gateway, to finish off any
unfortunate attackers.  Behind the portcullis, studded metal doorways lead
into the towers.

name: Onyx Lane
description:
You walk along Onyx Lane.  To the north you see the entrance to the
Tested Traveller.  The thick spear wall which surrounds Udgaard Loke's Farm
is to your south.

name: Thorne's Sharps
description:
Various weapons fill the racks hanging on the walls of this weapons shop.
Battered straw dummies are scattered about the room.  At each dummy, a
patron tests some of the store's wares.  A sign hangs from the wall here.

name: Kron's Spits
description:
You almost choke as you enter this store.  Dense smoke billows from spits
turning over numerous fires.  Geez, you'd think Kron would put in a chimney.
Ahh, but the food looks good.... A sign hangs from the wall here.

name: Bloodstone Lane
description:
Bloodstone Lane continues to the east and west.  To the north is the
Bear's Claw Cafe.  To the south is a large guard post.

name: Obsidian Lane
description:
You are on Obsidian Lane.  To the west are the town stables.  To the east
is the town mess hall.  Obsidian lane continues to north and south.

name: The Intersection of West Street and Turquoise Lane
description:
West Street leads to the east.  To the north and south runs Turquoise
Lane.  To the west is the west gate.

name: The Circle Cafe
description:
So named for the shape of it's famous pastries, the Circle Cafe is know
throughout Shalar.  It is especially known by the guards who come from the
guardhouse across the street.  A long counter stretches across the cafe,
with customers lined up on seats along it.  A small sign hangs from the
wall.

name: A Turn
description:
You are at the turn between Bloodstone Lane and Jade Lane.  Bloodstone
Lane continues west, while Jade Lane continues north.  A large guard house
lies to the south, and a furniture shop lies to the east.

name: A Guard House
description:
Similar in appearance to a barracks, this guardhouse is little more than
a long hall of beds.  A Jaette Anti-Paladin keeps order here with suprising
efficiency.  He glares at you for a moment, then realizes you are not a
stray guard and dismisses you.

name: Marble Lane
description:
Marble Lane runs north and south of here, following the wall around the
city.  A wall of foot-wide spears stands to the east, framing the city
within it's dangerous ramparts.  To the west the battlements of Udgaard
Loke's palace rise, towering above an entrance into the palace.

name: The East Gate of Udgaard Loke's Farm
description:
Flanked by twin towers, an enormous stone gateway rises to protect the
city.  A darkened steel portcullis here serves to close the gates when
necessary.  Jutting out of the thick grating, huge spikes fend off would-be
assailants.  Archer's slits look down into the gateway, to finish off any
unfortunate attackers.  Behind the portcullis, studded metal doorways lead
into the towers.

name: Marble Lane
description:
Marble Lane runs north and south of here, following the wall around the
city.  A wall of foot-wide spears stands to the east, framing the city
within it's dangerous ramparts.  To the west, the Magic Arcade welcomes you.

name: The Magic Arcade
description:
This broad hallway connects Marble Lane and Jade lane.  Two of the local
mages have taken advantage of the continuous traffic between these streets
to create their thriving businesses.  The Necromancer's Delight lies to the
north, and The Liquid Gate lies to the south.

name: Jade Lane
description:
Many mages wander in this area.  To the east, a worn building with
cracked walls and shattered windows advertises, \Thieves' Guild\".

area_id: Conversely
room_id: to the west a small sign swings over a prospering weapons repair

area_id: shop.  Jade Lane continues north and south.

name: The Boiling Cauldron
description:
True to it's name a huge cauldron of a dark liquid boils behind the
counter.  As customers order, the bartender dips a skull ladle into the
cauldron and fills their cups.  All types of mages congregate here,
comparing notes and chatting with acquaintances.  There is a small sign on
the wall here.

name: The Western Warrior's Guild
description:
The only brick buildings in town, the Warrior's guild is one of the most
well kept establishments in the area.  A slate roof protects this guild from
even the worst weather, and the members tirelessly keep this guild clean and
safe.  Several large warriors stand outside the entrance, examining those
who enter.  Many others sit inside on comfortable stools, swapping tales. 
There is a rope ladder leading up to the Drilling Room.

name: Onyx Lane
description:
You walk along Onyx Lane.  You are flanked on the south by the thick
spear wall surrounding Udgaard Loke's Farm, and on the north by the eastern
warriors' guild.  Onyx lane continues to the east and west.

name: Base of a Gate Tower
description:
Cold and dark, these towers stand guard against Udgaard Loke's enemies. 
Many a OneHeart Warrior has died while trying to storm their walls.  There
is a wooden ladder leading up.

name: Outside the South Gate
description:
A foreboding wall of spears expands east and west from an enormous stone
gate to the north.  Guards patrolling the wall cry out to you to identify
your business in Udgaard Loke's Farm.  In the distance, you see a wooden
palace rise from within the city.

name: Base of a Gate Tower
description:
Cold and dark, these towers stand guard against Udgaard Loke's enemies. 
Many a OneHeart Warrior has died while trying to storm their walls.  There
is a wooden ladder leading up.

name: The Tested Traveller
description:
This store caters to the needs of travelers within Udgaard.  All sorts of
containers, light sources, and other general needs imported from the master
craftsmen of Shalar are sold here.  The store leads west to a teller.

name: Onyx Lane
description:
You walk along Onyx Lane.  The thick spear wall which surrounds Udgaard
Loke's Farm is to your south.  To the north you see the exit from the Tested
Traveller.

name: The Bear's Claw Cafe
description:
So named for the shape of it's famous pastries, The Bear's Claw Cafe is
know throughout Shalar.  It is especially known by the guards who come from
the guardhouse across the street.  A long counter stretches across the cafe,
with customers lined up on seats along it.  A small sign hangs from the
wall.

name: A Guard House
description:
Similar in appearance to a barracks, this guardhouse is little more than
a long hall of beds.  A Jaette Anti-Paladin keeps order here with suprising
efficiency.  He glares at you for a moment, then realizes you are not a
stray guard and dismisses you.

name: A Turn
description:
You are at the turn between Bloodstone Lane and Obsidian Lane. 
Bloodstone Lane continues west, while Obsidian Lane continues north.  A
large guard house lies to the south, and a flower shop lies to the west.

name: Obsidian Lane
description:
You stand on Obsidian Lane.  To the west, a rich private home sits, and
to the east is the town pharmacy.  Obsidian Lane continues north and south.

name: The City Stables
description:
Mounds of hay and weeds sit scattered about the room.  Mixed in with the
horses, several Tadarth move restlessly about.  The Tadarth are a type of
carnivorous lizards that the Jaette have domesticated as steeds.  They look
at you hungrily.  A small sign hangs here.

name: Turquoise Lane
description:
Turquoise Lane runs north and south of here, following the wall around
the city.  A wall of foot-wide spears stands to the west, framing the city
within it's dangerous ramparts.  To the east the battlements of Udgaard
Loke's palace rise, towering above an entrance into the palace.

name: Turquoise Lane
description:
Turquoise Lane runs north and south of here, following the wall around
the city.  A wall of foot-wide spears stands to the west, framing the city
within it's dangerous ramparts.  To the east, the smell of fresh baked bread
makes your stomach growl.

name: The West Gate of Udgaard Loke's Farm
description:
Flanked by twin towers, an enormous stone gateway rises to protect the
city.  A darkened steel portcullis here serves to close the gates when
necessary.  Jutting out of the thick grating, huge spikes fend off would-be
assailants.  Archer's slits look down into the gateway, to finish off any
unfortunate attackers.  Behind the portcullis, studded metal doorways lead
into the towers.

name: The Furniture Shop
description:
This shop looks more like a warehouse than a business.  Huge stacks of
chairs, tables, and other furnishings rise stacked to the ceiling.  A small
section of the store is devoted to ships and smaller vessels.  A small sign
hangs on the wall.

name: A Guard House
description:
You are in a guard house.  Everything is well scrubbed and clean. 
Several lower level officers stand here barking orders to their charges.  A
guard looks up wondering why you are here.

name: Marble Lane
description:
Marble Lane runs north and south of here, following the wall around the
city.  A wall of foot-wide spears stands to the east, framing the city
within it's dangerous ramparts.  To the west the battlements of Udgaard
Loke's palace rise.

name: Base of a Gate Tower
description:
Cold and dark, these towers stand guard against Udgaard Loke's enemies. 
Many a OneHeart Warrior has died while trying to storm their walls.  There
is a wooden ladder leading up.

name: Outside the East Gate
description:
A foreboding wall of spears expands north and south from an enormous
stone gate to the west.  Guards patrolling the wall cry out to you to
identify your business in Udgaard Loke's Farm.  In the distance, you see a
wooden palace rise from within the city.  Many of the travellers going to
and from Greenleaf Dale come through these gates.

name: Base of a Gate Tower
description:
Cold and dark, these towers stand guard against Udgaard Loke's enemies. 
Many a OneHeart Warrior has died while trying to storm their walls.  There
is a wooden ladder leading up.

name: Marble Lane
description:
Marble Lane runs north and south of here, following the wall around the
city.  A wall of foot-wide spears stands to the east, framing the city
within it's dangerous ramparts.  To the west, a black edifice pierces the
sky.  A strange symbol rests over its entrance.

name: The Necromancer's Delight
description:
A slight haze hangs in the air here, making it difficult to see the items
for sale.  Slow moving men with glazed eyes restock items on the shelves. 
There is an unholy reek in the air.  A low doorway is visible leading north.
A small sign hangs on the wall.

name: The Liquid Gate
description:
Thick glass tubes wind along the walls.  Colored liquids mix and flow
through the pipes.  The tubes end at brass faucets behind a counter, where
an apprentice fills opaque flasks.  A small sign hangs on the wall.

name: The Broken Hilt
description: A prospering business, The Broken Hilt services those items which \chip

area_id: flake
room_id: or break\" during combat.  A large anvil takes up much of the center

area_id: of the store.  Other blacksmith items lie scattered about.  Soot rises from
the furnace on the southern wall
room_id: while a slave repairs items for customers.

name: The Thieves' Guild
description:
Although still operating, the Thieves' Guild is in poor shape.  Frequent
raids have moved most of this guild's members to Udgaard Loke's Prisons. 
Inside, a single table lies surrounded by broken chairs.  The trapdoor that
used to lead to the guildmaster's secret yard has been smashed, as has the
room beyond.  Now, the guild must operate in this single chamber.  It is
deserted save for a guard posted here.  As you enter, he scribbles something
on a small pad of paper.

name: The Eastern Warriors' Guild
description:
The only brick buildings in town, the Warrior's guild is one of the most
well kept establishments in the area.  A slate roof protects this guild from
even the worst weather, and the members tirelessly keep this guild clean and
safe.  Often, the Eastern Warriors' Guild will house a member of a visiting
clergy.  In return, these priests consecrate the warriors for battle, and
tend to the seriously wounded.

name: The Drilling Room
description:
In this room, practicing warriors duel with each other to learn their
skills.  As they fight, a circle of grizzled warriors led by the guildmaster
evaluates their techniques and gives instruction.  Eventually, when a
warrior has mastered a skill, he is welcomed into the circle to instruct
others.

name: Onyx Lane
description:
You walk along Onyx Lane.  You are flanked on the south by the thick
spear wall surrounding Udgaard Loke's Farm.  To the north a small private
home is nestled among the larger buildings.  Onyx lane continues to the east
and west.

name: The Top of a South Gate Tower
description:
The guards posted on these towers huddle beneath cloaks as a continuous
wind howls through the battlements.  Heavy black cauldrons are settled
amongst the merlons, and archer slits angle onto the plains below.  A small
wooden ladder leads down into the base of the tower.

name: The Top of a South Gate Tower
description:
A lone sentry stands looking south from the remains of this tower. 
Obviously, something very large has attacked this area.  The entire
battlement is in rubble, and men struggle to repair the damage.  Long, deep
claw marks scar the floor.  A small wooden ladder leads down to the base of
the tower.

name: The Tested Traveller
description:
A short line of customers waits for a teller to sum up their purchases. 
Boxes of inventory are being stacked behind the counter, waiting to be
packed onto the shelves.  Rows of goods stretch to the east, and Onyx Lane
lies to the south.  A small sign hangs on the wall.

name: Onyx Lane
description:
You walk along Onyx Lane.  You are flanked on the south by the thick
spear wall surrounding Udgaard Loke's Farm.  To the north are the burnt out
remnants of a building.  Onyx lane continues to the east and west.  A
crooked sign hangs by a single chain here.

name: A Guard House
description:
You are in a guard house.  Everything is well scrubbed and clean. 
Several lower level officers stand here barking orders to their charges.  A
guard looks up wondering why you are here.

name: A private home
description:
Rich candelabras light this house with a soft glow.  Stained glass lets
in light during the day, and carpeting muffles the sound of heavy boots.  A
portrait of the owner hangs above a fireplace, and a bookcase leans against
the wall.

name: The Ivy Patch
description:
Unlike any flower shop you have previously seen, this building is more
like a maze of bushes and weeds.  Out of the corner of your eye you catch a
sharp movement.  As you turn to look, you see a plant bend back into the
shadows.  A small sign hangs on the wall.

name: The Farmacy
description:
A slave stands beside a large pill dispenser.  Vials and pillboxes are
sold near the door, and aisles of pharmaceuticals run the length of the
store.  Several mortar and pestles rest on counters in the rear of the
building.  A small sign hangs on the wall.

name: Turquoise Lane
description:
Turquoise Lane runs north and south of here, following the wall around
the city.  A wall of foot-wide spears stands to the west, framing the city
within it's dangerous ramparts.  To the east the battlements of Udgaard
Loke's palace rise.

name: The Baker's Rise
description:
All the food here is freshly made, and the smells waft out along the
street outside.  Great metal ovens warm this store, releasing bursts of
flame as the workers check their contents.  A delicate glass counter
contains many of breads sold here.  A small sign hangs on the wall.

name: Turquoise Lane
description:
Turquoise Lane runs north and south of here, following the wall around
the city.  A wall of foot-wide spears stands to the west, framing the city
within it's dangerous ramparts.  To the east a wooden shack stands empty.

name: Base of a Gate Tower
description:
Cold and dark, these towers stand guard against Udgaard Loke's enemies. 
Many a OneHeart Warrior has died while trying to storm their walls.  There
is a wooden ladder leading up.

name: Base of a Gate Tower
description:
Cold and dark, these towers stand guard against Udgaard Loke's enemies. 
Many a OneHeart Warrior has died while trying to storm their walls.  There
is a wooden ladder leading up.

name: Outside the West Gate
description:
A foreboding wall of spears expands north and south from an enormous
stone gate to the east.  Guards patrolling the wall cry out to you to
identify your business in Udgaard Loke's Farm.  In the distance, you see a
wooden palace rise from within the city.  You notice that this is by far the
most heavily guarded of the gates, as Udgaard Loke is constantly vigilant
against OneHeart Warrior attacks from their cities west of here.

name: Marble Lane
description:
Marble Lane runs north and south of here, following the wall around the
city.  A wall of foot-wide spears stands to the east, framing the city
within it's dangerous ramparts.  To the west the battlements of Udgaard
Loke's palace rise, towering above an entrance into the palace.

name: The Top of an East Gate Tower
description:
The guards posted on these towers huddle beneath cloaks as a continuous
wind howls through the battlements.  Heavy black cauldrons are settled
amongst the merlons, and archer slits angle onto the plains below.  A small
wooden ladder leads down into the base of the tower.

name: The Top of a South Gate Tower
description:
The guards posted on these towers huddle around the remains of a long
dead fire.  The embers barely glow as the wind continues to blow.  Heavy
black cauldrons are settled amongst the merlons, and archer slits angle onto
the plains below.  A small wooden ladder leads down into the base of the
tower.

name: Marble Lane
description:
Marble Lane runs north and south of here, following the wall around the
city.  A wall of foot-wide spears stands to the east, framing the city
within it's dangerous ramparts.  To the west is the campus of a small
school.

name: The Dark Library
description:
It is easy to become lost within the thousands of scrolls and tomes here.
Small study rooms branch off a main corridor which leads to the circular
desk of the librarian.  For a price, she can help you find much of the
hidden knowledge within this building.  It has been whispered that the
workers of this place no longer carry the concerns of the living.  A small
sign hangs on the wall.

name: The Old Dwarf's Home
description:
An old dwarf of the Horde has built himself a safe haven here.  Within
his house, a small man-made pond surrounds an atrium.  You see Coy fish
lazily swimming within the pond.  This whole area gives a welcome feeling of
relaxation compared to the activity outside.

name: A Turn
description:
You stand at the turn in the road of the cities southeast corner.  A wall
of foot-wide spears stands to the south and east, framing the city within
it's dangerous ramparts.  Marble Lane continues north to the mage's quarter,
and Onyx Lane continues west to the South Gate.

name: The Burned Guildhouse
description:
The charred ruins of a guildhouse fill this ravaged lot.  A raging fire
has gutted this building, leaving nothing save some frayed splotches of
carpeting.  A silver cross lies imbedded in a cracked altar, melted almost
beyond recognition.  Several headless statues of the gods have been toppled
to the ground.

name: The Mages' Guild
description:
Etched upon the walls of this chamber, symbols flicker with energy.  The
room itself seems to groan under the strain of the symbols written upon it. 
A strange pentagram begins to glow upon the north wall as you enter. 
Suddenly, a writhing mist clouds the center of the symbol, and you find you
can see beyond the wall...

name: The Ninja Study
description:
Little physical training goes on in this arena.  The focus of this Dojo
is mastery through mental discipline.  Small rugs are available for
meditation, and incense burns sweetly in the corners of the room.  A few
combatants are scattered about practicing the more physical aspects of their
skills.

name: Turquoise Lane
description:
Turquoise Lane runs north and south of here, following the wall around
the city.  A wall of foot-wide spears stands to the west, framing the city
within it's dangerous ramparts.  To the east the battlements of Udgaard
Loke's palace rise, towering above an entrance into the palace.

name: The Cobbler's Shack
description:
A run down shack barely stands here.  Its wooden walls lean against the
surrounding buildings for support, and you worry about your safety as you
enter.  A makeshift counter is here, formed out of crates and a thin slice
of birch wood.  Although poor, the cobbler has a good reputation for fine
work within this city.

name: Turquoise Lane
description:
Turquoise Lane runs north and south of here, following the wall around
the city.  A wall of foot-wide spears stands to the west, framing the city
within it's dangerous ramparts.  To the east, a dingy bar is the hangout of
the off-duty Jaettes.

name: The Top of a West Gate Tower
description:
You notice that there are many more guards on the western towers than on
the other towers surrounding the city.  The guards posted on these towers
grimace at your arrival, hoping you are a replacement.  The wind is strong
here, and the guards have constructed a temporary shelter which does nothing
more than channel the wind away from them.  Heavy black cauldrons are
settled amongst the merlons, and archer slits angle onto the plains below. 
A small wooden ladder leads down into the base of the tower.

name: The Top of a West Gate Tower
description:
You notice that there are many more guards on the western towers than on
the other towers surrounding the city.  The guards posted on these towers
grimace at your arrival, hoping you are a replacement.  Heavy black
cauldrons are settled amongst the merlons, and archer slits angle onto the
plains below.  A small wooden ladder leads down into the base of the tower.

name: The Small School
description:
A small school was constructed here during more peaceful times.  Now it
is used by the army as an area to train their troops.  Usually, it is
possible to convince one of the unemployed teachers to train you if you ask.

name: A Turn
description:
You are at a bend in the road.  A wall of foot-wide spears stands to the
west and south, framing the city within it's dangerous ramparts.  Turquoise
Lane leads north to the West Gate, and Onyx Lane leads east to the South
Gate.

name: The Chamber of the Mind
description:
You step through the portal into a room of indescribable proportions. 
This area would not fit within the entire city walls of Udgaard.  Briefly
you wonder where you are.  Swirling colors and pulses of lightning fill the
ceiling.  Far in the distance, mages practice the mystic arts.  You find
yourself a spot and wait for an instructor....

name: The Supply Room
description:
In this room, a Sukuinage distributes equipment of the ninja class. 
Silently, the ninja points to an article nailed to his desk.... There is
also a small sign hanging on the wall.

name: A Turn
description:
You are at a bend in the road.  A wall of foot-wide spears stands to the
west and north, framing the city within it's dangerous ramparts.  Turquoise
Lane leads south to the West Gate, and Opal Lane leads east to the North
Gate.

name: The Jaette Bar
description:
This broken down bar is a favorite of the local troops in Udgaard Loke's
army.  The owner seems to accept the brawls which break out here every
night, considering the Jaette business it brings in.

name: A Turn
description:
You stand at the turn in the road of the cities northeast corner.  A wall
of foot-wide spears stands to the north and east, framing the city within
it's dangerous ramparts.  Marble Lane continues south to the east gate, and
Opal Lane continues west to the North Gate.

name: Opal Lane
description:
You walk along Opal Lane.  You are flanked on the North by the thick
spear wall surrounding Udgaard Loke's Farm.  To the South Udgaard Loke's
Palace towers above you.  Opal lane continues to the east, and a turn in the
road is west.

name: Opal Lane
description:
You walk along Opal Lane.  You are flanked on the North by the thick
spear wall surrounding Udgaard Loke's Farm.  To the South Udgaard Loke's
Palace towers above you.  Opal lane continues to the west, and a turn in the
road is east.

name: Opal Lane
description:
You walk along Opal Lane.  You are flanked on the north by the North Gate

you.  Opal lane continues to the east and west.

The guards posted on these towers huddle beneath cloaks as a continuous
wind howls through the battlements.  Heavy black cauldrons are settled
amongst the merlons, and archer slits angle onto the plains below.  A small
wooden ladder leads down into the base of the tower.

name: The Dark Clerics' Guild
description:
Scattered about the room you see bloodstained pentagrams, carved symbols
of evil, and the drained corpses of tributes.  As you kneel to worship, you
feel a corrupt power surge within you.  The Afskyelige wander about,
prohibiting the entrance of non believers.

name: The Monk's Guild
description:
This guild is used by the fearsome monks that reside in these lands. 
Strong and ferocious, they use their skill, strength and courage to do
battle.

name: The Village Road
description:
You stand now on the northern road just beyond Cimar's gates.  To the
north extends the outlying village community of Cimar's influence.  Here,
the Border Patrol of Cimar's Army takes over jurisdiction.  You can see
all manner of low buildings to the north, as well as one impressive one to
your northwest.

name: The Village Road
description:
You stand now on the northern road just beyond Cimar's gates.  To the
north extends the outlying village community of Cimar's influence.  Here,
the Border Patrol of Cimar's Army takes over jurisdiction.  You can see
all manner of low buildings to the north, as well as one impressive one to
your northwest.

name: The Village Road
description:
You stand now on the northern road just beyond Cimar's gates.  To the
north extends the outlying village community of Cimar's influence.  Here,
the Border Patrol of Cimar's Army takes over jurisdiction.  You can see
all manner of low buildings to the north, as well as one impressive one to
your northwest.

name: The Village Road
description:
This is the southern end of Koteras Village, before reaching the famed
city of Cimar.  Here, the dirt road extends north as well, to the village
itself, and a small side road beckons toward a wooden longhouse with a
small belltower behind it.

name: The Village Road
description:
You stand on the southern edge of Koteras Village, among dwellings of
city laborers, serfs, and merchants alike.  A marketplate looms up ahead,
and some thatch huts sit on the western side of the road.

name: A peasant hut
description:
You stand within a small domicile that, were justice rampant, should
house perhaps two people.  In the world of the peasant, four families must
take up residence here.  A small firepit is dug in the center of the dirt
floor, and piles of skins and straw provide sleeping quarters for these
unfortunate people.

name: The Village Road
description:
You stand on Koteras Village's main road, stretching through the north
plains that border Cimar.  A marketplace looms ever closer, and from here
you can actually catch smells of burning coal and roasted meats.  To the
west, several thatch huts line the road.

name: A peasant hut
description:
You stand within a small domicile that, were justice rampant, should
house perhaps two people.  In the world of the peasant, four families must
take up residence here.  A small firepit is dug in the center of the dirt
floor, and piles of skins and straw provide sleeping quarters for these
unfortunate people.

name: The Village Road
description:
You stand on the road stretching through Koteras Village on the northern
spur of the grand city of Cimar.  Just north of you, a wide marketplace opens
into the town square.  To the east and west are dwellings, though the wooden
cabin to your east seems quite a bit more hospitable than the thatch hut to
the west.  The road here is cleaner, more well kept.

name: A peasant hut
description:
You stand within a small, cramped hut that seems to be the living space
for several families, though in time of comfort would perhaps serve only a
largish pet.  It is well-kept, however, and the serfs here are even good
enough to dispose of their trash by burning it in the center firepit.

name: Village Square
description:
Here, you stand upon the southern edge of the village proper.  Not quite
within the grasp of the bustling marketplace that Koteras is built around,
here you see mainly smaller vendors, peddlers from the city offering trinkets
and useless furs, things of no real value.  A large, somewhat opulent
residence lies off to the east, and the cobblestones here in the square have
become much easier to walk upon.

name: Inside a cabin home
description:
Within this small domicile lives a family who must be one of the lucky
few to succeed in peddling their goods, or perhaps the family of one of the
town's rather prosperous shop keepers.  It is comfortable but not lavish,
with sturdy wooden walls, hardwood floors, and even a bank of crystal
windows set into the eastern wall.

name: A small storeroom
description:
This provides the family a place for hanging meats, keeping belongings
and extra clothing.  It is somewhat cramped, but still of good, sturdy
construction and quite warm in the wintertime.  The hardwood floor shows
signs of being well-cared for.  This also serves as a pantry for the
family, as dried goods and jars of food are kept here on shelves.

name: The Center of the Square
description:
Here, you stand in the commercial and geographical center of Koteras
Village.  Vendors struggle all around you to garner position for themselves,
and citizens bustle about as well as serfs on their trek to or from the
cantrevs.  Here the town meetings are held, or in the Inn, depending on
weather.  The cobblestones here have been worn down from years of the heavy
commercial traffic.

name: Village Square
description:
You stand on the eastern edge of the bustling center of this village.
Vendors rich and poor, peddlers local and famous alike vie for position on
the grey cobblestones, while around you rise wooden buildings and shops.

name: In a canvas shelter
description:
Here, inside the giant canvas strung up by large metal stakes, there
is quite obviously a smithy of some kind.  A short black anvil rests in
the center of the grass, with buckets of oil and water sitting beside it.
Metal implements for shaving, smelting, and shaping are strewn about on
a nearby table.  The smell of burning coal fills the tent.

name: A road of whitened earth
description:
This trail, while not cobbled, serves as a main east-west thoroughfare
for the citizens and the commerce of the village.  The solid, packed earth
that comprises the road is whitish in color, and is covered with a fine,
white dust that swirls about in the slight breeze.

name: A road of whitened earth
description:
You stand on a road of solid, packed earth that serves as the main
east-west thoroughfare for the citizenry and commerce of Koteras Village.
The road itself is of a fine, white dust that swirls about in the breeze.
To the north of you is a small stone house, and thatch huts line the south
edge of the road.

name: A peasant hut
description:
You stand within a small domicile that, were justice rampant, should
house perhaps two people.  In the world of the peasant, four families must
take up residence here.  A small firepit is dug in the center of the dirt
floor, and piles of skins and straw provide sleeping quarters for these
unfortunate people.

name: A road of whitened earth
description:
You stand on a road of solid, packed earth that serves as the main
east-west thoroughfare for the citizenry and commerce of Koteras Village.
The road itself is of a fine, white dust that swirls about in the breeze.

name: Inside a small stone dwelling
description:
You are within a cozy granite and mortar dwelling belonging likely
to one of the town's prosperous resident merchants, most likely the town
blacksmith.  A large fireplace decorates the western wall, and shelves
line the other walls, bearing food as well as books scribed in what
appears to be dwarvish lettering.  A large rug of some unknown animal
fur covers the hardwood floor, and a soft bed lies in one corner.

name: A road of whitened earth
description:
You stand on a road of solid, packed earth that serves as the main
east-west thoroughfare for the citizenry and commerce of Koteras Village.
The road itself is of a fine, white dust that swirls about in the breeze.
Another trail, this one of cobbled stone, leads away south toward a large
brick tower.

name: A road of whitened earth
description:
You stand on a trail of whitened earth that has been packed solid by
the meanderings and commerce of the village and its relationship with the
lords of the northern cantrevs.  The earth is covered in a fine white dust
that swirls in the slight breeze.

name: A twisting path of cobbled stone
description:
This road is of evenly placed cobbled stone, and worn ruts show the
frequent passage of carts and wagons.  The path was obviously laid by
a scenic-minded person, and bends to showcase the few trees lining the
path here.  To the east and south, a short, iron fence encloses a small
cemetery.

name: A twisting path of cobbled stone
description:
This road is of evenly placed cobbled stone, and worn ruts show the
frequent passage of carts and wagons.  The path was obviously laid by
a scenic-minded person, and bends to showcase the few trees lining the
path.  To the east, an iron gate beckons you to a final resting place.

name: A silent cemetery
description:
A black iron fence boxes in this plot of land, though scattered
gravestones dot the field beyond it.  The ground here is uneven and
crowded with chiseled monuments to faceless thousands, gone before in
the long march to the Gates of Silence.  A large stone near the east
edge of the yard proclaims a mass grave for fallen warriors in the ages-old
defense of the \grandest city ever to rise on proud earth\".  The spirits

area_id: of those resting here seem to compel you to honor them and quiet yourself.

name: A twisting path of cobbled stone
description:
You stand on a path that turns and twists like a serpent past a long
wooden structure on the west, and a fenced enclosure on the east.  The
stones are evenly placed and smooth, and the path's turns take you near
the few trees that dot the landscape.

name: A well-maintained churchyard
description:
Here the dirt and rock and rubble of the terrain have been cleared
away, and a tranquil lawn of groomed grass provides solace and peace
to weary travellers.  In the southeast corner of the yard, a brick
tower looms over the yard and most of the village.

name: A well-maintained churchyard
description:
Here the dirt and rock and rubble of the terrain have been cleared
away, and a tranquil lawn of groomed grass provides solace and peace
to weary travellers.  The long, soft grasses bend over themselves,
creating a cushion to weary feet and sitting visitors.  On the borders
of the lawn, azaleas and lilacs dot the grass, emanating light,
sweet fragrances.

name: Inside a brick belltower
description:
You are at the foot of spiral stone steps that look to oudate
the church, oddly, by several hundred years or more.  They are
chiseled out of a black stone with an oddly metallic sheen, though
nowhere near as reflective as obsidian.  The stairs lead up, and
the bricks must have been laid around it, though they show the
cracking and faded look of long years as well.

name: In the tower bell chamber
description:
You stand in a small, open chamber at the top of the brick bell
tower serving the village church.  A giant copper bell sways heavily
in the center of the chamber, and several smaller bells decorate
the top of each arch facing the cardinal directions. A strange stone
stairway leads back into the interior of the tower.

name: Inside a longhouse cathedral
description:
This wooden structure is quite sturdy, and has stood the test of
time and the elements to serve this small community.  The church of
Cimar has donated a fair amount to establishing this center of
holiness in a Border Patrol region, mainly for the comfort of the
village and the soldier's families.  Beautiful hardwood pews are
furnished with layers of pillows to make services more bearable, and
the altar at the front of the sanctuary is laden with gold cloth.

name: Inside a longhouse cathedral
description:
You stand in the southern end of a large nave that serves the entire
community of Koteras.  Elegant hardwood pews are cushioned and numerous
enough to seat the whole community twice over, it seems.  Many pilgrims
come to see the church that has utilized its donations with a good idea
of the aesthetic.  Double doors beckon the populace in to the south,
while a small, candle-lit alcove lies to the west.

name: Inside a longhouse cathedral
description:
You stand at the northern end of a vast sanctuary, entirely
constructed of hardwood, right down to the altar itself.  The timber
likely imported from the river valley nobility holdings and shaped
by their serfs to sweeten the deal.  The craftsmanship looks exceptional,
however, and the floor is carved with images of a grand city, perhaps
a representation of the beauties of the heavens.  Simple wooden
chandeliers provide the lighting for the entire cathedral.

name: At the altar
description:
Upon a raised dais, this wooden altar is covered in crimson velvet and
white cloth lined with shimmering golden thread.  A pulpit, also of sturdy
wood construction, stands off to one side.  From here, voices echo all
throughout the church as if you stood overlooking an expansive valley. All
the wood walls act as sounding boards, to heighten the intensity and volume
of the speaking priest.

name: A small, candle-lit alcove
description:
Here, worshippers can escape the noise and populace of the general
service to find more personal prayer time.  A series of low tables along
the western wall hold hundreds upon hundreds of white candles, long-
burning beeswax that sheds a soft glow upon the faces of the faithful
and gives the hardwood church a homey look.  Small cushions are also
provided for those who kneel in silent prayer here.

name: A small dirt road
description:
You stand on a small road before an imposing wooden longhouse.  A
pair of wooden double doors that reach perhaps fifteen feet in height
beckon to the north, and the road itself, of solid, packed brown earth
and dotted with small chunks of strangely smooth rock, leads west.

name: A small dirt road
description:
You stand on a small dirt road at the southwestern corner of a
large wooden longhouse.  On occasion you can hear the singing of a
large group of people echoing through the structure, the strains of
a nameless hymn of praise.  The entrance to the longhouse is east
of here, while the road leads west, bending north.

name: A small dirt road
description:
You stand on a small dirt road, wending its way through the huts and
cabins to end east of here at an exceptionally large structure.  The road
itself is solid, packed earth, though occasional rubble dots its surface.
The rubble is of well-shaped stone that bears centuries of weather on its
face, yet seems structurally little the worse for wear.

name: A small dirt road
description:
You stand on a small dirt road, wending its way through the huts and
cabins to end east of here at an exceptionally large structure.  The road
itself is solid, packed earth, though occasional rubble dots its surface.
The rubble is of well-shaped stone that bears centuries of weather on its
face, yet seems structurally little the worse for wear.

name: A small dirt road
description:
You stand on a small dirt road, wending its way through the huts and
cabins to end east of here at an exceptionally large structure.  The road
itself is solid, packed earth, though occasional rubble dots its
surface. The rubble is of well-shaped stone that bears centuries of
weather on its face, yet seems structurally little the worse for wear.

name: A small dirt road
description:
You stand on a small dirt road, wending its way through the huts and
cabins to end east of here at an exceptionally large structure.  The
road itself is solid, packed earth, though occasional rubble dots its
surface. The rubble is of well-shaped stone that bears centuries of
weather on its face, yet seems structurally little the worse for wear.
The road also joins the main village path to the west of here.

name: The Village Road
description:
You stand on the main village road just north of a large market-
place.  The cobblestone road leads north and south, and to the immediate
west of you stands a large longhouse, with a stone chimney that pours
out black, greasy-looking smoke.  More cabins lie to the north on this
road.

name: The Village Road
description:
You stand on the main village road north of the large marketplace
which serves Koteras in its entirety.  To your west, a longhouse stands
imposingly wide, and from the east, the thick, coppery reek of blood
emanates with brutal intensity.

name: The Village Road
description:
You stand on the main village road nearing the northern edge of the
community of Koteras.  The cobblestones are extremely well-placed in
this district of town, as the soldiers who are remanded for any sort
of disciplinary action usually draw that job.

name: The Village Road
description:
You stand at the veritable end of the village service-road.  To the
north, it becomes the solid earth of the North Cimar Road.  Some of the
village's merchants have their shops set up here, mostly so the odors
from their wares do not infest the entire town.  The butcher, the
tanner, and anyone peddling pungent herbs are all encouraged to seek
the downwind side of north.

name: North Cimar Road
description:
You stand upon the wide, solid earth of the North Cimar Road, the
pride, joy, and primary responsibility of the city's Border Patrol. The
low cabins and huts of the village to the south give way to rolling,
verdant pastures, and far-off woodlands to the north.

name: North Cimar Road
description:
You stand upon the wide, solid earth of the North Cimar Road, the
pride, joy, and primary responsibility of the city's Border Patrol.
The low cabins and huts of the village to the south give way to rolling,
verdant pastures, and far-off woodlands to the north.

name: North Cimar Road
description:
You stand upon the wide, solid earth of the North Cimar Road, the
pride, joy, and primary responsibility of the city's Border Patrol.
The low cabins and huts of the village to the south give way to rolling,
verdant pastures, and far-off woodlands to the north.

name: The Northern Crossroads
description:
You stand before a large way-post maintained by the Cimar Army's
prestigious Border Patrol.  A wooden barricade with stakes tipped with
razor-sharp steel is dug in awaiting a horde of brigands, or goblins,
or anything to keep the patrolmen in practice.  On either side of you,
deep green pastures open up, thanks to the nearby river valley's
fertility.  The road branches here, one continuing north, and another
leading west.  A large wooden sign sits next to the barricade.

name: North Cimar Road
description:
You stand upon Cimar's main commercial artery for trading with the
northern cities.  Here the road joins to the south with others, and
beyond that is bordered on either side by rolling, verdant green
pastures. The road itself bends to the east here.

name: North Cimar Road
description:
You stand upon Cimar's main commercial artery for trading with the
northern cities.  Here the road wends its way northward and east, and
to the southeast lie verdant, rolling pastures rich with plant life.

name: North Cimar Road
description:
You stand upon Cimar's main commercial artery for trading with the
northern cities.  Here the road wends its way northward and east, and
to the southeast lie verdant, rolling pastures rich with plant life.

name: North Cimar Road
description:
You stand upon Cimar's main commercial artery for trading with the
northern cities.  Here the road wends its way northward and east, and
to the southeast lie verdant, rolling pastures rich with plant life.

name: North Cimar Road
description:
You stand upon Cimar's main commercial artery for trading with the
northern cities.  Here the road wends its way northward and east, and
to the southeast lie verdant, rolling pastures rich with plant life.
North of here, a road stretches into the mountains at the horizon.

name: A wide road
description:
This road runs east and west just north of Cimar's outlying village
community.  Here you are just west of the barricade and crossroads
maintained by the Border Patrol.  To your south a large, rich green
pasture opens up.

name: A wide road
description:
This road runs east and west just north of Cimar's outlying village
community.  Here you are just west of the barricade and crossroads
maintained by the Border Patrol.  To your south a large, rich green
pasture opens up.  North of here, another road branches off.

name: A rolling, verdant pasture
description:
You stand upon an expansive field of soft grasses and tall thistle,
blowing gently in the breeze.  Rabbit dens are scattered throughout the
area, and the rare pile of stones denotes some ancient cairn, worn
down to a simple monument.

name: A rolling, verdant pasture
description:
You stand upon an expansive field of soft grasses and tall thistle,
blowing gently in the breeze.  Rabbit dens are scattered throughout the
area, and the rare pile of stones denotes some ancient cairn, worn
down to a simple monument.

area, and the rare pile of stones denotes some ancient cairn, worn
down to a simple monument.

blowing gently in the breeze.  Rabbit dens are scattered throughout the

description:
You stand upon an expansive field of soft grasses and tall thistle,
blowing gently in the breeze.  Rabbit dens are scattered throughout the
area, and the rare pile of stones denotes some ancient cairn, worn
