name: Before the Black tinged tower in the swampy ruins
description:
You find yourself at the end of the swamp paths and before a large tower black
tinged stone. The surface of the strange building appears smooth and strong,
and it looks new even though the swamp growth has covered almost halfway up
it's height. There is a black door leading north into the tower.

name: In a black hallway
description:
You are in a hallway surrounded by black stone and silence. Nothing seems to
stir, not even the air from the marshes outside. Their is something cold and
evil in the air here. The hallway heads east and west, and there is a black
door in the south wall leading outside.

name: In a black hallway
description:
You are in a hallway surrounded by black stone and silence. Nothing seems to
stir, not even the air from the marshes outside. Their is something cold and
evil in the air here. The hallway heads north and west.

name: In a black hallway
description:
You are in a hallway surrounded by black stone and silence. Nothing seems to
stir, not even the air from the marshes outside. Their is something cold and
evil in the air here. The hallway heads north and south.

name: In a black hallway
description:
You are in a hallway surrounded by black stone and silence. Nothing seems to
stir, not even the air from the marshes outside. Their is something cold and
evil in the air here. The hallway heads south and west.

name: Before a huge black door
description:
You are in a hallway surrounded by black stone and silence. To the south you
can almost feel a prescence of pure evil through a massive green door.

name: In a black hallway
description:
You are in a hallway surrounded by black stone and silence. Nothing seems to
stir, not even the air from the marshes outside. Their is something cold and
evil in the air here. The hallway heads south and east.

name: In a black hallway
description:
You are in a hallway surrounded by black stone and silence. Nothing seems to
stir, not even the air from the marshes outside. Their is something cold and
evil in the air here. The hallway heads north and south.

name: In a black hallway
description:
You are in a hallway surrounded by black stone and silence. Nothing seems to
stir, not even the air from the marshes outside. Their is something cold and
evil in the air here. The hallway heads north and east.

name: A cold dark room
description:
You have entered a room of the coldest winter. The air from your breath
freezes upon your lips and your body almost goes into shock from the cold.
There is nothing but ice and darkness in here. A massive green door lies in
the northern wall and a stairwell heads up into the cold night.

name: In a chilling dark hallway
description:
The hallway here is not only dark but freezing cold. Ice hangs from the roof
and staligmites of frozen blood protrude from the floor. The hallway heads off
south, or you can take a staircase leading down.

name: Before a door of frozen blood
description:
You are standing in a freezing room where even the walls themselves seem to
be shivering. To the south there is a door of what looks like frozen blood.

name: In a pitch black room
description:
It's totally dark in here, your own light can't even penetrate more than two
feet into the night. The air freezes on your breath, and even more chilling is
the sound of something horribly powerful breathing and sending tremors through
the tower. There is a bloody frozen door in the north wall and a staircase
leading up.

name: In a patch black hallway
description:
It's totally dark here and you only know it is a hallway by the shape of the
walls around you. Somewhere nearby a deep rumbling sends tremors through the
floor and a heart stopping breathing sound can be heard. There is a staircase
leading down, or you can go north along the hallway.

name: Before a dark blue door
description:
You are in a totally dark hallway and the only thing you can see is the faint
glow of a blue door in the north wall. As you approach it a physical feeling
of pure hate and malice seems to come washing through it at you.

name: In a bare black room
description:
This room is totally bare, like a monastic refuge. The atmosphere, however, is
chilling and almost overpowering in it's hate and evil. You can hear what is
unmistakably the breathing of some massive and powerful creature nearby. To
the south is a huge dark blue door, and a staircase heads up.

name: Before a massive door of blackened heartstone
description:
You are standing in a room of pure black rock. A prescence of immense power
can be physically felt from here, almost like it was existing beyond the normal
sense of real. In the north wall there is a door of indestructable heartstone
that has somehow been charred and blackend.

name: In the room of Binding Light
description:
This room is totally different to those before it. In here there is light that
seems almost blinding and the atmosphere is one of subdued violence. Somehow
something of divine power has created a room to nullify the darkest powers that
reside in this ruined city, but not powerful enough to destroy it. The only
way out is through the blackened heartstone door in the south wall.

name: On a dock in a bloody harbour
description:
You are on a collapsed and ruined dock made of rusted steel and decayed wood.
To the south you can see one of the harbours of Myth Drannor, filled with a
shallow blood red water that laps continuosly upon the ruined harbour. The
salty smell of blood fills the air, and there is something powerful and
disturbing about the way the region seems locked in time. It is as if the
bloodshed of the elves were only yesterday and not centuries ago. There is a
ruined boathouse to the north, or you can walk east across the docks. West of
here lie the marshlands of the Drannor ruins.

name: On a dock in a bloody harbour
description:
You are on a collapsed and ruined dock made of rusted steel and decayed wood.
To the south you can see one of the harbours of Myth Drannor, filled with a
shallow blood red water that laps continuosly upon the ruined harbour. The
salty smell of blood fills the air, and there is something powerful and
disturbing about the way the region seems locked in time. It is as if the
bloodshed of the elves were only yesterday and not centuries ago. You can walk
east and west across the docks, or head south into the shallow blood red
waters of the harbour.

name: On a dock in a bloody harbour
description:
You are on a collapsed and ruined dock made of rusted steel and decayed wood.
To the south you can see one of the harbours of Myth Drannor, filled with a
shallow blood red water that laps continuosly upon the ruined harbour. The
salty smell of blood fills the air, and there is something powerful and
disturbing about the way the region seems locked in time. It is as if the
bloodshed of the elves were only yesterday and not centuries ago. You can walk
east and west across the docks, or head south into the shallow blood red
waters of the harbour.

name: On a dock in a bloody harbour
description:
You are on a collapsed and ruined dock made of rusted steel and decayed wood.
To the south you can see one of the harbours of Myth Drannor, filled with a
shallow blood red water that laps continuosly upon the ruined harbour. The
salty smell of blood fills the air, and there is something powerful and
disturbing about the way the region seems locked in time. It is as if the
bloodshed of the elves were only yesterday and not centuries ago. You can walk
east and west across the docks, or head south into the shallow blood red
waters of the harbour. There is a ruined old boat house to the north.

name: End of a dock in a bloody harbour
description:
You are on a collapsed and ruined dock made of rusted steel and decayed wood.
To the south you can see one of the harbours of Myth Drannor, filled with a
shallow blood red water that laps continuosly upon the ruined harbour. The
salty smell of blood fills the air, and there is something powerful and
disturbing about the way the region seems locked in time. It is as if the
bloodshed of the elves were only yesterday and not centuries ago. There is an
old boat house to the north, or the docks head west towards the harbour.

name: In a destroyed boat house
description:
This old wooden shack on the harbour is totally demolished. The wood and
scraps left over from the city's destruction lie cluttered amidst the wet,
bloody waters seeping in from the harbour. The only exit is back to the
south to the ruined docks of the Drannor harbour.

name: Within a blood soaked boat house
description:
This destroyed boat house is still covered in wet, warm blood. It is
almost as if the annihilation of the elven people in the city had only
just occurred in the last few hours, rather than centuries ago. The scent
of warm salty blood still hangs in the air, and the waters outside lap up
into the shack carrying more bloody red waters. The only exit is back to
the south onto the ruined docks of the harbour.

name: In the northern ruins of the city
description:
The ruins here seem to have been cleared somewhat and it is possible to just
make your way through the rubble and into the northern part of the ruins. All
around you the air seems unnaturally still an atmosphere of contained evil
hangs all around you.

name: In the northern ruins of the city
description:
You are standing in the rubbled remains of the ancient elven city. Very little
has been left to observe and it's hard to see the old grandeur that once was.
You can just make your way a little more north through the cleared rubble or
head south to the main ruins.

name: In the northern ruins of the city
description:
You are standing at the most northern part of the ruins that seems accessable.
From here the rubble and ruin is impassable in all but the south, and even
there it is only passable because someone has recently cleared a narrow path.

name: Wading through the bloody waters of the harbour
description:
You are standing knee deep in the red tinted waters of the ancient
harbour. Your steps are made harder by the sucking and clinging mud
beneath the murky water, and the air is warm with the smell of blood.
There are no fish to be seen and there is a total lack of animal prescence
where normally water would attract much attention. Something very
disturbing has happened here, and the power of it still lingers in the
region. The harbour heads south and west, or you can go north onto the
ruined docks.

name: Wading through the bloody waters of the harbour
description:
You are standing knee deep in the red tinted waters of the ancient
harbour. Your steps are made harder by the sucking and clinging mud
beneath the murky water, and the air is warm with the smell of blood.
There are no fish to be seen and there is a total lack of animal prescence
where normally water would attract much attention. Something very
disturbing has happened here, and the power of it still lingers in the
region. The harbour waters go north, east and south. You can make out the
docks off to the north.

name: Wading through the bloody waters of the harbour
description:
You are standing knee deep in the red tinted waters of the ancient
harbour. Your steps are made harder by the sucking and clinging mud
beneath the murky water, and the air is warm with the smell of blood.
There are no fish to be seen and there is a total lack of animal prescence
where normally water would attract much attention. Something very
disturbing has happened here, and the power of it still lingers in the
region. The harbour waters head off in all directions around you. In the
distance to the north you can make out some docks.

name: Wading through the bloody waters of the harbour
description:
You are standing knee deep in the red tinted waters of the ancient
harbour. Your steps are made harder by the sucking and clinging mud
beneath the murky water, and the air is warm with the smell of blood.
There are no fish to be seen and there is a total lack of animal prescence
where normally water would attract much attention. Something very
disturbing has happened here, and the power of it still lingers in the
region. The harbour waters head off to the north, south and west. You can
just make out the docks in the distance to the north.

name: Wading through the bloody waters of the harbour
description:
You are standing knee deep in the red tinted waters of the ancient
harbour. Your steps are made harder by the sucking and clinging mud
beneath the murky water, and the air is warm with the smell of blood.
There are no fish to be seen and there is a total lack of animal prescence
where normally water would attract much attention. Something very
disturbing has happened here, and the power of it still lingers in the
region. The harbour waters head off to the north and east.

name: Before a bloody river outlet in the harbour
description:
You are standing knee deep in the red tinted waters of the ancient
harbour. Your steps are made harder by the sucking and clinging mud
beneath the murky water, and the air is warm with the smell of blood.
There are no fish to be seen and there is a total lack of animal prescence
where normally water would attract much attention. Something very
disturbing has happened here, and the power of it still lingers in the
region. The harbour waters head off to the north, east and west. To the
south the harbour narrows into a small channel of blood filled water.

name: Wading through the bloody waters of the harbour
description:
You are standing knee deep in the red tinted waters of the ancient
harbour. Your steps are made harder by the sucking and clinging mud
beneath the murky water, and the air is warm with the smell of blood.
There are no fish to be seen and there is a total lack of animal prescence
where normally water would attract much attention. Something very
disturbing has happened here, and the power of it still lingers in the
region. The harbour waters head off to the north and west.

name: Wading through the bloody river outlet
description:
You stand knee deep in the murky blood red waters of a small river
flowing out of the harbour to the north. There is no sign of the normal
animal activity you expect from a river in fertile forest land, and
something dark and disturbing is in the air. The river continues to flow
south, or you can head north into the shallow harbour waters of one of
Drannor's ancient ports.

name: Wading through the bloody river outlet
description:
You stand knee deep in the murky blood red waters of a small river
flowing out of the harbour to the north. There is no sign of the normal
animal activity you expect from a river in fertile forest land, and
something dark and disturbing is in the air. The river continues to flow
east or you can wade back north through it.

name: Wading through the bloody river outlet
description:
You stand knee deep in the murky blood red waters of a small river
flowing out of the harbour to the north. There is no sign of the normal
animal activity you expect from a river in fertile forest land, and
something dark and disturbing is in the air. The river continues to flow
east or you can wade back west through it.

name: Wading through the bloody river outlet
description:
You stand knee deep in the murky blood red waters of a small river
flowing out of the harbour to the west and north. There is no sign of the
normal animal activity you expect from a river in fertile forest land, and
something dark and disturbing is in the air. The river continues to flow
east or you can wade back west through it.

name: A bend in the bloody river outlet
description:
You stand knee deep in the murky blood red waters of a small river
flowing out of the harbours to the west and north. There is no sign of the
normal animal activity you expect from a river in fertile forest land, and
something dark and disturbing is in the air. The river continues to flow
south or you can wade back west through it.

name: In a bone and blood filled river outlet
description:
The blood red river is mixed with floating bones of elven origin. All
around you bones of all sizes, from babies to adults, bob up and down in
the murky river. None show signs of corrosiion or decay as you would
expect after centuries in the water, and some even appear to almost have
flesh still hanging off them. It is as if the region were preserved as it
was on the day that the massacres occured. The river heads east where you
can make out a large embankment of bones sitting high upon the river, or
back north.

name: At the edge of a bone embankment
description:
You have reached the edge of a huge, isle-like embankment made of bones
from long dead elves. The bloody waters of the river flow around and
through the gaps in the bone isle, and it is almost as if the massacre
were yesterday rather than centuries ago. Something further off in the
bone structure stirs, sending a tremor through them. The river heads back
west, or you can go east onto the bone isle.

name: On an isle of elven bones
description:
You stand on an isle consisting almost purely of bones from long dead
elves. There must be thousands of bodies piled up here, all left to rot
and decay in the bloody waters. Yet somehow they seem recent, like they
were slain only recently rather than centuries ago. Something very dark
and disturbing sends a chill through you as you gaze over the piles of
bones. To the north and east you can see the ruins of many ships that were
destroyed as the elves tried to flee the massacre. West of here the isle
heads out to the river.

name: On an isle of elven bones
description:
You stand on an isle consisting almost purely of bones from long dead
elves. There must be thousands of bodies piled up here, all left to rot
and decay in the bloody waters. Yet somehow they seem recent, like they
were slain only recently rather than centuries ago. For a moment it seems
the isle shifts beneath you as if the bones were still alive...a chill
through you as you gaze over the isle of bones. To the north you can see
the ruins of many ships that were destroyed as the elves tried to flee the
massacre.

name: On an isle of elven bones
description:
You stand on an isle consisting almost purely of bones from long dead
elves. There must be thousands of bodies piled up here, all left to rot
and decay in the bloody waters. Yet somehow they seem recent, like they
were slain only recently rather than centuries ago. For a moment it seems
the isle shifts beneath you as if the bones were still alive...a chill
through you as you gaze over the isle of bones. To the north  and west you
can see the ruins of many ships that were destroyed as the elves tried to
flee the massacre. East of here there is a huge mountain of bones blocking
the river flow.

name: At the entrance to a restored building
description:
Here amongst the ruins of Myth Drannor a single building seems to have been
restored from the destruction. The stone building shows the signs of massive
damage that everything else shows, but it has been restored to an almost decent
level by someone or something. As you walk by the building your feet slip in
some thick, sticky fluid that gives off a terribly stench. A doorway leads
north into the building or you can go east, south or west around the rubble of
the city.

name: On an isle of elven bones
description:
You stand on an isle consisting almost purely of bones from long dead
elves. There must be thousands of bodies piled up here, all left to rot
and decay in the bloody waters. Yet somehow they seem recent, like they
were slain only recently rather than centuries ago. For a moment it seems
the isle shifts beneath you as if the bones were still alive...a chill
through you as you gaze over the isle of bones. To the north you can see
the ruins of many ships that were destroyed as the elves tried to flee the
massacre.

name: On an isle of elven bones
description:
You stand on an isle consisting almost purely of bones from long dead
elves. There must be thousands of bodies piled up here, all left to rot
and decay in the bloody waters. Yet somehow they seem recent, like they
were slain only recently rather than centuries ago. For a moment it seems
the isle shifts beneath you as if the bones were still alive...a chill
through you as you gaze over the isle of bones. To the west and north you
can see the ruins of many ships that were destroyed as the elves tried to
flee the massacre.

name: Before a dam built from elven bones
description:
You are at the edge of the isle of bones where a huge pile has been
erected to totally seal of the river. There must be thousands of dead
elves left here to dam up the river, preventing the waters from flowing
out of the harbours of Myth Drannor, and keeping it forever in a state of
bloody waters. The bones around you seem to shift slightly, and it's like
being in an earthquake of bones. The isle heads back to the west, and
there is no way through the solid blockade to the east.

name: Standing at the edge of a huge graveyard of ships
description:
Here at the northern edge of the bone isle you can see the extent of the
massacre that must have occured centuries ago. Scores of large ships and
boats have been totally demolished and left to rot in the bloody, bone
filled waters. Burnt and blasted hulls litter the entire region, and
skeletons of elves hang lifelessly from the helms and bridges of them.
There is no doubt that the forces that blocked and slayed the elves as
they tried to flee were powerful beyond anything seen in recent times. The
smashed boat graveyard is too hazardous to explore, and you can only head
back south onto the isle of elf bones.

name: In the ruins of the city walls
description:
The walls here is hollowed out for defence, but the dried skeletons that
lie scattered across the floor show that it did little good. The air is
dusty and dry, stale with ages of being kept locked up. There is slight
break in the west wall here, or you can head south along the inside of the
wall.

name: In the ruins of the city walls
description:
The crumbling walls here are just as bad as outside, and the air is stale
and stinks of death. You can head south or north.

name: Above a hole in the city walls
description:
Here in the crumbling walls of the city you can see a small hole that has
been excavated in the ground. The work is poor and hasty, and there is no
signs of life down below. The wall passage heads back north.

name: In a small excavated hole beneath the walls
description:
You are in a small hole that seems to have been dug out in a hurry. The
ground is littered with long dead elven skeletons, and there is nothing of
interest that hasn't already long been decayed. A hole leads back up, or
you can go north to what appears to be a door.

name: Outside a door in the crumbling walls
description:
You are standing in the dark tunnel beneath the city walls. For some
reason the tunnel here hasn't collapsed like most of the ruins, and there
is a large oak door in the east wall which is in extremely good condition.

name: Inside a small room beneath the crumbling walls
description:
You are in a tiny, bare room that is in almost perfect condition. Unlike
the rest of the ruins this room has no signs of decay or ruin, and it is
almost as if it had been built yesterday. There is, however, nothing of
interest in it but the large oak door in the west wall.

name: On an isle of elven bones
description:
You stand on an isle consisting almost purely of bones from long dead
elves. There must be thousands of bodies piled up here, all left to rot
and decay in the bloody waters. Yet somehow they seem recent, like they
were slain only recently rather than centuries ago. For a moment it seems
the isle shifts beneath you as if the bones were still alive...a chill
through you as you gaze over the isle of bones. To the east and north you
can see the ruins of many ships that were destroyed as the elves tried to
flee the massacre.

name: On a wet, marshland path in the ruins
description:
You are on a path through the marshlands that have overgrown the ancient
ruins. There is a faint smell of salty sea water coming from the east,
and to the west the path heads back to a T-junction in the swamps.

name: Wading through the bloody waters of the harbour
description:
You are standing knee deep in the red tinted waters of the ancient
harbour. Your steps are made harder by the sucking and clinging mud
beneath the murky water, and the air is warm with the smell of blood.
There are no fish to be seen and there is a total lack of animal prescence
where normally water would attract much attention. Something very
disturbing has happened here, and the power of it still lingers in the
region. The harbour heads east and south, or you can go north onto the
ruined docks.

name: Wading through the bloody waters of the harbour
description:
You are standing knee deep in the red tinted waters of the ancient
harbour. Your steps are made harder by the sucking and clinging mud
beneath the murky water, and the air is warm with the smell of blood.
There are no fish to be seen and there is a total lack of animal prescence
where normally water would attract much attention. Something very
disturbing has happened here, and the power of it still lingers in the
region. The harbour heads east, south and west, or you can go north onto
the ruined docks.

name: In a burnt out harbour-master's room
description:
You are in the ruined remains of what was once the harbour master's room
for this port of Myth Drannor's boats. There is nothing here now but the
smell of blood and a feeling of disturbed peace. It is as if time has
stopped here, capturing the feel and blood of the ancient fall of the
city, rather than being just another dried out hole that you would expect.
You can head south onto the docks.

name: At the edge of the swampland ruins
description:
You are at the eastern edge of the ruins amongst the overgrown swamps. To
the east you can make out what looks like the ruins of one of the city's
ancient harbours. Unlike the rest of the swampy ruins the harbour to the
east seems to be relatively free of swamp and forest growth, and there is
the strong smell of salt water, or blood, in the air...

name: Before the Rakshasa Tower
description:
You are standing before a massive tower seemingly carved from a single piece
of solid granite.  Black as night, the stone appears to absorb all light that
comes near, and the closer you get, the less light your lanterns seem to
radiate.  At the base of the tower is a pair of huge doors, apparently leading
inside.  Up ahead you see a guard post, manned by some large tigers which seem
to be standing on two feet. To the south there is an open door way leading
out to the ruins.

name: Guard Post Outside the Tower
description:
This area teems with activity, many rakshasa and drow coming and going from
the tower up ahead.  There are guards stationed here, observing those coming
and going, and questioning those who they deem not to belong.  As you watch,
one of the guards stops a young drow man, asks him a few questions, and
seeming dissatisfied, proceeds to beat the young man, sending him fleeing
back the way he came.  You may enter the tower to the north, or return to the
west.

name: Guard Post Outside the Tower
description:
This area teems with activity, many rakshasa and drow coming and going from
the tower up ahead.  There are guards stationed here, observing those coming
and going, and questioning those who they deem not to belong.  As you watch,
one of the guards stops a young drow man, asks him a few questions, and
seeming dissatisfied, proceeds to beat the young man, sending him fleeing
back the way he came.  You may continue east or west.

name: Guard Post Outside the Tower
description:
This area teems with activity, many rakshasa and drow coming and going from
the tower up ahead.  There are guards stationed here, observing those coming
and going, and questioning those who they deem not to belong.  As you watch,
one of the guards stops a young drow man, asks him a few questions, and
seeming dissatisfied, proceeds to beat the young man, sending him fleeing
back the way he came.  You may continue east or west.

name: A Corridor in the Tower
description:
Dark, steamy, and quiet.  Too quiet.  Long shadows creep up and down the walls
in the flickering torchlight, occasionally obscured by the steam whisping along
the floor.  The flagstones here are slick with moisture, and the roof is
slightly too low for comfort.  You can continue into the darkness to the north
or return to the east.

name: Inside the Tower
description:
You are standing inside the left gate of the tower.  Light spills in through
the cracks around the gate, but is obscured by light wisps of steam seeming
coming from nowhere.  There is a sort of opressive darkness here, boding of
great evil somewhere within these walls.  Perhaps you should turn back now?
You may continue into the tower to the east and west, or leave to the south.

name: Entrance to the Dark Temple
description:
Before you lies a sight like nothing you have ever seen.  Tall guards stand
inside the entrance to what appears to be a temple.  The doorway is in the
shape of a gigantic skull, with torches lit in the eye sockets for
illumination.  From inside you can hear a deep, resonant chanting, and
occasionally a scream.  You may head back into the the darkness to the east
and west.

name: Inside the Tower
description:
You are standing inside the left gate of the tower.  Light spills in through
the cracks around the gate, but is obscured by light wisps of steam seeming
coming from nowhere.  There is a sort of opressive darkness here, boding of
great evil somewhere within these walls.  Perhaps you should turn back now?
You may continue into the tower to the east and west, or leave to the south.

name: A Corridor in the Tower
description:
Dark, steamy, and quiet.  Too quiet.  Long shadows creep up and down the walls
in the flickering torchlight, occasionally obscured by the steam whisping along
the floor.  The flagstones here are slick with moisture, and the roof is
slightly too low for comfort.  You can continue into the darkness to the north
or return to the west.

name: Barracks
description:
Rows of bunks line the walls in this small alcove.  Plush furs adorn the bunks,
obviously used by the rakshasa guards at night.  At the base of each bunk is a
small footlocker, which upon examination contains little of value.  The room
is lit by a single lantern suspended from the ceiling.  You may exit this part
of the barracks to the north.

name: Barracks
description:
Rows of bunks line the walls in this small alcove.  Plush furs adorn the bunks,
obviously used by the rakshasa guards at night.  At the base of each bunk is a
small footlocker, which upon examination contains little of value.  The room
is lit by a single lantern suspended from the ceiling.  You may exit this part
of the barracks to the north.

name: A Corridor in the Tower
description:
Dark, steamy, and quiet.  Too quiet.  Long shadows creep up and down the walls
in the flickering torchlight, occasionally obscured by the steam whisping along
the floor.  The flagstones here are slick with moisture, and the roof is
slightly too low for comfort.  You can continue into the darkness to the north
or return to the east.

name: A Corridor in the Tower
description:
Dark, steamy, and quiet.  Too quiet.  Long shadows creep up and down the walls
in the flickering torchlight, occasionally obscured by the steam whisping along
the floor.  The flagstones here are slick with moisture, and the roof is
slightly too low for comfort.  You can continue into the darkness to the west
or return to the south.

name: Inside the Lich Temple
description:
You are standing in the southwestern corner of a Temple of the Lich.  Rakshasa
come here to worship the lich priest and pay their respects to their God.
Towering above you is a pile of bones, many of them human and elven, which form
the Lich's altar of sacrifice.  The temple continues north and east.

name: Entrance to the Lich Temple
description:
As you enter this temple, you are filled with a feeling of dread and fear.
Evil fills the air, the chants of rakshasa sing tales of doom and dread, and
rising up before you is one of the most hideous things you have ever seen.  A
massive pile of bones and carrion forms an altar of worship to the Lich, a
revered and respected religious head in rakshasa lore.  It is a testament to
the sincerity of the rakshasa's hold on this land that one such as this would
be here.  The temple continues east and west, or you can leave to the south.

name: Inside the Lich Temple
description:
You are standing in the southeastern corner of a Temple of the Lich.  Rakshasa
come here to worship the lich priest and pay their respects to their God.
Towering above you is a pile of bones, many of them human and elven, which form
the Lich's altar of sacrifice.  The temple continues north and east.

name: A Corridor in the Tower
description:
Dark, steamy, and quiet.  Too quiet.  Long shadows creep up and down the walls
in the flickering torchlight, occasionally obscured by the steam whisping along
the floor.  The flagstones here are slick with moisture, and the roof is
slightly too low for comfort.  You can continue into the darkness to the east
or return to the south.

name: A Corridor in the Tower
description:
Dark, steamy, and quiet.  Too quiet.  Long shadows creep up and down the walls
in the flickering torchlight, occasionally obscured by the steam whisping along
the floor.  The flagstones here are slick with moisture, and the roof is
slightly too low for comfort.  You can continue into the darkness to the north
or return to the west.

name: Barracks
description:
Rows of bunks line the walls in this small alcove.  Plush furs adorn the bunks,
obviously used by the rakshasa guards at night.  At the base of each bunk is a
small footlocker, which upon examination contains little of value.  The room
is lit by a single lantern suspended from the ceiling.  You may exit this part
of the barracks to the north.

name: Barracks
description:
Rows of bunks line the walls in this small alcove.  Plush furs adorn the bunks,
obviously used by the rakshasa guards at night.  At the base of each bunk is a
small footlocker, which upon examination contains little of value.  The room
is lit by a single lantern suspended from the ceiling.  You may exit this part
of the barracks to the north.

name: Officer's Quarters
description:
This room is different to the normal barracks.  The beds are single, not bunks,
and next to each is a small writing desk, obviously for filling out forms and
such.  The trappings on the bunks are more plush than those in the regular
barracks, and the footlockers are larger, but equally as uninteresting.  You
may return to the barracks to the east.

name: Corridor in the Barracks
description:
You are standing in a spartan corridor in what appears to be a soldier's
barracks.  There are schedules for guard changes on the walls, and lists of
names indicating merit or lack thereof.  You notice three different lists, each
of which being a different color, black, red or brown, indicating status in the
King's guard.  You see small alcoves to the north and south, a door to the
west, or you can return to the east.

name: Corridor in the Barracks
description:
You are standing in a spartan corridor in what appears to be a soldier's
barracks.  There are schedules for guard changes on the walls, and lists of
names indicating merit or lack thereof.  You notice three different lists, each
of which being a different color, black, red or brown, indicating status in the
King's guard.  You see small alcoves to the north and south,  or you can return
to the east.  The barracks continue to the west.

name: A Corridor in the Tower
description:
Dark, steamy, and quiet.  Too quiet.  Long shadows creep up and down the walls
in the flickering torchlight, occasionally obscured by the steam whisping along
the floor.  The flagstones here are slick with moisture, and the roof is
slightly too low for comfort.  You can continue into the darkness to the north
or return to the south.  You see light coming from a corridor to the west.

name: Alcove in the Temple
description:
You are standing in a small alcove off the main temple.  Squat wooden benches
lined with furs sit here in rows.  Worshippers wait here before paying their
respects to the Lich, although it appears to be rather quiet at the moment.  In
the north wall you see the faint outline of a door.  You can enter the temple
to the east.

name: Inside the Lich Temple
description:
You are standing on the western side of a Temple of the Lich.  Rakshasa
come here to worship the lich priest and pay their respects to their God.
Towering above you is a pile of bones, many of them human and elven, which form
the Lich's altar of sacrifice.  The temple continues north and south.  You see
a small alcove to the west.

name: Atop the Tower of Carrion
description:
You are currently standing atop the tower of carrion, before the Altar of the
Lich.  The floor here is made up of femurs of humans and elves, slick with
thick blood of recent sacrifices.  There is an altar of human skulls standing
in the centre of the tower where the sacrifices to the Dark Lord are made.
Behind this altar is the throne of the Lich himself.  The only way out of here
is back down the tower.

name: Inside the Lich Temple
description:
You are standing on the eastern side of a Temple of the Lich.  Rakshasa
come here to worship the lich priest and pay their respects to their God.
Towering above you is a pile of bones, many of them human and elven, which form
the Lich's altar of sacrifice.  The temple continues north and south.  You see
a small alcove to the east.

description:
You are standing on the northern side of a Temple of the Lich.  Rakshasa
come here to worship the lich priest and pay their respects to their God.
Towering above you is a pile of bones, many of them human and elven, which form
the Lich's altar of sacrifice.  From here you can see a staircase of bones,
slick with blood, leading up to the top of the tower of carrion.  The temple
continues east and west.

description:

description:
Dark, steamy, and quiet.  Too quiet.  Long shadows creep up and down the walls
in the flickering torchlight, occasionally obscured by the steam whisping along
the floor.  The flagstones here are slick with moisture, and the roof is
slightly too low for comfort.  You can continue into the darkness to the north
or return to the west.

name: Antechamber
description:
This small room is furnished with some of the finest furs and wall hangings
that you have seen yet.  Along the walls are several plush chairs and small
tables containing various refreshments.  Guests wait here before going in to
see the King, but this doesn't mean they shouldn't be comfortable.  You can
exit the antechamber to the north.

name: A Corridor in the Tower
description:
Dark, steamy, and quiet.  Too quiet.  Long shadows creep up and down the walls
in the flickering torchlight, occasionally obscured by the steam whisping along
the floor.  The flagstones here are slick with moisture, and the roof is
slightly too low for comfort.  You can continue into the darkness to the north
or return to the east.

name: A Corridor in the Tower
description:
Dark, steamy, and quiet.  Too quiet.  Long shadows creep up and down the walls
in the flickering torchlight, occasionally obscured by the steam whisping along
the floor.  The flagstones here are slick with moisture, and the roof is
slightly too low for comfort.  You can continue into the darkness to the west
or return to the south.

name: A Corridor in the Tower
description:
Dark, steamy, and quiet.  Too quiet.  Long shadows creep up and down the walls
in the flickering torchlight, occasionally obscured by the steam whisping along
the floor.  The flagstones here are slick with moisture, and the roof is
slightly too low for comfort.  You can see a brightly lit room to the east,
or return to the south.

name: Before the Throne room
description:
Standing here you know majesty.  This room is lit by large sconces on the walls
adorned with precious stones of all descriptions.  The floor is of polished
granite overlaid with fine rugs and pelts.  In the centre of the room is a
large crystal chandelier lit by over 50 candles which throws sparkling light
over everything in the room.  Tall golden doors fill the north wall, and you
can see a smaller alcove to the south.

name: A Corridor in the Tower
description:
Dark, steamy, and quiet.  Too quiet.  Long shadows creep up and down the walls
in the flickering torchlight, occasionally obscured by the steam whisping along
the floor.  The flagstones here are slick with moisture, and the roof is
slightly too low for comfort.  You can see a brightly lit room to the west,
or return to the south.

name: Entrance of the Throne Room
description:
You are standing in the entrance area of the King's throne room.  Valuable furs
and gold leaf are everywhere, opulence seeming to be a part of life for the
King and his family.  The vaulted ceilings are so high that you can't see all
of them, and the walls are made of black granite with gold flecks.  This huge
room extends far to the north, or you can exit through the double doors to the
south.

name: King's Chambers
description:
You are standing in a small side-room of the King's chambers, which appears to
be used for nothing more than closet space.  There are racks of clothing here
covering three out of four walls, and dozens of pairs of furry slippers on the
floor.  You can return to the main chambers to the north.

name: Prince's Chambers
description:
You are standing in the bedchamber of the rakshasa Prince.  There is a large
fur covered bed sitting in the centre of the room, and a tall changing screen
in one corner, obviously for the benefit of his mistresses.  There are lurid
tapestries on the wall showing all types of erotic scenes, the centrepiece
being one showing the Prince himself.  You may exit to the east.

name: Prince's Chambers
description:
This is the main chamber in the Prince's quarters.  It has 3 plush couches
along the walls for guests to relax on, and a pair of smaller tables containing
refreshments.  There is a large, decorative rug on the granite floor and a
chandelier hung from the ceiling.  You can continue into the Prince's chambers
to the west, or leave through the door in the east wall.

name: West Alcove of the Throne Room
description:
This is a small alcove off the west side of the throne room.  It is lit by a
pair of flaming torches, one on each wall.  On the west wall is a pair of
curtains covering a heavy wooden door.  There is also a pair of curtains on
the eastern entrance to hide this alcove from the throne room proper.

name: The Throne Room
description:
Stupendous, opulent beyond belief, you stand in the throne room of the rakshasa
King.  Polished granite highlighted with carved gold inlays are features of
this enormous room, but the massive crystal chandelier lit by magical globes
is possibly the single most marvellous thing you have ever seen.  Furs, rugs,
tapestries, fine metals, gemstones all are in abundance here, fixed into the
furnishings here.  There are piles of soft cushions for dignitaries to rest
upon whilst talking to the king, and tables filled with every delicacy
imaginable lining the edges of the room.  Just to the north is the King's
throne, and you can see curtains east and west covering small alcoves.

name: West Alcove of the Throne Room
description:
This is a small alcove off the west side of the throne room.  It is lit by a
pair of flaming torches, one on each wall.  On the east wall is a pair of
curtains covering a heavy wooden door.  There is also a pair of curtains on
the western entrance to hide this alcove from the throne room proper.

name: King's Chambers
description:
You are standing in the centre of the King's private chambers.  There is a
small desk and chair here, and a small but comfortable sofa.  On the walls
there are several ceremonial swords and shields, made of various precious
metals, and as such unsuitable for battle.  The room is very much different
from the throne room outside, having almost no luxuries, but instead being
quite spartan and neat.  The throne room continues north and south.  On the
east wall you see a very large reinforced door.

name: King's Treasure Chamber
description:
This is a small, fortified room with a steel-lined door, and a large chest
bolted to the floor.  The walls aren't finished smoothly like the rest of the
tower, but instead have been left rough, you don't know why.  You can, however,
see various stains on the walls which appear to be the blood of former
pilferers...

name: Before the King's Throne
description:
You are standing before the King's throne.  Finely crafted from rare woods,
gold and cut rubies, you are duly impressed by this throne.  It stands on
a pedestal of polished black granite and is upholstered in fine velvet.
Behind the throne is a rack for the King to store his sword and shield
handy for any emergency.  You can return to the throne room to the south.

name: King's Chambers
description:
You are now in the King's private bedchamber.  Along one wall is a large
but relatively plain single bed.  On the walls are two tapestries, both
depicting scenes of war and bloodshed.  The floor is polished granite,
but there are no rugs to warm the floor, only cold hard stone.  It seems
the King doesn't wish to become soft in his reign.  You can return to the
main part of the chambers to the south.

name: In the foyer of a stone building
description:
You find yourself standing at the entrance to a large stone building. Unlike
most buildings in the ruins this one has been restored and kept in reasonable
condition. Large sticky globs of some fluid line the walls and floors, and
a disgusting smell fills the air. To the east and west you can see that the
corridor heads towards a pair of balconys overlooking the main entrance here.
South of here is a door leading out to the ruins.

name: In a stone corridor
description:
You are standing within a wide stone hallway. There are large pools of ichor
and fluids on the walls and floors. A horrible smell permeates the air and
threatens to choke you. To the east you can see the corridor leading to
the entrance of the building, while west the corridor turns towards a large
balcony that overlooks the entrance.

name: A bend in the stone corridor
description:
You are in a wide stone corridor of what appears to be a recently restored
building. The sticky ichor that clings to the walls of the building is very
thick here, almost like it was smothered onto the walls. To the north you
can see a staircase heading up to a balcony. The corridor itself heads back
east.

name: Beneath a wide staircase
description:
You are standing beneath a wide stairwell made of wood. It appears to be a
new feature of the building, replacing the older stone steps that had been
destroyed with the rest of Myth Drannor.

name: In a stone corridor
description:
You are standing within a wide stone hallway. There are large pools of ichor
and fluids on the walls and floors. A horrible smell permeates the air and
threatens to choke you. The corridor heads east and west.

name: A bend in the stone corridor
description:
You are in a wide stone corridor of what appears to be a recently restored
building. The sticky ichor that clings to the walls of the building is very
thick here, almost like it was smothered onto the walls. To the north you
can see a staircase heading up to a balcony. The corirdor itself heads back
west.

name: Beneath a wide staircase
description:
You are standing beneath a wide stairwell made of wood. It appears to be a
new feature of the building, replacing the older stone steps that had been
destroyed with the rest of Myth Drannor. Sticky ichor drips from the stairs
and hangs heavily from the roof. Above you there are faint sounds of
something breathing hard.

name: On a recently built wooden balcony
description:
You are standing on a recently constructed platform overlooking the main
entrance to this building. Your feet make SQUELCHing sounds as you step in
the thick, sticky ichor and gore that clings to the floor. There is an almost
overwhelming stench of something putrid in the air. The balcony heads west
to an alcove, or back down.

name: An alcove overlooking the main entrance
description:
You stand in wide alcove overlooking the building's entranec. From here it
is easy to see any intruders who may enter. There is a huge pool of sticky
fluids and green ichor on the floor and dripping from the walls here. The
only exit appears to be back east along the balcony.

name: On a recently built wooden balcony
description:
You are standing on a recently constructed platform overlooking the main
entrance to this building. Your feet make SQUELCHing sounds as you step in
the thick, sticky ichor and gore that clings to the floor. There is an almost
overwhelming stench of something putrid in the air. The balcony heads east
to an alcove with some stairs leading up, or back down to the main entrance
place.

name: An alcove overlooking the main entrance
description:
You stand in wide alcove overlooking the building's entrance. From here it
is easy to see any intruders who may enter. There are huge pools of sticky
fluids on the floor and green ichor dripps from the walls. The balcony heads
back west. A stairwell heads up to the second floor where you can hear heavy
ghastly breathing and disgusting suction sounds.

name: On a wide stairwell
description:
You are standing at the top of a wide stairwell. The stone walls around you
are covered in sticky gore and the air is almost unbreathable. Something
truly disgusting has been living in the building and the air reeks of it's
prescence. A decaying stone corridor heads south into the building's
second floor where you can hear the sounds of awful sucking and breathing.

name: In a stone corridor
description:
You are walking down a wide corridor made of rough hewn stone. The most
immediate aspect of the region is the terrible stench of some disgusting
creature. On the floor and walls are large sticky masses of slime and
gore. A pair of alcoves are to the east and west, while the corridor heads
north and south.

name: In a stone corridor
description:
You are walking down a wide corridor made of rough hewn stone. The most
immediate aspect of the region is the terrible stench of some disgusting
creature. On the floor and walls are large sticky masses of slime and
gore. A pair of alcoves are to the east and west, while the corridor heads
north and south.

name: In a beholder's alcove
description:
You are in a large alcove in the stone building. The walls are packed with
gross slime and fluids from some unspeakable beast. Burnt and mangled
corpses of some unidentifiable creatures litter the floor. There is very
little else other than the overwhelming smell of putrid decay. The alcove
heads back east to the corridor.

name: In a beholder's alcove
description:
You are in a large alcove in the stone building. The walls are packed with
gross slime and fluids from some unspeakable beast. Burnt and mangled
corpses of some unidentifiable creatures litter the floor. There is very
little else other than the overwhelming smell of putrid decay. The alcove
heads back east to the corridor.

name: In a beholder's alcove
description:
You are in a large alcove in the stone building. The walls are packed with
gross slime and fluids from some unspeakable beast. Burnt and mangled
corpses of some unidentifiable creatures litter the floor. There is very
little else other than the overwhelming smell of putrid decay. You can
only head back west to the corridor.

name: In a beholder's alcove
description:
You are in a large alcove in the stone building. The walls are packed with
gross slime and fluids from some unspeakable beast. Burnt and mangled
corpses of some unidentifiable creatures litter the floor. There is very
little else other than the overwhelming smell of putrid decay. The only
exit is back west to the corridor.

name: Bottom of a wide stairwell
description:
You are standing at the southern end of a wide stone corridor. Sticky
green fluids and ichor drip off the walls and an awful stench reeks in the
air. A wide, slime encrusted stairwell heads up into the building.

name: On a large stairwell in a building
description:
You are standing on a large, wide stone stariwell. The steps are slippery
and slick with strange green ichor and thick sticky slime. Heavy breathing
and disgusting sounds of eating can be heard echoing all around you. There
are small alcoves in the stairwell in all directions, while the stairs
themselves head up and down.

name: In a beholder's alcove
description:
You find yourself in a small chamber off of the stairwell heading up and
down in the building. Putrid, decayed corpses of some unidentifiable
creatures lie upon the floor and smaller body parts are stuck in the slime
and ichor clinging to the walls. You can only go south to the stairwell.

name: In a beholder's alcove
description:
You find yourself in a small chamber off of the stairwell heading up and
down in the building. Putrid, decayed corpses of some unidentifiable
creatures lie upon the floor and smaller body parts are stuck in the slime
and ichor clinging to the walls. You can go west to the stairwell.

name: In a beholder's alcove
description:
You find yourself in a small chamber off of the stairwell heading up and
down in the building. Putrid, decayed corpses of some unidentifiable
creatures lie upon the floor and smaller body parts are stuck in the slime
and ichor clinging to the walls. The only exit is north to the stairwell.

name: In a beholder's alcove
description:
You find yourself in a small chamber off of the stairwell heading up and
down in the building. Putrid, decayed corpses of some unidentifiable
creatures lie upon the floor and smaller body parts are stuck in the slime
and ichor clinging to the walls. The only exit is east to the stairwell.

name: At the top of a wide stairwell
description:
You are standing at the northern end of a wide stone corridor. Sticky
green fluids and ichor drip off the walls and an awful stench reeks in the
air. A wide, slime encrusted stairwell heads down into a dark stairwell.
To the south you can hear muted sucking sounds and heavy wet breathing.

name: In a slime encrusted corridor
description:
The corridor here is filled with thick warm mucus and green bile. It looks
like dozens of huge mouths have been drooling their saliva onto the floor
and walls for days on end. There is also an almost deadening stench of
something vile and despicable. The corridor heads north to some wide stairs
or south to a doorway.

name: Outside a huge iron door
description:
You are standing at the southern end of a slimy, disgusting corridor in the
stone building. Wisps of steaming green mist rise from the slime that lies
on the floor, indicating that it is very fresh and warm. A huge ornate iron
door has been set into the east wall, and you can make out belaboured
breathing of some horrible beasts on the other side. The corridor itself
heads back north.

name: SW corner of the Beholder Corps hall
description:
You stand within a massive open hall. The stone walls of the building have
been broken down between the individual rooms up here and cleared away in
order to provide a single huge, open area. Green warm gas fills the air as
it rises in stinking clouds from the mucus and slime pooling on the floor.
Large globs of ichor drip off the ceiling and onto you, causing burning and
itching. All around you the sounds of heavy breathing and rumbling voices
echo and revererate. There is a large iron door in the west wall, and the
hall heads of north and east.

name: Southern end of the Beholder Corps hall
description:
You stand within a massive open hall. The stone walls of the building have
been broken down between the individual rooms up here and cleared away in
order to provide a single huge, open area. Green warm gas fills the air as
it rises in stinking clouds from the mucus and slime pooling on the floor.

echo and revererate.

name: The Inner Chamber
description:
You are in th dangerous inner chamber of the beholder corps' main level.
Here there is very little to see but blank walls, there beholders
preferring to indulge themsleves in amusements not seen in the mortal
realm. There is a golden door in the west wall, and the chambers continue
east.

name: The Inner Chamber
description:
You are in th dangerous inner chamber of the beholder corps' main level.
Here there is very little to see but blank walls, there beholders
preferring to indulge themsleves in amusements not seen in the mortal
realm. There is a single ebon door in the south wall, or you can head west
through the chambers.

name: The Chamber of Xanath
description:
You stand in the blank but foreboding room of the Myth Drannor beholder
Corps' current beholder leader.  It is rather bland, but then beholder's
see things that mortals don't and there is probably more to the room than
meets the eye. An ebon door heads north, or you can climb some stairs up.

name: On a wide stairwell
description:
You stand at the head of a large staircase heading down. The walls here are
cleaner than those in the rest of the building and the stench of beholder
excretions is not so strong in the air. To the north the building opens into
a crossroads of corridors.

name: A junction in the cleared corridors
description:
You are in a corridor of the old building that seems better restored and kept
than the majority of the region. The air still has the foul stench that fills
the area, but it is not so strong here. Some inscriptions and paintings of dark
elven people adorn the walls along the corridor. The junction here goes north,
east and west, or south towards some stairs heading down.

name: In a wide cleaned corridor
description:
You are in a wide cleared out corridor in the restored beholder building. The
walls and floor are much cleaner than in the rest of the building, and the
foul stench of beholder excretions is not so strong here. The corridor heads
off east and west.

name: A bend in a wide cleaned corridor
description:
You are in a wide cleared out corridor in the restored beholder building. The
walls and floor are much cleaner than in the rest of the building, and the foul
stench of beholder excretions is not so strong here. The corridor heads off to
the north and west.

name: In a wide cleaned corridor
description:

walls and floor are much cleaner than in the rest of the building, and the foul
stench of beholder excretions is not so strong here. The corridor heads off to
the north and south, while plain wooden door are set into the east and west
walls.

name: Beneath a large stairwell
description:
There is a strong odour of disgusting beholder excretions blowing in from the
area above the stairs. Down here the stench is not so strong and the corridors
seem to have been cleaned of the sticky green saliva like mess. The stairs go
up or you can head east into the corridors.

name: Beneath a large stairwell
description:
There is a strong odour of disgusting beholder excretions blowing in from the
area above the stairs. Down here the stench is not so strong and the corridors
seem to have been cleaned of the sticky green saliva like mess. The stairs go
up or you can head west into the corridors.

name: Above a large stairwell
description:
You are standing at the top of a stairwell amidst a virtual lake of disgusting
beholder excretions. The stench from here is overwhelming and you can barely
breath as it rises around you in steaming wafts. To the east is a large open
space that almost looks like it's a pool of exrection and waste. The stairwell
leads back down.

name: In a hall of beholders
description:
You stand ankle deep in the sticky green excretions of a massive number of
beholders. The room is filled with thick steaming gas as it rises from the mess
on the floor, and you find it hard to breath. All around you there is the sick
sound of heavy laboured breathing. You can see a stairwell to the west.

name: In a hall of beholders
description:
You stand ankle deep in the sticky green excretions of a massive number of
beholders. The room is filled with thick steaming gas as it rises from the mess
on the floor, and you find it hard to breath. All around you there is the sick
sound of heavy laboured breathing. The halls head east, south and west.

name: In a well furnished room
description:
This room has all the trappings of a lords bedroom. It is spacious and very
expensively decorated. It looks like something other than just foul beholder
beasts live in this tower. There is a door in the west wall leading out to
the corridors.

name: In a dark room of arcana power
description:
This room has the feel of supressed violence and magical forces waiting to
be released. Despite the vileness of the room there is something almost making
you feel in awe of the power that is building up in here. The only exit out of
the room is to the west through a door.

name: In a bare room filled with rubble
description:
This room hasn't been restored like the rest of the building. There is a pile
of rock and debris dumped in here, indicating that much of the clean up ended
up being deposited in this room rather than carried all the way outside. There
is a door in the east wall leading out into the corridors.

name: The prisoner's room
description:
This bare room is mostly filled with rocks and derbis left over from the clean
up of the building. Some strong manacles hang off the west wall and pools of
thick blood and torn black fur are scattered around the room.

name: In a bare room filled with rubble
description:
This room hasn't been restored like the rest of the building. There is a pile
of rock and debris dumped in here, indicating that much of the clean up ended
up being deposited in this room rather than carried all the way outside. There

name: In a slime encrusted room
description:
The room is totally drenched in the foul smelling liquids of beholder drool.
There is nothing in the room untouched by the sticky green substance, and you
can barely see through the steaming mist rising from the warm mess. There is
a door leading west into the clean aired corridors.

name: A stone filled room
description:
The room is filled with stones and rubble of all size. The rocks here are in a
very ordered fashion, set up almost as if being used as furniture. There is a
door leading east out to the corridor.

name: A room of foul smelling vapours
description:
This room is filled with the smell of disgusting beholder matter. There is
little of real interest in it however, and you can barely breathe while in
here. The best way out is the door in the east wall.

name: In a bare room filled with rubble
description:
This room hasn't been restored like the rest of the building. There is a pile
of rock and debris dumped in here, indicating that much of the clean up ended
up being deposited in this room rather than carried all the way outside. There

name: The Dark Room
description:
This room is dark, with no lights at all within it. It is like some kind
of shrine to the night. The only thing you can see of interest is a lage
iron door in the north wall.

name: In a hall of beholders
description:
You stand ankle deep in the sticky green excretions of a massive number of
beholders. The room is filled with thick steaming gas as it rises from the mess
on the floor, and you find it hard to breath. All around you there is the sick
sound of heavy laboured breathing. The halls head north, east and south.

description:
You stand ankle deep in the sticky green excretions of a massive number of

name: Approaching the Cimar Harbor
description:
Just when you wonder if you will ever see civilization again you spot the
Cimar harbor.  Never in your life have you been so happy to see land.  As
the harbor approaches you can see the citizens of Cimar busily working.
You might just survive this journey.

name: Near the Shore
description:
Large waves crash up against jagged rocks here.  The water swirls around
as you come close to shore.  Some small pieces of debris float around in
the water, perhaps from ships that have been smashed on the rocks.  A large
rock here or there pokes up out of the water making this area very
treacherous.  Better be careful or you won't make it to shore.

name: Near the Shore
description:
Large waves crash up against jagged rocks here.  The water swirls around
as you come close to shore.  Some small pieces of debris float around in
the water, perhaps from ships that have been smashed on the rocks.  A large

treacherous.  Better be careful or you won't make it to shore.

description:

the harbor approaches you can see the citizens of Cimar busily working.
You might just survive this journey.

name: On the Crimson Sea
description:
You can no longer see shore as you continue along the rough water.  The
swells must be nearly eight feet deep and the constant rocking leaves
you feeling a bit ill.  The water stings as it hits your eyes. The only
other life present is the occasional sea creature swimming near you or
a bird circling overhead.

name: The Eastern Sea
description:
The currents are very strong making navigation difficult.  In the
distant west you can barely see some type of land structure.  The water
around here is filled with weeds and they have all taken on the same
red color that the water has.  The chance of seeing other people seems
slim. Perhaps you will be lucky enough to run into a friendly ship.

name: Just South of the Cimar Docks
description:
Various small fishing craft can be seen as you leave the Cimar dock.
Gulls and an assortment of finches circle overhead.  The strong smell
of saltwater fills your nose as the surf breaks at your feet.  The
ground and all of the earth around you is a dark shade of red.  You can
only assume this is because of the massive iron deposits nearby.

name: Before a Shipyard
description:
As you continue near the shore you notice a great deal of ships to your
north.  Obviously this docking area is important to the productivity of
Cimar.  The water is rough and you find yourself wondering if you
should just head back.  As you gaze off to the south you see nothing
but sea.

name: The Western Sea
description:
This area of the sea, while still rough, seems calmer than the rest of
the raging body of water. Every now and then you see a giant turtle or
some other sea creature sunning itself at the surface. This area seems
to be much more shallow than the rest of the sea.  As you look down you
can observe large boulders sitting on the sea floor.

swells must be nearly eight feet deep and the constant rocking leaves
you feeling a bit ill.  The water stings as it hits your eyes. The only
other life present is the occasional sea creature swimming near you or
a bird circling overhead.

name: The Island Guardian's Refuge
description:
You are high on a cliff on the north-eastern part of the island.  There
is a truly beautiful view of the entire sea from here.  You can see the
cliffs marking the beginning of Cimar to the north, and the cities
docksto the west.  You feel lost in the grandeur this great place.
Waves crash against the rocks below the cliffs, spraying up to this
height.  An enormous throne captures your attention.  The giant who
rules from this mighty throne must truly be a powerful man.  To either
side of the throne stands a large red banner with some strange markings
written on them.  The cliffs around this place make it suicidal to go
any direction but south.

name: On the Crimson Sea
description:
You can no longer see shore as you continue along the rough water.  The
swells must be nearly eight feet deep and the constant rocking leaves
you feeling a bit ill.  The water stings as it hits your eyes. The only
other life present is the occasional sea creature swimming near you or
a bird circling overhead.

name: The Eastern Sea
description:
The currents are very strong making navigation difficult.  In the
distant west you can barely see some type of land structure.  The water
around here is filled with weeds and they have all taken on the same
red color that the water has.  The chance of seeing other people seems
slim. Perhaps you will be lucky enough to run into a friendly ship.

name: The Eastern Sea
description:
The currents are very strong making navigation difficult.  In the
distant west you can barely see some type of land structure.  The water
around here is filled with weeds and they have all taken on the same
red color that the water has.  The chance of seeing other people seems
slim. Perhaps you will be lucky enough to run into a friendly ship.

name: The Western Sea
description:
This area of the sea, while still rough, seems calmer than the rest of
the raging body of water. Every now and then you see a giant turtle or
some other sea creature sunning itself at the surface. This area seems
to be much more shallow than the rest of the sea.  As you look down you
can observe large boulders sitting on the sea floor.

description:

name: The shore of a small island
description:
Finally solid ground.  You are walking on the slightly red sands of a
small island.  Many trees can be seen a little farther on shore, and
there is tall grasses all around.  Everything seems to have taken on a
slight red tint, like the water of the sea.  The noise of the raging
waters of the sea seems to quiet here, and the sun seems to come
through the clouds just a bit.  This island is a completely opposite of
the sea that surrounds it.  It is like a calm in the middle of a raging
storm.  A feeling of peace comes from this island.

name: The shore of a small island
description:

you lies the rough waters of the sea.  Hopefully you won't need to
return there soon.  Many trees can be seen a little farther on shore to

name: A cliff overlooking the sea
description:
As you continue walking about the ground turns more rocky on this part
of the island.  A few larger rocks lie about and the grasses are more
sparse, finding few cracks in the rock to take root in.  A few trees
are rooted into the rock making large cracks open up.  The rock is a
deep red color, much darker that that of the sands or water of the sea.
A small path has been worn into the rock leading to the north.  As you
follow the path with your eyes you make out a large throne sitting in
the middle of a clearing in that direction.  To the east the sheer
cliff makes way to the ocean, though you wouldn't want to try and go
that way because of the several large rocks that would hurt somewhat to
land on.  The rocky ground leads off to more cliffs to the south.

name: The shore of a small island
description:
You are walking on the slightly red sands of a small island.  Behind
you lies the rough waters of the sea.  Hopefully you won't need to
return there soon.  Many trees can be seen a little farther on shore to
the south, and there is tall grasses all around.  Everything seems to

east the trees seem to thicken somewhat and the grasses become more
dense.  There is no discernible way to go into the foliage, so you
might as well just push your way through.  The red sands of the beach
continues to the north and south.

name: On a small island
description:
You are standing in the middle of what amounts to a small forest.  Many
trees grow all around you and grass is growing everywhere that a tree
is not.  All of the foliage has a bit of a red color to it, more-so
than that of the plants along the beaches.  The ground is firmer here
that that of the sand.  You can even see a patch of rock here or there
in the grass.  You here the sounds of a small bird or two coming from
somewhere in one of the trees.  Off the north-east you see a rise
in the island that is rather barren looking.  In all directions that
foliage starts to thin out and you can start to hear the sounds of the
waves coming onto shore.

east.  To the south-east the waters of the sea crash up on large rocks
along the shore.

of the island.  A few larger rocks lie about and the grasses are more

deep red color, much darker that that of the sands or water of the sea.

want to try and go that way because of the several large rocks that
would hurt somewhat to land on.  The rocky ground leads off to more
cliffs to the north and south.  To the west the ground starts to slope
down toward the rest of the island.

description:

name: Rough waters near some cliffs
description:
The waters of the sea are very violent here.  On two sides there are
huge rocks that the waves crash into mercilessly.  You should try and
stay away from them or else you might get hurt.  You are almost
defended by the nose of the water crashing about.  The water becomes
slightly more calm to the south, but to the east it is just as bad.

name: Under the sea
description:
You are now below the surface of the sea.  The red waters completely
envelope you.  The water is quite cold against your skin and it seems
to have a slight salty taste to it.  As you look up you can see the
turbulent waves rolling past occasionally carrying various pieces
of flotsam along.  The sun manages to break through the clouds now
and then sending a ray of light down through the water.  The darkness
of the water makes it hard to see more than a few feet in any
direction.  From time to time you feel something against your leg.
Though you can't be sure if it is seaweed or something more
disagreeable.

Though you can't be sure if it is seaweed or something more
disagreeable.

name: Under the sea
description:
You are now below the surface of the sea.  The red waters completely
envelope you.  The water is quite cold against your skin and it seems
to have a slight salty taste to it.  As you look up you can see the
turbulent waves rolling past occasionally carrying various pieces
of flotsam along.  The sun manages to break through the clouds now
and then sending a ray of light down through the water.  The darkness
of the water makes it hard to see more than a few feet in any
direction.  From time to time you feel something against your leg.
Though you can't be sure if it is seaweed or something more
disagreeable.

name: An alcove within the cliffs
description:
Jagged rocks around you break the foamy crimson waves, sending the
pungent scent of wet rock and sea water into the air.  The cliff rises above
you on all sides, but in the western cliff wall, a dark opening echoes,
returning the ocean's roar.  The open sea lies back to the south.

name: A Crescent-Shaped Beach
description:
A beautiful beach, forming the shape of a crescent moon, stretches
out from the edge of the woods.  Deep, red sand lends an air of
relaxation to this utopian setting.  The water, in sharp contrast,
to the sand, starts out as a brilliant green, then turns to a
beautiful shade of turquoise all the way to the horizon.  A few
islands can be seen far into the distance.

name: A Crescent-Shaped Beach
description:
Extending out in the shape of a crescent-moon, the beach is a
perfect paradise.  It gives off the appearance of twilight no
matter the time of day, as deep, red sand stretches from one
end to the other.  A few palm trees dapple the shoreline,
adding to the breathtaking beauty of the place.  Some small
islands can be seen off in the horizon.

name: The Shallows
description:
Brilliant, green water breaks gently off the shoreline.  Here
and there, small fish can be seen darting in and out among the
waves in what appears to be a playful manner.  Far off in the
distance, a seagull is heard calling to its mate.

name: The Shallows
description:
The soothing sound of the surf can clearly be heard as beautiful,
clear, green water rushes back and forth to the shore, creating
complex patterns in the sand below.  Sunlight dances off the
cresting waves, creating a dazzling display of sparkles.

name: The Shallows
description:

and there, small fish can be seen darting in and out among the
waves in what appears to be a playful manner.  Far off in the

name: Sandbar
description:
A large sandbar runs parallel to the beach.  The normally clear
water is murky here as waves break violently across it trying
to reach the shoreline.  No life teems beneath these rough,
cloudy depths.

name: Sandbar
description:
No life can be seen here, as the water hurtles across the sandbar
in protest to being denied easy access to the shore.  A piece of
seaweed gets tossed violently about, caught in the endless currents
ripping back and forth.

name: Sandbar
description:
A large sandbar runs parallel to the beach.  The normally clear
water is murky here as waves break violently across it trying
to reach the shoreline.  No life teems beneath these rough,
cloudy depths.

name: A Coral Reef
description:
Clear, turquoise water houses a spectacular variety of exotic,
colorful fish living on a magnificent reef.  The reef is composed
of various hues of coral, sea fans and seaweed.   Numerous species
of sea urchins and starfish cling to the coral, waiting for food
to drift close.  Crabs can be seen scurrying about, trying to
avoid predators.

name: A Coral Reef
description:
Hundreds of different species of fish drift across the reef,
their painted bodies blending together with the corals and
sea fans to create a glorious kalidescope of swirling colors.
Tiny seahorses cling to seaweed, drifting back and forth with
the tides.  A large stingray skims across the top of the reef,
searching for its next meal.

name: The Naiadian Sea
description:
Gentle swells, no more than two feet in height, rise up and down
in a gentle rythm.  The water is a brilliant shade of turquoise,
so crystal clear it almost seems like you can see the bottom.
Here and there, small pieces of seaweed can be seen floating on
the waters surface.

name: The Naiadian Sea
description:
Diamond-like sparkles ripple across the turquoise water, dazzling
the eyes with its brilliance.  Dark shapes, large and small, can
be seen darting beneath the water's surface.  Some shapes are
clearly distinguishable as fish, while others just appears as
dark blurs moving to and fro.

name: The Naiadian Sea
description:
Crystal clear, turquoise water rises gently up and down, teeming
with life.  A large school of fish can be seen dashing about
a short distance below the surface, its sheer mass turning the
water black.  A large piece of seaweed drifts along the surface,
bobbing up and down in the gentle waves.

name: A Sandy Beach
description:
Nestled in a small, rocky cove, this tiny beach is the only
feasible access to the island.  Pitch black sand is covered
in sand dollars of varying shapes, washed in from the
occasional storm raging across the sea.  The clear, green
water is placid here, protected by the jutting rocks that
form the cove.

name: An Outcropping of Rocks
description:
Massive boulders jut up out of the depths of the sea from a
dormant volcano just beneath the surface.  Worn smooth from
thousands of years of sea water, the rocks have become a
favored sun bathing spot of the merfolk, for which the sea
was named.  The water is a deep blue here, not even a hint
of green can be detected.
