Nothing dares go near it for fear of becoming entangled.

name: The Naiadian Sea
description:
Crystal clear, turquoise water rises gently up and down, teeming
with life.  A large school of fish can be seen dashing about
a short distance below the surface, its sheer mass turning the
water black.  A large piece of seaweed drifts along the surface,
bobbing up and down in the gentle waves.

name: The Naiadian Sea
description:
Gentle swells, no more than two feet in height, rise up and down
in a gentle rythm.  The water is a brilliant shade of turquoise,
so crystal clear it almost seems like you can see the bottom.
Here and there, small pieces of seaweed can be seen floating on
the waters surface.

name: The Naiadian Sea
description:
Diamond-like sparkles ripple across the turquoise water, dazzling
the eyes with its brilliance.  Dark shapes, large and small, can
be seen darting beneath the water's surface.  Some shapes are
clearly distinguishable as fish, while others just appears as
dark blurs moving to and fro.

name: Within the Glimmering forest
description:
Ancient trees as wide as a ten feet stretch from the ground to the canopy
unbranched, upon reaching the canopy massive arms spread wide their fingers
straining to gain as much coverage as possible.  Wildlife noises echo
through the forest from trunk to trunk in a weird eerie way.  Light cascades
through the canopy upon each gust of wind, beams of light strike spots
lighting it up for a brief moment before the shifting canopy casts it in
shadow again.

name: Southern trail
description:
A bare dirt trail snakes its way through the forest, thick gnarled roots
occasional surface through the bare packed dirt.  On either side of the
trail are bushes and young trees waiting for a lucky break when they might
be able to spring up to take the place of a fallen giant.  A strong breeze
gusts its way up and down the trail, swirling with it lose dirt and the rare
fallen leaf.

name: The edge of the forest
description:
Ancient trees reach to the upper canopy as smaller bushes and shrugs
strive to reach the edge of the forest.  The mountain starts to slope slowly
then rapidly climbs into a cliff face that is covered with eight to ten foot
high shrubs.  The breeze is a lot stronger here at the edge of the forest
where the ancient trees hold little cover over the foothill.

name: Within the Glimmering forest
description:
Some small vegetation has managed to strangle a tree of its sustenance,
culling its ability to absorb light at the canopy level and enabling enough
light to shine through to provide for those plants underneath it.  Even
patches of grass has started to grow in the fertile ground.  Smaller
wildlife can be seen scurrying from bush to bush as the occasional bird can
be seen flying through the maze of tree trunks.

Ancient trees as wide as a ten feet stretch from the ground to the canopy
unbranched, upon reaching the canopy massive arms spread wide their fingers
straining to gain as much coverage as possible.  Wildlife noises echo
through the forest from trunk to trunk in a weird eerie way.  Light cascades
through the canopy upon each gust of wind, beams of light strike spots
lighting it up for a brief moment before the shifting canopy casts it in
shadow again.

name: The edge of the forest
description:
Ancient trees reach to the upper canopy as smaller bushes and shrugs
strive to reach the edge of the forest.  The mountain starts to slope slowly
then rapidly climbs into a cliff face that is covered with eight to ten foot
high shrubs.  The breeze is a lot stronger here at the edge of the forest
where the ancient trees hold little cover over the foothill.

name: Before a cool spring glade
description:
Ancient trees have grown excedingly tall with a small shaded glade spring
at their feet.  Smaller bushes line the edged of the spring and even grass
has managed to take hold where the soil is to shallow for larger plants to
grow.  When light manages to break through the canopy above the spring
luminates into a iradescent blue.

name: Within the Glimmering forest
description:
Some small vegetation has managed to strangle a tree of its sustenance,
culling its ability to absorb light at the canopy level and enabling enough
light to shine through to provide for those plants underneath it.  Even
patches of grass has started to grow in the fertile ground.  Smaller
wildlife can be seen scurrying from bush to bush as the occasional bird can
be seen flying through the maze of tree trunks.

name: Western trail
description:
A bare dirt trail snakes its way through the forest, thick gnarled roots
occasional surface through the bare packed dirt.  On either side of the
trail are bushes and young trees waiting for a lucky break when they might
be able to spring up to take the place of a fallen giant.  A strong breeze
gusts its way up and down the trail, swirling with it lose dirt and the rare
fallen leaf.

name: Scaling the mountain side
description:
Perched on a small outcropping of rock surrounded by extremely dense
bushes on all sides you can just see out above the upper canopy of the
forest that lies to the east, rising high and steep to your west is the
heavily vegetated cliff.  The air is clear and full of the fresh smells of
nature giving rise to the urge to push onwards.

name: Scaling the mountain side
description:
The bushes are not as dense here as they seem to struggle in finding foot
in the cracks and gaps between rocks.  Large rocky protrusions stick up from
the ground a couple feet, some many feet.  Wind wisps by the rocks with an
eerie wail that sounds more of a chime than a howl.

name: Scaling the mountain side
description:
The bushes are not as dense here as they seem to struggle in finding foot
in the cracks and gaps between rocks.  Large rocky protrusions stick up from
the ground a couple feet, some many feet.  Wind wisps by the rocks with an
eerie wail that sounds more of a chime than a howl.

name: Scaling the mountain side
description:
A small trail lined with dense bushes on either side snakes its way
across the mountainside.  Sections of rocks have crumbled away making this
trail extremely dangerous.  With the diminished cover of the bushes the wind
gusts are considerably stronger here.  The footing and wind conditions could
make for a dangerous crossing.

name: Within the Hermits abode
description:
Stepping into this small abode is quiet an outstanding sight, A half
spherical cage grows to about the height of ten feet.  Branches have woven
themselves over and under each other as it guided by some mystical force. 
Upon the ground even the rocks appear to be well worn and in comfortable
looking shapes, a slight rise in the center that is reasonably level appears
to be a table.  Small sunken indentations around the raised section of stone
appear to be cushioned positions to sit.

name: Within the hidden caves
description:
This natural cavern looks like water at one stage had carved out its
bowls.  When the cavern had neared the surface the pressure had caused a
collapsed and the fallen rock looks to have blocked off the water causing it
to flow in a different route.  Long needles of light puncture the darkness
of this cave splintering off in a myriad of shards when it strikes the rocks
strewn over the floor.  The air is still fairly damp and a large amount of
lichen and mosses grow upon the walls.

name: Within the hidden caves
description:
;This natural cavern looks like water at one stage had carved out its
bowls.  When the cavern had neared the surface the pressure had caused a
collapsed and the fallen rock looks to have blocked off the water causing it
to flow in a different route.  This section however isn't as deeply cut as
other sections, a small platue leveling off a couple feet above the floor. 
Strew across this raised section is what looks to be an extremely large
nest, belonging to which creature you do not know.

name: before a desecrated shrine
description:
This natural cavern looks like water at one stage had carved out its
bowls.  When the cavern had neared the surface the pressure had caused a
collapsed and the fallen rock looks to have blocked off the water causing it
to flow in a different route.  Placed in the center of this room is a large
granite tablet.  Shards of granite, obvious from the tablet, lay struin
around the room.  Years of not being touched mosses and lichens have claimed
owner ship of everything.

name: A rough trail
description:
You find yourself on a rough and ragged trail. Kicking up a rock or two as
you walk you notice exactly how barren this trail actually is. No plants
along the side, no trees for atleast 50 or so paces on each side, no
animals. To the south you can make out a road heading towards Varggin Shih.

name: A clearing
description:
This clearing seems to have been made by some unnatural force. Trees cut
down and no grass or plantlife of any kind. A strange smell wafts in from
the north. Looking closer you think you can make out tents and a large
fortress of some type. There is a rough trail to the south.

name: A dark encampment
description:
The encampment is small at first glance, but when you see how efficiently
the Obsidian soldiers handle their space you see it is no problem for them.
The ground is somewhat muddy from recent rain and the smell of something
strange wafts your way. There is a tent to the west.

name: Inside the tent
description:
The tent is filled with objects both strange and deadly in design. Jars of
blood litter bookshelves and a few weapons clash together in a corner. There
do not seem to be any beds in this room, only a few sheepskin thrown about
on the floor. The soldiers must not need the comforts of a soft bed. In times
of war one must be at their utmost level of strength.

description:
The encampment is small at first glance, but when you see how efficiently
the Obsidian soldiers handle their space you see it is no problem for them.
The ground is somewhat muddy from recent rain and the smell of something
strange wafts your way. You see a hill leading down.

name: At the Bottom of the Hill
description:
At the bottom of this hill you can see many things that the soldiers have
discarded here. Bodies, for one thing. You also see a sharp piece of dark
obsidian jutting out of the hill. You see no way to pull or push to break
it free, and it seems to hum with life and magical power.

name: Before the Obsidian Fortress
description:
The fortress itself is made completely of obsidian, giving the impression
it was forged from one solid piece. The outer gates are laced with mithril
and quite possibly the largest you have ever seen. On the front of the door
there is a crest of the Obsidian Order. You notice that the outer walls of
this fortress seem to hum softly.

name: Entrance way
description:
This large room serves as an entrance way to the fortress. The room itself
is quite large and the chandelier in the center of the ceiling illuminates it
quite well. To the south you see the large gates which lead out into the
encampment of the soldiers of the order and to the west is a long hallway.

name: A long hallway
description:
The hallway is somewhat dark due to the walls being made from obsidian, yet
they seem to provide a feeling of calmness. Nothing covers the walls which
seem to hum with power. The high ceiling makes your footsteps echo loudly
throughout the hall, making you all too aware of the emptiness of it.

name: A long hallway
description:
The hallway is somewhat dark due to the walls being made from obsidian, yet
they seem to provide a feeling of calmness. Nothing covers the walls which
seem to hum with power. The high ceiling makes your footsteps echo loudly
throughout the hall, making you all too aware of the emptiness of it. A
large set of double doors are to the north.

name: A long hallway
description:
The hallway is somewhat dark due to the walls being made from obsidian, yet
they seem to provide a feeling of calmness. Nothing covers the walls which
seem to hum with power. The high ceiling makes your footsteps echo loudly
throughout the hall, making you all too aware of the emptiness of it. A
set of stairs lead up.

description:

description:

name: A turn in the hall
description:
The hall here is the same as the rest of the hallways you have seen so far.
Hallways go in both the southern direction as well as the eastern direction.
You notice your footsteps do not seem to echo as much here. On the western
wall you see a strange looking painting.

name: An Office
description:
The room is filled with a light smoke that hangs in the air with an almost
sickening smell. Papers litter both the floor and the large desk that sits
in the center of the room. You notice there is a window that looks out over
the entire encampment and also gives a good view of the surrounding areas.
The door to the room that leads north has been torn from it's hinges and
thrown on the floor.

name: The Commanding Room
description:
This is the room of the Commander of the soldiers of the Obsidian Order. The
floor is littered with plans that have been drawn up and discarded. The
center of the room has a scaled down version of much of thera, where the
encampment of the Obsidian soldiers is the center. There is an office to the
south.

name: A secret room
description:
This room is basically non-descript other than the stairway that leads up
and the back of a painting to the east.

name: Stairway
description:
The stairway continues in both directions. Made of obsidian and humming
softly, this stairway is much like the rest of the walls you have seen. The
only difference is that the higher you climb, the louder the humming gets.

name: A landing
description:
The walls here seem to hum louder than the hallways you have been through.
You feel almost as if you were floating, weightless and oblivious to the laws
of nature. A set of stairs leads down and the small landing continues to the
east.

name: A landing
description:
The walls here seem to hum louder than the hallways you have been through.
You feel almost as if you were floating, weightless and oblivious to the laws
of nature. A set of stairs leads up and the small landing continues to the
west.

name: A landing
description:
The walls here seem to hum louder than the hallways you have been through.
You feel almost as if you were floating, weightless and oblivious to the laws
of nature. A set of stairs leads down and the small landing continues to the
east.

name: A landing
description:
The walls here seem to hum louder than the hallways you have been through.
You feel almost as if you were floating, weightless and oblivious to the laws
of nature. To the east there is a shimmering door while the small landing
continues to the west.

name: The Large Room
description:
As you enter the room you are hit with many sensations; taste, smell,
sound, and sight. All overloaded with a blinding flash of mist before you.
The room itself doesn't even seem like a room, but more of just space. You
don't even feel like you are standing on a floor, just floating in a cloud
of swirling colors, smells, and sounds. You cannot pinpoint any definate
shape in the room, only the sensations brought about by them.

name: On a ladder
description:
You are climbing on a ladder through a tunnel. The smooth obsidian walls
provide what seems like an easy climb, although you are not sure how. Just
above your head is a grate that leads into a hallway of the fortress and
below you is a small hallway.

name: A small hallway
description:
This hallway is much darker than the rest you have seen. Little light is
provided by the single torch that hangs on the wall. Cobwebs grow in a few
corners and a spider spins it's webbing around a fresh fly. To the east you
notice the hallway continues and a ladder leads up from here.

name: A small hallway
description:
This hallway is much darker than the rest you have seen. Little light is
provided by the single torch that hangs on the wall. Cobwebs grow in a few
corners and a spider spins it's webbing around a fresh fly. To the west you
notice the hallway continues and a ladder leads down from here.

name: The Dungeon
description:
This room is part of the dungeon of the Fortress. The Obsidian Order places
people here who oppose it or get in the way of it's reign of terror. There
is a cell door to the north, east, south, and west, as well as a ladder
leading up.

name: A dark cell
description:
This cell neither smells good or looks good. A constant dripping from an
unknown source is enough to drive the contained mad. It is also very small
and very dark, which makes it difficult to see.

name: A dark cell
description:
This cell neither smells good or looks good. A constant dripping from an
unknown source is enough to drive the contained mad. It is also very small
and very dark, which makes it difficult to see.

name: A dark cell
description:
This cell neither smells good or looks good. A constant dripping from an
unknown source is enough to drive the contained mad. It is also very small
and very dark, which makes it difficult to see.

name: A dark cell
description:
This cell neither smells good or looks good. A constant dripping from an
unknown source is enough to drive the contained mad. It is also very small
and very dark, which makes it difficult to see.

name: Interrogation Room
description:
This is where the Obsidian Order takes people to get knowledge from. Be it
spies or rebel leaders, they are subject to the harsh interrogation of the
Obsidian Order. In the center of this room is a large table. There are many
types of items used in both torture and interrogation hung on the walls and
closed in racks.

name: The Room of Invasion
description:
This room is primarily used by the troops. Magically opened long ago it
serves as a doorway to the many areas of Shalar. To the east you see the
Temple of the Gods in Cimar, to the south you see what appears to be a
barbarian's village, and to the west you see the Intersection in Melcene.
Looking up, you notice a peculiar glow radiating from a strange magical path,
while looking down you see nothing but shadows.

name: Room of Magical Regeneration
description:
This room is filled with spiritual and magical sensations, stimulating your
mind in many ways making you produce twice the amount of magical energy than
usual. Unfortunately, with all the mental activity, your physical wounds
seem to take twice as long to heal. Something is scrawled sloppily on one
of the walls.

name: The Mess Hall
description:
Many tables fill this small room, all covered with fresh bowls of soup. This
is the mess hall for the soldiers of the Obsidian Order. Although they do
not enjoy comfort and pleasure, they need to survive, and thus are required
to eat. The smell from the soup wafts your way and you detect many smells
you wish you hadn't.

name: Inside the tent
description:
The tent is filled with objects both strange and deadly in design. Jars of
blood litter bookshelves and a few weapons clash together in a corner. There
do not seem to be any beds in this room, only a few sheepskin thrown about
on the floor. The soldiers must not need the comforts of a soft bed. In times
of war one must be at their utmost level of strength.

name: A Fog-Shrouded Trail
description:
You are on a fog-shrouded trail which runs up the side of this dark
mountain.  The ground is wet and muddy with melted snow, and the path which
should lead to the shores of the Naiadian Sea disappears amongst the mist
and the trees.  There is nothing for you to do but follow the trail that
twists up towards the broken, snow-covered heights of the mountain range. 
An old stone tablet with inscriptions stands beside a bush in the corner.

name: The Haunted Pine Forest
description:
The snow begins to fall thickly as you enter a pine forest in the
mountains.  The burnt remains of two log cabins lie in a clearing
about a dozen yards off the path.  There is a disconcerting silence
in these woods, an oppressive lifelessness that makes you want to
leave them immediately.  The trail stretches through these haunted
woods up the side of the mountain and down through the fog to the
foothills of the range.

name: Near the Summit
description:
It has become almost unbearably cold as you trek near the very summit
of the mountain.  The bare and broken trees provide no cover for you as
a cold and gusty wind whips the falling snow harshly into your face.
A pine forest covers the slopes of the mountain, while to your south
you spot a narrow mountain pass.

name: A Mountain Pass
description:
You are in a steep pass between mountain peaks.  It descends sharply to
the south, while heading north towards a summit.  All around you, you
see only the mountain rises and the wind-swept plateaus of these
ancient highlands.

name: A Mountain Pass
description:
The mountains part breath-takingly to reveal a huge forest of tall and
majestic oaks.  You can walk along a mountain creek which winds west,
down the side of the mountain and into the forest, or follow the trail
you are on and continue up the mountain pass.

name: A Thickly-Wooded Dell
description:
You are in a secluded dell at the foot of a great mountain range.  Old
valley ash are crowned with the slightest hint of frost, and bushes of
flowering foxglove line the bank of a stream which runs west into a
small vale.  To the south there is a great forest of majestic oaks,
while to your east a trail that seems little-used heads into the
mountains.

name: A Signpost in the Enchanted Forests
description:
Through the majestic oaks of these ancient woods, the deep earthiness of
the forest permeates your senses, while a gentle hum of magic in the air
pulses low and vibrant.  A shy nymph peeks inquisitively at you from
behind a tree before disappearing with a titter.  An old but sturdy
signpost stands beside a crossing in the paths, which lead in every
direction.

name: A Fae Crossing
description:
The path has taken you to a junction over which hangs the twisted
branches of two Blackthorn trees and an Elderwood tree.  You remember
folktales which tell that spiteful faeries lurk under the meetings of
such trees to waylay and confound woodland travellers.  Feeling a little
uncomfortable, you look south, where the forest seems to darken
menacingly.  The east trail beckons you to the safety of the Emerald
Forest.

name: Road to the Vale of Clover
description:
You are on an old road which runs alongside a clear stream.  It leads
to the Vale of Clover, a small valley at the foot of the mountains.
Looking down the road, you see a small village nestled beside a bend
in the stream.  Tall heather blows in the wind and you see some cows
grazing idly nearby.  The road east runs down into a wooded dell.

name: In Clover
description:
It's quite beautiful here in the quiet village of Clover.  The air is
fresh and filled with the scent of flowers.  There are some quaintly-
appointed cottages painted in bright colors on either side of the road.
You hear ringing laughter to the east, where a country path winds up a
hillock.  The village square lies to the north.

name: A Green Hillock
description:
You are on a small meadow on the hillock.  This seems to be where the
folk of Clover have their picnics.  From the sound of manly crooning
accompanied by girlish titters, you deduce it also where the local lasses
receive the attentions of their suitors.  Scattered trees and trimmed
hedges provide the green with shadynooks and pivate arbors.  The
hillock continues north, while the path west will take you back to the
village.

name: A Secluded Corner of the Meadow
description:
You are in a quiet corner of the meadow, well-shaded by two large cypress
trees.  Though empty now, it seems a likely spot for young couples to
exchange professions of love, undisturbed by friends or irate parents.
Having no time for such adolescent frivolities, you quickly scan the
countryside and note that from this vantage point, you can look over the
entire village of Clover.  You espy a dirt track which leads west from
the village and then turns north to a ruined abbey.

name: The Village Square
description: A couple of farmers are erecting a \Harvest Moon Festival\" sign over

area_id: where you are standing.  A gaggle of goodwives are gossiping by the
village well while their children are chasing a playful dog.  An apple
tree lends its shade to two old men who are sharing a large tankard of
cider.  You see a large farm to the north and a beaten dirt track to
the west.

name: An Old Dirt Track
description:
You are on an old dirt track outside the village of Clover.  The path
seems little travelled, and wildflowers grow abundantly by the side of
the track.  Heading east, you will return to the village.  The dirt track
continues west for some miles.

name: An Old Dirt Track
description:
Looking north, you see a ruined monastery at the end of the track, half-
hidden by a copse of cypress trees.

name: Farmer Griff' Farm
description:
You stand in front of a gaily-painted barnhouse.  Old Griff - farmer,
freeman and entrepreneur - seems to be having a little trouble keeping
his livestock in order.  His chickens are harrying his ducks in the
duck pond, while a big brown shaggy dog is chasing his pigs around the
entire farm.  From inside a blue and yellow farmhouse you hear Princess
Yaruga, the farmer's wife, shouting angrily in a foreign tongue.

name: The Witch Wood
description:
You are in the eerie domain of the Weird Sisters.  Ghost lights flicker
palely about your feet and cast a shadowed eye on a variety of rotting
plants and animals that cover the forest floor.  The twisted thorn trees
groan at your approach, and you are aware of a slow hissing that seems
to taunt you from the cover of darkness.  The forest stretches on for
miles.

name: The Witch Wood
description:
You are in the eerie domain of the Weird Sisters.  Ghost lights flicker
palely about your feet and cast a shadowed eye on a variety of rotting
plants and animals that cover the forest floor.  The twisted thorn trees
groan at your approach, and you are aware of a slow hissing that seems
to taunt you from the cover of darkness.  The forest stretches on for
miles.

name: The Altar of Sacrifice
description:
The trees seem to hang back in fear as you walk into a wide clearing in
the witch wood.  The clearing is dominated by a broken stone altar that
is caked red and black and the blood and grime of centuries of evil.
The torches that hang from the boles of the trees ringing the clearing
throw a halflight on a deep hole in the altar.

name: The Witch Wood
description:
You are in the eerie domain of the Weird Sisters.  Ghost lights flicker
palely about your feet and cast a shadowed eye on a variety of rotting
plants and animals that cover the forest floor.  The twisted thorn trees
groan at your approach, and you are aware of a slow hissing that seems
to taunt you from the cover of darkness.  The forest stretches on for
miles.

name: The Witch Wood
description:
You are in the eerie domain of the Weird Sisters.  Ghost lights flicker
palely about your feet and cast a shadowed eye on a variety of rotting
plants and animals that cover the forest floor.  The twisted thorn trees
groan at your approach, and you are aware of a slow hissing that seems
to taunt you from the cover of darkness.  The forest stretches on for
miles.

name: The Witch Wood
description:
You are deep in the Witch Wood.  The evil that taints these woods grows
palpable here.  Directly to your north is a wall of shifting shadows that
your light cannot penetrate.  Tall reeds with thorny blades grow around
a path that leads west into the mists.  The forest lies to your east and
south.

name: The Wall of Shadows
description:
You step into shadows and suddenly hellish voices shriek into your ears.
Your light flares brightly for an instant and you see the trees around
you writhing while they burn in black flames.  They bend their branches
into a series of glyphs and runes, forming an archway across the entrance
of a cavern to the east.  The voices stop suddenly, and you are once again
all alone in the darkness.

name: The Cavern of the Witch Sisters
description:
This is the abode of the Witch Sisters.  Gibbets hang from the ceiling,
scrying pools lie placid while cauldrons gurgle awfully.  From a large
rift in the ground infernal flames belch forth.  The heat in the cavern
is almost unbearable and you begin to feel yourself passing out from
the oppressive stench of brimstone.

name: The Witch Wood
description:
You are in the eerie domain of the Weird Sisters.  Ghost lights flicker
palely about your feet and cast a shadowed eye on a variety of rotting
plants and animals that cover the forest floor.  The twisted thorn trees
groan at your approach, and you are aware of a slow hissing that seems
to taunt you from the cover of darkness.  The forest stretches on for
miles.

name: The Witch Wood
description:
You are in the eerie domain of the Weird Sisters.  Ghost lights flicker
palely about your feet and cast a shadowed eye on a variety of rotting
plants and animals that cover the forest floor.  The twisted thorn trees
groan at your approach, and you are aware of a slow hissing that seems
to taunt you from the cover of darkness.  The forest stretches on for
miles.

name: The Witch Wood
description:
You are in the eerie domain of the Weird Sisters.  Ghost lights flicker
palely about your feet and cast a shadowed eye on a variety of rotting
plants and animals that cover the forest floor.  The twisted thorn trees
groan at your approach, and you are aware of a slow hissing that seems
to taunt you from the cover of darkness.  The forest stretches on for
miles.

name: The Witch Wood
description:
You are in the eerie domain of the Weird Sisters.  Ghost lights flicker
palely about your feet and cast a shadowed eye on a variety of rotting
plants and animals that cover the forest floor.  The twisted thorn trees
groan at your approach, and you are aware of a slow hissing that seems
to taunt you from the cover of darkness.  To the south a fog rolls out
onto a dead marsh.

name: The Entrance of the Witch Wood
description:
Your uneasiness mounts as you walk along this haunted stretch of road.
The mist clears, and you find yourself in a nightmarish forest.  The
empty husk of a dead nymph lies at your feet, and on either side of you,
the trees look twisted and tortured into unnatural shapes.  The depths
of the forest sends up a hopeless cry to usher you into the woods that
ring the edge of Hell.

name: Under Dark Woods
description:
The path continues darkly under rows of Elder trees.  A crooked road
leads west through a tangled hedge of briars.  A mist prevents you from
looking beyond the hedge, but you sense a powerful and oppressive evil
reaching out towards you with cold and clawed fingers.  To the south,
the forest seems to lighten considerably, and you are about to leave
in that direction when a tattered parchment, flapping weakly in the
wind, falls at your feet.

name: The Emerald Forest
description:
All the lingering beauty of these green woods conspire to charm you into
staying here forever.  Woodlarks are singing high in the boughs of trees
while shafts of sunlight turn the forest floor into a carpet of gold and
green.  The woodland trails running through this area of the forest seem
well-kept, yet untravelled.

name: The Emerald Forest
description:
All the lingering beauty of these green woods conspire to charm you into
staying here forever.  Woodlarks are singing high in the boughs of trees
while shafts of sunlight turn the forest floor into a carpet of gold and
green.  The woodland trails running through this area of the forest seem
well-kept, yet untravelled.

name: A Well-Used Trail Through The Forest
description:
You are on a forest trail that runs in all directions but north, where
the forest skirts the sheer mountain face.  Dew-covered hawthorn bushes
flank the east trail, along which several rangers are walking.  It seems
to be the woodkeepers' outpost.

name: The Woodkeepers' Outpost
description:
Your fellow rangers hail you as you stride into this wide clearing.
Some are preparing to leave on their daily treks through the forest,
while others are tending to injured woodland animals.  The Guildmaster's
cabin lies to the north, while several smaller cabins lie to the south.
A fair-sized lodge sits beneath a Redwood tree to your east.

name: The Guildmaster's Cabin
description:
Built from the logs of sturdy cypress trees from the Vale of Clover,
the Guildmaster's cabin has a homely feel to it.  Oaks have grown their
low branches across the roof of the cabin and any number of small forest
animals race along the length of the porch.  Elesar of the Woods is here,
instructing a young woodkeeper.

name: Smokey's Supplies
description:
You enter a lodge which sits under the shade of an ancient Redwood tree.
All manner of supplies and equipment useful to rangers and woodkeepers
are neatly stacked on shelves or stored in closets.  A parchment tacked
on a wall lists the supplies which you may purchase from Smokey, the
Ranger Bear who runs the supply store.

name: The Emerald Forest
description:
All the lingering beauty of these green woods conspire to charm you into
staying here forever.  Woodlarks are singing high in the boughs of trees
while shafts of sunlight turn the forest floor into a carpet of gold and
green.  The woodland trails running through this area of the forest seem
well-kept, yet untravelled.

name: In the Emerald Forest
description:
A circle of blue-capped mushrooms form an old faerie ring by the side
of the path you are on.  On certain nights of the year, the faerie folk
wander out into such rings for wild dances by the moonlight.  It is
said that mortals who are drawn into the dancing circle on such nights
can be held captive by faerie food or a faerie's kiss and made to dance
on and on for a period of seven years.  You hear a titter of laughter
from the branches of a tree, but when you look up you see nothing.

name: Before the Great Tree
description:
You stand at the perimeter of the largest, most incredible tree that
you have ever laid eyes on.  It has gold-flecked leaves that are the
size of small horses, with thick roots supporting a massive trunk that
is easily twice the size of the grand fortress of the Templar Knights
of Renhorden.  It seems to stretch endlessly into the sky, and you
wonder why you did not see it towering above all the other trees in
the forest.  You long to inch closer, but cannot seem to move beyond
an invisible barrier that keeps you about a hundred yards away.  You
see movement and lights in and about the tree, but there seems to be
no way you can get closer to it.

name: The Lost Grotto
description:
You follow the stream to a limpid pool where the waters lap gently
against the rocks.  Large ferns provide shade from above and the petals
of brightly-colored flowers float in the pool.  Sitting on the moss-
covered rocks by the pool is a slim young girl dressed in green.  She
has long black hair and elfin features, a yew bow slung across her back.
She seems oblivious to your presence and hums softly as she passes her
hand through the waters.

name: By a Stream
description:
You stand by a wide stream that flows swiftly to the north.  Drawn by
the sudden sound of musical laughter, you look over the tops of some
lilac bushes and spy a group of nymphs frolicking in the stream.  It
seems like a vision captured from some nature god's idyllic dream.  You
hear the distant roar of a waterfall to your south.

name: The Waterfall Glade
description:
A majestic waterfall pours from high above the mountains to the south.
Great torrents of water crash down on the rocks in a wide pool, and even
where you stand in a shaded glade, the wind blows sprays of water into
your face.  A profusion of flowering shrubs grow at the edge of the
pool.  In a large shaded retreat made by the overhanging branches of
silver oak trees stands a likeness of Altariel, the Lady of the Woods.
At the base of the waterfall, a rock pool with crystal clear water has
formed.

name: In the Emerald Forest
description:
The path here runs around a low grassy mound.  Looking closer, you see
the smallest of windows built into the mound.  It appears this is a
faerie hill, from which the faerie Rades ride out in celebration
through the wood paths of the Emerald Forest.  The angry face of a
faerie suddenly stares out at you from the window and interrupts your
scrutiny with a string of curses.

name: In the Emerald Forest
description:
You are at a three-way junction in the middle of the woods.  Wild trumpet
creepers run along the footpaths here.  It would seem some mischievous
pixie has drawn the vines across the path with the hope of tripping
woodland travellers such as you.  You watch your step.

name: The Emerald Forest
description:
All the lingering beauty of these green woods conspire to charm you into
staying here forever.  Woodlarks are singing high in the boughs of trees
while shafts of sunlight turn the forest floor into a carpet of gold and
green.  The woodland trails running through this area of the forest seem
well-kept, yet untravelled.

name: The Only Stump in the Forest
description:
In this small lonely clearing is an ancient stump.  Many years ago, a
forester callously hewed down a tree here.  In retribution, Altariel,
whose sanctuary the Emerald Forest is, transformed him into a poplar
tree.  The poplar tree stands here beside the stump, its branches cut
by the rangers of the forest whenever they are in need of wood.

name: The Emerald Forest
description:
All the lingering beauty of these green woods conspire to charm you into
staying here forever.  Woodlarks are singing high in the boughs of trees
while shafts of sunlight turn the forest floor into a carpet of gold and
green.  The woodland trails running through this area of the forest seem
well-kept, yet untravelled.

name: The Forest Road
description:
You are at the head of a long north-south road in the forest.  The
Greenbrier bushes that grow beside the path have shed their heart-shaped
leaves on the road.  All is quiet here.  To the north, dark Elder trees
loom out ominously.  The road continues south.

name: The Dead Moors
description:
Everything is black here.  These bleak moorlands are where the witches
plant the bodies of their victims, where the rotted corpses will rise by
moonlight as souless pumpkin men.  The fetid marsh pools have been the
graves of countless creatures, and the choking stench of death rises
from them.

name: The Dead Moors
description:
Everything is black here.  These bleak moorlands are where the witches
plant the bodies of their victims, where the rotted corpses will rise by
moonlight as soulless pumpkin men.  The fetid marsh pools have been the
graves of countless creatures, and the choking stench of death rises
from them.

name: The Dead Moors
description:
Everything is black here.  These bleak moorlands are where the witches
plant the bodies of their victims, where the rotted corpses will rise by
moonlight as soulless pumpkin men.  The fetid marsh pools have been the
graves of countless creatures, and the choking stench of death rises
from them.

name: The Dead Moors
description:
Everything is black here.  These bleak moorlands are where the witches
plant the bodies of their victims, where the rotted corpses will rise by
moonlight as soulless pumpkin men.  The fetid marsh pools have been the
graves of countless creatures, and the choking stench of death rises
from them.

name: A Hill in the Marsh
description:
You have come upon a low hill in the marsh.  As you ascend it, you
notice that the fog that covers the rest of the fens rolls away.  The
weeds are dry at the edge of the mound and the grass that grows here is
is lush and green.  A lone oak tree stands on the mound, like a beacon of
goodness that repels the evil of the witches.

name: The Forest Road
description:
You are walking a long a north-south road in the forest.  The Greenbrier
bushes that grow beside the path have shed many heart-shaped leaves on
the road.  Two blue-breasted swallows swoop low in front of you, trilling
out a morning song.  The road continues north and south.

name: The Forest Road
description:
You are walking a long a north-south road in the forest.  The Greenbrier
bushes that grow beside the path have shed many heart-shaped leaves on
the road.  Two blue-breasted swallows swoop low in front of you, trilling
out a morning song.  The road continues north and south.

name: A Trail
description:
Pausing a moment from your travels through the Emerald forest,
you hear the gurgling sound of moving water coming from the east,
while to the south the forest continues on with oak, pine and
rosewood. Peering intently toward the source of the sound, you
notice a faint outline of a bridge resting in the shade of the long
leafy branches of the tall, flanking trees.

name: A Shady Bridge
description:
You stand on the western end of a wooden bridge in the Emerald Forest.
It's origin is a mystery, but the fine detail and craftsmanship it bears
would rival even the most cunning of woodsmiths.  The branches of the
tall trees that grow on the banks of the stream cover the bridge in a
soft cool embrace while a breeze flows in from the north.  Huge salmon
and rainbow trout weave their way amongst the rocks in the stream below.
To the west the forest stretches on, while the sounds of laughter and
play drift in softly from the south.

name: The Shady bridge
description:
You stand on the eastern end of a finely crafted wooden bridge. It's
edges have small engraved runes carved into them, and the wood
is probably a form of pine or oak from the Emerald Forest itself.
Lacking the dull weathered tone and creaking of most wooden
bridges, it spans across a fairly wide river flowing in a north-south
direction. The height of the surrounding trees provide a pleasant
shade from the noon-day sun.

name: A Woodland Trail
description:
You are following a small woodland trail in the Emerald Forest. The
hear the sound of moving water to the west, and squinting a bit
intently you see a blurred outline of a small wooden bridge in the
distance. Who built that bridge? And why? Only a few seasoned rangers
have ever come this deep into the enchanted wood, and none ever
mentioned the existence of construction of a bridge. As far as you
know, the forest has resisted gently but firmly all attempts at
colonisation or lumbering, which makes it quite a curiousity.

name: A Dense Path
description:
You are walking deep in the Emerald Forest. The protective canopy of
the tall rosewood trees offer a welcomed protection against the sun's
rays as well as providing a home for thousands of living things, some of
whom chirp, sing or buzz their existence for all to know, while others
remain silent, at least to your ears while the aroma of fresh woodland
flowers fill the air.

name: A Woodland Trail
description:
You are following a small woodland trail in the Emerald Forest.  Off in
the distance to the east, you hear the sound of a roaring waterfall.
The trail continues to the north and south.

name: In the Emerald Forest
description:
You are walking deep in the Emerald Forest.  The tall oak trees all
around you offer welcome shade and provide homes for innumerable
woodland creatures.  You spot a brown squirrel darting away from the
bole of a tree in an industrious search for more nuts and berries.
The paths lead north, south and west.

name: The Emerald Forest Choir
description:
Pushing aside a tangle of falling vines, you find yourself on a trail
deep in an unexplored area of the Emerald Forest.  Passage to the north
and south are blocked by clustered thickets of sagebrush and rosemary.
The cheerful croaking of a tree-frog catches your eat, accompanied by
the soprano trill of a swallow and an acapella team of bush insects.
The trail allows travel to the east and west.

name: A Woody Copse
description:
You've stumbled into a small woody copse.  The trees here have grown
close and their curtains of vines obscure the view in any direction.
The fresh scent of wild thicket flowers hang in the air, the source of
which cannot be found.  A small green carpet lies in the middle of a
clearing, leading you to believe you've happened across someone's
quiet time area.

name: The Tree House
description:
This is a small platform with four walls and a leaf roof rather than
a proper tree house.  Nevertheless, it is very cosy and could accomodate
two quite comfortably.  A pot of jasmine tea is simmering over a fire
and a few plush cushions are scattered on a rug in one corner.  On a
shelf on the west wall are the complete works of Shakespeare, while
another book lies half-read on the floor.

name: A Small Clearing
description:
You stand in a small clearing deep in the Emerald Forest. The ground
shows no evidence of trees being cut down or any other indication
that the clearing is carved from axe or hand, yet the borders seem too
neat to be the result of Mother Nature's whim. In some areas the
shrubs and bushes appear to have gone out of their way (if that is
possible) to align themselves, and the soft wood grass while not having
the blunt heads of a kept garden seem to be growing neatly in line all
by themselves. Strong magic is at work here.

name: The Ragged Trail
description:
You stand on a ragged forest trail with passage leading in all four
directions. The pathways to the north, south and east lead deeper
into the woods, while a winding trail west seems to end in a small
clearing. From where you stand you can see small movement and
curious sound which you can't quite make out. The tree branches
sway softly while you decide your next course.

name: The Honey Bun
description:
Two lines of pixies and brownies stand facing one another yelling
and hooting in excitement. They seem to be deep in a game of
'pixie, brownie and Honey Bun'. A small bag filled with pipeweed
seed is placed squarely in the middle of the line, while both teams
are numbered off. A number is called, and the respective brownie
or pixie has to run forward, grab the bag and return to the line
without being touched. Looks like great fun.

name: A fairly large clearing
description:
There is an incredible sight before you! Dozens and dozens of
green clad pixies and oak brown dressed brownies are milling
around in a fairly large clearing, which stretches on to the east and
south. Little temporary stalls have been set up, selling a wide
variety of enchanting desserts, cream puffs and wonderful potions.
The grand pixie-brownie Bonanza Festival seems up in force, and
there are no signs of it ending in the near future...

name: The three way woodland
description:
You stand at the middling spot of a three way woodland trail deep
in the Emerald Forest. There are clear passages to the north, west
and east, while the path to the south abruptly ends at the foot of a
sheer cliff face, with a wall so smooth that it would be impossible
to climb. A variety of bird song and animal sound fill the air.

name: A Forest Trail
description:
The somewhat ragged west-ward forest trail makes a sharp right and
southernly turn here, making further travel to the west difficult
if not impossible, would be safer to backtrack and find another
path instead of hacking through the notoriously resilient trees of the
Emerald Forest. A tall tree with huge leafy branches branches stands
here tempting you to take a break and rest in it's shade.

name: A Dwindling Forest Path
description:
The forest path begins to dwindle here.  It's obvious you've entered
a part of the forest seldom visited by anyone.  You notice the richness
of the flora here, with a wider and thicker range of herbs growing in
wild abandon across the ground or in small cul-de-sacs formed at the
roots of the oak trees.  You hear a rustle in the bushes, but staring
intently without trying to look too obvious, you notice nothing.

name: A Lovely Trail
description:
You are following a faint north-south trail in the Emerald Forest.
Swallows and Bluebirds fill the air with song and laughter, and you
spy a small red-breast Robin sitting motionless on a branch on one of
the oak trees. The serenity of this forest is amazing, you feel at
peace and safe, as though you just stepped into a fairy tale where
the knights kill all the trolls, and nobody stays hungry. It's hard
not to day dream, walking here.

name: The Tombstone
description:
There is something rather peculiar about this part of the Emerald
Forest. A small tombstone sits in the middle of a small clearing.
Carved from a white substance, it's shiny surface reflects what
little sunlight that manages to escape from the umbrella covering
of trees surrounding the grave. Freshly picked flowers lie at the
foot of the tombstone, while strange symbols are lovingly engraved
on it. The strange thing is there are no paths leading from or to the
area, which would puzzle even the most observant elf or ranger. Who
would pick flowers for a lone grave and leave no evidence of passing?

name: The Wood-Path
description:
The Wood-path you're following gets more pronounced and used here,
a testimony that the Emerald Forest isn't populated (or at least
explored and travelled) only by it's original furry or buzzing citizens.
Multi-coloured flowers dance gaily in the wind while clinging to the feet
of the tall oak and pine trees flanking the forest road. Flying
squirrels leap from branch to branch, probably searching for a
delicious cashew or two.

name: Woodkeeper's Clearing
description:
The path ends in a medium sized clearing. A small wooden sign states
quite dogmatically \WoodKeeper's Clearing. Forest haters not welcomed.

area_id: Orcs
room_id: Bugbears and Goblins keep out!\". A number of elves and humans

area_id: dressed in a mixture of green and brown stand around here engaging in
friendly conversation. The actual Keeper's Meet hasn't started yet
apparently there are rangers from distant woodlands still trying to
make it for the meeting. A pile of scrolls sit on a small table
probably pamphlets to be distributed to the arriving participants of
the meeting.

name: The Green Vines
description:
Thick green vines form an impossible barrier to the south. There is
no reason to doubt that these vines possess the same ability to
block even the most determined machete-armed lumber-dwarf then all
the others. What does seem a bit strange, however, are faint footsteps
leading up to the vines and abruptly stopping. Could they merely be
tracks from an age past, now lost to the world and found only in time
and memory?

name: The Silent Grove
description:
You've managed to wander into a small silent grove in the forest.
For some strange reason most of the forest noises seem to have
disappeared, though you can feel the rustle of the leaves beneath
your feet as you walk. The silence isn't really eerie, however, but
more of a contemplative quietness. Small stones are arranged in an odd
fashion on the ground, much the way seating chairs would be arranged
should the speaker be in the middle of a circle. It's almost as though
a little tribe of beavers just had a river-dam guild meeting and have
left for lunch.

name: The Southern border
description:
You are skirting the southern border of the Emerald Forest. A sheer
mountain face blocks any further exploring to the south and east,
while the forest streches on to the north and to the west. A fallen
log lies here, softing morning due and rain spray clinging to it's
sparkling bark. No rotting scent seems to come from it as most
logs would emit.

name: The Wood Area
description:
The trail leading south from here starts sloping downward into a
richer wood area. The undisturbed nature of the flora suggests that
this is a rarely travelled part of the forest even by it's own
standards. A small mouse-deer runs across the trail, followed by
a lazy looking lynx. To the north you can just make out a clearing
through the trees, and there seems to be movement.

name: The Bonanza
description:
Standing here at the south-west end of the brownie-pixie Bonanza
Festival, your senses are quickly overloaded with sight, sound
and smell. brownies clad in soft brown cloth with little feathered
hats mingle happily with their slightly smaller and greener cousins,
the forest pixies. An almost musical chitter-chatter fills the
air, while the aroma of freshly baked treats drift in from the
north. There seems to be a forest dweller's competition, what
with the many games the pixies and brownies seem to be playing. A tug
of war is currently in progress, with the heaving brownies having
a slight lead over the grunting pixies.

name: In a Myrtle Shade
description:
You are in a clearing ringed by mulberry bushes.  You hear racuous
shouts of festivity coming from the north  where the brownie-pixie
Bonanza is in full swing.  In the centre of the clearing is an old
Myrtle tree, under the shade of which some revellers have taken to
rest.  A lone thrush sighs from a branch of the tree.  To the west
a trail slopes gently down.

name: The Bonanza
description:
You are standing at the south-east end of the brownie-pixie Bonanza
Festival. A major element of the celebration involves the grand
feasting of the Great Pie of Friendship. A great huge pumpkin pie
the size of farmer's cart stands proudly on a stone table with a white
tablecloth amidst a bodyguard regiment of apples, peaches, raspberries
and cookies. The dozens of eager eaters seem a bit impatient,
apparently this year's Bonanza Chairman (or Grand Pooh-ba) hasn't
opened the ceremony yet.

name: South-easterly end of the forest
description:
You stand at the southern most end of the Emerald Forest. The path
continues on north, while to the west appears to be a large clearing
with sounds of laughter and conversation drifting in with the breeze.
There is a sheer drop to the south, while moutains stretch on as far
as your eyes can see. The terrain belows seems mostly rock and stone
and has spare vegetation. You can just make out a small path heading
roughly to the east through a cluster of bushes and trees.

name: Within a garden
description:
You've managed to stumble into an oriental home. A small wooden hut
sits to the south of a garden lovingly nurtured with blooming yellow,
white and red flower blossoms. Two stone lions sit on wooden pillars
guarding entrance to the garden, while two jade dragons guard the door
to the hut proper. A small bucket pulled well stands next to a pen of
chickens and ducks who cluck and quack away merrily. Carrots, cabbages
and rice are grown in a medium sized plot of land to the north. There
is a small rock pool to the east.

name: A peaceful rock pool
description:
You've entered a very peaceful part of the mystic's home. A crystal clear
pool sits here with large smooth pebbles neatly arranged all around it's
circumference. Peering into the pool, the unmoving mirror like surface of
the water reflect your image. There is no way of knowing exactly how deep
the pool is, but it must be very deep since you can't see the bottom. There
is a small wooden bench here beckoning you to sit and rest for a while,
and ponder things you've put aside, and think on matters you've forgotten.

name: Yun Fei Yang's humble abode
description:
You stand in the living room of a small wooden hut. A small partioned
kitchen is to the south of here. The spartan furniture, tidiness and
simple basic furniture hint at the occupier's character. There is a
beautiful painting of a young oriental women dressed in long flowing
silk on one of the walls. Parchments with foreign exotic wordings in
flowing black ink script sit on a desk. A small book catches your eye,
it's title being \Zhuge Liang's Chinese-Shalaran Dictionary\". Some of

area_id: the scrolls here are written in a language you can understand.

name: The Ruined Monastery
description:
Tangled vines of ivy hang down from what remains of the arch-entranced
of this small monastery.  It is ruined beyond repair and seems to have
been abandoned many years ago.  There is a quiet and melancholic silence
in the air.  You notice footprints in the dust that lead west into a
leaf-strewn courtyard and continue into a small chapel.  You notice for
the first time that that area of the monastery seems to have been spared
the dereliction that the rest of the monastery has fallen into.

name: The Chapel of Saint Sebastian
description:
You stand within the only standing structure of the once proud Monastery.
Evidently the chapel is looked after for the floors are swept, pews wiped
and the stained-glass windows in good working order. A modest pulpit
made of mahogany with a carved pine cross attached to it faces a few rows
of wooden benches. Probably cared for by questing paladins or clerics
on a pilgrimage, you wonder if any of the faithful might be nearby. To
the west wall you see a hole large enough for you to squeeze through.

name: Outside the Wall of the Monastery
description:
You stand in a small clearing outside the west wall of a small
chapel within a monastery. Birdsong fills the air while butterflies
yellow and red flutter about happily. A tall large oak brings shade
further west, but all movement to the north and south is prevented by a
combination of trees and the old stone walls of the monastery. There
is a serenity and a sense of life and peace, hinting that it is often
used by others as a place of worship or contemplation.

name: The Dead Moors
description:
Everything is black here.  These bleak moorlands are where the witches
plant the bodies of their victims, where the rotted corpses will rise by
moonlight as soulless pumpkin men.  The fetid marsh pools have been the
graves of countless creatures, and the choking stench of death rises
from them.

name: The Dead Moors
description:
Everything is black here.  The fogs rolls into the edge of the woods to
the north, while in every other direction the desolate marshes darken
your spirits.  Small creatures are feeding on each other at your feet,
while others are clawing their way to the surface of the mud.  A sudden
wind blows the fog away, and you see a small lake through the tall reeds
to the west.

name: The Dead Moors
description:
Everything is black here.  The fog rolls into the edge of the woods to
the north, while in every other direction the desolate marshes darken
your spirits.  Small creatures are feeding on each other at your feet,
while others are clawing their way to the surface of the mud.

name: The Witch Wood
description:
You are in the eerie domain of the Weird Sisters.  Ghost lights flicker
palely about your feet and cast a shadowed eye on a variety of rotting
plants and animals that cover the forest floor.  The twisted thorn trees
groan at your approach, and you are aware of a slow hissing that seems
to taunt you from the cover of darkness.  To the south a fog rolls out
onto a dead marsh.

name: A Broken Jetty
description:
You are at the head of a broken jetty, feeling the rotted timbers give
way beneath your feet.  The end of the jetty, which has long since
collapsed, stands over a dark still lake.  You look over the deep black
waters and see lights on the shore of an island hidden in the mists.

name: A Woodkeeper's Cabin
description:
You walk into the first cabin you see.  It is simply but comfortably
furnished.  There are four beds in the cabin, where the woodkeepers of
the Forest may rest after their patrols.  There is a small chest by the
foot of the bed.

name: Inside the mountain
description:
This deep enclosure within the mountain is of moderate size and mostly
empty, save some broken shards of pottery and a few strange mosses and
lichens growing despite the lack of sunlight.  To the west, a crude door
blocks the way out.

name: Inside a Cottage
description:
You are inside a neat and spotlessly clean cottage. The sanded wood plank
floors and timbered walls gleam in the soft light of several small oil lamps,
polished and waxed. Small ornaments of various shapes and sizes hang on the
walls and bright tapestries drape the rough wooden furniture and curtained
glass windows. Odd pieces of silver and crystal are sitting upon a long
trestled table in the middle of the room. Flowers from the forest, all cut
and arranged blossom from various vases and clay pots. The whole cottage
looks bright and cheerful even with nightfall. Obviously, someone with
good tastes lives here!

name: Iuppiter's Bedroom
description:
You walk into a much smaller room filled with sculptures instead of small
ornaments: over a hundred of them, lining the walls in holographic niches
as well as scattered around the floor on ornate pedestals. The variety, as
you have come to expect, is astonishing, ranging from human-style chunks of
simple stone and wood to others that were more like tethered living creatures
than works of art. Each is illuminated by a flaming blood candle, giving a
sharp contrast to the darkness around. You can barely make out a huge bed
that lies in the northeast corner of this gloomy room. Several other portals
seem to lead out of this room. You wonder where they may lead to...

name: Entrance of a Kelp Forest
description:
You float in the water before a large forest of kelp that is incredibly
dense and impassable.  You float in the cold waters of the Crimson Sea and
the cloudy seascape makes it hard to see very far.  The currents are very
strong here, not allowing you to swim upwards towards the surface.  The sea
life swims through here, paying you little attention.  Looking more closely
at the forest of kelp you suddenly notice that there is a small path that
leads straight to the south.  You stop to wonder what could force the huge
stalks of kelp to grow in the shape of a small path.  Looking to your north
you can see the vastness of the Crimson Sea.

name: Beginning of an Old Stone Path
description:
You are surprised when you see a cracked stone path suddenly appear beneath
your feet.  Looking behind you, you can see that it disappears into the sand.
The path is cracked and eroded, judging by the condition of the path, it must
have been underwater for a long time.  Several fish swim by, uninterested with
your presence.  To your east and west you can see a huge forest of kelp that
blocks any movement in those directions.  The path itself continues south and
it seems lead to the entrance of the kelp forest to the north.  A small cracked
sign lies on the side of the path, you think you can make a few words out on
its dilapidated surface though.

name: Old Stone Path
description:
The stone path is just as eroded here as the beginning and in places the
entire path disappears beneath the silt for a few feet.  The path takes a
sharp turn here towards the east but you cannot tell what lies there because
of the murky sea. Two large columns of the same material as the path lie
in pieces to the south.  Pieces of kelp and numerous fish float through here,
but most of the sea life pays you no mind.  Every once and awhile you think
you see a swimming form as large as twenty men, but you must be mistaken.
You notice that as you progress further and further down the path, the water's
temperature has begun to rise.  To your south you think you see a huge shadow
through the forest of kelp.  The water here is very murky, filled with enough
dust as to slightly obscure sight.

name: Old Stone Path
description:
The worn down path takes another turn, this time towards the south and as far
as you can tell it continues that way for awhile.  The water is so murky that
you have trouble making out your own hand and the sea of kelp looks like a
green wall.  There is definitely a large shadow to the south, that much you can
tell, what it is you cannot guess however.   The forest of kelp has begun to
fade a bit, but with the murkiness of the ocean you would probably get lost
without the guidance of the path.  The only exits that you can take are to the
west, to the ocean, or towards the shadow to the south.

name: Old Stone Path
description:
The water has become very warm here now that you are closer to the large
shadow in the distance.  The visibility has increased, and you can see that
the stone path is in much better condition here.  The kelp forest has all but
disappeared, and you can see many dead plants floating in the water. The large
shadow looms ahead of you, but the murkiness of the water still obscures what
its true identity is.  The path leads directly south towards the huge shadow
like an arrow.  You can either follow the path south towards the large shadow,
or go north into the murky waters.

name: Before the Walls
description:
You instinctively crane your neck back to look at the towering walls to your
south.  The walls are some of the tallest you have ever seen, reaching high
into the ocean and stretching out to either side of the horizon until you lose
sight of them.   The water is quite warm but the murkiness has finally lifted,
giving you a clear view.  Looking down the path, it leads straight south
towards the giant walls, hopefully to a gate of some sort.  Your only options
are to either go south to the gate of the city, or leave towards the north.

name: Before the Ruined Gates
description:
The gates that should lie before you are completely destroyed on the ocean
floor.  The high walls that loom above you are riddled with cracks and seem
ready to collapse at any moment.  The path below your feet is in just as bad
condition, with ruts and potholes everywhere.  Once it seems a large
civilization thrived here, but it has long since been abandoned.  Nature has
begun to take over here, as seaweed has begun to peek out of the cracked
streets.  A small crumbling staircase leads high up into the battlements and a
wide street leads south into the ruined city.

name: Atop the Battlements
description:
The battlements here allow you to see quite far across the entire surrounding
area.  You can see all of the city to your south.  Closest to you, there is
what seems to be a road full of large houses, most of which are two stories
high and must have at least ten rooms.  Further south you can see the main
residential area of the city, small one-room houses where the majority of the
city obviously lived at one time.  At the southern end of the city you can
barely make out two large buildings, although at this distance you cannot
determine the nature of either.  To your side you see a small crumbling
staircase that leads back down to the gates below.  The cracked battlements
continue to your east and west.

name: Atop the Battlements
description:
The battlements here allow you to see quite far across the entire surrounding
area.  You can see all of the city to your south.  Closest to you, there is
what seems to be a road full of large houses, most of which are two stories
high and must have at least ten rooms.  Further south you can see the main
residential area of the city, small one-room houses where the majority of the
city obviously lived at one time.  At the southern end of the city you can
barely make out two large buildings, although at this distance you cannot
determine the nature of either.  You cannot see any way to safely get down from
here.  The dilapidated battlements continue to your east and west.

name: Atop the Battlements
description:
The battlements here allow you to see quite far across the entire surrounding
area.  You can see all of the city to your south.  Closest to you, there is
what seems to be a road full of large houses, most of which are two stories
high and must have at least ten rooms.  Further south you can see the main
residential area of the city, small one-room houses where the majority of the
city obviously lived at one time.  At the southern end of the city you can
barely make out two large buildings, although at this distance you cannot
determine the nature of either.  You cannot see any way to safely get down from
here.  The dilapidated battlements continue to your east and west.

name: Atop the Battlements
description:
The battlements here allow you to see quite far across the entire surrounding
area.  You can see all of the city to your south.  Closest to you, there is
what seems to be a road full of large houses, most of which are two stories
high and must have at least ten rooms.  Further south you can see the main
residential area of the city, small one-room houses where the majority of the
city obviously lived at one time.  At the southern end of the city you can
barely make out two large buildings, although at this distance you cannot
determine the nature of either.  You cannot see any way to safely get down
from here.  The dilapidated battlements continue to your east and west.

name: Atop the Battlements
description:
You have reached the far eastern part of the battlements, and you can see
straight down the eastern part of the city.  You can see a cracked tower to
your east, but the battlements here have partly collapsed.  Looking further
to the east, you can see that much of those battlements have collapsed as well,
leaving only the tower standing.  Southward, you can see much of the city laid
out before you.  Closest are a multitude of small buildings, which seem to be
shops, long abandoned.  Beyond the center of commerce, you can see a large row
of what appears to be one-room houses.  Further south you can see an elegant
stone building that must be a palace or merchant house of some type.  You
cannot go any further east, but the cracked battlements lead back to the west.

name: Atop the Battlements
description:
The battlements here allow you to see quite far across the entire surrounding
area.  You can see all of the city to your south.  Closest to you, there is
what seems to be a road full of large houses, most of which are two stories
high and must have at least ten rooms.  Further south you can see the main
residential area of the city, small one-room houses where the majority of the
city obviously lived at one time.  At the southern end of the city you can
barely make out two large buildings, although at this distance you cannot
determine the nature of either.  You cannot see any way to safely get down from
here.  The dilapidated battlements continue to your east and west.

name: Atop the Battlements
description:
The battlements here allow you to see quite far across the entire surrounding
area.  You can see all of the city to your south.  Closest to you, there is
what seems to be a road full of large houses, most of which are two stories
high and must have at least ten rooms.  Further south you can see the main
residential area of the city, small one-room houses where the majority of the
city obviously lived at one time.  At the southern end of the city you can
barely make out two large buildings, although at this distance you cannot
determine the nature of either.  You can see large figures of stone standing
here staring out at the ocean floor, watching for intruders that will not
come.  You cannot see any way to safely get down from here.  The dilapidated
battlements continue to your east and west.

name: Atop the Battlements
description:
The battlements here allow you to see quite far across the entire surrounding
area.  You can see all of the city to your south.  Closest to you, there is
what seems to be a road full of large houses, most of which are two stories
high and must have at least ten rooms.  Further south you can see the main
residential area of the city, small one-room houses where the majority of the
city obviously lived at one time.  At the southern end of the city you can
barely make out two large buildings, although at this distance you cannot
determine the nature of either.  You can see large figures of stone standing
here staring out at the ocean floor, watching for intruders that will not
come.  You cannot see any way to safely get down from here.  The dilapidated
battlements continue to your east and west.

name: Atop the Battlements
description:
You have reached the far western part of the battlements, and you can see
straight down the western part of the city.  To your west, the battlements have
collapsed, and you can see a fallen tower as well.  To your south, the city
stretches out before you.  Closest, there are large buildings that seem to have
been guilds of some sort when this city was inhabited.  Further south, there
are rows of one-room buildings, most likely houses or storage areas.  At the
edge of your vision, you can see a huge, stone building near the south end
of the city.  It is completely plain and you have no idea what its purpose is.
There is no way to go to the west, but the old battlements lead back to the
east.

name: On a Ruined Street
description:
You walk down the ruined with care, afraid that the wrong move would make the
fragile-looking buildings crush you.  The street is quite wide, enough for
five wagons to go through at once.  Large stone buildings lie to your east and
west, although you cannot gain entrance to them here.  The street is flat
stone, not cobblestones like most cities, but cracks cover its surface.  Blue-
green plants grow from these cracks and you see small fish swim amongst the
buildings.  Obviously, nature has begun to retake what once was civilization.
A large sigil is carved into the center of the street, bearing a picture.
Further south you can see what seems to be a large intersection of roads. Back
to your north you can see the ruined gates and the crumbling battlements.

name: Large Intersection of Two Streets
description:
You have come to a large intersection of two streets, creating a large square,
at one point a place for commerce.  Now, all that remains is a large seal in
the middle of the square, and a stone fountain off to the side.  Long stalks of
seaweed grow from every crack in the street, giving it the appearance of a
grassy field. To your east you can see a long, thin street that connects with
many, small buildings which seem to be shops and stores.  To your west you can
see a long wide road that on either side there are large, expensive-looking
buildings, guilds or merchant houses of some type.  You can see the residential
area of the city to your south, and the gates of the city lie back to the
north.

name: On a Ruined Street
description:
The street that you walk down upon is both cracked and eroded.  Pieces of rock
lie everywhere, and in parts the street has completely eroded away, revealing
a thick layer of silt beneath it.  Not all that Looking to your east you can
see the side of a stone building, but there is no way to access it.  To your
west you can see a large, elaborately carved house, that must have belonged to
someone of considerable wealth.  The street leads southward towards small stone
buildings that were once houses.  Towards the north you can see a large
intersection of two streets.

name: On a Ruined Street
description:
The street is wide, and at one time was a single piece of stone.  Now however,
cracks and potholes riddle its hard surface.   Directly to your west you
see a carved wall of a large building that at one time belonged to a rich group
or person.  To your east you see an altar that people probably used to pray
at while they went around their daily business.  The cracked road continues
south to intersect with a street that leads to the abandoned houses of the city.
To the north, the road eventually crosses paths with a large street.

name: On a Ruined Street
description:
The street you walk upon is in a terrible state.  Cracks cover its surface,
and you must watch your step else a part of the street collapses beneath your
feet.  Small fish dart around you, most you have never seen or heard of before
and others look vaguely familiar.  The seaweed grows thickly through the cracks
in the street, impeding movement and sight.  To both your east and west you
can see the sides of simple houses.  Directly to your south you can see the
road that leads to the houses intersect with the one that you walk upon.  To
the north the cracked road leads back towards the center of commerce.

name: At a Small Intersection of Two Streets
description:
Two streets intersect here, the main street that goes from the northern to the
southern part of the city and the small street that leads to the ruined houses
of the city.  The wreckage of stone houses extend as far as you can see in both
east and west. In the middle of the cracked intersection, there is a large
circle of gold.  The cracked street is filled with sea life, from simple fish
to a translucent jellyfish.  Less amounts of seaweed grow here than other parts
of the city, but for what reason you cannot begin to guess.  To the north and
south, the main street continues its path down the middle of the inner city.
To the east and west, a smaller street allows access to the residential area.

name: On a Ruined Street
description:
The cracked street has obviously seen too much time underwater, for cracks and
potholes are prominent over its surface.  Seaweed grows out of most of these
cracks and sways in the currents of the ocean, making it look like  tall grass
blowing in the wind.  Fish, crabs and other sea life make their way through
here, paying you no mind at all.  To your east and west you can see the old,
crumbling walls of two houses.  Directly to your north you can see this street
intersecting with a smaller one that leads to the houses of the abandoned city.
Southward you are able to make out the forms of two huge buildings that extend
as far as you can see.

name: On a Ruined Street
description:
The street that you walk upon is riddled with cracks and holes.  Nature has
begun to take over as seaweed grows out of any available hole in the ground.
All other types of undersea life spend their lives amongst this ruined city,
completely ignoring your presence.  Looking to your east, you can see the
walls of the large palace, but you cannot see any entrance here.  To your west
you see the grey stone of a large and plain building, its purpose you cannot
tell.  To the north you can go towards the residential area of the city and
eventually the abandoned market as well.  Looking southward you believe that
you can see the gates that lead into the palace.

name: Before the Entrance to the Palace
description:
The street is pitted and cracked beneath your feet, giving the seaweed plenty
of room to grow.  Fish dart through the streets, completely unconcerned with
your presence.  Even with the beautiful sea life, your attention is completely
grasped by the gates to the palace that lie to your east.  The towering
palace looms to your east and you are captured at the beautiful architecture
that has survived the punishment of the water.  To your west you see the high
walls of a large, seemingly plain structure that is made from a strange, dark
grey stone. You can proceed to the abandoned houses to the north, or you can
progress towards the southern end of the city.

name: On a Ruined Street
description:
The street is cracked and filled with deep and wide potholes, making you glad
that you don't have to walk.  Sprouts of blue-green seaweed comes out of almost
every crack, making the street take on the appearance of a strange forest.
Colorful sea life swims everywhere, unconcerned with your presence, and the fact
that their home was once a immense city.  To your east you can see the walls of
the palace, but there is no way in as far as you can see.  To your west is the
wall of a large, plain building made from a grey stone.  North you think you
can see the gates to the palace, but with all the seaweed you cannot tell.  To
the south the cracked road continues along with the walls of the two large
buildings.

name: On a Ruined Street
description:
The road beneath your feet is cracked and pitted, creating troubles with
walking, even underwater.  Small sprigs of seaweed grow from the cracks in the
