name: In a Large Dark Room
description:
You float in the southeastern quadrant of a large, dark room.  The walls are
made from the same grey stone as the rest of the temple although they have
not survived the trials of the sea quite as well.  Your light source only allows
a small radius of illumination, you can only guess what is just beyond the
reach of the light.  The broken pieces of stone beneath you are covered with a
dark green sea moss that flakes off quite readily if touched.  You are quite
certain that the large room extends to your west and north, but you cannot be
sure.  Through the empty door frame to your east you can proceed to the dark
corridor.

name: In a Large Dark Room
description:
You float in the southwestern quadrant of a large, dark room.  The walls are
made from the same grey stone as the rest of the temple although they have
not survived the trials of the sea quite as well.  Your light source only allows
a small radius of illumination, you can only guess what is just beyond the
reach of the light.  The broken pieces of stone beneath you are covered with a
dark green sea moss that flakes off quite readily if touched.  You are quite
certain that the large room extends to your east and north, but you cannot be
sure.  In the corner you see a small statuette that is connected to the wall.

name: In a Large Dark Room
description:
You float in the northwestern quadrant of a large, dark room.  The walls are
made from the same grey stone as the rest of the temple although they have
not survived the trials of the sea quite as well.  You light source only allows
a small radius of illumination, you can only guess what is just beyond the
reach of the light.  The broken pieces of stone beneath you are covered with a
dark green sea moss that flakes off quite readily if touched.  You are quite
certain that the large room extends to your east and south, but you cannot be
sure.  To the north you can see the beginning of a corridor which disappears
into the darkness.

name: In a Large Dark Room
description:
You float in the northeastern quadrant of a large, dark room.  The walls are
made from the same grey stone as the rest of the temple although they have
not survived the trials of the sea quite as well.  You light source only allows
a small radius of illumination, you can only guess what is just beyond the
reach of the light.  The broken pieces of stone beneath you are covered with a
dark green sea moss that flakes off quite readily if touched.  You are quite
certain that the large room extends to your west and south.

name: In a Thin Corridor
description:
You are forced to stand upon the cracked and cold floor because of the low
ceiling in this thin corridor.  The corridor itself seems to spiral inwards
somewhat, leading to an unknown destination.  The pitch dark of the watery
depths seems to eat away at your light source.  A thin layer of silt covers
the ground and swirls into dark clouds as your feet brush by.  A dark green
moss grows upon the walls and pieces of broken stone.  The corridor spirals to
your west eventually leading to the south.  Back to the south the corridor
leads to a large dark room.

name: In a Thin Corridor
description:
You are forced to stand upon the cracked and cold floor because of the low
ceiling in this thin corridor.  The corridor itself seems to spiral inwards
somewhat, leading to an unknown destination.  The pitch dark of the watery
depths seems to eat away at your light source.  A thin layer of silt covers
the ground and swirls into dark clouds as your feet brush by.  A dark green
moss grows upon the walls and pieces of broken stone.  The corridor spirals
slightly to the south in both directions, but, it leads east and west for now.

name: In a Thin Corridor
description:
You are forced to stand upon the cracked and cold floor because of the low
ceiling in this thin corridor.  The corridor itself seems to spiral inwards
quite a bit here, leading to an unknown destination.  The pitch dark of the
watery depths seems to eat away at your light source.  A thin layer of silt
covers the ground and swirls into dark clouds as your feet brush by.  A dark
green moss grows upon the walls and pieces of broken stone.  The corridor
spirals towards your south and your east.

name: In a Thin Corridor
description:
You are forced to stand upon the cracked and cold floor because of the low
ceiling in this thin corridor.  The corridor itself seems to spiral inwards
somewhat, leading to an unknown destination.  The pitch dark of the watery
depths seems to eat away at your light source.  A thin layer of silt covers
the ground and swirls into dark clouds as your feet brush by.  A dark green
moss grows upon the walls and pieces of broken stone.  The corridor spirals
slightly to the south in both directions, however, it leads north and south
for now.

name: In a Thin Corridor
description:
You are forced to stand upon the cracked and cold floor because of the low
ceiling in this thin corridor.  The corridor itself seems to spiral inwards
quite a bit here, leading to an unknown destination.  The pitch dark of the
watery depths seems to eat away at your light source.  A thin layer of silt
covers the ground and swirls into dark clouds as your feet brush by.  A dark
green moss grows upon the walls and pieces of broken stone.  The corridor
spirals towards your north and your east.

name: In a Thin Corridor
description:
You are forced to stand upon the cracked and cold floor because of the low
ceiling in this thin corridor.  The corridor itself seems to spiral inwards
quite a bit here, leading to its final destination.  The pitch dark of the
watery depths seems to eat away at your light source.  A thin layer of silt
covers the ground and swirls into dark clouds as your feet brush by.  A dark
green moss grows upon the walls and pieces of broken stone.  The corridor
spirals towards your north into a room that glows with a strong gold light.
To your west the corridor spirals slightly in that direction.

name: Within the Altar Room
description:
You float within the large room which was the destination of the spiraling
corridor.  The room is made of the same grey stone that the rest of the temple
was, but here it seems to exude an aura of peace and tranquility.  The walls
are covered with carvings and strange writings of a language that you have
never seen.  Upon the floor there is a large carving of a sunburst, with a
small circle that is big enough for you to sit cross-legged in.  The walls
are completely clear of any cracks or holes and the entire room seems to be
in perfect condition.  Sitting near the north wall is the reason that this
room is lit with a golden glow, a large and beautiful altar blazes with light
and seems to emit a feeling of joy and love into you.  The only exit from this
beautiful room is back to the spiraling corridor to your south.

name: Below the Altar
description:
You float in a dark room which is cramped and dark, it appears to have been
once carved in the shape of a perfect cube.  The walls are completely blank,
made of a cool grey stone that is coarse to the touch and is as unyielding and
strong as the mountains of the North.  A small layer of silt has begun to form
upon the ground and swirls into tiny clouds as you float past.  You assume
that this was a room to place the sacrifices to the altar, a storage room or
perhaps to hide something very important.  Upon the western wall, there is a
small alcove carved, quite cleverly as it is not very easily noticed.  To the
north, the perfect wall has been destroyed by some incredible force, creating
a rough tunnel that continues into the utter darkness.  The hidden door above
you beckons back to the brightly lit room of the altar.

name: The End of the Tunnel
description:
The rough tunnel stops here, widening into a larger room and relieving the
feeling of claustrophobia.  This room appears to have been rended in the same
manner as the tunnel, through a massive destructive force of some kind.  The
room is still littered with small pieces of rock and the water is extremely
murky due to the large amount of dust.  Nothing grows here at all, in fact you
can see the bones of dozens of fish upon the ground, many of them horribly
mangled and destroyed.  The ceiling is roughly rounded into the walls, creating
a sense of vertigo as you cannot truly tell which way is up while in the water.
Upon the western wall, you see a perfect steel door, easily standing out against
the rough walls.  To the south the rough tunnel leads back to the small room
beneath the altar.

name: A Rough-Walled Side Room
description:
This tiny side room is in the general shape of a sphere, the ceiling and walls
do not exist, creating a profound sense of misdirection within you.  The room
seems to have been rended from the rock with pure force as the sides are
extremely rough and pieces of stone still lie about.  The room is quite small,
and combined with its round shape, you feel extremely uncomfortable while in
here.  The small blasted chamber is completely bare of any sea life or fauna,
only the shadows seem to dance in the back of your head and your mind reels
constantly, making it hard to think.  A large ornate chest is partially melded
with the stone in the middle of the rounded floor, a large platinum padlock
protecting it from prying hands.  The steel door to your east stands out in
plain contrast to the rough walls, leading to the large rough-walled room.

name: The Source of Magic
description:
This small shop is crammed full of magical things, although
everything is very orderly and well seperated.  There are
potions, scrolls, artifacts, components, and other items too
numerous to mention.  A beautiful woman, with gentle brown
eyes, offers you foci and implements of magical origins.  She
has quite a collection of some of the most fascinating treasures
you have ever seen.  The doorway to the north leads back out
into town.

name: Road in the SouthWest Quadrant
description:
Anemonies, ranging in various shades of white, red and purple, lend a
lively air to the street leading around the SouthWest Quadrant.  Carefully
laid out and lovingly tended, they form the shapes of the beautiful mermaids
and handsome mermen for which the town was named.  The street itself
is paved in brick, imported from some faraway land.  The road continues
to the north and east.

name: Road in the SouthWest Quadrant
description:
Anemonies, ranging in various shades of white, red and purple, lend a
lively air to the street leading around the SouthWest Quadrant.  Carefully
laid out and lovingly tended, they form the shapes of the beautiful mermaids
and handsome mermen for which the town was named.  The street itself
is paved in brick, imported from some faraway land.  To the east is
the South gate and the road continues to the south and west.

name: South Gate
description:
Ivy, carefully pruned back so as not to overwhelm the flowers growing
nearby, creeps up the brick colonnades and onto the gates themselves.
Painted white to offset the gracefully climbing vines, the gates are
handworked wrought iron, specially treated to avoid rust in the corrosive
sea air.  This gate is never closed, as many couples, yearning for a
few minutes alone, and townsfolk, seeking some exercise, enjoy taking
moonlit strolls through the beautiful gardens to the south.  North
leads to the Center Square, east leads to the SouthEast Quadrant and
west leads to the SouthWest Quadrant.

name: Road in the SouthEast Quadrant
description:
Multicolored crocus, of every conceivable hue and shade, stylishly
enchace the street leading around the SouthEast Quadrant.  Carefully
laid out and lovingly tended, they form the shapes of the wild and
deadly sea serpents that plague those who travel across the Naiadian
Sea.  The street itself is paved in brick, imported from some faraway
land.  To the west is the South Gate and the road continues to the
south and east.

name: Road in the SouthEast Quadrant
description:
Multicolored crocus, of every conceivable hue and shade, stylishly
enchace the street leading around the SouthEast Quadrant.  Carefully
laid out and lovingly tended, they form the shapes of the wild and
deadly sea serpents that plague those who travel across the Naiadian
Sea.  The street itself is paved in brick, imported from some faraway
land.  The road continues to the north and west.

name: The General Store
description:
Bins of various supplies fill this store.  Adventuring needs,
household provisions and more are available to suit any purpose.
The items have been thoughtfully grouped together by type of
need to make shopping easier.  The shopkeeper stands behind a
counter, smiling a friendly, welcoming smile as you enter the
room.  The doorway to the north leads back out to the street.

name: Antiques and Collectibles
description:
At first, the clutter in this room seems to be just junk and refuse
of the worst possible sort.  But, after consideration, you notice
that these items are retrieved salvage from nearby shipwrecks.  Each
individual piece has its own unique history.  Entering this room is
like stepping back in time to when these pieces belonged to others.
A matronly woman bustles up and begins telling you tales about each
piece that you seem interested in.  The doorway to the east leads
back to the normal flow of things.

name: Road in the SouthEast Quadrant
description:
Multicolored crocus, of every conceivable hue and shade, stylishly
enchace the street leading around the SouthEast Quadrant.  Carefully
laid out and lovingly tended, they form the shapes of the wild and
deadly sea serpents that plague those who travel across the Naiadian
Sea.  The street itself is paved in brick, imported from some faraway
land.  To the west is Antiques and Collectibles and the road continues
to the north and south.

name: Road in the SouthWest Quadrant
description:
Anemonies, ranging in various shades of white, red and purple, lend a
lively air to the street leading around the SouthWest Quadrant.  Carefully
laid out and lovingly tended, they form the shapes of the beautiful mermaids
and handsome mermen for which the town was named.  The street itself
is paved in brick, imported from some faraway land.  To the east is
Aquatic Pets and the road continues to the north and south.

name: Aquatic Pets
description:
This classy little shop contains an assortment of playful animals.
Just like everything else on the island, there is a little bit of
a maritime air about the place.  There are large fishtanks with
beautiful exotic species of fish swimming inside.  There are also
island lizards, a few species of bird, and even a few seals.  A
friendly young lady walks up and ask to assist you in any way she
can.  The street continues to the west.

name: The Storeroom
description: The pets are kept here.

name: The Vegetarian's Delight
description:
A tempting variety of fruits and vegetables fill the shelves of this cozy
cafe.  Everything from seaweed to fresh fruits of many varieties are offered
here.  The owner smiles pleasantly at you as he points out the specials he
is offering today.  The street continues to the east.

name: Road in the SouthWest Quadrant
description:
Anemonies, ranging in various shades of white, red and purple, lend a
lively air to the street leading around the SouthWest Quadrant.  Carefully
laid out and lovingly tended, they form the shapes of the beautiful mermaids
and handsome mermen for which the town was named.  The street itself
is paved in brick, imported from some faraway land.  To the west is the
Vegetarian's Delight and the road continues to the north and south.

name: Path to the Gardens
description:
Half sand, half dirt, this small path is extremely well traversed.
Rows of multicolored pansies and petunias, patterened in the shapes of the
surrounding sealife, line both sides of the walkway, giving passerbys
a small preview of the elegantly laid out gardens they lead to.  The
path leads north to town and south to the gardens.

name: Road in the SouthEast Quadrant
description:
Multicolored crocus, of every conceivable hue and shade, stylishly
enchace the street leading around the SouthEast Quadrant.  Carefully
laid out and lovingly tended, they form the shapes of the wild and
deadly sea serpents that plague those who travel across the Naiadian
Sea.  The street itself is paved in brick, imported from some faraway
land.  To the east is the Sushi Bar and the road continues to the
north and south.

name: The Sushi Bar
description:
Several intimate tables have been spaciously scattered throughout the
restuarant.  Vases, artistically decorated with deep blue orchids, grace the
center of each table.  Candlelight casts soft shadows across the room, as
waiters move discretely from table to table, serving meals with the utmost
effeciency and decorum.  The road is to the west.

name: Ye Olde Salt Saloon
description:
Walking the streets of this island paradise can sure work up a thirst.
Luckily, an old sailor noticed the lack of quality drinking establishments
in the city.  Opening this tavern turned out to be the finest decision of
his life.  People fill this room constantly.  There is always a line at the
door waiting to get in.  Waitresses walk by carrying trays laden with fine
beverages.  A large bouncer sits at one end of a long teakwood and mahoganey
bar, while the bartender rushes to keep up with all the orders.  The doorway
to the south leads out to the street.

name: Gemstones
description:
Long glass cases containing red velvet settings fill this chamber.
The jewelry and baubles here would impress anyone.  There are rare
black pearls and fascinating amethysts and sapphires.  Diamonds,
emeralds, and rubies abound as well.  All of the fittings appear
to be either platinum or gold of the highest quality.  Necklaces
that seem to be worth a king's ransom lie beside some of the most
exquisite rings you have ever seen.  A leathery old man with a
jeweller's loupe in his eye looks up as you enter and offers to
help you make your selection.  The doorway to the east returns to
the street.

name: Road in the SouthEast Quadrant
description:
Multicolored crocus, of every conceivable hue and shade, stylishly
enchace the street leading around the SouthEast Quadrant.  Carefully
laid out and lovingly tended, they form the shapes of the wild and
deadly sea serpents that plague those who travel across the Naiadian
Sea.  The street itself is paved in brick, imported from some faraway
land.  To the west is Gemstones and the road continues to the north
and south.

name: Road in the SouthEast Quadrant
description:
Multicolored crocus, of every conceivable hue and shade, stylishly
enchace the street leading around the SouthEast Quadrant.  Carefully
laid out and lovingly tended, they form the shapes of the wild and
deadly sea serpents that plague those who travel across the Naiadian
Sea.  The street itself is paved in brick, imported from some faraway
land.  To the south is the Thieves' Guild and the road continues to
the east and west.

name: Road in the SouthEast Quadrant
description:
Multicolored crocus, of every conceivable hue and shade, stylishly
enchace the street leading around the SouthEast Quadrant.  Carefully
laid out and lovingly tended, they form the shapes of the wild and
deadly sea serpents that plague those who travel across the Naiadian
Sea.  The street itself is paved in brick, imported from some faraway
land.  The road continues to the north and west.

name: The Anti-Paladin's Guild
description:
You are in a dark, cold room filled with devices of torture and
unholy symbols dedicated to the dark Gods. Men and women of all
races study to better themselves at the arts of harming the realm
and its' inhabitants.  The only exit is east to the buildings
entrance.

name: Entrance to the Anti-Paladin's
description:
The building erected here is dark and forboding.  Unlike the
rest of the city this guild appears almost to be relegated to
the backstreets as some kind of foul parasitic presence.  The
road lies to the north.

name: Entrance to the Paladin's Guild
description:
A small plot of undeveloped land is here.  There are various plants
growing upon it that, although naturally occurring in this environment,
don't really fit in with the general aesthetic beauty of the rest of
the town.  The street continues to the north or you can go further into
the plot to the south.

name: Entrance to the Cleric's & Monk's Guild
description:
A small wayside temple is to the east.  Non-descript and completely
unadorned, you barely glance at it once and then continue on your way.
The road continues to the north.

name: The Cleric's & Monk's Guild
description:
This temple is much grander than it appeared from the outside.
There are many men and women here, some are involved in hand
to hand and light weapons combat training, while others sit in
contemplative study.  A woman with a broad smile on her face
walks toward you and offers her services.  The doorway to the
west leads outside.

name: Path to the Gardens
description:
Half sand, half dirt, this small path is extremely well traversed.
Rows of multicolored pansies and petunias, patterened in the shapes
of the surrounding sealife, line both sides of the walkway, giving
passerbys  a small preview of the elegantly laid out gardens they
lead to.  The path leads north to town and south to the gardens.

name: Entrance to the Assassin's Guild
description:
A beautiful Zan rock garden is open here beside the street.  Every
individual stone seems to have its own place in the greater whole.
The mastery of this garden shows that someone or more than likely
a group of someones has dedicated years to making this garden perfect.
A small pagoda-style building stands to the south or you may continue
along the road to the north.

name: Entrance to the Thieves' Guild
description:
A warehouse sits here, abutting the city wall.  This is more than
likely the storage location for most of the merchants in this area.
The door into the offices leads to the east, and the street lies
back to the north.

name: The Thieves' Guild
description:
With surprise, you realize just how much of those merchant's wealth
comes here.  There are piles of every conceivable type of valuable
merchandise from everywhere in the town.  The thieves in this town
must use this as a centralized clearing house.  From the look of
things, the local law enforcement officials are woefully overpaid.
A short, nondescript man looks up as you enter.  He quietly asks
you to state your business.  The doorway to the west returns you
to the warehouse.

name: The Paladin's Guild
description:
The back half of the plot contains a magnificent altar.  An elegant
man intones words of praise to the Gods of good.  Wave after wave of
peace washes over you as the beauty of this holy place eases your
fears and worries.  The elegant looking man turns toward you and offers
you a comfortable place to rest before asking what assistance you might
have need of.  The street is farther back to the north.

name: The Orchid Garden
description:
Graceful and delicate, orchids of every imaginable color and size
fill one corner of the garden.  Every available space is taken up
by these beautiful buds, barely leaving enough room for people to
stroll through.  Here and there, a hummingbird can be seen flitting
from flower to flower, looking for nectar.  The path leads south
and east.

name: A Path in the Garden
description:
Rows of rare and exotic flowers line the carpeted pathway.  The fusion of
colors is perfectly coordinated to create a magnificent feast for the eyes.
Lovingly tended and perfectly manicured, the gardens are treasured by all
who call Naiadia home.  The path leads north to town and south, east
and west through the gardens.

name: The Sunflower Garden
description:
Sunflowers, bright as the midday sun, create a haven for frogs, mice
and other small creatures that thrive within their gentle shade.
Standing as tall as a the tallest man, they lend a lively, cheerful
air to their corner of the gardens.  The path leads south and west.

name: The Assassin's Guild
description:
This pagoda contains the local branch of the brotherhood of assassins,
a closeknit group of people whose worldwide network of guilds allow
them the ultimate in information gathering.  These people do not kill
for spite or whim.  They serve any who will meet their price, merely
doing their job in a slick and businesslike manner.  An aged man bows
as you enter and offers his service in training you in the ways of
your path.  The garden lies back to the north.

name: A Path in the Garden
description:
Rows of rare and exotic flowers line the carpeted pathway.  The fusion of
colors is perfectly coordinated to create a magnificent feast for the eyes.
Lovingly tended and perfectly manicured, the gardens are treasured by all
who call Naiadia home.  The path leads north, south and east.

name: The Fountain
description:
Four beautiful mermaids, contentedly sunning themselves on an
outcropping of rocks, graces this finely detailed and exquisitely
sculpted fountain.  Each mermaid, lovingly fashioned by a true
master of his craft, is such a rare and stunning beauty that you
find yourself completely mesmerized, wondering if such perfection
of form and face could truly exist.  A small rainbow archs
gracefully over the fountain, shimmering with a magical aura.
The path leads north, south, east and west.

name: A Path in the Garden
description:
Rows of rare and exotic flowers line the carpeted pathway.  The fusion of
colors is perfectly coordinated to create a magnificent feast for the eyes.
Lovingly tended and perfectly manicured, the gardens are treasured by all
who call Naiadia home.  The path leads north, south and west.

name: The Lily Garden
description:
Virginal white water lilies fill the small pond in this quiet
corner of the gardens.  Here and there, a goldfish can be
swimming amongst the flowers, its golden scales reflecting the
light, while dragonflies whiz about, causing tiny ripples along
the waters surface.  A multitudes of tiger lilies surround the
pond on three sides, lending a tropical air to this serene
setting.  The path leads north and east.

name: A Path in the Garden
description:
Rows of rare and exotic flowers line the carpeted pathway.  The fusion of
colors is perfectly coordinated to create a magnificent feast for the eyes.
Lovingly tended and perfectly manicured, the gardens are treasured by all
who call Naiadia home.  The path leads north, south, east and west.

name: The Rose Garden
description:
Tall and proud, a multitude of rose bushes vie for dominance in this
corner of the garden, their riotous colours sparkling brilliantly with dew.
Even in the heat of midday, the bushes are so dense and healthy that the sun
cannot burn off the water.  Their distinct, yet delicate fragrances swirl
together to create an intoxicating aphrodesiac that stimulates the senses.
The path leads north and west.

name: The Lover's Nest
description:
The only spot in the gardens where trees can be found, this tiny paradise
is almost completely hidden away, making it a perfect spot for clandestine
meetings.  Flowering vines, nurtured by the tiny pool in the center of the
glade, wind their way up the tree trunks, as they lightly scent the air with
their intoxicating fragrance.  A small path leads east.

name: A Path in the Garden
description:
Rows of rare and exotic flowers line the carpeted pathway.  The fusion of
colors is perfectly coordinated to create a magnificent feast for the eyes.
Lovingly tended and perfectly manicured, the gardens are treasured by all
who call Naiadia home.  The path leads north, east and west.

name: A Cozy Nook
description:
Nestled admist the wildflowers is a beautifully carved, wooden bench
for two.  Barely discernible from the path, many lovers seek it as
a refuge from the rest of the world.  The muted sounds of bird calls
fill the air, lending to the tranquil quality of this tiny hide-a-way.
A small path leads west.

name: Skins 'R' Us
description:
This quaint little boutique contains a nice selection of various
articles of clothing made from the local sealife.  Everything
from a genuine sharkskin suit to a naughty little teddy made of
seashells.  Trained salesclerks wander through the store assisting
the customers.  The doorway to the south leads back to the street.

name: The Respite
description:
A cool pond of crystal clear water lies in the middle of a small
clearing.  Flowers of various colors surround the pond, and birds
frolic through the air singing happy songs.  The peaceful sensation
urges you to sit down, rest, have a drink of fresh water, and take
a relaxing break from the toils the forest has to offer.

name: The Channeler's & Elementalist's Guild
description:
Upon entering this room, you are amazed at how tidy it actually is.
It goes against everything you have ever heard of about a wizard's
workshop.  There are orderly bookshelves along all of the walls,
containing treatises on magic and magic theory.  Tables are spaced
evenly throughout the room, allowing contemplative study and thought.
The guildmaster sits at his desk, patiently leafing through a
spellbook, waiting to answer any questions you may have for him.
The doorway to the south leads outside.

name: The Ranger's Guild
description:
This peaceful appearing glade contains several people tending to a
wide variety of wild animals or working on an assortment of wooded
projects.  The fluid grace with which they go about their tasks
belies their deadly combative skills.  The guildmaster queitly
approaches and offers her services.  Civilization starts to the
south.

name: Entrance to the Channeler's & Elementalist's Guild
description:
A nice footpath leads to an elegant house set back off the street,
overlooking the ocean.  A crisp breeze ruffles your hair as you walk
up to the door.  The front door of the residence is to the north and
the street continues to the south.

name: Entrance to the Necromancer's Guild
description:
A wizard's tower stands before you.  Tendrils of smoke seem to waft
from the windows as you approach.  The door appears to be to the
east, while the street continues to the south.

name: The Necromancer's Guild
description:
The prototypical wizard's laboratory.  Beakers and vials of every
shape and size clutter the workbenches lining the walls of this
room.  Corpses in every state of decay are strewn throughout the
room.  A wizened old woman stands by one of the tables and offers
her assistance in training you.  The doorway to the west leads out.

name: The Warrior's Guild
description:
A large training field and parade ground are here.  Scores of young
people are paired off to train defensive and offensive skills with
each other, both hand to hand and weapon's training.  A very large
man is efficiently aiding any and all who seek to learn from his
great wisdom in all the tactical disciplines.  A doorway leads to
the east.

name: Entrance to the Warrior's Guild
description:
A large tent-like structure sits right off the roadway here.  It
has a weapons rack and an armor rack leaned against opposite walls.
Through the doorway to the west, sounds of clashing arms can be
heard.  The street continues to the south.

name: Entrance to the Ranger's Guild
description:
A small glade is here.  It appears very peaceful and quiet.  A sense
of serenity passes over you as you hear a large variety of birds
singing.  A trail leads further north through the glade while the
street is to the south.

name: Road in the NorthWest Quadrant
description:
Varicolored peonies, of every imaginable tint, create a winsome,
lighthearted atmostphere along the street leading around the
NorthWest Quadrant.  Carefully laid out and lovingly tended, they
form the shapes of the exotic, and sometimes dangerous, fish that
grace the sea surrounding the town.  The street itself is paved
in brick, imported from some faraway land.  The road continues to
the south and east.

form the shapes of the exotic, and sometimes dangerous, fish that
grace the sea surrounding the town.  The street itself is paved
in brick, imported from some faraway land.  To the east is the
Naiadian Guardsmen's Headquarters and the road continues to the
north and south.

name: The Naiadian Guardsmen's Headquarters
description:
This obsidian building stands out like a rose among briars in
this lovely city, but it has a beauty of a subtly different
nature, making it fit in easily.  The shield and symbol of the
Naiadian Guardsmen adorn the walls to either side of the doorway.
The business offices are functional, but slightly enchanting as
well.  The guardsmen come here to receive their orders for the
day and to unwind after their shifts.  The place seems to be alive
with a constant bustle, but no one seems to be rushed.  The lack of
serious crime on this island is apparent in the easy manner of the
guards; however, they do handle their weapons in a professional
manner.  The training facilities are state of the art and the
instructors are firm taskmasters.  Clearly this professional force
can handle any amount of trouble if the need were ever to arise.
The street continues to the west.

name: The Mayor's Office
description:
This is the place where it all begins, the office of the lady in
charge.  Here is where legislation from the town council is signed
into law.  The mayor is a happy woman, and it shows in the way
she runs things.  People from near and far come to Naiadia to study
the day to day operation of this government, for it is truly a
marvel of the known world.  The street continues to the north.

name: The Naiadian Townhall
description:
This is the building in which the Naiadian Council meets to pass the
laws governing this fair city.  All meetings are open to any who wish
to view them, but only the council members may vote.  No meeting is
currently going on, but people wander through the building, admiring
the works of art and talking.  The street continues to the east.

name: Road in the NorthWest Quadrant
description:
Varicolored peonies, of every imaginable tint, create a winsome,
lighthearted atmostphere along the street leading around the
NorthWest Quadrant.  Carefully laid out and lovingly tended, they
form the shapes of the exotic, and sometimes dangerous, fish that
grace the sea surrounding the town.  The street itself is paved
in brick, imported from some faraway land.  To the west is the
Naiadian Townhall and the road continues to the north and south.

name: A Sandy Path
description:
This lovely, palm tree lined path is covered in fine beach sand, polished
by the wind and waves for so long that it is nearly white.  It reflects back
both the sunlight by day and the moonlight by night in an almost hypnotic
fashion.  The North Gate is to the south and the beach is to the
north.

name: Road in the NorthEast Quadrant
description:
Violets, ranging from the lightest mauves to the deepest midnight
blues, cheerfully decorate the street leading around the NorthEast
Quadrant.  Carefully laid out and lovingly tended, they form the
shapes of the various seashells that wash up on the beaches outside
of town.  The street itself is paved in brick, imported from some
faraway land.  To the east is the Lobster Pot and the road continues
to the north and south.

name: The Lobster Pot
description:
This small cozy restaurant has a decided nautical cast to its decor.
There are lifebuoys, life preservers, sailor's outfits, and other seagoing
items lining the walls.  The aroma of boiled lobster wafts from the kitchen,
making your mouth water as you wait for the first taste of the exquisitely
prepared food.  The doorway to the west leads back outside.

name: The Memorial
description:
As you enter this room, a wave of reverence fills your entire body.  This
shrine is dedicated to all of the ships that have been lost at sea over the
years.  The people of this fine city have placed a marker here commemorating
all the sailors lost in this region.

name: The Armory
description:
This small store is filled with an unbelievable assortment of armor
and protective devices.  There is a slight nautical cast to the
selection, as is to be expected in the middle of the sea, but there
are more common items as well.  The shopkeeper smiles a winning
smile as you enter the door and proudly shows you his wares.  The
street continues to the east.

name: Road in the NorthEast Quadrant
description:
Violets, ranging from the lightest mauves to the deepest midnight
blues, cheerfully decorate the street leading around the NorthEast
Quadrant.  Carefully laid out and lovingly tended, they form the
shapes of the various seashells that wash up on the beaches outside
of town.  The street itself is paved in brick, imported from some
faraway land.  To the west is the Armory and the road continues to
the north and south.

name: Road in the NorthWest Quadrant
description:
Varicolored peonies, of every imaginable tint, create a winsome,
lighthearted atmostphere along the street leading around the
NorthWest Quadrant.  Carefully laid out and lovingly tended, they
form the shapes of the exotic, and sometimes dangerous, fish that
grace the sea surrounding the town.  The street itself is paved
in brick, imported from some faraway land.  To the east is the
Naiadian Jail and the road continues to the north and south.

name: The Naiadian Jail
description:
Even the detention center for this community is aesthetically pleasing.
Troublemakers are kept in orderly rooms, furnished adequate food, and
treated with respect even though they broke the law.  The windows are
numerous and filled with a magical construct of glassteel, utterly
unbreakable but transparent as a still pond.  The walls are of thick marble,
but they are in pastel shades to match the ever present flora of the city.
The doorway to the west leads back to the street.

name: First Bank of Naiadia
description:
Tastefully decorated in an ocean motif, the First Bank of Naiadia
happily caters to the townsfolk and all the seafarers just passing
through.  A small, plush couch has been placed along one wall for
the comfort of those waiting their turn in line.  Beautifully hand
embroidered, it depicts a scene of a coral reef.  The road is to
the south.

name: North Gate
description:
Ivy, carefully pruned back so as not to overwhelm the flowers
growing nearby, creeps up the brick colonnades and onto the
gates themselves.  Painted white to offset the gracefully
climbing vines, the gates are handworked wrought iron, specially
treated to avoid rust in the corrosive sea air.  Although
closed at night, the gates are never locked, for the people of
Naiadia have always led an untroubled, worry-free existance.
North leads to the sea, south leads to the Center Square, east
leads to the NorthEast Quadrant and west leads to the NorthWest
Quadrant.

name: The Training Yard
description:
People from all walks of life come to this place to enrich
themselves, physically and mentally.  There are knowledgeable
instructors on hand to show you how to properly work out to
increase your physical and mental attributes.  As you enter,
a genial, young man walks up to you and offers his services.
The street continues to the south.

name: The Weapon's Emporium
description:
This small shop contains the finest in weaponry, both exotic and
commonplace.  There is a large variety to choose from and the salesman is
quite knowledgeable about their origins.  With a knowing eye he appraises
your weapons and offers you the assortment that seems to be what you are in
need of.  The doorway to the east leads back out to the street.

name: The Central Walkway
description:
The busiest section of Naiadia, many townsfolk stroll around
the walkway, stopping almost constantly to chat with neighbors
and friends.  Wrought iron benches, painted white and handworked
to depict life under the sea, have been thoughfully laid out at
intervals so that those wishing to stay and talk for a while can
make themselves comfortable.  Tulips of various shading and hues
have been lovingly planted on either side of the benches to
further enhance the cozy atmosphere.  The gentle fragrance of
magnolias drifts past from a nearby tree.  The walkway continues
to the south and east.

continues to the north and south.

name: Center Square
description:
A giant magnolia tree, its heady fragrance intoxicating the senses,
stands in the heart of Naiadia casting soft shadows all across the Center
Square.  It's branches sway back and forth in the gentle breeze drifting in
off the ocean, gently rocking the small swing someone attached to it.  When
the healer is free from his regular duties, he gladly pushes any small child
who wants a ride.  Despite the fact that all meeting and gatherings are held
here, the grass is always perfectly manicured and not a speck of litter can
be found anywhere.  The Square leads north, south, east and west to
the Central Walkway.

name: Road in the SouthWest Quadrant
description:
Anemonies, ranging in various shades of white, red and purple, lend a
lively air to the street leading around the SouthWest Quadrant.  Carefully
laid out and lovingly tended, they form the shapes of the beautiful mermaids
and handsome mermen for which the town was named.  The street itself
is paved in brick, imported from some faraway land.  The road continues
to the south and east.

enchace the street leading around the SouthEast Quadrant.  Carefully
laid out and lovingly tended, they form the shapes of the wild and
deadly sea serpents that plague those who travel across the Naiadian
Sea.  The street itself is paved in brick, imported from some faraway
land.  To the north is the East Gate and the road continues to the
south and east.

name: Road in the SouthEast Quadrant
description:
Multicolored crocus, of every conceivable hue and shade, stylishly
enchace the street leading around the SouthEast Quadrant.  Carefully
laid out and lovingly tended, they form the shapes of the wild and
deadly sea serpents that plague those who travel across the Naiadian
Sea.  The street itself is paved in brick, imported from some faraway
land.  To the south is the General Store and the road continues to
the east and west.

name: Road in the SouthWest Quadrant
description:
Anemonies, ranging in various shades of white, red and purple, lend a
lively air to the street leading around the SouthWest Quadrant.  Carefully
laid out and lovingly tended, they form the shapes of the beautiful mermaids
and handsome mermen for which the town was named.  The street itself
is paved in brick, imported from some faraway land.  To the east is the
Land Lubber's Boat Shop and the road continues to the north and south.

name: The Land Lubber's Boat Shop
description:
This bungalow contains rafts and boats of all types.  All of the
selections are in pristine order, as if the proprietor had just finished the
final coat of paint.  A smiling sailor welcomes you and offers his wares.
The steet continues to the west.

name: On the Road
description:
A smaller, narrower road than the one to the east, this is little more
than a path between two villages: Koteras and Dagdan.  To the south, Koteras
beckons with its proximity to Cimar.  Northwest of here, Dagdan promises an
exciting and untamed wilderness beyond the forests and mountains mapped thus
far.

name: On the Road
description:

than a path between two villages: Koteras and Dagdan.  To the south, Koteras
beckons with its proximity to Cimar.  Northwest of here, Dagdan promises an

than a path between two villages: Koteras and Dagdan.  To the south, Koteras

exciting and untamed wilderness beyond the forests and mountains mapped thus
far.  Directly to the east, a dusty saloon filled with unsavory characters
blocks your view of the other road.

name: On the Road
description:
A smaller, narrower road than the one to the east, this is little more
than a path between two villages: Koteras and Dagdan.  To the south, Koteras
beckons with its proximity to Cimar.  Northwest of here, Dagdan promises an
exciting and untamed wilderness beyond the forests and mountains mapped thus
far.

name: The Road to Dagdan
description:
This is a wide dirt path made from moist, healthy soil.  It leads from
west to east, and is wide enough for ten men to walk abreast.  To the south,
the plains reach as far as the eye can see with no break save for the road
to Koteras off to the east.  To the north, the dazzling forest you've been
gawking at is clear through the mist which seems to envelop it.  The sound
of strange birdcalls is audible, and you've not heard their like anywhere
else in the world... To the northwest, you can make out a cluster of
buildings along the edge of the huge forest.

name: A Turn
description:
Here, the road to Dagdan bends from north to east and from east to north.
This area is covered with cobblestones, and as you look to the north, they
continue on toward a cluster of buildings to that direction -- presumably
Dagdan itself.  The street ends here, and to the south and west stretch
endless plains.  Off in the east, you see the road to Koteras, and beyond
the city to the north is a vast forest, nearly covering the horizon in that
direction.  There's a very strange warbling sound in the air all around
you...

name: The Road to Dagdan
description:
This fine cobblestone street leads north and south, through the heart
of the great plains of the northwest.  To the north, the amazing Giant
Forest becomes clearer and clearer in the distance through the mists
which enshroud it, and the tiny town it nearly encircles seems
friendly enough.  Certainly, it's a welcome place to rest your tired
feet.  To the south, spreading out in every direction, a sprawling
plain interrupted by only a tiny cobblestone avenue -- the one you're
on.

name: The Gate to the Great Northwest
description:
On the very outskirts of Dagdan, you encounter a huge sign painted
in mostly gold and silver which reads:

\Welcome to Dagdan
sector_type: the Gate to the Great Northwest.\"

area_id: Just down the street to the north
room_id: the tiny town of Dagdan sits

area_id: nearly devoured by the Giant Forest beyond it.  The town is close
enough that you can make out every detail
room_id: and yet it is this forest

area_id: which dominates your field of view.  It towers above the town and
looms like a titanic predatory animal ready to descend and crush the
infinite plains to your south.  You are still well beyond its reach
and yet it seems to curve through the air above you and soar so far
into the air directly above you
room_id: that you stumble backwards glimpsing

area_id: the tops of these impossibly tall trees.

name: Dagdan's South Gate
description:
This collection of shops and streets forms a quaint little town, and
its setting is one of the most dramatic in Shalar -- right on the brink
of the Giant Forest.  Those trees stand like sentinels over this tiny
settlement, and the trade done here all takes place within their
shadow.  If a traveler has just arrived, he's either come from the
forest to the north or the plains to the south, and in need of
significant rest.  If he's leaving, he's on his way to one of those,
and this tradepost of a city exists to provide him with supplies for
the long journey ahead.

name: Tree Road
description:
While unimaginatively named by the inhabitants of Dagdan, this road
seems to be a well-kept one.  People wander the streets happily,
purchasing goods and looking for a place to rest.  A few animals are
even seen dashing about from place to place, as though they had
purpose.  As you glance upward, you are reminded of the Giant Forest,
and naming a piece of a town with something so mind-numbingly simple
as \Tree Road\" seems as though it would be fairly easy to do.

name: A Grassy Spot
description:
This area holds many small plants and flowers, but is covered mainly
by beautifully maintained grass.  There must be someone in town with a
great love for plants, and knowledge enough to cause them to thrive in
a city setting.  This place would be ideal for rest, or for simple
contemplation.

name: A Noisy Spring
description:
The water streaming from a crack in the ground here is ice cold.
Rocks, stones, and pebbles of all sizes litter the ground, and all
have been worn completely smooth by centuries of uninterrupted passage
of water.  Animal tracks lead from this spot out into the plains to
the south, as though to occasional prairie animal -- made bold by
its need for water -- comes here to drink.

name: Tree Road

seems to be a well-kept one.  People wander the streets happily,
purchasing goods and looking for a place to rest.  A few animals are

purpose.  As you glance upward, you are reminded of the Giant Forest,
and naming a piece of a town with something so mind-numbingly simple
as \Tree Road\" seems as though it would be fairly easy to do.  A

area_id: large ornate door is in a building to your west
room_id: and you stand in the

area_id: southwestern corner of a small square.

name: The Mayor's Home
description:
This is Baram Evir's private dwelling, inhabited usually only during
the evenings.  When Baram isn't here, he's out greeting travelers and
seeing to the enforcement of his anti-outlaw plan.  Nearly everything
in this room is of the highest quality, constructed of the most
expensive materials imaginable.  Trade, and the constant flow of
business in travelers coming through, has obviously been good to
Dagdan and it's mayor.  The room consists of a desk in the center
with a large chair behind it.  Several bookshelves line each wall,
and a small bed is in the northwest corner next to a fireplace.

name: Tree Road

While unimaginatively named by the inhabitants of Dagdan, this road
seems to be a well-kept one.  People wander the streets happily,
purchasing goods and looking for a place to rest.  A few animals are
even seen dashing about from place to place, as though they had
purpose.  As you glance upward, you are reminded of the Giant Forest,
and naming a piece of a town with something so mind-numbingly simple
as \Tree Road\" seems as though it would be fairly easy to do.  You

area_id: stand in the northwest corner of a small marketplace
room_id: and the sound

area_id: of metal striking metal grates upon your ears
room_id: flying from the north.

name: Tarni's Smithy
description:
This humble shop houses some of the most beautifully rendered mithril
armor in Shalar.  Its owner must be amazingly skilled in the art of
mithril smithing.  Lined against one wall are stacks and piles of
breastplates, shining in the sun which filters through the shop's
straw roof.  Against the opposite wall, helmets and gauntlets,
leggings and sleeves are all lovingly mounted and displayed.  As you
step through the center of the shop, you see a desk of sorts
separating the front of the shop from the back, and an open door
behind it leading into the work room.

name: The Back Room
description:
This room is much, much warmer than the front of Tarni's shop.  The
main reason for that is likely the forge which burns merrily in a
corner.  Huge blocks of mithril litter the floor here, varying in size
and shape, and in eventual purpose.  Tools of all sorts for
manipulating the glowing heated mithril the forge produces daily are
hanging on the wall.  To the south, a door leads back into the main
shop.

seems to be a well-kept one.  People wander the streets happily,
purchasing goods and looking for a place to rest.  A few animals are

purpose.  As you glance upward, you are reminded of the Giant Forest,
and naming a piece of a town with something so mind-numbingly simple
as \Tree Road\" seems as though it would be fairly easy to do.  You

area_id: stand in the southeast corner of a small marketplace
room_id: and gentle

area_id: lilting music throbs and swells through the air
room_id: coming from the

area_id: east.

name: Tree Road
description:
While unimaginatively named by the inhabitants of Dagdan, this road
seems to be a well-kept one.  People wander the streets happily,
purchasing goods and looking for a place to rest.  A few animals are
even seen dashing about from place to place, as though they had
purpose.  As you glance upward, you are reminded of the Giant Forest,
and naming a piece of a town with something so mind-numbingly simple
as \Tree Road\" seems as though it would be fairly easy to do.  You

area_id: stand in the northeast corner of a small marketplace.  To the east
you see a dark area of the street.

name: The Wooden Porch
description:
This is the front porch of Norman's Inn, a well-known establishment
in this part of the world for its beer, its hospitality, and for its
music and entertainment.  This wooden platform has housed performances
of nearly every recently popular tragedy, and the finest composers'
tunes all reach this stage eventually.  To the east, Norman's Inn
beckons, and to the west is Dagdan's marketplace.  North, you see a
darker part of the street.

name: A Dark Corner
description:
This is one place where Tree Road comes to an end.  Dark and
foreboding, the corner of this area of the city is likely where the
criminal element spends much of its time...  A distinctly cold breeze
rushes down through the leaves of the Giant Forest and along an
alleyway to the north.  By the time this air reaches you, it already
seems stale and lifeless.

name: A Dark Alley
description:
The ground here is slick, like rocks on the shore of a stagnant body of
water.  A musty, damp smell that is altogether unpleasant drifts through
here, and you nearly gag as this odor assaults your senses.  It is here of
all places, a damp and dark hole of utter displeasure, that an under-born
halfling peddler has chosen in which to show his wares.

name: A Dark Junction
description:
The ground here is slick, like rocks on the shore of a stagnant
body of water.  A musty, damp smell that is altogether unpleasant
drifts through here, and you nearly gag as this odor assaults your
senses.  The darkness is nearly overwhelming, and the only light you
can see is being reflected from the street by the slimy surface of the
cobblestones.  Here, the alley makes a T-intersection.

name: A Dark Alley
description:
The ground here is slick, like rocks on the shore of a stagnant
body of water.  A musty, damp smell that is altogether unpleasant
drifts through here, and you nearly gag as this odor assaults your
senses.  The darkness is nearly overwhelming, and the only light you
can see is being reflected from the street by the slimy surface of the
cobblestones.  The alley ends abruptly here, and you don't doubt that
if you couldn't see by your own means, you would have met the wall to
the west rather bodily.

name: The Entrance to the Assassins' Guild
description:
The darkness continues here, and the sounds of dripping water are the
only ones audible.  Peering to the east, you can barely distinguish a
few dark forms slipping back and forth.  To the west, the dark
alleyway.  A musty smell hangs in the air, and you feel as though
there is movement all around.

name: The Dark Spot
description:
Dark as the Devil's back pocket, this spot is rumored to be the place
where the most hated assassins, mercenaries, and bounty hunters
in the world congregate to compare winnings and to plot with and
against one another.  More schemes have been hatched here than
anywhere else.  The wall is lined with the sharp and exotic implements
of silent warfare.  In fact, the entire room seems to be bristling
with venomous blades... and yet, no one seems to worry.  The assassins
whispering their quiet way across the floor like ghosts pay no
attention to the blades, simply gracefully slipping from place to
place around and between the piles and stacks of deadly metals.

name: The Southern Commons
description:
This is the southern end of a huge hall, the main room of Norman's
Inn.  Mounted on the wall is a large friendly sign.  Norman's
customers mill around like ants here, conversing with gratuitous
volume and examining the items they've purchased today in Dagdan's
many shops and markets.  Hanging from the ceiling, you see a large
wagon wheel studded with magical orbs of continually glowing light,
illuminating the room at all times of the day.  It appears that this
wheel can be turned, obscuring as many of the orbs as seems necessary
behind a wooden panel in order to dim the room's lighting.  A
fireplace crackles merrily at one end of the room, and paintings line
every possible vertical surface.

name: The Northern Commons
description:
This is the northern end of a huge hall, the main room of Norman's
Inn.  Norman's customers mill around like ants here, conversing with
gratuitous volume and examining the items they've purchased today in
Dagdan's many shops and markets.  Hanging from the ceiling, you see a
large wagon wheel studded with magical orbs of continually glowing
light, illuminating the room at all times of the day.  It appears that
this wheel can be turned, obscuring as many of the orbs as seems
necessary behind a wooden panel in order to dim the room's lighting.
To the north, you can spot a man that could only be Norman himself.

name: Norman's Bar
description:
A bar larger than any you've seen graces the northwest area of this room,
obviously the centerpiece of this entire floor.  Fully thirty feet long, its
expansive surface seats as many as fifteen men or six titans.  Behind,
Norman stalks back and forth grinning evilly and swapping evil jokes, and a
cabinet -- also thirty feet long -- holds the most amazing amount of liquor
you've ever seen collected.  Loud men drink and shout, and women scurry back
and forth to serve those patrons who have seated themselves in the common
room.  Judging by the food they carry, there must be a grill behind the bar
as well, but it is entirely obscured by either the drunkards, the immense
liquor cabinet, or Norman himself.

name: The Inn's Stairwell
description:
A large wooden staircase leads up to the second level of Norman's Inn.
The entire Inn is made of beautiful timberframe construction, and
these stairs are an amazing example of that.  Reddish wood from the
Giant Forest to the north tightly panels the walls and the high
ceiling, and makes up the stairs and railings.  Support struts,
seemingly more for decoration than any structural purpose, add to the
strange beauty of this simple spiral stairwell.  The red wood has a
wonderful, sweet smell to it, and this smell permeates the whole Inn.

name: Upstairs Hall
description:
A large wooden staircase leads down to the ground level of Norman's
Inn.  The entire Inn is made of beautiful timberframe construction,
and these stairs are an amazing example of that.  Reddish wood from
the Giant Forest to the north tightly panels the walls and the high
ceiling, and makes up the stairs and railings.  Support struts,
seemingly more for decoration than any structural purpose, add to the
strange beauty of this simple spiral stairwell.  The red wood has a
wonderful, sweet smell to it, and this smell permeates the whole Inn.
To the east and west, doors made of this scented wood lead to separate
private rooms.

name: The Inn's Storage Room
description:
This area of the Inn seems to be where Norman stores his extra beer
and other supplies.  A stack of chairs here, a pile of mugs there,
this room is a large jumble of the makings of an inn and could likely
furnish an entire separate inn, should Norman someday be inclined to
expand his operation.  There are no windows in this room, and the red
wooden walls smell like the Giant Forest.  Shalar's largest beer keg
stands against the southern wall.

name: A Grassy Trail
description:
Outside the city, this grassy trail leads through the serene outskirts
of Dagdan between Norman's Inn and the road outside town.  South
and east of here, the expansive plains of the northwest stretch on to
the horizon.  To the north, Norman's Inn beckons.  No fence stands
between you and the plains to the south and east -- simply the
buildings of Dagdan and a few trees on one side, endless plains on the
other.  Staring out at the plains, it's easy to feel very small and
lost...

and east of here, the expansive plains of the northwest stretch on to
the horizon.  A small pile of brush lies here on the trail.  No fence
stands between you and the plains to the south and east -- simply the
buildings of Dagdan and a few trees on one side, endless plains on the
other.  Staring out at the plains, it's easy to feel very small and
lost...

name: Behind the Brush
description:
A tiny clearing between a few trees north of a trail, this dark area
is buzzing with tiny gnats.  The earth is moist, and seems unusually
soft.  The smells of earth and sweet wood are almost overwhelming.

name: A Grassy Trail
description:
Outside the city, this grassy trail leads through the serene outskirts

as \Tree Road\" seems as though it would be fairly easy to do.  The

area_id: sound of chattering women nearly deafens you
room_id: charging from the north.

name: Pzandra's Smithy
description:
Dank and dreary, poor lighting dooms this shop to little business.
A few works of iron are scattered around the floor, and the small
forge in the corner sits cold and unused like a sleeping mammoth.
Examining the iron strewn about the shop, you realize what an ugly
metal it is... dusty and dull, poorly shaped and constructed,
Pzandra's items aren't worth real money.  The noise in this shop is
loud and obnoxious, but it isn't what you might expect -- the sound
of metal striking metal is mysteriously absent.  Instead, shrill
voices chatter and gossip late into the night every day...

name: Tree Road
description:
While unimaginatively named by the inhabitants of Dagdan, this road
seems to be a well-kept one.  People wander the streets happily,
purchasing goods and looking for a place to rest.  A few animals are

purpose.  As you glance upward, you are reminded of the Giant Forest,
and naming a piece of a town with something so mind-numbingly simple
as \Tree Road\" seems as though it would be fairly easy to do.  The

area_id: stench of death wafts in from the north
room_id: and the perfume of life from

area_id: the south.

name: The Butcher Shop
description:
This establishment is not kept clean.  That much is evident as you
nearly slip and fall in a pool of animal blood near the door.  This
town's butcher is apparently an over-enthusiastic fellow... the walls
are spattered with blood, and in some places, even the ceiling is
spotted with the dried, dark red substance.  Despite the horrible
conditions, the cuts of meat seem well carved, and have been wrapped
to prevent flies from getting to them.  Enthusiasm is to be lauded,
at least...

name: The Little Vale
description:
Plants and pots, dirt and water... these are the themes of this small
and simplistic shop.  Simple, yet perhaps the most wonderful in
Dagdan.  You see plants of types that are as common as grass, and more
which have no name in your mind.  There are scents you've never
imagined breezing about, riding through the store on a forest wind
from the north.  Leaves and vines flutter in this breeze, and flower
petals ride through the air along with the damp air.  This shop truly
does remind you of a miniature version of the beautiful Vale of
Arendyl.

name: Tree Road
description:
While unimaginatively named by the inhabitants of Dagdan, this road
seems to be a well-kept one.  People wander the streets happily,
purchasing goods and looking for a place to rest.  A few animals are
even seen dashing about from place to place, as though they had
purpose.  As you glance upward, you are reminded of the Giant Forest,
and naming a piece of a town with something so mind-numbingly simple
as \Tree Road\" seems as though it would be fairly easy to do.  Here

area_id: Tree Road branches off in three directions.

name: A Dark Alley
description:
The ground here is slick, like rocks on the shore of a stagnant
body of water.  A musty, damp smell that is altogether unpleasant
drifts through here, and you nearly gag as this odor assaults your
senses.  The darkness is nearly overwhelming, and the only light you
can see is being reflected from the street by the slimy surface of the
cobblestones.

area_id: north
room_id: the Giant Forest looms very near.

name: The End of the Road
description:
Staring toward the forest from here, you receive a sensation of
hurtling from the civilized world directly into the jaws of nature...
The trees may appear giant from the town to the south, but from this
vantage point, their monolithic size is disquieting.  All around you,
tree trunks the size of houses fire angrily upward from the soil at a
dizzying rate to slash the very surface of the celestial hemisphere
above.  If you keep your eyes to the ground, perhaps you will avoid
the overwhelming feeling of disorientation that comes with this
forest.  North, you can easily make out a clearing between several
massive trunks.  To the south, the tiny town of Dagdan breaks its
way free of the Giant Forest's clutches.

name: A Tiny Clearing
description:
A bed of grass and the fine mulch of rotted leaves makes for very
comfortable footing here.  Any intake of breath nearly overwhelms you,
the amazingly sweet scent of the wood of this forest is pungent enough
to pierce any haze you may be experiencing mentally, and then create a
whole new one for you.  The light which filters down this far through
the tree cover above you is a deep green color, casting an eerie glow
upon all of your surroundings.  To the north, the Giant Forest dives
down the steep sides of a huge valley that's impossible to see from
outside the woods south of here...  You can actually peer between the
massive trunks to the immediate north, and above the treetops far off
in the distance.  The view from here, provided that you can find a
line of sight through the trees, is amazing.  A vast mountain range
strikes its way through the clouds in the northeast, and to the
northwest, this forest continues beyond the opposite edge of the deep
valley which neutralizes its towering height, and on to the horizon.

name: The Giant Forest
description:
The edge of a monstrous valley, this part of the forest is on a fairly
steep incline.  The trail you are on leads north into the valley and
south out of it.  The leaf cover far above you almost entirely snuffs
out any light which might attempt to pierce it.  The forest around you
is not dark by any means, but its lighting is twilight-like at best,
perpetually.  An odd warbling sound fills the forest -- the call of
the wild turkey, an odd looking species of bird which is one of many
that are unique to this part of the continent.  To your north, the
valley continues toward what appears to be the edge of the world (but
what is likely simply the other side of this titanic valley).  South,
you can climb up to the edge of this side.

name: A Dead End
description:
Tree Road simply comes to an end here... you can see directly out the
end of Dagdan, along the edge of the Giant Forest and into the plains
to the west.  It's odd spots like this one that ruin the overall
impression of a comfortable little village that the rest of Dagdan
exudes, and make it feel more like an uncivilized frontier town.
This is likely one place where the Mayor plans to expand and continue
to build.

name: A Warehouse
description:
This barren building is nearly empty, and entirely dark.  It's obvious
that this is where incoming and outgoing loads of material, goods, and
various other movable assets are stored, but right now seems to be a
bit of a lull in Dagdan's commercial activity.  Peering through the
dusty darkness, you can make out what few piles remain here underneath
sheets for protection and anonymity.  To the north, the brightness
outdoors causes spots to float in front of your eyes.  You can move
south and east through the warehouse.

name: A Warehouse
description:
This barren building is nearly empty, and entirely dark.  It's obvious
that this is where incoming and outgoing loads of material, goods, and
various other movable assets are stored, but right now seems to be a
bit of a lull in Dagdan's commercial activity.  A dusty cloth pile
here seems to cover the shape of a wagon.  You can move south and west
through the warehouse.

name: A Warehouse
description:
This barren building is nearly empty, and entirely dark.  It's obvious
that this is where incoming and outgoing loads of material, goods, and
various other movable assets are stored, but right now seems to be a
bit of a lull in Dagdan's commercial activity.  This part of the
warehouse seems as though it's devoted to empty beer kegs...  You can
move any direction but west from here.

name: In the Rafters
description:
The reason you climbed up here is a fact you've forgotten, and in its
place is a great deal of concern for your well-being.  The upper level
of this warehouse is extremely hot -- the prairie sun beats down on it
all day long, and the heat inside the rest of the warehouse all rises
to here.  Beyond the uncomfortable warmth, the only way to move around
is by edging along the rafters in any given direction.  The fact that
it's very dark up here doesn't help matters in that respect any,
either.  The sweet scent of the wood everything in Dagdan is
constructed with is baked by the sweltering heat, and its intensity is
nearly sickening up here.

name: Through the Hole
description:
It's quite a lot cooler on this side of the wall than inside the
warehouse.  In fact, this small tunnel-like structure doesn't even
appear to be indoors... rather, roughly built upon the roof of a
building next to the warehouse, as though it were an afterthought
and not a part of the original design.  To the south, a few faint
whispers can be heard in the cool darkness.  To the west, you can
crawl through a hole and into the rafters of the warehouse next door.

name: Entrance to the Thieves' Guild
description:
This part of the impromptu tunnel widens somewhat, and a few quiet men
have gathered here to whisper.  Grey cloth is draped across the wooden
framework of the tunnel, in order to make it \lightproof.\"  The system

area_id: seems to work
room_id: as this area is pitch black.  To the south

area_id: light source flickers gently off the walls
room_id: while to the north

area_id: blackness consumes the tunnel once again.  The air is cool
room_id: and flows

area_id: gently back and forth as though it were just another whisperer in the
dark.

name: The Hidden Room
description:
A tiny candle flickers from the center of a small table here,
illuminating what appears to be a friendly card game.  The men in this
room are all experienced thieves, and the card players intently watch
each other's hands to insure that no unauthorized thievery breaks out.

It is here that some of the finest thieves in this region of Shalar are
trained.  A few dummies with pockets of varying size have been stuffed
into a corner to collect dust -- this guild's master believes in
practice in the field.

name: Behind the Wall
description:
This appears to be a very tight hallway which was actually built into
the structure, simply by placing a second wall at this edge of the
building.  West, the boards have been carelessly placed and allow
passage into a warehouse, while the hallway itself moves south.  The
floor here is littered with papers and bottles, as though it receives
quite a bit of traffic and no sanitary visitations.

name: Behind the Wall
description:
This appears to be a very tight hallway which was actually built into
the structure, simply by placing a second wall at this edge of the
building.  Here, the hallway moves north and south.  The floor here is
littered with papers and bottles, as though it receives quite a bit of
traffic and no sanitary visitations.  Several slightly muffled sounds
are made as you crunch your way across the dirty floor.

name: Behind the Wall
description:
This appears to be a very tight hallway which was actually built into
the structure, simply by placing a second wall at this edge of the
building.  The floor here is littered with papers and bottles, as
though it receives quite a bit of traffic and no sanitary visitations.
The hall comes to an abrupt end here, with no apparent exit -- save
for the way back north.

name: A Private Room
description:
Norman has spared no expense in furnishing these private rooms for
paying customers.  An evening's respite, a good night's sleep, and a
place to reflect upon the long journey behind you (or ahead of you)
are all provided perfectly by this comfortable room.  Glass statuettes
and pewter figurines decorate shelves along the walls, and the entire
place is the same orangish-reddish hue as the rest of the inn, made of
that same red wood from the Giant Forest.  Here, though, the wood has
been aged somewhat, and the sometimes sickeningly sweet smell is
slightly less intrusive.  A bed and a cabinet furnish one side of the
room (both made of red wood), and a small linen closet stands open at
the other side, ready for your belongings should you wish to stay and
sleep.

name: On the Road
description:
A smaller, narrower road than the one to the east, this is little more
than a path between two villages: Koteras and Dagdan.  To the south, Koteras
beckons with its proximity to Cimar.  Northwest of here, Dagdan promises an
exciting and untamed wilderness beyond the forests and mountains mapped thus
far.

name: A collapsed tunnel
description:
The persistent sound of dripping water echoes throughout the cave, and the
air feels heavy with moisture.  Fallen rocks and dirt lie scattered about,
providing a path for you to climb back up, if you pick your way cautiously.
Whatever water source caused this cave-in remains hidden from view, though
it appears to have soaked into everything in sight.  You suddenly notice what
appears to be a body partially buried under the rocks and mud, as you draw
near you also find a small rusted plaque near the outstretched hand.  The
darkness of another tunnel appears through the rocks to the south.

name: Within the Barren Hollows
description:
What you can see of the caves looks jagged and uneven, apparently crafted by
nature.  The air is motionless and stale, contributing to the oppressive
feeling of tons of rock and earth surrounding you.  The smallest sounds echo
madly through the caves, assaulting your ears from every direction at once.
The endless tunnels of rock extend to the north and south.

name: The pool
description:
The floor of this room has filled with water, quite shallow at first, but a
a large patch of darker water suggests it deepens further in.  Every inch of
stone in this room is covered with a slimy green fungus which glows slightly,
casting a greenish light throughout the room.  Several unidentifiable tracks
through the fungus lead up to the edge of the pool, though you have seen no
sign of life through the tunnels.  A slight ripple disturbs the otherwise
still surface of the water.

name: A vast cavern
description:
The tunnel suddenly opens up into a much wider cavern.  The ceiling reaches
up into the darkness, ending somewhere beyond your sight.  Large stalactites
reach down from the shadows of the ceiling, their jagged points stabbing
towards the top of your head.  Several smaller stalagmites reach up from the
ground, forcing you to walk around them.  From the sound of the echos, the
cavern continues for some distance.  The smaller tunnels continue to the
north.

name: A vast cavern
description:
This size of this cavern is immense, in stark contrast to the often cramped
caves of the Hollows.  The ceiling reaches up into the darkness, ending
somewhere beyond your sight.  Large stalactites reach down from the shadows
of the ceiling, their jagged points stabbing towards the top of your head.
Several smaller stalagmites reach up from the ground, forcing you to walk
around them.  From the sound of the echoes, the cavern continues for some
distance.

caves of the Hollows.  The ceiling reaches up into the darkness, ending
somewhere beyond your sight.  Large stalactites reach down from the shadows
of the ceiling, their jagged points stabbing towards the top of your head.
Several smaller stalagmites reach up from the ground, forcing you to walk
around them.  From the sound of the echoes, the cavern continues for some
distance.

name: A vast cavern
description:
This size of this cavern is immense, in stark contrast to the often cramped
caves of the Hollows.  The ceiling reaches up into the darkness, ending
somewhere beyond your sight.  Large stalactites reach down from the shadows
of the ceiling, their jagged points stabbing towards the top of your head.
Several smaller stalagmites reach up from the ground, forcing you to walk

Several smaller stalagmites reach up from the ground, forcing you to walk
around them.  From the sound of the echoes, the cavern continues for some
distance.  A large pile of rocks allows for careful climbing to a small
ledge on the eastern wall, just visible at the edge of your sight.

description:
This size of this cavern is immense, in stark contrast to the often cramped
caves of the Hollows.  The ceiling reaches up into the darkness, ending
