a divine prescence watching you.

name: In a room with a green fountain
description:
This room is humming with the sound of magical energy of some divine nature.
In the centre is a fountain which is glowing with a sickly green aura. In
all directions around you there are strong steel doors, and a stairwell leads
down.

name: In a sparse room
description:
The room is empty except for the insistent glow of sickly green that hangs
throughout the tower air. The only exit is a door in the west wall.

name: In a meditation room
description:
This room has the trappings of a cleric's retreat. Except the symbols hanging
on the walls are dusty with neglect and the cross that hangs over the door
is inverted and covered in blood. The only exit is back south through the
doorway.

name: In a room of healing
description:
This room has been set up for the recuperation of patients who may have been
hurt during fights or on hunting trips. Except that right now it appears the
beds are soaked in blood and there are no patients, just long dead skeletons
of elves who were brought here for aid. The only exit is east through the
doorway.

name: In the holy place
description:
This shrine is bathed in a glaring sickly green light that warms you with it's
unholy energy. The holy symbols and tablets scattered about the room are dust
covered and bloody, signs that the times of peace are long gone in this place.
There is a door leading north, and a stairway heading up.

name: Ascending into an unholy green light
description:
You have stepped into a glaring green light that sends flowing warmth through
your body. Despite this warm feeling it has sends a sickly shudder through
you as it penetrates your very bones. Below you is a stairwell leading down
into a room, and there are doors in the north and south walls.

name: In an unholy green light
description:
You stand in the flowing green light that permeates this tower. From here you
can see the glaring green light is filtering in from above you. There is a
door to the north that helps to stem the flood of light into the lower
level.

name: In an unholy green light
description:
You stand in the flowing green light that permeates this tower. From here you
can see the glaring green light is filtering in from above you. There is a
door to the south that helps to stem the flood of light into the lower
level.

name: In a burning green light of unholy fire
description:
You have stepped into a light of sickly green that is so intense it burns the
skin and sears your eyes. All around you there is the ringing sound of deep
chanting in some arcane tongue, but you are able to hear that the tone is
one of dark evil. Below you is a way down through the light, and to the south
is the source of the unholy energy that surges around you.

name: In a burning green light of unholy fire
description:
You have stepped into a light of sickly green that is so intense it burns the
skin and sears your eyes. All around you there is the ringing sound of deep
chanting in some arcane tongue, but you are able to hear that the tone is
one of dark evil. Below you is a way down through the light, and to the north
is the source of the unholy energy that surges around you.

name: Within the unholy fire
description:
The room here is burning in unholy green fire. The light from it blasts out
of the room north and south into the rest of the tower, but it is here that
the green light is of burning intensity. You can practically feel the heat
of the flames searing your soul, and a divine prescence can be felt watching
and enjoying the light as it gathers power.

name: A Dusty Saloon
description:
Pushing through the creaky, swinging wooden doors, you enter what appears
to be a well established saloon.  Despite the dust and dirt that seems to
pervade everywhere around here, the occupants seem to be enjoying
themselves, as the loud buzz of dozens of simultaeneous conversations
reaches your ears.  Ahead of you is the bar, stocked with a surprising
number of odd looking bottles for such a homely establishment, while on
either side of you card games and their grizzled, tough looking players
continue unabated.  A small door in the corner leads off to a quiet
corridor.

name: A Quiet Corridor
description:
Strangely quiet, stepping inside this narrow, wood paneled corridor
provides a sharp contrast to the noise and bustle of the saloon outside. 
You notice a thick, reinforced door straight ahead, opened, with a chair and
spitoon, clearly intended to provide some convenience to someone guarding
this odd door.  A small sign on the door says 'Hunters'.

name: A Back Room
description:
Unidentifiable smoke hangs thickly in this dimly lit, quiet room.  Old,
broken backed chairs have been discarded carelessly in the corners, while
the gloomy, inadequate light in the room is provided by a flickering, rusted
lantern.  A wide, creaky wooden staircase leads down into what appears to be
some sort of basement, while to the north a small, dark alcove lies.

name: Before the Vault
description:
Dominating the room, a massive iron vault looms over the northern edge of
the room.  Dark grey in color, thick steel bands wrap around it, adding even
more protection to the giant vessel.  Visible even in the dim light is a
large combination lock, the doors closed.  Behind you, the creaky wooden
stairs offer the only escape from the vault room.  Eerie shadows seem to
move in the scant light provided by the flickering torches that are the only
source of illumination.

name: A Small Alcove
description:
This small, dark alcove is lit only by tiny candles interspersed around
its semicircular shape.  Miniature statues and religious relics to more
deities than you can count adorn the room.  In the center of the alcove is a
large, round statue of a fat man with a disturbing grin on his face.  Below
the statue is a tiny tag, etched with some words you can just barely make
out.  To the south the alcove expands into the back room.

name: A Darkened Hallway
description:
Unidentifiable smoke hangs thickly in this dimly lit, quiet hallway. 
Old, broken backed chairs have been discarded carelessly in the corners,
while the gloomy, inadequate light in the room is provided by a flickering,
rusted lantern.  The darkened hallway continues around to the north, into
what appears to be a small study, and out into a larger room to the west.

name: Within Dargor's Study
description:
This small, cramped room is full of all manner of books, maps, and
papers.  Near the eastern wall, as large desk faces the hallway, with one
particularly large book sitting atop it.  A rather seedy-looking man sits at
the desk, writing in the book, often in languages you have never seen
before.

name: A long cobblestone path lined with torches
description:
Shadows and smoke dance across this cobblestone path as it moves eastward
toward a massive wooden structure.  The path is wide and roughly placed,
with large conglomerate cobblestones creating the path.  Tall torches
stained with blood maintain the light for this outdoor corridor while huge
oak trees and heavy undergrowth keeps anyone from straying off the path.  It
is obvious you have come across the home of some great force in the land.

name: A Massive Oak Planked Longhouse
description:
A huge building blankets you in shadows as you stand before it.  Large
oaken planks the size of great trees line the front of the building.  The
planks come to the edge of a massive rectangular archway that opens up in
front of you like a mouth ready to swallow you whole.  Sounds of laughter,
battle, and war spill from the opening and you sense that this place is not
for the weak of heart or arm.  The archway itself is made up of rough cut
stones and suspended in the mortar seems to be skulls of various humanoids. 
The keystone of the archway has an etching inscribed into it, a huge silver
flagon overfilled with blood, the symbol of the barbarian Horde.

name: An overgrown path
description:
Utilizing all your strength you push your way through the underbrush and
fall upon a small path.  The dark woods surrounding you seem to come alive
with activity.  The calls of many animals as well as the rustling of
branches and leaves keeps you wary.  The path you have stumbled on to
continues south into darkness where hanging vines and moss block your view
of what is beyond.  To the north, the light of the cobblestone path can be
seen through the thick underbrush.

name: The Shrine of the Barbarian Horde
description:
You struggle through the foliage when you happen upon a clearing enclosed
by the surrounding trees and foliage.  A small opening in the canopy above
allows only a small amount of light to filter in.  The light from above is
just enough to reveal to you the contents of this strangely silent clearing.
Lining the edge of the circular clearing are long wooden poles.  Each pole
is adorned with the skull of a different animal.  You recognize some of the
skulls as a bear, wolf, elk, lion, and jackal, while others are foreign to
you.  The eyes of each skull ignore you and focus in on the slightly
upraised granite platform in the center of the clearing.  The large stone
obelisk stretches upward stopping barely short of the top of the canopy. 
The obelisk itself has four sides, with each side covered in runes and
strange markings.  Dominating the top portion of each side is the symbol of
the Horde.  Below each of the symbols are lesser symbols of unknown origin. 
You truly believe you are standing in a holy place.  The only way out is to
return to the darkness of the path north.

name: The Clan Ale Hall
description:
A huge table dominates this drinking hall.  You see chairs of every shape
and size lining the circumference.  Some seem to be looted thrones from
kingdoms long dominated while others seemed to have been constructed as
needed from what was available.  Echoing out of the archway to the north are
screams of the dominated and sounds of laughter.  The sounds of equipment
being moved about and the clinking of gold and silver can be heard through
the archway to the south.  The archway to the west returns you to open air
while to the east brings you through an archway that heads farther into the
halls of the Horde.

name: The Stores of the Horde
description:
This part of the long house is dominated by a massive vault.  The wrought
iron vault runs the entire length of the north wall.  The vault door is open
slightly and you can see slaves of the dominated moving pillaged goods and
gold into it.  In front of the vault is a monster of a man.  He keeps you
from reaching any of the nice items and gold but will sell you any of the
items that he deems fit.  The only way you can exit is to return to the main
meeting hall to the north.

name: A massive firepit surrounded by heaps of furs
description:
Dominating this part of the longhouse is a massive fire pit lined with
hundreds of skulls.  Monstrous licks of flame spurt from the center of the
pit, barely reaching the top of the long house.  A large opening above the
fire allows smoke and soot to be expelled into the outside air, but still
some of the smoke spills into the chamber causing a burnt oak smell to cross
your nose.  Outside of the pit are many places to sit, relax and enjoy the
spoils of war.  Server girls quickly scamper about performing whatever tasks
the barbarians wish as meats of all kinds are constantly being cooked over
the gigantic blaze.  Drawing your attention to the northern wall is a
gargantuan animal trophy.  Its size is awe inspiring and the rest of the
animal must have been majestic.  It is obvious this is a place of
celebration and endulgement after a successful raid.  The only way you can
go in this great hall is back south toward the main ale hall.

name: Horde Trophy Hall
description:
This whole hall is filled with trophies of war.  Most do not seem to be
worth anything monetary but they seem to hold great value to the Horde. 
Lining the walls to the left and right are various trophies including
scalps, wilted and dried heads, various bones and skulls, and decanters full
of curdled blood from fallen generals of armies long past.  A monstrous
chest sits high on the farthest most wall.  The size of the chest as well as
the feeling you glean from it makes you certain that contained within is the
most treasured trophy of the Horde.  The only way out of this hall is back
west through the archway.

name: A Grassy Meadow Surrounded by Trees
description:
You shake your head, clearing the cobwebs from the bizarre battle
sequence you have just witnessed, and survey your surroundings.  You are in
a clearing of emerald-green grass hemmed in on all sides by ancient pines
that seem to brush the sky with their branches.  A gentle breeze swirls
around you, and the trees sway rhythmically with the motion of the air.  As
you look up, a blur of motion streaks toward you!

name: A Broad Landing
description:
Upon stepping onto this landing, the noise from the lower levels of the
tower suddenly ceases.  The red carpet on the floor continues up the
staircase, into the top level of the tower. A window on the western wall looks
out over the city of Melcene, allowing a bit of natural light to shine onto
the spiral staircase. The red carpet on the floor continues up the stairs,
into the top level of the tower.

name: A Small Antechamber
description:
The light in this room emanates from a pair of large, slender glass
candles, each lit with a magical flame.  Portraits of the more famous mages
of the Scions of Knowledge line the walls.  A thin red carpet covers the
marble floor, leading from the top of the spiral staircase below you to the
door set into the north wall and a wide set of heavy double-doors are set
into the southern wall, behind the staircase.

name: The Grand Hall of Magic
description:
A golden domed ceiling looms over the tiled floor, shedding its own light
into the room below. The sounds of quiet voices, shuffling papers and the
invocation of minor magical items fill the Grand Hall, and the acoustic
quality of the room allows for much of it to be heard quite clearly. Two large
and ornate glass pillars are on either side of the archway to the north, which
leads into a broad hallway, while to the west lies another smaller hallway. To
the east lies an archway that has been blocked off...

name: A Broad Hallway
description:
A thin red carpet trimmed with gold is perfectly centered between the
walls of this broad hallway; the standard grey marble tiles make up the rest
of the floor.  Oddly-shaped, twisted lamps supporting glowing orbs line the
walls, providing bright light to the hall.  Doors are set into the eastern
and western walls, and to the north, the hall ends in double doors and a
spiral staircase.

name: At the End of The Hallway
description:
The hallway ends here in walls to the east and west, and a set of glass
double-doors to the north, leading out to a balcony.  In the center of the
hallway, about eight feet away from the doors to the north is the beginning
of a spiral staircase leading up into a very bright room.

name: Within the Crystalline Minaret
description:
From the outside, this glasslike minaret is a combination of colors,
ranging from blue-green to dark copper.  From the inside, however, the
minaret is perfectly clear, allowing for an incredible view of Melcene, the
surrounding lands, and the massive sky.  The minaret itself is quite large,
and during the day, the light is completely natural, while during the night,
a single bright beacon light on the minaret's pinnacle illuminates its
inside as well as its outside.  The floor is made up of pure silver covered
by thick tiles of clear glass.  A raised platform stands in the exact center
of the minaret, and in the exact center of the platform lies a simple silver
box.

name: The Store of Greater Magic
description:
The room itself is small, and halved by a thick ivory counter just to the
north of the door.  Behind the counter, against the northern wall are dark
wooden shelves with various materials such as sheets of paper, inks wands,
powders, potions and books.  There is also an open door in the north wall,
leading into a very small room, hardly large enough for the shopkeeper to
fit into, containing spare and defective supplies.

name: The Library of The Ancients
description:
The walls of this room are off-white and dim.  Rectangular windows are
set into the top of the western wall, allowing for light to enter the
library, making the crystalline bookcases that line the walls sparkle
brilliantly at the right time of day.  The ceiling has interesting patterns
carved into it, still not confirmed to be the work of any race or culture. 
A door to the east leads back into the hallway.

name: Hall of Space and Time
description:
Scholars shuffle back and forth between the rooms to the north and south and
the Grand Hall to the west, books and papers in hand. From time to time,
you can hear a shout or an explosion coming from the room to the north,
and from the south, it is common to hear strange grunts, whistles, and more
unearthly noises. To the north, a door covered with runes leads into a small
chamber, while to the south, a door that continually changes colors leads
into another small chamber.

name: Chronomancer's Study
description:
Clocks of all different shapes and sizes cover the walls of this study.
Oddly enough, they all are timed perfectly so that all of the ticks and
tocks occur simultaneously. A glass cube hovers in midair over the center
of the room, rotating slowly. A number of books containing the results of
various experiments and other sorts of lore sit in bookshelves, constantly
being browsed by students and teachers alike, in hopes of proving magical
theories or writing papers on the subject of Chronomancy.

name: A Narrow Balcony
description:
The city of Melcene is spread out below this tiny balcony at the top of
this unbelievably high tower. From here, you can also see much of the lands to
the west. Above you, the famous minaret of the Glass Tower stands out against
the expanse of sky. The balcony continues to the east and west, and a heavy
glass door lies to the north.

name: Hall of Elemental Energies
description:
Scholars shuffle back and forth between the rooms to the north and south
and the Grand Hall to the west, books and papers in hand.  Unnatural groans
and scraping echo into this hall from the south, and the raw scents and
sounds of the elements waft in from the north.  The door to the south is
incredibly heavy and comprised of pure granite, while the door to the north
is pure steel, its handle covered with rubber.

name: Sorcerer's Study
description:
A mural spans across all of the walls, depicting all of the elements and
para-elements in their natural states.  A number of books containing the
results of various experiments and elemental lore sit in bookshelves,
constantly being browsed by students and teachers alike, in hopes of proving
magical theories or writing papers on the subject of Sorcery.

name: Necromancer's Study
description:
Body parts, bones, blood and chunks of flesh are strewn about the floor
in this room.  Unearthly constructs shamble around, groaning and snorting at
everything in their paths.  A number of books containing the results of
various experiments, anatomical and spiritual lore sit in bookshelves,
constantly being browsed by students and teachers alike, in hopes of proving
magical theories or writing papers on the subject of Necromancy.

name: Chamber of Practice
description:
This entire room is made up of completely sheer, smooth and solid glass.
Orbs of light float through the air, providing light to the room, and runes
of warding cover the walls and the doorway, preventing magical energy from
escaping.  To the south lies the balcony.

name: The Chamber of Crystals
description:
This massive, round room is crafted of pure crystal.  Light flows down
from the ceiling and reflects from the silver tiles in the floor and the
crystal that makes the room up causing the entire structure to glow
brilliantly.  In the center of the floor is a circle of lead that is about 9
feet wide.  The ground within the circle is scorched and scratched.  Four
crystals form a square around the circle, each atop a pedestal, and each a
different color.  The large doors to the north are heavily warded.

name: A Narrow Balcony
description:
The city of Melcene is spread out below this tiny balcony at the top of
this unbelievably high tower. From here, you can also see much of the lands to
the west. Above you, the famous minaret of the Glass Tower stands out against
the expanse of sky.

name: A slightly paved path
description:
Crossing a path inlaid with old worn stones, you come across a large door
barring the way into a large, wooden building to the north. Raising to a
full two stories, this structure seems to be the epitome of the local
activity reguarding adventure. The flaking white paint is one of many
obvious reasons why this establishment needs a few major repairs. Loud
raucous laughter eminates from the large oak doors, fading every so often
and rising again. A small, weather worn sign has been mostly hidden by a
large patch of weeds, paint flecked and wood warped.

name: The Adventurers Corner
description:
Reaching the southwest corner of the large room, a dark gloom falls over
the area. A few tables have been scattered about, some holding patrons,
some waiting to be used. Directly to the north lies a staircase, while to
the northeast rests the bar. Over the small wall directly to the east lies
the doorway to this fine establishment, while further east shouts rise from
a few of the more frequent customers.

name: Inside the Common Room
description:
A few tables are scattered about, some moved in places never originally
ment to be. Barmaids weave in and out between the tables, refilling cups
where needed, bringing food where wanted. To the west, a small wall climbs
half way between the floor and the ceiling, leaving the upper portion
unobstructed.

name: Inside the Common Room
description:
Standing at the entrance of the building, aromas galore assault your
nostrals. The smell of old sweat, ale, bread and the gods know what else
seem to have seeped into the very wood itself. Laughter rolls off the
tables from all directions, and a few yells can be heard when some
unfortunate patron loses at whatever gambling they are involved in.
Barmaids glide in and out of the tables, avoiding deft hands and managing
to keep all of the mug contents in, rather than out of the mug itself. A
set of pair of walls straddling the entrance way. They only climb half way
to the ceiling, leaving the upper half free of obstruction and hindering
any advancement to the eastern and western of the room.

name: Inside the Common Room
description:
A multitude of aroma's assult your sense of smell, ranging from the smoke
of a pipe, to the wonderful smell of fresh baked bread, to the pungent odor
of unwashed bodies. To the north, a visible bar can been seen, while a
blocked off room to the northeast hides it's contents well. Yells of a few
gambling men come from the east, while a small stage has been built for
the new aspiring actors hired by the barkeep.

name: Gamblers Corner
description:
The tables have been cleared so that the men and women can gamble away
their earned money, whether it be to a game of dice, a game of cards, or a
complex game of chess. To the north, a closed off area of the room has been
set aside for whoever's willing to for the privacy. To the west, a small
wall abruptly cut off direct access to the door, while a stage can be
barely seen on the far western wall. The bar, a commonly visited spot of
the losing folk, can be seen towards the middle portion of the north wall.

name: Before a Small Stage
description:
A small, but respectable stage has been erected here, just large enough for
a few props and an actor or two to perform comfortably. Towards the south,
a darker corner houses a few small tables, while to the southeastern
direction a few of the larger tables holds a few patrons. A few yells come
from the east, while to the northeast a cozy bar rests.

name: Inside the Common Room
description:
A few well made tables line the southern wall, as well as dot the immediate
area. To the northwest, you can see a stairwell leading up to the second
floor, while to the northeast is the bar. The faint aroma of warm bread and
spiced wine waft here.

name: In the Center of the Common Room
description:
Standing at the center of the large room, you can see all of the bustling
activity. Loud calls for a mug of ale to be refilled echo through this
large room, but nothing matches the loud hollers of of the men gambling
away their savings towards the east. A bit further north, you can see a
well tended bar, while to the south is a set of doors that lead outside. To
the west are a few tables to relax and enjoy a good drink from.

name: Inside the Common Room
description:
A few tables littered with patrons have been strewn about, some in quiet
conversation, others laughing and spilling their drinks. A few barmaids
weave inbetween the tables, forcing a kind smile, and actually giving a
heartfilled one on occasion. To the northeast, an enclosed area has been
sealed off from the rest of the room, while directly east a few men yell of
either winnings or losses of a dice or card game. To the south and lies a
few more tables, while to the southwest lies the entrance to this fine
establishment. Directly west, you can make out through the smoke a small
makeshift stage in the distance.

name: Inside the Common Room
description:
The chairs and tables have been cleared out of this immediate area, and
replaced with several men crouched about, playing at dice or a hand of
cards, or some other form of gambling. The faint armoa of stale alcohol and
sweaty bodies hangs in the air like a wet cloth, clinging to anything and
everything. From this close distance, you can see that the men spread their
gamblings to the south, while you can see many tables and chairs between
here and the western most wall. A small enclosure to the north has been
blocked off, as well.

name: A Creaky Staircase
description:
A creaky old staircase climbs its way to the second floor. The old wooden
stairs seem sturdy enough to support even the stockiest of dwarves, while
accomodating the widest of minotaurs. A few chairs have been set about to
the south, pointed to provide the best seating to view the rickity stage
that has been set up. A bar older than the building itself lies to the east,
a few patrons seated at or near it; barmaids visiting more often than the
kitchen.

name: Inside the Common Room
description:
Pinned between the bar and the staircase, the local area doesn't have much
happening. A few patrons quietly sip their drinks, or eat a warm meal in
silence, occasionaly piping up to call over a barmaid or speak to his or
her companions. The staircase for the second floor lies west, resting
against the wall, while in the opposing direction sits the old bar. More
tables can be seen to the south, holding more customers than not.

name: The Bar
description:
A large wooden bar sits here, a few patrons seated nearby at tables or
right up next to the bar on sturdy wooden stools. A few barmaids with trays
walk up to the bar to gather a few things to fill their trays with, only to
disperse back into the crowd. The pungent smell of ale and whiskey hangs in
the air, giving the area it's own aromatic aura. Directly east of here lies
a closed off portion, while to the west, a set of stairs lead to the second
floor. Directly south is the entrance to the building.

name: Inside the Common Room
description:
From this vantage point of the room, you can almost see all of the bustling
activity. Loud calls for a mug of ale to be refilled echo through this
large room, but nothing matches the loud hollers of of the men gambling
away their savings towards the east. A bit to the west, you can see a well
tended bar, while to the southwest is a set of doors that lead outside. To
the far west and slightly south are a few tables to relax and enjoy a good
drink from, while past those a rickety stage has temporarily been put up
for entertainment. Directly east of here, lies a enclosed area where a few
patrons can go to enjoy a quiet meal or drink.

name: Private dining area
description:
A small enclosed area has been barred off from the rest of the main room,
to allow the a few well paying customers a quiet area for a decent meal. A
long oak table sits in the center of the room, surrounded by large, sturdy
oaken chairs. Lining the walls are various pictures, pertaining to random
outdoors scenes.

name: Second Floor Stairwell
description:
At the pinnacle of the stairwell, the creaky old staircase sprawls out to
become the second floor, while the base releases to become the first floor.
The narrow hallway leads to the south, stopping abruptly and veering east.
A few pictures hang on the walls, decorating the bland walls as best as
they can.

name: Second Floor Hallway
description:
The narrow hallway stops its pathway south and turns eastward, revealing a
much longer passageway. A few doors can be seen lining the walls to the
north and south, while one on the far eastern wall where the hallway comes
to another end. Towards the north, the stairway leading to the second floor
can be noticed. A few pictures line the walls occasionally, overlaying some
expensive looking wallpaper.

name: A cozy room
description:
This cozy little room holds the basics of a normal inn room: a bed with a
few blankets and a down pillow, a washstand and mirror, a small wooden
chair and a few pegs to hang your cloak and other assorted items on. A
small fireplace has been set into the eastern wall; a few fresh logs have
been set both inside the fireplace and set in the woodrack nearby. A few
small tapestries have been placed decoratively on the walls, depecting a
few animals in a outdoors setting. The thick wooden door lies to the south,
the only obvious exit.

name: The Upstairs Hallway
description:
Running both east and west, this hallway would be almost pitch black if it
weren't for a pair of burning oil lamps straddling the wall every few feet.
An almost hypnotic carpet design creeps along the floor, adding a dazzling
brilliance to this otherwise dull passage. A pair of doors lie both to the
north and to the south of the walkway, blocking passage to the respectable
rooms of the inn. Off into the near east, another set of doors rest in the
wall, as well as the ending of the hallway, while to the west the hall
veers north and out of sight.

name: A cozy room
description:
This comfortable little room is supplied with everything needed for a
decent nights stay. A small fireplace to fend off the brisk, cold mornings
rests in the eastern wall. A few small logs can be found inside the
fireplace, as well as a small wood rack off to the side, supplied by the
inn free of charge. A small wash and mirror stand lies opposite of the
fireplace, against the western wall. A few small pegs have been driven into
the wall next to the doorway, an ample spot to hang a cloak for the night.
A door lies in the northern wall, the only exit noticeable in the room.

name: A cozy room
description:
This cozy little room holds the basics of a normal inn room: a bed with a
few blankets and a down pillow, a washstand and mirror, a small wooden
chair and a few pegs to hang your cloak and other assorted items on. A few
small tapestries have been placed decoratively on the walls, depecting a
few animals in a outdoors setting. A small fireplace has been set into the
western wall; a few fresh logs have been set both inside the fireplace and
set in the woodrack nearby. The thick wooden door lies to the south, the
only obvious exit

name: The Upstairs Hallway
description:
Coming to a dead end, the hallway has completed it's task of supplying
ample walkway to all of the available rooms of the Common Room Inn. The two
remaining rooms lie to the north as well to the south, while a few more of
the rooms rest along the western portion of the walkway. The carpeting has
an almost hypnotic feel to the patterns woven into it; a very dedicated
hand was used to make it, as well as well paid, of course. A few pictures
line the walls inbetween the oil burning lamps, some seeming more valuable
than the rest, but all securely bolted down.

name: A cozy room
description:
This comfortable little room is supplied with everything needed for a
decent nights stay. A small fireplace to fend off the brisk, cold mornings
rests in the western wall. A few small logs can be found inside the
fireplace, as well as a small wood rack off to the side, supplied by the
inn free of charge. A small wash and mirror stand lies opposite of the
fireplace, against the eastern wall. A few small pegs have been driven into
the wall next to the doorway, an ample spot to hang a cloak for the night.
A door lies in the northern wall, the only exit noticeable in the room.

name: The Kitchen
description:
A harsh smell of cooking meats and breads fill the air with their unique
aromas all about the area. The intense heat is caused by the lit cooking
stoves lining the walls. Dishes of all assortments line the shelves, some
waiting to be used, some already that already have been.

name: Before the Regal Theatre
description:
Heavy oak doors carved with intricate designs mark the entrance
to an elaborate stone building.  Polished square stones hug the
large doors to form an archway, each etched and painted to depict
action scenes from the stage.  The wide granite stairs that lead
up to the arched stone doorway are immaculately clean despite the
great deal of foot traffic that passes through.

name: The Lobby of the Theatre
description:
Benches cushioned with blue velvet pillows line the walls of the
high ceiling foyer.  Along side each bench stands an oak hall tree
covered in cloaks and coats of the people here to enjoy performances.
A few portraits and other fine works of art give life to the clean
walls of the entry way.  The soft glow of candle light from their
wall sconces give a warm and welcoming atmosphere to the theatre.

name: Below a Spiral Staircase
description:
A narrow red rug runs up the center of the twisting stairway, metal
railings curving around to offer support on the climb.  Wall sconces
lit with candles decorate the solid mahogany walls here, giving life
to the flicker shadows of the sturdy rails.  Behind the staircase, a
small hallway extends toward the south.  The buzzing of the crowded
lobby fills your ears from the east.

name: The Regal Tavern
description:
Rustic wooden chairs, scruffy tables and bar stools give this small
tavern a rough, comfortable and inviting.  The bar covers the entire
northern wall, displaying a vast selection of bottles, and kegs behind
it.  Torches line the mahogany walls in even intervals, but shadows
still keep the bar in a shadowy light.  The walls are otherwise void
of decoration, thanks to the rough clientel that usually resides here.
A well-lit, less seedy area extends off the tavern to the south.

name: A Large Auditorium
description:
An army of wooden chairs fills the large auditorium before you.  The
lights along the walls are of a magical nature, as they simply seem to
glow with their own power.  Several aisles cloaked in red velvet run
down the length of the auditorium, all the way to the raised platform
that makes up the stage.  Murals cover the walls, their colorful paint
giving a new life to the auditorium.

name: A Small Hallway
description:
Candles line the mahogany walls along this small, undecorated hall.
There seems to be little of interest for the average theatre patron,
though it is obviously kept clean and doesn't smell of disuse. A stout
wooden door in the south end of the hallway is all you can see.  A
brightly painted sign is suspended from a rusty nail on the door
itself.

name: Backstage
description:
Props lie scattered about in this large, backstage area.  Costumes,
both finished and not, cover the limited amount of counter space as
provided by a few wooden tables.  A dark curtain hangs down from the
ceiling, keeping the fluid workings of the stage crew invisible to
the audience.

name: Atop a Spiraling Staircase
description:
A narrow, red rug runs down the center of the twisting stairway,
metal railings curving around to offer support should you wish to
descend.  Wall sconces lit with candles decorate the solid mahogany
walls here, giving life to the flicker shadows of the sturdy rails.
There seems to be little in the way of entertainment on this level,
but you also notice that there is a door in the southern wall and
the hallway extends farther to the west.

name: A Small Lobby
description:
The hallway here comes to dead end and expands into a lobby similar
to the one downstairs.  A few cushioned benches line against the back
wall, and some smaller paintings hang here as well.  Wall sconces as
seen in other portions of the theatre light the way here, making this
gathering space warm and cozy.  A doorway is set into the south wall,
leading out onto the balcony seating.

name: Overlooking the Stage
description:
From above the downstairs seating, the view of the stage can only
be described as extraordinary.  The smaller, more cozy seating of the
balcony also looks to be for special guests, as the chairs here are
cushioned as opposed to the bare seating of the main section.  Guard
rails carved out of solid pieces of oak safely keep you from tumbling
over to what would be a rather rough landing.  The lighting here is
similar to that of the main seating area, balls of light seem to glow
with a life all their own.

name: Upon the Stage
description:
The auditorium is seen from a new perpective here on the stage.
Whether the seats are full or empty, there's a certain rush you
get just by standing here in anticipation of your performance.
A red velvet curtain is pulled to each side from the stage with
lengths of golden rope.  The wooden boards that make up the stage
itself are scuffed and worn, their ordinariness calming your nerves.

name: A Quiet Corner
description:
Candles of all different sizes emit a warm glow to this somewhat
less rowdy corner off the tavern's main room.  Comfortable looking
chairs and pillows are scattered throughout the room.  A few wooden
tables are thrown into the mix, some well worn books in able reach
for the reading enthusiast.  Soft, woven rugs cover the otherwise
plain floor and despite their scruffy appearance, they feel like
heaven against your feet.

name: A Private Library
description:
It looks as though you have wandered into the private collection of
books belonging to the Regal Theatre.  Every wall, from the ceiling to
the floor, is lined with book after book.  Many of them are worn with
use, the lettering on the binding completely gone off some of them.  A
ladder is set off to the side of the doorway, used to get some of the
harder to reach volumes.  A small table and matching chair is all the
furniture that fits in the room.  A few magical globes illuminate over
the table itself, shedding enough light to read by.

name: A Bustling Kitchen
description:
Cook's aids and serving wenches scurry through the kitchen, plates of
steaming food giving a tasty aroma to the place.  Pantries filled with
unprepared foods line many of the walls, and a large fireplace is set
in the western wall.  A small tripod fashioned from metal balances a
pot of beef stew over the flames.  A large wooden table takes up the
majority of the room in the kitchen.  Utensils, kettles, and all sorts
of food lay heaped up on the counters, and you wonder how anything can
possibly get done.

name: The Western Arch
description:
A large, gleaming glass arch rises above you, completely devoid of any
sort of designs or markings.  Through the arch, you can see the lobby of the
Glass Tower, a mecca of magic that is as famous as it is ancient.  There are
few inhabitants of Melcene anywhere nearby, save a commoner or two who has
come to gawk at the Tower's splendor.  A way off to the west, you can see
the buzzing streets of Melcene, seeming almost muted from here.  A tiny
inscription has been written on a stone in the ground.

name: The Glass Tower, Lobby Level
description:
Everything around you is made of glass, but none of it bears so much as a
tiny scratch. Though much of it is clear, some are made opaque by the colors
that they are stained, ranging from red to copper to blue to a milky white.
The shuffling feet of scholars echo off of the crystalline walls, which give
the resounding sounds a strange, otherworldly quality. To the north,
a door leads into a library. To the east, the lobby continues, while to the
south you can see the base of the western staircase.

name: At the Bottom of the Western Staircase
description:
Everything around you is made of glass, but none of it bears so much as a
tiny scratch.  Though much of it is clear, some are made opaque by the
colors that they are stained, ranging from red to copper to blue to a milky
white.  Jutting up from the opaque glass floor in such a way that it is
apparent that the glass was never cut, and was simply molded, is a spiral
staircase that leads up into a higher level of the tower.  The lobby
continues in all directions around you.

the resounding sounds a strange, otherworldly quality. To the south,
a door leads into a magic shop. To the north, you can see the bottom of the
western staircase, while to the east, the lobby continues.

tiny scratch. Though much of it is clear, some are made opaque by the colors

Jutting up from the opaque glass floor in such a way that it is apparent that
the glass was never cut, and was simply molded, is a spiral staircase
that leads up into a higher level of the tower. The lobby continues in all

name: The Glass Tower, Lobby Level
description:
Everything around you is made of glass, but none of it bears so much as a
tiny scratch. Though much of it is clear, some are made opaque by the colors
that they are stained, ranging from red to copper to blue to a milky white.
The shuffling feet of scholars echo off of the crystalline walls, which give
the resounding sounds a strange, otherworldly quality. To the south,
a door leads into a small room, while to the north, you can see the bottom of
the eastern staircase. To the west, the lobby continues.

name: The Eastern Arch
description:
A large, gleaming glass arch rises above you, completely devoid of any
sort of designs or markings.  Through the arch, you can see the lobby of the
Glass Tower, a mecca of magic that is as famous as it is ancient.  There are
few inhabitants of Melcene anywhere nearby, save a commoner or two who has
come to gawk at the Tower's splendor.  A way off to the west, you can see
the buzzing streets of Melcene, seeming almost muted from here.

name: The Scribe's Shop
description:
Different kinds of magical inks, papers and quills line shelves all around
the room. A glass case set into the counter displays a number of scrolls, each
carefully placed on red velvet stands, leaning back, so that the scrolls face
the customers. Each scroll has a silver plaque underneath it inscribed with
the magics that it contains. To the south, a door leads back out into the
lobby.

name: The Alchemist's Shop
description:
The pungent odors of herbs, chemicals and metals being brewed combine to make
an overpowering stench that easily drives out those that do not have a
need to be here. A hunch-backed old man wearing a turban of dark magenta
shambles around behind the counter at an alarming speed, grabbing reagents
and various mixing, measuring and pulverizing instruments and putting them
to use. A doorway lies to the north, leading back out into the lobby.

name: The Enchantress' Shop
description:
Hundreds of tiny charms hang from the ceiling, each seemingly very fragile
and delicate and of various colors and materials. A light incense burns
behind the counter, where the enchantress stands. Curtains cover up the
storage area behind her, in which boxes are barely visible in the
darkness. A doorway leads to the north into the lobby.

name: Guest Library
description:
This room is massive. Ornate carpets are placed neatly in certain spots about
the floor, covering the silver and glass tiles. An unidentifiable source of
light shines down upon the room from the ceiling, reflecting and refracting
from multiple places about the room. Large bookshelves have been set into the
walls, housing some important works.

name: The Second Floor of the Glass Tower
description:
The glass surrounding you seems to be slightly different than the glass in
the Tower's lobby. Very thin, seemingly frail columns of the luminescent yet
opaque material sporadically rise up from the ground near the walls and meld
into the ceiling, seeming to be more for decoration than support. A single
line of mahogany marble bisects the hallway, which continues to the east.

name: Western Staircase of the Second Level
description:
The glass surrounding you seems to be slightly different than the glass in
the Tower's lobby. Very thin, seemingly frail columns of the luminescent yet
opaque material sporadically rise up from the ground near the walls and meld
into the ceiling, seeming to be more for decoration than support. A single
line of mahogany marble bisects the hallway, which continues to the east and
west. A door lies to the south. In the center of the hallway, there is a wide,
round glass tube with a gaping arched entrance; the western staircase.

name: A Small Hallway
description:
The glass has taken on a softer and simpler appearance in this small
hallway. The powerful elegance of the Tower, however, is not lacking here. The
simple hallway continues to the east into the main hallway, and to the south,
into a smaller room.

walls, and a mahogany cabinet stands up against the southern wall, along with
a desk and a cot that lies perpendicular to the cabinet against the eastern
wall.

name: The Third Floor of the Glass Tower
description:
Thick pillars of glass line both sides of the hall, each casting a
shimmering glow that is reflected and refracted by the unnaturally flawless
crystal that makes up the Tower. Quiet whispers can be heard from time to
time; ethereal echoes chilled by the walls of glass. A single line of ebon
marble bisects the hallway, which continues to the east.

description:

shimmering glow that is reflected and refracted by the unnaturally flawless

name: The Fourth Floor of the Glass Tower
description:
The glass on this floor is completely opaque, and ranges in color from
obsidian to cyan and copper, much of it looking as if it were stained by some
exotic oil. A strange chemical scent fills the air, and the scholars that
happen to be passing through these halls seem to be in a state of perpetual
panic and anxiety. There is little, if any audible whispering here, but
strange chanting by unseen denizens of the tower echo throughout this floor. A
single line of crimson marble bisects the hallway, which continues to the
east.

name: Fourth Level Western Staircase
description:

obsidian to cyan and copper, much of it looking as if it were stained by some
exotic oil. A strange chemical scent fills the air, and the scholars that
happen to be passing through these halls seem to be in a state of perpetual
panic and anxiety. There is little, if any audible whispering here, but
strange chanting by unseen denizens of the tower echo throughout this floor. A

name: A Small Room
description:

echo throughout this floor. Small shelves line the walls, and a crimson cabinet
stands up against the southern wall, along with a desk and a cot that lies
perpendicular to the cabinet against the eastern wall.

name: The Fifth Floor of the Glass Tower
description:
The most striking feature of this particular floor is not the beautiful
prismatic glass that makes it up, nor is it the strange windchime-like sound
that mingles with the faint chanting from the floor below, but the complete
and utter absence of scholars or scholar's quarters. The entire hallway
brightens and dims slowly, as if it should somehow be connected with the
beating heart of the Tower, if the Tower were to have such a thing. This
brightening and dimming would be more likened to the sun passing behind
a field of sporadically placed clouds than an intense exhibition of magical
power, though it is rather obvious that it is the latter.

name: The Top of the Western Staircase
description:
The most striking feature of this particular floor is not the beautiful
prismatic glass that makes it up, nor is it the strange windchime-like sound
that mingles with the faint chanting from the floor below, but the complete
and utter absence of scholars or scholar's quarters. The entire hallway
brightens and dims slowly, as if it should somehow be connected with the
beating heart of the Tower, if the Tower were to have such a thing. This
brightening and dimming would be more likened to the sun passing behind
a field of sporadically placed clouds than an intense exhibition of magical
power, though it is rather obvious that it is the latter. The staircase
reaches its pinnacle here, the glass tube which contains it rising exactly
half-way up to the ceiling. Below you, the swirling structure rigidly descends
into its crystalline tomb.

name: The Foyer of The Great Sun Temple
A Short Hallway Within the Temple
Entrance to the Dead Forest
description:
The land around you becomes more ravaged and decimated.  Trees that were
lush and green to the north seem more twisted and dried here.  To the south
the forest appears darker and more foreboding, as if something has corrupted
the very essence of it.

name: Near the Entrance to the Dead Forest
description:
Here inside the beginings of the forest there are signs of wildlife, but
they are few and far between.  The normal forest sounds of birds and small
animals in the underbrush seem absent and the darkness around you is most
unnatural.  The trees around you seem to be twisted and dead, like something
had drained the life from them.

name: Within the Dead Forest
description:
Around you the trees appear dead and lifeless.  Even the small vegetation
that has grown on the forest floor has a taint of evil to it.  Faint mist
swirls around you and sends beams of light scattering into the darkened
forest.

description:

regrowing.

name: A bloody part of the Dead Forest
description:
The ground here is covered in sticky green ichor and scaly bits of flesh.
The smell of putrid waste and wafts in the air, mixing in with the stench of
dead foliage and carrion matter.

name: Before a Black River
description:
The forest ends here before a dark river.  Small malformed shapes squirm
and thrash about in the liquid but it is hard to see exactly what they are
over the mist that hangs loosely across the water.  A makeshift bridge has
been partially erected over the river.

name: On a decayed bridge
description:
You stand upon a decaying and decrepit bridge made from some kind of dead
tree trunk.  Below you a hideous black river flows past, tiny shapes
splashing and hissing within.  The bridge heads north and south.

name: On a decayed bridge
description:
You stand upon a decaying and decrepit bridge made from some kind of dead
tree trunk.  Below you a hideous black river flows past, tiny shapes
splashing and hissing within.  The bridge heads north and south.

name: On the South side of the Bridge
description:
You stand at the south side of a decaying old bridge made from the trunk
of a dead tree.  Around you mist lies softly upon the forest floor,
partially hiding the decay and death.  Only twisted and crumpled trees lie
all around you.  To the north the bridge crosses over a black river, while
south there appears to be a large dark clearing.

name: Within a Dark Clearing
description:
The dead forest seems not quite so bad here.  Trees are still twisted but
not quite so badly, and some greenery still exists in sparse spots.  All
around you the dark clearing extends.  For off to the south you hear the
faint sounds of real forest animals.

name: Within a Dark Clearing
description:

not quite so badly, and some greenery still exists in sparse spots.  All
around you the dark clearing extends.  For off to the south you hear the

around you the dark clearing extends.  To the south the forest seems to
become more lush and green...

name: Within a Dark Clearing
description:
The dead forest seems not quite so bad here.  Trees are still twisted but
not quite so badly, and some greenery still exists in sparse spots.  All
around you the dark clearing extends.  Something seems a bit different about
this part of the clearing...

name: On a sparsely vegetated path
description:
You stand upon a path with sparse but green foliage.  To the north the
forest becomes dead and dark, with a large clearing all you can see.  South
of here the region seems to get greener and more like a REAL forest.

name: Entrance to the Dying Forest
description:
The forest around you seems to be in the last stages of life. Everywhere you
look there is decay and rot. There are sounds of normal wildlife, but they
seem muted and scarce. Further to the west you can see the faint glow of
orange that seems to be from fires.

name: Within the Dying Forest
description:
The forest seems strangely subdued, as if in the last stages of life.
Wildlife can be heard, but it is muted and scarce. Around you there are signs
of small bushfires that have been started but somehow stopped before getting
out of hand.

name: Within the Dying Forest
description:
The forest seems strangely subdued, as if in the last stages of life.
Wildlife can be heard, but it is muted and scarce. Around you there are signs
of small bushfires that have been started but somehow stopped before getting
out of hand.

name: Within the Dying Forest
description:
The forest here is well kept and seems more lush than the majority of the
region. Plants bloom in several places and the sounds of small animals in the
underbrush can be heard. Large hoof marks in the dirt are the only sign of any
real large creatures. It is almost as if the darker inhabitants avoid this
section.

name: Within a Centaur Settlement
description:
You stand on a small pathway through what appears to be a very hastily built
settlement. Centaur hoof marks have dug up the ground all around you and
small huts line the pathway. The forest here is much better kept than the rest
of the region, almost like it was in a totally sperate region. To the north is
a small hut.

name: Within a Centaur Hut
description:
You are within a small but well kept hut. A tiny fire has been built in the
ground and the smell of recent cooking wafts through the air. The only exit
appears back south to the settlment pathway.

name: On a Wide Road
description:
The road here is a wide dirt track, running on a beeline to the north
amid the rolling pastures that extend to the east and west.  In the distance
to the north, fields turn to foothills and the foothills then give way to
towering mountain peaks.  To the south, the verdant fields seem to stretch
endlessly into the distance.  Their beauty is marred somwhat, however, by
the road that widens to the south and the hint of civilization beyond.

name: A Bend in the Road
description:
The wide dirt track loops here, tracing its way through the rolling green
pastures to the south and east.  In the distance to the north, fields turn
to foothills and the foothills then give way to towering mountain peaks. 
The road runs off into the distance to the east, disappearing from sight. 
To the south, faint hints of civilization can be detected along the road.

name: On a Wide Road
description:
This wide dirt track traces its way through rolling green pastures that
stretch out far to the south.  In the distance to the north, fields turn to
foothills and the foothills then give way to towering mountain peaks.  The
road disappears off into the distance to the east, and reaches a looping
bend to the west, where it leads back toward civilization.

name: On a Wide Road
description:
This wide dirt track traces its way through rolling green pastures that
stretch out far to the south.  In the distance to the north, fields turn to
foothills and the foothills then give way to towering mountain peaks.  The
road stretches off to the east and west, looking relatively well-traveled
considering the pristine beauty of the untouched surroundings.

name: A Bend in the Road
description:
This wide dirt track reaches a bend here, tracing its way to the north
and west through rolling green pastures that extend far to the south.  In
the distance to the north, fields turn to foothills and the foothills then
give way to towering mountain peaks.  The road twist around a corner to the
west, and widens at a small intersection to the north.  Black city walls are
barely visible far to the north.

name: An Intersection of Roads
description:
The dirt track grows even a bit wider here, this intersection an
elliptical blemish amid the rolling green pastures that extend into the
southern horizon.  In the distance to the north, fields turn to foothills
and the foothills then give way to towering mountain peaks.  The road twists
around a corner to the south, and a smaller dirt road continues to the east.
In the distance to the north, dark city walls lie in the shadow of the
mountains.

name: On a Wide Road
description:
This wide dirt track traces its way through rolling green pastures that
stretch out far to the south.  In the distance to the north, fields turn to
foothills and the foothills then give way to towering mountain peaks.  The
road widens to the south as it reaches a small intersection.  Dark city
walls are visible in the shadow of the mountains to the north.

name: On a Wide Road
description:
This wide dirt track traces its way through rolling green pastures that
stretch out far to the south.  In the distance to the north, fields turn to
foothills and the foothills then give way to towering mountain peaks.  The
road continues to the south, and dark city walls rise up in the distance to
the north.

name: On a Wide Road
description:
This wide dirt track traces its way through rolling green pastures that
stretch out far to the south.  In the distance to the north, fields turn to
foothills and the foothills then give way to towering mountain peaks.  The
road continues to the south, and the gated entrance to a city lies to the
north.

name: On a Wide Road
description:
This wide dirt track runs to the north and south, carved out between
fields of tall grass that extend to the east and west.  The road is
well-traveled here, with city walls visible just to the southeast.  A narrow
field is accessable to the west, while the gates of Melcene lie just to the
south.

name: On a Wide Road
description:
This wide dirt track runs on a beeline to the north and south, carved
out between fields of tall grass that extend to the east and west.  The road
is well-traveled here, with city walls visible in the distance to the south.
The road continues to the north and south.

name: On a Wide Road
description:
This wide dirt track runs on a beeline to the north and south, carved out
between fields of tall grass that extend to the east and west.  The road is
well-traveled here, with city walls visible in the distance to the south. 
To the north, the road widens into an intersection.

name: An Intersection of Roads
description:
The dirt track reaches a junction here, branching off in three
directions.  To the west, the road winds itself through rolling plains that
stretch off into the horizon.  To the east, the trail becomes narrower as it
runs through narrow fields of tall grass.  To the south, the road grows a
bit wider as it extends toward civilization in the distance.

name: A Bend in the Road
description:
The wide dirt track reaches a bend here, winding its way through rolling
plains into the horizon to the northwest.  In the distance to the north,
fields turn to foothills and foothills then give way to towering mountain
peaks.  Occasionally, small clusters of trees break up the otherwise
sprawling landscape.  The road continues to the north, and reaches an
intersection to the east.

name: On a Wide Road
description:
This wide dirt track winds its way through rolling plains into the
horizon to the southeast.  In the distance to the north, fields turn to
foothills and foothills then give way to towering mountain peaks. 
Occasionally, small clusters of trees break up the otherwise sprawling
landscape.  The road continues here to the north and south.

name: A Road Through the Fields
description:
To the north and south extend huge fields, the long grasses rippling
faintly with the passing breeze.  Beyond the fields to the north some
rolling foothills sprout up in the distance.  Far to the south a walled city
is barely visible.  This dirt track stretches out through the fields to the
east, where the plains seem to become even more expansive.  An intersection
of roads lies to the west.

name: A Road Through the Fields
description:
To the north and south extend huge fields, the long grasses rippling
faintly with the passing breeze.  Beyond the fields to the north some
rolling foothills sprout up in the distance.  Far to the south a walled city
is barely visible.  This dirt track stretches out to the west, and to the
east where the plains seem to become more expansive.

name: A Bend in the Road
description:
To the north and south extend huge fields, the long grasses rippling
faintly with the passing breeze.  Beyond the fields to the north some
rolling foothills sprout up in the distance.  Far to the south a walled city
is barely visible.  This dirt track stretches out to the west, and bends to
the north as it leads toward the plains.

name: A Bend in the Road
description:
To the north and south extend huge fields, the long grasses rippling
faintly with the passing breeze.  Beyond the fields to the north some
rolling foothills sprout up in the distance.  Far to the south a walled city
is barely visible.  This dirt track stretches out to the east as it leads
toward the plains, and reaches a bend to the south.

name: A Road Through the Fields
description:
To the north and south extend huge fields, the long grasses rippling
faintly with the passing breeze.  Beyond the fields to the north some
rolling foothills sprout up in the distance.  The dirt track continues here,
reaching a bend to the west and an intersection to the east.  In the
distance to the east a forest rises up out of the plains.

name: An Intersection in the Plains
description:
This intersection is little more than an elliptical patch of dirt carved
out among the fields of high grasses.  Off to the east, the road grows
narrow as it makes its way into a forest which rises out of the plain.  The
dirt track also continues to the west, and to the north the grasses have
been trampled down to form a path leading through the plains.

name: A Road Near the Forest
description:
The dirt track stretching through this area is narrow, but well-traveled.
To the north and south, plains stretch out into the horizon, long grasses
swaying gently in the breeze.  The road continues to the west here toward a
small intersection, and runs also to the east where a small village sits in
the shadow of a larger forest.

name: A Road Near the Forest
description:
The dirt track stretching through this area is narrow, but well-traveled.
To the north and south, plains stretch out into the horizon, long grasses
swaying gently in the breeze.  The road continues to the west through the
plains, and runs to the east toward a small village which sits in the shadow
of a larger forest.

name: A Road Near the Forest
description:
The dirt track stretching through this area is narrow, but well-traveled.
To the north and south, plains stretch out into the horizon, long grasses
swaying gently in the breeze.  The road continues to the west through the
plains, and runs to the east toward a small village which sits in the shadow
of a larger forest.

name: A Road Near the Forest
description:
The narrow dirt track is somewhat shaded here, as it approaches a small
village to the east.  To the southeast a rather large forest looms above the
village.  The dirt road runs to the west, where vast plains stretch out to
the north and south.  Stretching into the horizon, the prospect of
civilization seems more likely beyond the plains to the west.

name: A Snowy Trail
description:
Light filters down through the branches of sparsely set trees that line
the sides of the road.  Beyond the trees to the north, a wide field leads
off toward a larger forest in the distance.  The plain also runs to the
south along the city wall.  A large gate offers entrance to the city to the
west, and the dirt road continues to the east.

name: A Snowy Trail
description:
Light filters down through the branches of sparsely set trees that line
the sides of the road.  Beyond the trees to the north, a wide field leads
off toward a larger forest in the distance.  The plain also runs to the
south along the wall of a city that rises up to the west.  A large gate is
visible in the distance to the west, while the road continues to the east.

name: A Snowy Trail
description:

the sides of the road.  Beyond the trees to the north, a wide field leads
off toward a larger forest in the distance.  The plain also runs into the
horizon to the south.  The road continues to the east, and west toward a
large, black-walled city.

the sides of the road.  Beyond the trees to the west lies a wide field that
leads into the distance where a dark-walled city rises up.  The plains also
stretch out into the horizon to the east.  The road continues to the north
and south.

description:

toward a larger forest in the distance.  The plains also stretch out into
the horizon to the south.  The road continues here to the east and west.

description:

description:

name: A Bend in the Trail
description:
Light filters down through the branches of sparsely set trees that line
the sides of the road.  A grassy plain stretches out between the trees to
the south and east.  To the west the tree-lined road continues.  To the
north, the trees grow a bit thicker as the road approaches a larger forest.

name: A Forested Trail
description:
Light filters down through the branches of evenly set trees that line
the sides of the road.  The trees are rather thick here, obscuring vision
into the distance to the east and west.  The road leads to the south, where
the trees grow more sparse .  To the north, the road leads into thicker
cover, the beginning of a larger forest.

name: A Bend in the Trail
description:
Light filters down through the branches of evenly set trees that line
the sides of the road.  The forest grows close all around here, the canopy
thickening significantly as you move away from the road.  The road becomes
more of a woodland trail to the west, leading into the depths of the forest.
The road continues to the south, where the trees lighten in the distance.

name: A Worn Trail, Before the Gates of Iseldheim
description:
This trail is really just a worn area that wanders through this deolate
plain of parched earth.  Furrows and cracks run along the ground, the
thirsty land gaping at the sky in its plea for water.  Here and there short,
leathery plants spring up from the ground, the sole survivors of this
hostile land.  A city rises up to the east, and the trail continues to the
west.

name: The Light of Creation
description:
Slowly, your eyes open, admitting the warm light of this new world.  You
find yourself awash in the sounds of the sea, as waves break against the
shore and gulls fly overhead -- you turn to watch them, and see nothing but
the light which surrounds you.  Subtly, the sound in the air shifts to
rustling leaves and a crackling fire; the scent of burning wood reaches you,
tickling you further toward consciousness.  As you become fully aware for
the first time, a booming voice strikes out through the white void: \Welcome

area_id: to Shalar
room_id: young pilgrim.  You have chosen to inhabit this vessel

area_id: commend you for your choice.  In the coming minutes
room_id: you will become

area_id: accustomed to life here; I will guide you by placing signs with the
information you need.  You may look at the very first sign here in this
room.  Good luck -- I will be watching over you.\"

name: An Expansive Hall
description:
Abruptly you find yourself plunged into pitch darkness.  Your eyes seem
to widen of their own accord, struggling to take in your surroundings and
adapt to the new level of light.  As they do so, you realize that the room
you have entered is actually quite well-lit, with softly flickering candles
lining each wall.  Numerous portraits and busts fill your field of vision
and stretch off down corridors to the north, south, and west, as far as your
eyes can see.  To the east is a large wooden door.  Glancing upward, you
note that wherever you came from is no longer a viable travel destination.

name: A Storage Room
description:
Your explorations have landed you in what looks to be a closet of sorts. 
Dozens of paintings and statues which seem as though they're in the same
style as those you saw outside are irreverently piled on top of each other
here.  A significant layer of dust covers most everything, and every
movement you make kicks another cloud of it into the air.  The only clean
thing in the room is a bust at the south end of the room, up atop a marble
shelf.  The man depicted wears a tiny set of spectacles and has a
well-trimmed mustache.  Despite the fact that he is carved from stone, you
have the distinct impression that his cold eyes are watching you...

name: A Hidden Chamber
description:
The way you have opened widens into a small, featureless chamber with
flat steel walls all around.  Behind you, the hidden doorway is still
visible, leading to the north.  But in every other direction, cursory
glances reveal no other possible exits.  The sound of dripping water echoes
into this metal tomb, resonating in such a way as to discomfit the
listener... you receive the eerie sensation of being buried alive.  The dim
light here is provided by sources through the door to the north, and it
seems as though the temperature is dropping as you stand here.

name: Between the Walls
description:
Whirling around, you see that the north wall of this tiny space is the
same featureless steel as was prominent in the last room.  It appears as
though whatever opening you passed through moments ago has closed up behind
you; the wall ripples and shivers for an instant, however, indicating that
you could probably push your way back through to the north if you wanted to.
Turning your attention to the rest of the space you've entered, the design
seems nonsensical until you realize that you are literally between the walls
of whatever structure this is.  In the same instant as this realization, yet
another sign shoots up from the ground, and a huge portal snaps into
existence.

name: A Huge Mattress
description:
From the way it's been beaten almost completely flat, it's apparent that
this barely-padded floor serves as the entry point for people new to the
Academy.  A slight shimmering in the ceiling indicates the direction from
which those new to Shalar plummet.  The walls to the north, south, and east
are covered with signs and posters, mostly written in languages you can't
understand and pasted up on top of one another in such a manner as to make
them mostly illegible.  To your west, you see an intersection of hallways.

name: A Junction of Hallways
description:
Here, you are presented with two hallways down which you might travel; to
the west, the sounds of many busy people waft in on a hot breeze... to the
south, you can see daylight outside a large temple.  A sizeable map on the
wall provides passersby with directions, though it seems largely
unnecessary.  Above you, a timber-frame style of construction holds the
ceiling up.  This Academy seems almost to be built within a mine shaft,
though it is well lit and comfortable.

name: A Hallway in the Academy
description:
This hallway has a bit of a claustrophobic feel to it.  The walls taper
together here from both directions, reaching their closest point at a sort
of bottleneck in this room.  Hot air from the Academy rushes by you toward
the temple to the south in a constant, pressing wind.  You feel almost as if
you are being pushed out into the world by some great, warm invisible hand. 
Peering to the north, you can barely make out a junction of hallways to the
north, and a large map on the wall.  South, the light of the High Temple of
Cimar beckons you.

name: A Bend in the Hall
description:
The winding, mineshaft-like hallway through the Academy bends here, and
you can continue to the north or east.  One support beam has begun to buckle
in from the rock ceiling's massive weight, but a closer examination shows
that it has likely been broken and reinforced several times in the last
century or so.  There are no lights in this section of the tunnel, but what
comes in from both directions provides plenty to see by; ore deposits of
some sort in the walls reflect the light and glitter like stars in the
darkness.

name: A Large Guildhall
description:
Torches line this massive hall, each adding to the chaos of flickering
shadows cast about this room.  A twenty foot high fireplace of reddish stone
roars on the north wall, casting incredible heat throughout the Academy. 
The ceiling here is much higher than in the tunnels to either side; the weak
firelight provides ample visibility on the floor, but strains to reach the
top of the room.  Despite this, you can make out a huge, black, wrought-iron
chandelier which is apparently in a state of disuse.  Behind each torch on
the walls, crude paintings of famous Shalaran heroes to have come through
here for training at some point early in their lives are proudly displayed. 
Dozens of recruits mill through this vicinity, guided by several large men
who look to be in charge; you must move in order to avoid being trampled by
any of a number of herds.

name: A Small Shop
description:
This room, barely more than a wide spot in the Academy's hallway, has
been set up as a shop for recruits.  Through a window in one rocky wall,
between two huge wooden strut supports, a shopkeeper peers at you
expectantly.  His wares are on display on a countertop of stone, set at
eye-level for a sidhe, and a sign hangs prominently above it.  To the north,
a hallway leads further into the Academy, and to the east, the huge, hot
guildhall bustles energetically.

name: A Short Hallway
description:
This portion of the hallway which stretches through the Academy is fairly
cool.  A breeze wafts in from the north and passes gently by, caressing your
skin like a mother would her child's.  Brilliant, flaring torchlight
reflected around the corner from the guildhall southeast of here is still
plenty to illuminate this section of tunnel; as such there are no direct
light sources here.  The result is a strange effect on the walls and ceiling
-- long shadows cover large sections of the rock and vacillate slowly, as if
there were huge black snakes all around you.

name: The Dispatch
description:
A large sign on the wall in this room indicates, with a large arrow
pointing to the left, that you may pass into the training cages to the west;
with a smaller arrow pointing to the right, it shows you that you may enter
the \Overrun Area\" to the east.  Two small piles of stones here look to have

area_id: been delicately arranged; noticing that each stone has a name inscribed upon
it in tiny print
room_id: you receive a sudden impression that they signify the

area_id: number of people who have died in either direction.  Furthermore
room_id: you notice

area_id: that the pile on the right is significantly larger.

name: The Gibberling Cage
description:
The keening, whining wail of the gibberlings in this room is deafening. 
Through a large barred door to the north, you see one of the beasts...
hairless, toothless, and thumping about on all fours.  Behind it, another
barred door conceals another gibberling.  On the south wall opposite this
cage, a lever practically begs to be pulled.  It takes little imagination to
conjure up an image of what precisely will happen once that takes place, of
course.  To the east, the intersection of tunnels that leads into these
training cages is visible.  West of here, the deeper cages present much more
difficult challenges.

name: The Goblin Cage
description:
Here, the cage is filled with goblins.  Wearing nothing but loincloths,
the filthy little beast men lunge at the bars, straining to reach one
another and you.  The goblin which is closest to you in the first cage
breathes with the sound of a dying animal; his frenzied exertions seem to be
tiring him out somewhat, but his beady red eyes remain locked on you
relentlessly.  From the east, you can still hear the wailing gibberlings. 
The sound from the west is far more chilling; a deep howling sound born in
the depths of the Abyss rolls over you.  Another lever is in the wall behind
you here.

name: The Mastiff Pens
description:
This, the deepest of the training cages, is the home of the hellish
mastiffs of the west.  Such a far-ranging beast often roams over the
mountains and into the areas surrounding Cimar... in that case, they are
captured and brought here.  The huge animals farther back in the cage bay
and howl incessantly, separated from each other by thick iron bars and
impatient for a good hunt.  The one nearest you, however, remains calmly
seated upon its haunches and stares directly at you, licking its lips
occasionally.  Another lever is in the wall to the south, and east of here
lie the rest of the cages.

name: The Outpost
description:
This slick-sided tunnel is walled with panels of wood.  The ceiling and
floor are wood as well, all of it dripping wet.  The sounds of water falling
and flowing echo in from a dim cavern to the east.  It looks as though
you're standing in the last remnant of the Academy's structure before what
is commonly referred to as the Overrun Area... which seems to be a large
natural cavern, punctured by huge root systems which form small caverns and
pockets and tunnels of their own.  Strange, animal sounds creak and croak
from the root-filled caverns, and you begin to sense why new recruits are
gently dissuaded from heading in that direction.

name: The Entrance to the Overrun Area
description:
The air in this cavern is thick with moisture so cold and dense that it
feels like a slap on the face every time you turn your head.  Horrible
sounds drift all through the area; what sounds like a corpse being devoured
messily is what sticks out most between sharp, punctuating animal calls. 
The roots here are the size of century-old trees in some places, but dangle
like thick, clammy hair in others.  It's difficult to find any trace of a
trail or any sort of landmarks... one could very easily become very lost in
here.  West of here, you can make out the exit past a curtain of dangling
roots.
