name: A Murky Hole
description:
More of a wide crack in the floor of the cavern overhead than anything,
this tunnel burrows beneath the root system above and delves deep into the
earth.  Above you, roots dangle, dripping moisture onto your head; below
you, the soft earth gives way as you pass, as though it has been a very long
time since anyone has trodden here.  To the east, a soft glow indicates some
sort of light source, but you cannot determine what it is, precisely.  To
all other sides, you are surrounded by rancid earth and mossy rock.

name: The Lair of the Mutant
description:
The walls, ceiling, and floor of this room are all covered by iridescent
moss.  The ethereal yellowish glow generated by it is what lights this
cavern, in a decidedly eerie fashion.  To your east, a small stone tablet
rests against the moss-covered wall of the cavelike fissure, and to the
west, the sound of trickling water emanates gently.  This room stinks of
decay, and occasionally something rustles just out of sight.  Between the
thick, stifling, scent-laden air and the closed quarters, this particular
spot could make most anyone feel slightly claustrophobic.

name: The Mutant's Hoard
description:
This room was created by hands, dug from the loose earth of this fissure
below the caverns.  It looks like huge clots of dirt were torn free and
thrown to the west, as a large hump of tamped down earth narrows the
entrance considerably.  Strewn around this space, various bits of string and
colorful pieces of cloth are enshrined and lit by more garish yellow moss. 
Stuffed into the ceiling, a broken lamp protrudes downward, crowding
headroom.  A few tiles have been laid on the ground in a meticulous row, as
if in an abortive attempt to create a civilized space.

name: The Watering Hole
description:
This small cavern cracks its way from the Overrun Area to the north back
toward sections of the Academy to the southwest.  It looks as though this
area is free from the strange monsters inhabiting the caves to the north,
though you cannot be certain why at first.  However, very soon you note the
thick grease coating the walls and ceiling; the strange smell it gives off
is highly acetic.  Perhaps the beasts simply prefer to avoid this viscous
sludge.  At any rate, this room provides welcome respite, and is equipped
with a large basin full of crystal clear water.

name: A Steep Chute
description:
Strangely, the southern half of this room has a steeply sloping metal
plate for a floor.  It looks as though any southerly progress would be
rather irretraceable.  From what you can tell, this chute leads back to the
first area of the Academy; you see no way of returning here, however, short
of coming back through the Overrun Area.  To the east, the water basin
beckons you, but to the south, the warmth and light of the Academy are a
welcome change from the wet darkness of these caverns.

name: Within a Dark Crevice
description: (Missing, till I figure out just what is my area attached to)

name: Under the Crevice
description:
You find yourself in a wide maw within the earth.  Patches of sky can
still be seen from this point, should one gaze upward.  However, this is not
recommended since the terrain is treacherous and treading should be done
with the utmost care.  The terrain looks particularly slippery on the ravine
leading down.  Looking around you, you notice nothing but foreboding
darkness.

name: Under the Crevice
description:
A rare patch of brighter darkness pierces the darkness all around you. 
After a moment of confusion, you realize this is the light that still comes
in this place from the world outside.  The atmosphere of the rift is
oppresive and dank, heralding what lays ahead, should you venture deeper
into the caves.

name: Under the Crevice
description:
A rare patch of brighter darkness pierces the darkness all around you. 
After a moment of confusion, you realize this is the light that still comes
in this place from the world outside.  The atmosphere of the rift is
oppresive and dank, heralding what lays ahead, should you venture deeper
into the caves.

name: Pile of Rubble
description:
Jagged rocks fill this cold cave.  Aeons have worked their course,
forming impossibly sharp and long stalagmites on the cave floor.  The cave
is cold, and judging by the bones lying scattered among the rocks, many a
creature had met its demize here.  Fortunately for you, the fall had merely
stunned you.  You begin contemplating on your way back.

name: A Rough-Hewn Cavern Trail
description:
The trail ends abruptly here, at the base of a steep rise leading upwards
to the surface world.  Generations of Goblin miners have formed a haphazard
trail, whose primary purpose is to carry the crystal from the depths of
their mines to the dwellers under the skies.  The trails extends northwards
into the warm darkness, the pebbles ground into the dust beneath your feet.

name: A Rough-Hewn Cavern Trail
description:
The trail ends abruptly here, at the base of a steep rise leading upwards
to the surface world.  Generations of Goblin miners have formed a haphazard
trail, whose primary purpose is to carry the crystal from the depths of
their mines to the dwellers under the skies.  The trail extends northwards
into the warm darkness, the pebbles ground into the dust beneath your feet.

name: At The Turn In The Trail
description:
The trail is bent at an angle at this point, carved through the less
resistant rock.  It appears that a large block of iron oxide had blocked the
natural path and not even the stalwart goblin miners could dig through it. 
The path leads further towards the centre of the caves to the west, or
towards the surface world, to the south.

name: The Intersection of the Trails
description:
Trails leading eastward and westward meet at this cavern.  Somewhat
spacious, it is connecting the trails with the main complex of caves lying
to the north.  Seeing more traffic than either of the two trails, this
section looks considerably cleaner as well.

name: At The Turn In The Trail
description:
The trail is bent at an angle at this point, carved through the less
resistant rock.  It appears that a large block of iron oxide had blocked the
natural path and not even the stalwart goblin miners could dig through it. 
The path leads further towards the centre of the caves to the east, or
towards the surface world, to the south.

name: Before the Massive Stone Gate
description:
Huge bile of rock meets here, forming a natural chasm.  Between walls
ridden with minerals, goblins had built a massive protective stone gate. 
Carved from the most resilient of stone, it divides the inner goblin caves
from the rest of the world.  In the days long gone, it may have served a
defensive purpose, but nowadays, goblins leave it open as it lays on the
trade route.  Several torches are placed to the either side of the gate, so
as to allow more adventurous surface dwellers to prepare to brave the depths
lying north with greater ease.

name: At the Beginning of a Cavern
description:
The first contact with the goblin kingdom makes you realize that these
caves are not a mere mine excavation expoited by savages.  There seems to be
some sort of a pattern to the myriad of routes that goblin have created and
utilized.  The fervour of the creatures and the buzz of work and
conversation flows through the air from all around you.

name: In the Shades
description:
The darker shadows this place is immersed in seem unnatural.  So close to
the busy, massive stone gate, yet few goblins roam here.  The darkness is
augmented by the absence of the torches, which adorn the gate.

name: In the Shades
description:
The darker shadows this place is immersed in seem unnatural.  So close to
the busy, massive stone gate, yet few goblins roam here.  The darkness is
augmented by the absence of the torches, which adorn the gate.

name: An Expansive Cavern
description:
Sheer magnitude of this cave speaks volumes of the effort put in by
generations of Goblins working the earth.  Ceiling is lost at over 100 feet
of height and echoes of incessant Goblin chatter are multiplied under it. 
At either side of you, there is nothing but massive emptiness, telling you
that the cave expands further on.

name: An Expansive Cavern
description:
Sheer magnitude of this cave speaks volumes of the effort put in by
generations of Goblins working the earth.  Ceiling is lost at over 100 feet
of height and echoes of incessant Goblin chatter are multiplied under it. 
At either side of you, there is nothing but massive emptiness, telling you
that the cave expands further on.

name: An Expansive Cavern
description:
Sheer magnitude of this cave speaks volumes of the effort put in by
generations of Goblins working the earth.  Ceiling is lost at over 100 feet
of height and echoes of incessant Goblin chatter are multiplied under it. 
At either side of you, there is nothing but massive emptiness, telling you
that the cave expands further on.

name: The Spacious Cave
description:
The true beginning of the rough miners' cave system, this spacious cave
has walls that have recent scars embedded in them, along with the ancient
ones.  It seems that miners make it a habit to chip at the wall as they pass
on north-east deeper into the caves.  Quite possibly, this is for good luck.
The draft of breeze cools your face from the south, and you realize that
huge expanse of a cave lies in that direction.

name: The Spacious Cave
description:
The true beginning of the rough miners' cave system, this spacious cave
has walls that have recent scars embedded in them, along with the ancient
ones.  It seems that miners make it a habit to chip at the wall as they pass
on north-east deeper into the caves.  Quite possibly, this is for good luck.
The draft of breeze cools your face from the south, and you realize that
huge expanse of a cave lies in that direction.

name: The Spacious Cave
description:
The true beginning of the rough miners' cave system, this spacious cave
has walls that have recent scars embedded in them, along with the ancient
ones.  It seems that miners make it a habit to chip at the wall as they pass
on north-east deeper into the caves.  Quite possibly, this is for good luck.
The draft of breeze cools your face from the south, and you realize that
huge expanse of a cave lies in that direction.  Another air stream caresses
your skin from the opposite direction.  The path north leads further into
the mines.

name: Along the Western Wall of An Expansive Cavern
description:
The cave finally ends here, and this only because of the impenetrable
rock that forms its western wall.  The seam between the ceiling swooping
from the dizzying heights and the wall is not artificial, but the work of
nature.  It seems that the goblins have realized that this rock they cannot
conquer and they had simply made the most of it.  The chatter of the
workplace seems a bit less loud here.

name: Along the Eastern Wall of An Expansive Cavern
description:
The cave finally ends here, and this only because of the impenetrable
rock that forms its eastern wall.  The seam between the ceiling swooping
from the dizzying heights and the wall is not artificial, but the work of
nature.  It seems that the goblins have realized that this rock they cannot
conquer and they had simply made the most of it.  The chatter of the
workplace seems a bit less loud here.  The air seems cooler here and there
are some small holes in the eastern wall.

name: The Corner of the Spacious Cave
description:
The true beginning of the rough miners' cave system, this spacious cave
has walls that have recent scars embedded in them, along with the ancient
ones.  It seems that miners make it a habit to chip at the wall as they move
deeper into the caves.  Quite possibly, this is for good luck.  A slab of
rock with fewer than usual chips attracts your attention.  The oppresive
walls encircle you to the north and west, forcing you to move east or south.

name: The Corner of the Spacious Cave
description:
The true beginning of the rough miners' cave system, this spacious cave
has walls that have recent scars embedded in them, along with the ancient
ones.  It seems that miners make it a habit to chip at the wall as they pass
on north-east deeper into the caves.  Quite possibly, this is for good luck.
The draft of breeze cools your face from the south, and you realize that
huge expanse of a cave lies in that direction.  The oppressive walls
encircle you north and east, cutting you off.

name: Beginning of a Dark, Busy Hallway
description:
This is hallway is one of the first mining sites in this complex.  Signs
of busy activity are all around you: shouts of miners as they call each
other, singing of pickaxes as they strike in unison and an occasional curse.
The rock through which the hallway has been carved is rich in crystal, with
biles glimmering against the light.  Thick, stout wooden beams support the
cave ceiling safely.

name: In a Dark, Busy Hallway
description:
The hallway rich with crystal bile is perpetually busy.  As one shift of
miners leaves, the other one instantly takes their place.  The walls of the
hallway are heavily chipped, as pickaxes and hammers constantly batter them,
in search of more crystal.  Thick, stout supporting wooden beams look
stable, as they support a low ceiling.

name: In a Dark, Busy Hallway
description:
The hallway rich with crystal bile is perpetually busy.  As one shift of
miners leaves, the other one instantly takes their place.  The walls of the
hallway are heavily chipped, as pickaxes and hammers constantly batter them,
in search of more crystal.  Thick, stout supporting wooden beams look
stable, as they support a low ceiling.

name: The End of Dark, Busy Hallway
description:
This is the end of the central hallway that leads through the mines.  The
reason the miners had stopped here is the thinning of the crystal biles. 
Apparently, natural formation of softer rocks gave way to granite here and
the bile had moved elsewhere.  A well-beaten path leads towards the more
civilized section of mines leads south.  Deeper into the mines, a steep
slope leads down.

name: At the Top of a Desolated Ravine
description:
The air in this corridor is dank and oppresive.  Humidity lingers around
you in the form of mist, carrying heavy scent from the pits beneath you. 
You could swear you hear restless rustling of leaves coming from the same
direction.  Your attention is captivated by an unnaturally smooth stone
wall.

name: In the Middle of Rancid Clearing
description:
An unexpected sight greets you: impossible combination of rusted, ancient
armour, bones of various creatures and what appears to be rotting, dead
plants lay scattered about.  The smell of decay is so strong that you feel
momentarily overwhelmed and pause to rest.  The way out of this insanity
leads up the steep cliff, while all around you the rustling grows louder... 
Anxious, it would seem.

name: In the Pungent, Rough Corridor
description:
The scattered debris had spilled over from the central room to the east
here.  Not even a tight corridor had kept it at bay.  The corridor itself is
clearly not a work of any mortal hand.  Erratic in its flow, its shadows are
deceptive and unnatural.

name: In the Pungent, Rough Corridor
description:
The scattered debris had spilled over from the central room to the west
here.  Not even a tight corridor had kept it at bay.  The corridor itself is
clearly not a work of any mortal hand.  Erratic in its flow, its shadows are
deceptive and unnatural.

name: In the Pungent, Rough Corridor
description:
The scattered debris had spilled over from the central room to the south
here.  Not even a tight corridor had kept it at bay.  The corridor itself is
clearly not a work of any mortal hand.  Erratic in its flow, its shadows are
deceptive and unnatural.  The temperature within this corridor is
considerably higher than in the rest of the caves.  You begin to sweat.

name: In the Pungent, Rough Corridor
description:
The scattered debris had spilled over from the central room to the north
here.  Not even a tight corridor had kept it at bay.  The corridor itself is
clearly not a work of any mortal hand.  Erratic in its flow, its shadows are
deceptive and unnatural.

name: In the Western Forgotten Caven
description:
A surprisingly small chamber unravels before you.  The ceiling lays low,
with the walls oppressively propelling it.  The floor is uneven, covered in
scattered debris, small rocks and an occasional bone protruding upwards. 
The air is dank, stale and perpetually caressed by a sweet, smelly musk.

name: North End of Western Forgotten Cave
description:
A surprisingly small chamber unravels before you.  The ceiling lays low,
with the walls oppressively propelling it.  The floor is uneven, covered in
scattered debris, small rocks and an occasional bone protruding upwards. 
The air is dank, stale and perpetually caressed by a sweet, smelly musk.

name: South End of Western Forgotten Cave
description:
A surprisingly small chamber unravels before you.  The ceiling lays low,
with the walls oppressively propelling it.  The floor is uneven, covered in
scattered debris, small rocks and an occasional bone protruding upwards. 
The air is dank, stale and perpetually caressed by a sweet, smelly musk.

name: In the Northern Forgotten Cave
description:
The warm phosphorous glow illuminates these small caverns.  It seems that
the glow comes from the plants themselves, as you are deeply entrenched
within earth.  However, although the glow is warm, the shadows it casts over
pitch-black granite are menacing.

description:

name: In the Southern Forgotten Cave
description:
Chillingly cold, the air in this cavern system forces you to puff out
small clouds from your lungs.  It seems that the plants here have rather
peculiar metabolism, that forces them to release frost into their
environment.  The white coating all around walls, floor and ceiling is a
thin layer of solid ice, glazed over pure white marble.

description:

description:

name: In the Eastern Forgotten Cave
description:
You find yourself in the lair of gargantuan proportions, inhabited by
thin, agile plants.  The walls, if there are any, are covered in thick
lime-coloured slime -- no doubt, a vile excretion of the plants themselves. 
The source of the scent that was ever so pervasive throughout this Gods
forsaken complex of caves is finally before your eyes: the rotting, pulsing
and flailing arms of the plants themselves.

description:

name: At the Corner of a Dark, Busy Hallway
description:
The hallway rich with crystal bile is perpetually busy.  As one shift of
miners leaves, the other one instantly takes their place.  The walls of the
hallway are heavily chipped, as pickaxes and hammers constantly batter them,
in search of more crystal.  Thick, stout supporting wooden beams look
stable, as they support a low ceiling.

name: In a Dark, Busy Hallway
description:
The hallway rich with crystal bile is perpetually busy.  As one shift of
miners leaves, the other one instantly takes their place.  The walls of the
hallway are heavily chipped, as pickaxes and hammers constantly batter them,
in search of more crystal.  Thick, stout supporting wooden beams look
stable, as they support a low ceiling.

name: The End of Dark, Busy Hallway
description:
This is the end of the central hallway that leads through the mines.  The
reason the miners had stopped here is the thinning of the crystal biles. 
Apparently, natural formation of softer rocks gave way to granite here and
the bile had moved elsewhere.  A well-beaten path leads towards the more
civilized section of mines leads south.  Deeper into the mines, a steep
slope leads down.

name: A Busy Intersection
description:
The steep ravine before you leads up, to the common area of the mines. 
All around you, there is nothing but darkness.  Although you cannot feel the
walls around you, you still feel entrapped.  This is due to the low ceiling
and the fact that in deep caves, such as there, there is no wind and the air
is dank and stale.  All around you, you hear busy chatter of a mine
production in full swing.

name: North of the Busy Intersection
description:
Rough rock with jagged edges surrounds you.  Crystal bile can be seen
embedded in it, and the miners are busily digging away, amassing their
wealth.  Fine layer of dust lingers all throughout these caves, as specks of
dust cannot escape on any wind.  All around you, the sound of many pick-axes
can be heard.

name: A Dead End of a Mine-Shaft
description:
The crystal bile exhausted, this section of the mine had been shut off. 
Only dark walls of soft rock, grazed by numerous empty channals bear witness
to one-time expansion of the mines.  The rock walls encircle you entirely
and the only way to leave this particular casement is the same way you
walked in.

description:

description:

name: The Beginning of a New Mine-Shaft
description:
Particularly rich finding of crystal lode mining is the reason this
tunnel has been recently cut.  Somewhat more tidy than the exploited
sections, there are relatively few scraps in the rock and few excavations. 
However, judging by the amount of work here, this will quickly change.  Only
the most sturdiest and strongest of the miners work here, because they were
able to surpress the weaker ones and keep them at bay.  The tunnel turns
here, wrapping around indestructible rock.

name: At the Turn near the Entrance to the New Mine-Shaft
description:
Particularly rich finding of crystal lode mining is the reason this
tunnel has been recently cut.  Somewhat more tidy than the exploited
sections, there are relatively few scraps in the rock and few excavations. 
However, judging by the amount of work here, this will quickly change.  Only
the most sturdiest and strongest of the miners work here, because they were
able to surpress the weaker ones and keep them at bay.  The tunnel turns

name: The End of a New Mine-Shaft
description:
The crystal is as strongly present in this cave as it is through the rest
of the region.  The only reason the miners did not expand here is because
they are too busy exploiting the shafts to the east of here.  The rock is
particularly soft here and it looks as if this spot will be very promising
indeed.  North and south, you notice expansive emptiness, with strange
sounds echoing through it.

name: A New Casement
description:
This particular casement within the rock has just recently been opened. 
Dark grey rock is speckled with the crystal throughout.  It seems that every
swing of a pick-axe would bring one a hefty amount of coins.  The miners who
work here certainly agree, as they furiously work on the site, bent over
under the low ceiling.

name: A Dry Tunnel
description:
This tunnel has seen better days: some time ago, while there was enough
crystal to attract the scores of best miners, this sector of caves was
bursting with activity.  Nowadays, second-tier miners have taken over,
scraping the remains, while the best of the miners had moved to the western
complex of caves.

name: A Turn in the Dry Tunnel
description:
This tunnel has seen better days: some time ago, while there was enough
crystal to attract the scores of best miners, this sector of caves was
bursting with activity.  Nowadays, second-tier miners have taken over,
scraping the remains, while the best of the miners had moved to the western
complex of caves.  The tunnel wiggles around the rock, passing it to the
north and west.

name: A Dry Tunnel
description:
This tunnel has seen better days: some time ago, while there was enough
crystal to attract the scores of best miners, this sector of caves was
bursting with activity.  Nowadays, second-tier miners have taken over,
scraping the remains, while the best of the miners had moved to the western
complex of caves.

name: The End of a Dry Tunnel
description:
The tunnel comes to an end here.  There is no crystal to be seen at all,
yet the tunnel is in good shape.  Even the debris that can be spotted
everywhere where miners are involved is not present here.  It seems as if
some care was taken to keep this tunnel in good shape.  You notice footsteps
in the dust in front of you.

name: At the Entrance of the Crude Stronghold
description:
Natural underground cliffs block your passage to the east and west. 
Abrupt wall rises in front of you, blocking the path to the north.  It seems
that it is partially natural, though you can clearly spot unsophisticated,
rough fortifications that were built atop the ridge.  In the centre of the
northern wall stands iron portcullis, barring the entrance beyond.

name: Inside an Old, Exploited Excavation
description:
Piles of debris and broken mining equipment are strewn across the uneven
floor of this excavation.  Where once there was a plethora of crystal, now
only little veins remain.  Just as the excavation has lost its glamour, so
did the miners that work it now: old and sturdy, they none the less lack the
strength of the younger miners.

name: Atop the Portcullis
description:
The quality of the air is somewhat better here.  This is likely due to
the fact that this point dominates the rest of the cave system visible to
you by its height.  Still, odours from below you drift up slowly of their
own accord, and you are soon reminded of the filth beneath you.  You can
continue to walk along the fortified wall either east or west.

name: Within a Wide Grotto
description:
The tall walls of grotto disappear into the darkness above you.  An
unexpected ending to the miners' tunnel, there is an uneasy feeling about
this place that you just can't quite name yet.  Crude voices can be heard
clamoring to the north.

name: Along the Southern Wall
description:
This is the southern wall surrounding the natural valley extending
northwards.  The wall is crude, tall and wide enough for a little group to
traverse easily.  It appears to have been created when a lava eruption from
times gone by finally solidified.

name: Along the Southern Wall
description:
This is the southern wall surrounding the natural valley extending
northwards.  The wall is crude, tall and wide enough for a little group to
traverse easily.  It appears to have been created when a lava eruption from
times gone by finally solidified.

name: At the South-Western Turret
description:
One of the sites that have seen the most of construction, this turret is
nothing more than a few rough wooden beams put together to support a few
guards as they oversee the cave.  The view from this point is rather good,
and the ugliness of a hobgoblin dwelling reveals itself in all of its
pitifulness.

name: At the South-Western Turret
description:

name: Along the Western Wall
description:
You are standing at the western side of a natural wall surrounding a
valley to the west.  You can spot a commotion all across valley, as it
hobgoblins move about in scores.  To your west, there is nothing but
darkness.

name: Along the Western Wall
description:
You are standing at the western side of a natural wall surrounding a
valley to the west.  You can spot a commotion all across valley, as it
hobgoblins move about in scores.  To your west, there is nothing but
darkness.

name: At the North-Western Turret
description:
Unlike the southern turrets, this one is constructed from a few
rough-hewn blocks of stone, joined together by mortar.  The reason for this
is the scarcitiy of the wood underground.  Never the less, there is enough
room for two guards to comfortably observe the activites at the valley
floor.

description:

name: Where the Wall meets the Ridge
description:
All the attempts of hobgoblins at further constructing the battlements on
the wall stop here.  Ill-executed masonary creations have been battered,
likely in frustration.  However, they had little reason to worry: nothing
can climb the ridge extending eastwards from you without being noticed by
guards.

name: Inside the Portcullis
description:
Massive iron portcullis is behind you to the south.  You can feel the
pungent odour of urin around you.  It is augmented by the warm, moist
atmosphere of the caves, making you quite nauseous.  The chamber itself
looks dank and oppresive, with pieces of garbage strewn across the uneven
floor.  You spot a narrow staircase which leads upwards.  Before you,
towards the north, a small dweling sprawls in the natural valley.

name: At the North-Eastern Turret
description:
Unlike the southern turrets, this one is constructed from a few
rough-hewn blocks of stone, joined together by mortar.  The reason for this
is the scarcitiy of the wood underground.  Never the less, there is enough
room for two guards to comfortably observe the activites at the valley
floor.

name: Where the Wall meets the Ridge
description:
All the attempts of hobgoblins at further constructing the battlements on
the wall stop here.  Ill-executed masonary creations have been battered,
likely in frustration.  However, they had little reason to worry: nothing
can climb the ridge extending westwards from you without being noticed by
guards.

name: The Main Chamber of the Hut
On the Main Path through the Stronghold
description:
The scattered debris lays all around you.  Heaps and heaps of the
discarded necessities of the life: torn, dried skins, broken weapons and
piles of excretements are all around you.  It is obvious that the denizens
of this stronghold did not attribute too much importance to the hygiene. 
However, one thing that makes this region stand out from the rest of the
fortress is that the debris has been pushed aside, so as to make a clear
path.

name: On the Main Path through the Stronghold
description:

discarded necessities of the life: torn, dried skins, broken weapons and
piles of excretements are all around you.  It is obvious that the denizens
of this stronghold did not attribute too much importance to the hygiene. 
However, one thing that makes this region stand out from the rest of the

path.

name: The End of the Main Path through Stronghold
description:
The piles of debris stocked up against either side of the path cease to
exist here.  Rather, the chaotic arrangement of the garbage form a uniform
mass once again before your eyes.  The stench of the garbage is accentuated
by the strong scent of unwashed goblin bodies.

name: Under the Northern Wall
description:
The oppresive, black wall rises before your eyes, disappearing in the
darkness of the caverns high above.  Upon closer inspection, it becomes
apparent that the wall is not the product of the goblins.  Rather, they seem
to have taken advantage of the natural formation of the rocks that already
existed here.

name: In the Stronghold
description:
The visible signs of rampant carelesness are laid out in front of your
eyes.  Piles of debris have been chaotically formed all over the perimiter
of the stronghold.  Where there is no debris, the stone has been charred by
what must have been a considerable fire.  The stench of goblin horde hovers
in the air, as the stronghold stretches all around you.

name: Under the Raised Hut
description:
The distinguishing feature of this locale is the hut that raises above
the flat, natural floor of the stronghold.  The hut is obscured by the
darkness, the only clearly visible part of it being numerous strong stone
pillars that support it.  A rough and primitive stone ladder has been carved
into one of the pillars.

name: The Forechamber of the Hut
description:
The first chamber of the hut is as opulent, by goblin standards, as the
entrance.  This is the central intersection of the hut, with the doorways
leading west and north.  The walls are decorated with crude pictures, while
the floor has a few dark stains across it.  There only air that comes in or
out of the chamber comes from the entrance to the south of you.  Thus it is
not surprising that the stench is rather strong.

name: At the Entrance of the Raised Hut
description:
The true magnitude of the hut is revealed only here.  Massive walls are
decorated with what must be the only traces of Art within the goblin tribes
miles around.  The pictures are crude and they portray the horde of goblins
devouring another, smaller group of goblins.  The wall ornament is
interrupted by gaping door.  Further through the door, the stench of goblin
is strong.

name: The Chamber of Fire
description:
Small chamber that branches off from the forechamber of the hut is
strangely devoid of any excessive ornaments which grace the rest of this
hut.  Ascetic and minimalistic, it seems that someone has taken a great deal
of effort to keep the place uncluttered by trinkets.  The ceiling of this
chamber is lower than the rest of the hut.  You notice that it is covered in
soot, as well as all the walls of the chamber.

name: A noble's room
description:
You are standing in a very nice room. It is not very large, but is clean
and has all necessary accommodations. There is a large bed against the wall
and a set of oak furnature is placed neatly throughout the room. This is
where
the nobles from visiting lands make thier stay.

name: A noble's room
description:

and a set of oak furnature is placed neatly throughout the room. This is

the nobles from visiting lands make thier stay.

name: The Monarchal wing
description:
This is the the Monarchal wing, or more commonly called the noble wing.
This is the area provided for the visiting nobles from other Kingdoms.
There is a red carpet running the length of the hall, and fine paintings and
statues line the hallway.

name: The Monarchal wing
description:
This is the the Monarchal wing, or more commonly called the noble wing.
This is the area provided for the visiting nobles from other Kingdoms.
There is a red carpet running the length of the hall, and fine paintings and
statues line the hallway. There is a large hall to the north.

name: The Great Hall of Brynn Mahar
description:
You are standing in hall of astounding size. It has a high cieling with
wooden
supports, and there are windows on the east and west sides that look into
the
courtyard's. Long tables line the room where the people sit to partake in
the
feasting, and the the Emperor's throne is seated near the north end.

name: The Monarchal wing
description:
This is the the Monarchal wing, or more commonly called the noble wing.
This is the area provided for the visiting nobles from other Kingdoms.
There is a red carpet running the length of the hall, and fine paintings and
statues line the hallway. To the north is the Viceroy's room. To the south
are the Royal Guard's barracks.

name: The Viceroy's room
description:
You are standing in a very neat and well kept office. There is a
bookshelf at the back wall. A desk in the middle of the room. There are
large maps of the kingdom pasted to the walls with different sectors marked
off. There are also several suits of armor against the west wall.

name: The Barracks
description:
This is where the Royal guard's sleep. The room smells of body oder, and
of armor. The room is filled with bunk beds. There are chests neatly at the
foot of each bed, where the guards keep thier personal belongings.

name: The Barracks
description:
This is where the Royal guard's sleep. The room smells of body oder, and
of armor. The room is filled with bunk beds. There are chests neatly at the
foot of each bed, where the guards keep thier personal belongings.

name: The Barracks
description:
This is where the Royal guard's sleep. The room smells of body oder, and
of armor. The room is filled with bunk beds. There are chests neatly at the
foot of each bed, where the guards keep thier personal belongings. There is
a bookcase against the south wall here, with scrap marks near it.

name: The secret room
description:
You have come upon a small room with rounded gambling tables. Even the
royal guards need to have thier fun. The walls are covered in paintings
of naked women dancing about. Also the back corner is occupied by several
kegs of the kingdom's finest ale.

name: The Monarchal wing

name: End of The Monarchal wing
description:
This is the the Monarchal wing, or more commonly called the noble wing.
This is the area provided for the visiting nobles from other Kingdoms.
There is a red carpet running the length of the hall, and fine paintings and
statues line the hallway. To the north is a steel door that has several
jewels
inlaid on it.

name: A narrow hallway
description:
You have entered a hallway lined with stain-glass windows. Along both sides
of
the wall the windows allow a miriad of colors to splash across the floor
creating
a beautiful sight. There are pastel curtains hanging down from the cieling
that
you must walk through to reach the end of the hall.

name: A narrow hallway
description:

of
the wall the windows allow a miriad of colors to splash across the floor
creating
a beautiful sight. There are pastel curtains hanging down from the cieling

you must walk through to reach the end of the hall.

description:

a beautiful sight. There are pastel curtains hanging down from the cieling

you must walk through to reach the end of the hall.

name: Bottom of the staircase
description:
You are standing at the end of the narrow hallway. A spiral staircase
stands in front of you, that lead up into the eastern-most spire. The scent
of
perfume seems overbearing at this point.

name: The Empress's chamber
description:
The room itself extremely feminine, pink is the dominant color in this
chamber. There is a large bed with pillows stacked upon it, and also a
large dresser with a mirror lined with precious gems. There is almost an
inumberable amount of perfumes and other feminine things stacked upon the
dresser. There is a large window open on the western wall and the drapes
around
it drift in the fresh breeze.

name: Before a mighty Kingdom
description:
You are standing before the massive outer wall of Brynn Mahar.
There is a gigantic stone wall in front of you. You can see the
grey stone of the castle rising above the walls before you.
>From the three spires the symbol of Brynn Mahar sways in the breeze.
Directly to the north lies a drawbridge leading to the castle gates.
You can head down a well groomed path to the south.

name: Door before the Empress's room
description:
You are standing at the top of the staircase. To the west is
a beautiful wooden door with the emblem of Brynn Mahar carefully carved
into it. You can head back down the stairs to the hallway below.

name: A well groomed path before a mighty kingdom
description:
You are standing upon a cobblestone path leading to the Kingdom of Brynn
Mahar.  On either side of the path tall trees rise up and form a canopy
above you.  The songs of various bird envelop you in a perfect harmony. 
Shafts of light make thier way through the shivering leaves overhead and
collide into the ground below.  Further down the path two the north you can
the great spires of Brynn Mahar piercing the sky.

name: Across the drawbridge
description:
You are upon a strong wooden bridge. Below you is a swampy moat
covered in a layer of green algae. Green vines creep along the
stone edges of the moat walls. To the north lies the iron
gates to the mighty city of Brynn Mahar. You can head back to
path to the south.

name: Before the gates of the Kingdom
description:
You are standing before the great iron gates of Brynn Mahar. Walls of grey
stone tower on either side of the gate. There are several lookout towers
spaced evenly along the top of the wall. Two guards stand posted here at
all times. Through the iron gates the city streets can be seen. The
drawbridge is off to the south.

name: The city streets
description:
You are standing on a cobblestone road that travels througout the city
streets of Brynn Mahar. Large brass stands rise several feet off the
the ground and hold burning incense to cover up the smells of the city.
Many of the townspeople walk past occupied with thier daily chores.
Woman are often walking up and down the streets selling thier
agriculteral goods.

name: The city streets
description:
You are standing on a cobblestone road that travels througout the city
streets of Brynn Mahar. Large brass stands rise several feet off the
the ground and hold burning incense to cover up the smells of the city.
Many of the townspeople walk past occupied with thier daily chores.
Woman are often walking up and down the streets selling thier
agriculteral goods. To the north you can see the Market Square.

name: The Market Square
description:
You are standing in the midst of the market square. There are people
scurrying all about with different goods in thier hands. Carts line the
edges of the square filled with food and different things. The vendors
scream thier various sales pitches insessantly. The city streets lead
off in all directions. Far off to the north lies the castle.

name: The city streets
description:

streets of Brynn Mahar. Large brass stands rise several feet off the
the ground and hold burning incense to cover up the smells of the city.
Many of the townspeople walk past occupied with thier daily chores.
Woman are often walking up and down the streets selling thier
agriculteral goods.  To the south you can see the guards headquarters,
and to the north lies the magistrates home. To the east you can see the
Market Square.

name: The guards headquarters
description:
This is a sort of barracks where the guards take there breaks. A large
wooden table is in the center of the room where the guards eat there meals.
Against the back wall there are piles of weapons and armor that the guards
have taken off while they eat and relax. To the south there is a wooden
door.

name: The Captain's room
description:
You are standing in a dank room with scatered papers lying here and
there. The wall is pasted with wanted posters for the outlaws of the land.
There is a old wooden desk near the back of the room, where the captain
spends the majority of his day. There is also a large sword and shield
hanging above the doorway.

name: The Magistrate's abode
description:
This building is quite lavish compared to the rest of the buildings on
The city street. The floor is covered in fine rugs and there is nice
furnature placed neatly throughout the room. There is a small staircase near
the back of the room, and a small door at the west wall.

name: The maids quarters
description:
This is quite a desolate room. There is merely a cot in the corner and a
small dresser against the wall.

name: The Magistrates bedroom
description:
This is another beautiful room furnished from floor to cieling. A large bed
is in the middle of the room, covered with pillows and red velvet blankets.
There is a chair and desk on the south side of the room covered in legal
pieces of paper.

name: The city streets
description:
You are standing on a cobblestone road that travels througout the city
streets of Brynn Mahar. Large brass stands rise several feet off the
the ground and hold burning incense to cover up the smells of the city.
Many of the townspeople walk past occupied with thier daily chores.
Woman are often walking up and down the streets selling thier
agriculteral goods. To the east you can see the Market Square.

description:

streets of Brynn Mahar. Large brass stands rise several feet off the
the ground and hold burning incense to cover up the smells of the city.
Many of the townspeople walk past occupied with thier daily chores.
Woman are often walking up and down the streets selling thier
agriculteral goods. To the north and south are houses. To the east
you can see the Market Square.

name: A small home
description:
This is quite a humble dwelling place. Most likely whomever lives here has
come with hopes of becomming a merchant, as this kingdown is known so well
for its ammount of merchants. The room is quit dimly lit, with a single
candle as the only light source.

name: Iron Fist tavern
description:
A cloud of smoke seems to inhabit this merry place. Tables are scattered
around and people are laughing and drinking together. This room has quite
a high ceiling, and the woodwork is very beautiful. A few fellows are
dancing in the corner as a few string player start up a lively tune.
There is also a burly man behind the bar wiping it down.

name: End of the road
description:
You have reached the end of this street. The massive walls of the Kingdom
stand before you. This looks like the type of place where vandals hang
out. The wall creates a large shadow and makes it difficult to see anything.

name: The city streets
description:
You are standing on a cobblestone road that travels througout the city
streets of Brynn Mahar. Large brass stands rise several feet off the
the ground and hold burning incense to cover up the smells of the city.
Many of the townspeople walk past occupied with thier daily chores.
Woman are often walking up and down the streets selling thier
agriculteral goods. North of here lies the butcher, and to the south is

name: The Butcher
description:
The stench in this room is quite pungent. Ribcages and other body parts
line the walls hung on iron hooks. Old blood is crusted in lines down the
wall, and several bloody butcher knifes hang from the ceiling.

name: The Apothecary
description:
This room is a little bit misty. The walls are lined with shelves, that
hold potions and vials of a all different colors, shapes, and sizes. The
entire
room seems to vibrate with energy.

name: The Cobbler
description:
This is a very simple building. There is a wooden counter across the
front of the room where you came in. On the other side there is a man
working at his bench. On the back wall there is a shelf with several
shoes on it.

name: End of the road
description:
You have reached the end of this street. The massive walls of the Kingdom
stand before you. The city wall casts a large shadow across the area making
it very difficult to see anything.

name: The common square
description:
This square is not like the busy Market Square, it is quite
peaceful. There are benches here and there, and a giant fountain in the
middle.
To the east and west lies Merchants row. South of here the Market Square can
been seen. To the North lies the road to the castle.

name: Merchant's row
description:
These streets are quite a step up from the streets south of here. Every
thing is
perfectly clean and kept up. There are street lamps that are constantly lit
shedding light upon the street. Larger homes line the street and are
inhabited
by the wealthy merchants of Brynn Mahar. To the north and south are
merchant's
homes.

name: A merchant's home
description:
A very spacious and elegant home. The walls are covered in beautiful
tapestrys. The room is very well furnished, and is quite neat. There are
several lampstands that light the room, and incense burns on a table in the
center of the room.

name: A road to the castle
description:
This is a very well kept road. The sides of the road are lined with large
boulders. And there have been flowers planted in front of them. The sweet
aroma
from the flowers has an intoxicating effect upon your senses.

description:

from the flowers has an intoxicating effect upon your senses. To the north
you
see the entrance to the castle.

name: Before the castle gates
description:
You are standing before the largest and most beautiful structure in the
land; the castle of Brynn Mahar. The grey stone rises high above you, and
it is quite a feat to look up towards the top most spires. Directly in front
of you lies the large iron gates.

name: Inside the castle gates
description:
You are standing in the entrance to the castle. Behind you lies the first
gates, and before you lies the secondary gate. To the east and west there
are
guard rooms.

name: A guard room
description:
This is a simple stone room. The guards may choose to interview people
here before letting them into the castle. The only piece of furnature is
a wooden chair.

name: A guard room
description:
This is a simple stone room. The guards may choose to interview people

name: The Courtyard
description:
This is a most beautiful sight. This very large courtyard contains
beautiful trees, flowers, and a pond. There are stone benches here and
there, with people sitting and talking. In the pond you notice
there are many colorful fish swimming throughout it. More incense burns
and waffs through the air. The courtyard continues in all directions.

name: Entrance to the Regal wing
description:
You are standing just inside the western wing of the castle. The hallway is
lined with a green carpet that seems to go on forever. There are suits of
armor lined against the walls, each embossed with the code of Brynn Mahar.
Elegant brass torches light provide a light that seems to dance quietly.

name: The Regal wing
description:
You are standing in an extremely long hall. The hall seems to go on
farther than you can see. There a suits of armor lined against the walls,
each embossed with the code of Brynn Mahar. A long green carpet stretches
down the length of the hallway. Elegant brass torches light provide a light
that seems to dance quietly. There are wooden doors to the north and south.

name: A guest's room
description:
You are in the middle of a very plain but elegant room. There is a bed and
a armoir. There seems to be just enough for a short stay. A door leads back
out to the hall.

description:

illuminating the way are several candles mounted on the walls. As you walk
down the hallyway the shadows dance here and there, making it very difficult
to see.

description:
You are on stairs made of the same grey stone as the rest of the castle.
Candles light the path downward. You can hear moanings of anguish and
despair in the distance. The door back to the hallway is to the north.

name: Bottom of the sprial stairway
description:
You have reached the bottom of the spiral stairway. In front of you is
another iron bound doorway. The cries of anguish are much louder here. The
stairway leads back up to the hall.

name: In the dungeon
description:
This is quite a dank pit, devoid of any comfort at all. The smell of human
excretion permiates the air, and a deep chill seems to sink into your bones.
The hall through the dungeon continues to the north.

name: In the dungeon
description:

The hall through the dungeon continues to the north. Imediatly to
the west lies a wooden door with a piece of paper nailed to it.

name: The dungeon keeper's room
description:
This room is covered in dirt and dust. There is only one desk in the room
with a beat up chair behind it. There is a key hook with several keys on it
on the wall.

description:
This is quite a dank pit, devoid of any comfort at all. The smell of human
excretion permiates the air, and a deep chill seems to sink into your bones.
The hall through the dungeon continues to the east. There are marks on the
floor here that look as something was dragged through the room.

The hall through the dungeon continues to the east. There are cells to the

name: A cell
description:
You are standing in a dark cell. A cot is the only piece of furnature in
this room.

description:

The hall through the dungeon continues to the east. The hall turns south
here.
There are marks on the floor here that look as something was dragged through

name: End of the hall
description:
This is quite a dank pit, devoid of any comfort at all. The smell of human
excretion permiates the air, and a deep chill seems to sink into your bones.
The hall through the dungeon ends here. The marks on the floor seem to end
here,however there seems to be something outlined in dust on the floor.

name: Through the trap door
description:
You have just crawled through a small trap door. To the north here there
is a pitch black door. The marks on the floor seem to continue through the
door.

name: A bloody room
description:
You have entered a room soaked in blood. There are unidentifiable objects
scattered about and a pile of maggots writhes on top of some piece of
flesh in the corner. A black door to the south is the only exit.

name: The Regal wing
description:
You are standing in an extremely long hall. The hall seems to go on
farther than you can see. There a suits of armor lined against the walls,
each embossed with the code of Brynn Mahar. A long green carpet stretches
down the length of the hallway. Elegant brass torches light provide a light
that seems to dance quietly.

description:

farther than you can see. There a suits of armor lined against the walls,
each embossed with the code of Brynn Mahar. A long green carpet stretches
down the length of the hallway. Elegant brass torches light provide a light
that seems to dance quietly. There are ornate double doors to the north.
There is a golden plaque on the wall next to the door.

name: The War Room
description:
You are standing in the castle's war room. This is where the Emperor and his
knights, contemplate thier different tactics in a war situation. There is a
giant round table in the middle of the room, with the emblem of Brynn Mahar
inlaid into it. There are great tapestrys hung from the walls, and a giant
rug on the floor.

name: The Regal wing
description:
You are standing in an extremely long hall. The hall seems to go on

name: The bottom of a staircase
description:
You are standing at the bottom of a large staircase. It is a quite plain
stone structure, and leads upward to one of the castles spires.

name: A covered archway
description:
You are standing underneath the covered archway that surrounds the
courtyard.
It is a high stone archway with beautiful crystal chaneliers hanging
down.You
can see several wooden doors underneath the archway ahead of you.

name: Entrance to the Royal wing
description:
You are standing in the entrance to the royal wing of the castle. Both the
wall
and the floor of this wing are made completely of black and white marble.
Portraits of the emperors of Brynn Mahar line the walls, and several busts
sit
upon pedestals here and there. The hall stretches to the north and there is
a
golden rug running down as far as you can see.

name: The Royal wing
description:
This hall stretches off to the north. The cieling in this hall is
rounded, and is covered with stensiled designs. Both the wall and the floor
of this wing are made completely of black and white marble. Portraits of the
emperors of Brynn Mahar line the walls, and several busts sit upon pedestals
here and there.

name: The Kitchen
description:
You have just entered a very large kitchen. There are cooks and servants
running around everywhere making sure the Emperor's food is satifactory.
The immediate sections you are standing in the servants area where they
prepare the food on plates. Farther back is where the cooks are working.

name: The Kitchen
description:
You are now in the midst of the great kitchen. In this section you see
the cooks running back and forth sturring the soups, and making sure the
meat doesnt burn.

name: A small hallway
description:
This small hallway with three wooden doors. This entire hallway is very
plain, besides several mirrors on the wall. The main hallway is off to the
east.

name: The Jester's room
description:
This is the royal jester's quarters. Gags and things the jester uses to
try and make the king laugh are laying all over the place. The only pieces
of furnature in the room are a chair and a large wooden chest.

name: The inner sanctum
description:
As you step in this room your nose is assaulted by perfume. Pillows cover
the floor and there is an abundance of silk drapery hanging about. Women
lay about waiting for the Emperor to call them to his service.

name: The Magician's quarters
description:
This room is scattered with wand's of every shape and size. This is where
the magician prepares illusions to ammuse the Emperor. There is a single
chair
in the middle of the room.

name: The Royal wing
description:
This hall stretches off to the north. The cieling in this hall is
rounded, and is covered with stensiled designs. Both the wall and the floor
of this wing are made completely of black and white marble. Portraits of the
emperors of Brynn Mahar line the walls, and several busts sit upon pedestals
here and there.

name: Before the Throne room
description:
You are standing before two large golden doors. Upon the golden doors two
large
eagles can be seen sitting on top of a large cliff. The cieling in this hall
is rounded, and is covered with stensiled designs. Both the wall and the
floor
of this wing are made completely of black and white marble. Portraits of the
emperors of Brynn Mahar line the walls, and several busts sit upon pedestals
here and there.  Beyond these doors is the Emperors throne and his personal
chambers.

name: The Throne room
description:
You are standing in a spectacular room. The whole room is guilded with gold
and
different scenes have been carved into the walls. There are large windows on
either
side of the room that look out into the emperor's private courtyard.
Directly to the
north lies the Emperors throne, which is formed by two lions for the arm
rests, and
a large eagle with wings outstretched for the back. It is inlaid with gems
of
every kind imaginable, and has a soft red cushion. Behind the throne there
is a well guarded door.

name: Bottom of the staircase
description:
You are standing at the bottom of the northern spire's staircase. Rugs hang
from
the stone walls up the stairs and golden torches burn constantly to light
the way.

name: A door before the Emperor's quarters
description:
You are standing before the door to the Emperor's quarters. It is a heavy
wooden door guilded with the golden symbol of the kingdom of Brynn Mahar.
Rugs hang
from the walls on the way down the stairway and golden torches line the way.

name: The Emperor's Quarters
description:
You are standing in the bedroom of the Emperor himself. This is the most
lavish room you have ever seen. Precious jewels and metals are common place,
and his bed is a masterpiece of carved wood. The Emperors dresser is on the
west wall. Out the window on the south wall there is a breathtaking view
of the whole Kingdom that the Emperor can survey.

name: The Monarchal wing
description:
This is the the Monarchal wing, or more commonly called the noble wing.
This is the area provided for the visiting nobles from other Kingdoms.
There is a red carpet running the length of the hall, and fine paintings and
statues line the hallway.

name: On the staircase
description:
This staircase is completely plain there are only staggered slit windows
on the way up the stairs. However, they provide a superb view of the city
below.

name: Top of the Western spire
description:
At the top of this staircase there is a strong door made of a pearly
material, and the door itself seems to hum softly. The stairs lead back down
to the main floor.

name: An indescript library
description:
The cieling in this room is cone shaped allowing for a beautiful mural
to be painted upon it. A depiction of great works of magic and war
is uncannily unfolded before your eyes. Four windows give way to a most
spectacular view of the Kingdom. Between each window large bookcases rise
up against the walls.

name: The hidden room
description:
You have stumbled upon a most interesting room. It is quite small and
contains only a small bookcase and a cot. There is only on circular window
in the wall, and the floor is covered by a small rug.

name: The Monarchal wing
description:
This is the the Monarchal wing, or more commonly called the noble wing.
This is the area provided for the visiting nobles from other Kingdoms.
There is a red carpet running the length of the hall, and fine paintings and
statues line the hallway.

name: A noble's room
description:
You are standing in a very nice room. It is not very large, but is clean
and has all necessary accommodations. There is a large bed against the wall
and a set of oak furnature is placed neatly throughout the room. This is
where
the nobles from visiting lands make thier stay.

name: A noble's room
description:
This room is much nicer than the other rooms. There is a large bed and
dresser in the corner, and the floor is covered in a large fur rug. The
ceiling is stensiled with a great forest scene, and there is incense
burning in the corner. This room is reserved for only the most prestigious
of guests.
